v8
V8 is Google’s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

483// #define TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC() do { PrintF("Start: %s\n", __func__); } while

485#else
486// #define TEMPORAL_DEBUG_INFO ""
487#define TEMPORAL_DEBUG_INFO AT

490// (false)
491#endif // DEBUG

494 NewTypeError( \
495 MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgumentForTemporal, \
496 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromStaticChars(TEMPORAL_DEBUG_INFO))

516// #sec-temporal-isodatetimewithinlimits
517bool ISODateTimeWithinLimits(Isolate* isolate,
518 const DateTimeRecord& date_time) {
519 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
537 if (date_time.date.year > -271821 && date_time.date.year < 275760)
538 return true;
539 if (date_time.date.year < -271821 || date_time.date.year > 275760)
540 return false;
541 if (date_time.date.year == -271821) {
542 if (date_time.date.month > 4) return true;
543 if (date_time.date.month < 4) return false;
544 if (date_time.date.day > 19) return true;
545 if (date_time.date.day < 19) return false;
546 if (date_time.time.hour > 0) return true;
547 if (date_time.time.minute > 0) return true;
548 if (date_time.time.second > 0) return true;
549 if (date_time.time.millisecond > 0) return true;
550 if (date_time.time.microsecond > 0) return true;
551 return date_time.time.nanosecond > 0;
552 } else {
553 DCHECK_EQ(date_time.date.year, 275760);
554 if (date_time.date.month > 9) return false;
555 if (date_time.date.month < 9) return true;
556 return date_time.date.day < 14;
557 }
558 // 1. Assert: year, month, day, hour, minute, second, millisecond,
559 // microsecond, and nanosecond are integers.
560 // 2. Let ns be ! GetEpochFromISOParts(year, month, day, hour, minute,
561 // second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond).
562 // 3. If ns ≤ -8.64 × 10^21 - 8.64 × 10^13, then
563 // 4. If ns ≥ 8.64 × 10^21 + 8.64 × 10^13, then
564 // 5. Return true.
565}
566
567// #sec-temporal-isoyearmonthwithinlimits
568bool ISOYearMonthWithinLimits(int32_t year, int32_t month) {
569 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
570 // 1. Assert: year and month are integers.
571 // 2. If year < −271821 or year > 275760, then
572 // a. Return false.
573 if (year < -271821 || year > 275760) return false;
574 // 3. If year is −271821 and month < 4, then
575 // a. Return false.
576 if (year == -271821 && month < 4) return false;
577 // 4. If year is 275760 and month > 9, then
578 // a. Return false.
579 if (year == 275760 && month > 9) return false;
580 // 5. Return true.
581 return true;
582}

584#define ORDINARY_CREATE_FROM_CONSTRUCTOR(obj, target, new_target, T) \
585 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> new_target_receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(new_target); \
586 DirectHandle<Map> map; \
587 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION( \
588 isolate, map, \
589 JSFunction::GetDerivedMap(isolate, target, new_target_receiver)); \
590 Handle<T> object = \
591 Cast<T>(isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(map));
592
593#define THROW_INVALID_RANGE(T) \
594 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
595
596#define CONSTRUCTOR(name) \
597 DirectHandle<JSFunction>( \
598 Cast<JSFunction>( \
599 isolate->context()->native_context()->temporal_##name##_function()), \
600 isolate)
601
602// #sec-temporal-systemutcepochnanoseconds
603Handle<BigInt> SystemUTCEpochNanoseconds(Isolate* isolate) {
604 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
605 // 1. Let ns be the approximate current UTC date and time, in nanoseconds
606 // since the epoch.
607 double ms =
608 V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->CurrentClockTimeMillisecondsHighResolution();
609 // 2. Set ns to the result of clamping ns between −8.64 × 10^21 and 8.64 ×
610 // 10^21.
611
612 // 3. Return ℤ(ns).
613 double ns = ms * 1000000.0;
614 ns = std::floor(std::max(-8.64e21, std::min(ns, 8.64e21)));
615 return BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(ns))
616 .ToHandleChecked();
617}
618
619// #sec-temporal-createtemporalcalendar
620MaybeHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> CreateTemporalCalendar(
621 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
622 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, DirectHandle<String> identifier) {
623 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
624 // 1. Assert: ! IsBuiltinCalendar(identifier) is true.
625 // 2. If newTarget is not provided, set newTarget to %Temporal.Calendar%.
626 // 3. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget,
627 // "%Temporal.Calendar.prototype%", « [[InitializedTemporalCalendar]],
628 // [[Identifier]] »).
629 int32_t index = CalendarIndex(isolate, identifier);
630
631 ORDINARY_CREATE_FROM_CONSTRUCTOR(object, target, new_target,
632 JSTemporalCalendar)
633
634 object->set_flags(0);
635 // 4. Set object.[[Identifier]] to identifier.
636 object->set_calendar_index(index);
637 // 5. Return object.
638 return object;
639}
640
641MaybeHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> CreateTemporalCalendar(
642 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> identifier) {
643 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
644 return CreateTemporalCalendar(isolate, CONSTRUCTOR(calendar),
645 CONSTRUCTOR(calendar), identifier);
646}
647
648// #sec-temporal-createtemporaldate
649MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> CreateTemporalDate(
650 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
651 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, const DateRecord& date,
652 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar) {
653 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
654 // 1. Assert: isoYear is an integer.
655 // 2. Assert: isoMonth is an integer.
656 // 3. Assert: isoDay is an integer.
657 // 4. Assert: Type(calendar) is Object.
658 // 5. If ! IsValidISODate(isoYear, isoMonth, isoDay) is false, throw a
659 // RangeError exception.
660 if (!IsValidISODate(isolate, date)) {
661 THROW_INVALID_RANGE(JSTemporalPlainDate);
662 }
663 // 6. If ! ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isoYear, isoMonth, isoDay, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0,
664 // 0) is false, throw a RangeError exception.
665 if (!ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isolate, {date, {12, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})) {
666 THROW_INVALID_RANGE(JSTemporalPlainDate);
667 }
668 // 7. If newTarget is not present, set it to %Temporal.PlainDate%.
669
670 // 8. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget,
671 // "%Temporal.PlainDate.prototype%", « [[InitializedTemporalDate]],
672 // [[ISOYear]], [[ISOMonth]], [[ISODay]], [[Calendar]] »).
673 ORDINARY_CREATE_FROM_CONSTRUCTOR(object, target, new_target,
674 JSTemporalPlainDate)
675 object->set_year_month_day(0);
676 // 9. Set object.[[ISOYear]] to isoYear.
677 object->set_iso_year(date.year);
678 // 10. Set object.[[ISOMonth]] to isoMonth.
679 object->set_iso_month(date.month);
680 // 11. Set object.[[ISODay]] to isoDay.
681 object->set_iso_day(date.day);
682 // 12. Set object.[[Calendar]] to calendar.
683 object->set_calendar(*calendar);
684 // 13. Return object.
685 return object;
686}

688MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> CreateTemporalDate(

690 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar) {
691 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
692 return CreateTemporalDate(isolate, CONSTRUCTOR(plain_date),
693 CONSTRUCTOR(plain_date), date, calendar);

696// #sec-temporal-createtemporaldatetime
697MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> CreateTemporalDateTime(
698 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
699 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, const DateTimeRecord& date_time,
700 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar) {
701 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
702 // 1. Assert: isoYear, isoMonth, isoDay, hour, minute, second, millisecond,
703 // microsecond, and nanosecond are integers.
704 // 2. Assert: Type(calendar) is Object.
705 // 3. If ! IsValidISODate(isoYear, isoMonth, isoDay) is false, throw a
706 // RangeError exception.
707 if (!IsValidISODate(isolate, date_time.date)) {
708 THROW_INVALID_RANGE(JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
709 }
710 // 4. If ! IsValidTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond,
711 // nanosecond) is false, throw a RangeError exception.
712 if (!IsValidTime(isolate, date_time.time)) {
713 THROW_INVALID_RANGE(JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
714 }
715 // 5. If ! ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isoYear, isoMonth, isoDay, hour, minute,
716 // second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond) is false, then
717 if (!ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isolate, date_time)) {
718 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
719 THROW_INVALID_RANGE(JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
720 }
721 // 6. If newTarget is not present, set it to %Temporal.PlainDateTime%.
722 // 7. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget,
723 // "%Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype%", « [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]],
724 // [[ISOYear]], [[ISOMonth]], [[ISODay]], [[ISOHour]], [[ISOMinute]],
725 // [[ISOSecond]], [[ISOMillisecond]], [[ISOMicrosecond]], [[ISONanosecond]],
726 // [[Calendar]] »).
727 ORDINARY_CREATE_FROM_CONSTRUCTOR(object, target, new_target,
728 JSTemporalPlainDateTime)
729
730 object->set_year_month_day(0);
731 object->set_hour_minute_second(0);
732 object->set_second_parts(0);
733 // 8. Set object.[[ISOYear]] to isoYear.
734 object->set_iso_year(date_time.date.year);
735 // 9. Set object.[[ISOMonth]] to isoMonth.
736 object->set_iso_month(date_time.date.month);
737 // 10. Set object.[[ISODay]] to isoDay.
738 object->set_iso_day(date_time.date.day);
739 // 11. Set object.[[ISOHour]] to hour.
740 object->set_iso_hour(date_time.time.hour);
741 // 12. Set object.[[ISOMinute]] to minute.
742 object->set_iso_minute(date_time.time.minute);
743 // 13. Set object.[[ISOSecond]] to second.
744 object->set_iso_second(date_time.time.second);
745 // 14. Set object.[[ISOMillisecond]] to millisecond.
746 object->set_iso_millisecond(date_time.time.millisecond);
747 // 15. Set object.[[ISOMicrosecond]] to microsecond.
748 object->set_iso_microsecond(date_time.time.microsecond);
749 // 16. Set object.[[ISONanosecond]] to nanosecond.
750 object->set_iso_nanosecond(date_time.time.nanosecond);
751 // 17. Set object.[[Calendar]] to calendar.
752 object->set_calendar(*calendar);
753 // 18. Return object.
754 return object;
755}

958inline double NormalizeMinusZero(double v) { return IsMinusZero(v) ? 0 : v; }
959
960// #sec-temporal-createdatedurationrecord
961Maybe<DateDurationRecord> DateDurationRecord::Create(
962 Isolate* isolate, double years, double months, double weeks, double days) {
963 // 1. If ! IsValidDuration(years, months, weeks, days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0) is
964 // false, throw a RangeError exception.
965 if (!IsValidDuration(isolate,
966 {years, months, weeks, {days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})) {
967 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
968 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
969 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
970 }
971 // 2. Return the Record { [[Years]]: ℝ(𝔽(years)), [[Months]]: ℝ(𝔽(months)),
972 // [[Weeks]]: ℝ(𝔽(weeks)), [[Days]]: ℝ(𝔽(days)) }.
973 DateDurationRecord record = {years, months, weeks, days};
974 return Just(record);
975}

979namespace temporal {
980// #sec-temporal-createtimedurationrecord
981Maybe<TimeDurationRecord> TimeDurationRecord::Create(
982 Isolate* isolate, double days, double hours, double minutes, double seconds,
983 double milliseconds, double microseconds, double nanoseconds) {
984 // 1. If ! IsValidDuration(0, 0, 0, days, hours, minutes, seconds,
985 // milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is false, throw a RangeError
986 // exception.
987 TimeDurationRecord record = {days, hours, minutes, seconds,
988 milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds};
989 if (!IsValidDuration(isolate, {0, 0, 0, record})) {
990 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
991 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
992 Nothing<TimeDurationRecord>());
993 }
994 // 2. Return the Record { [[Days]]: ℝ(𝔽(days)), [[Hours]]: ℝ(𝔽(hours)),
995 // [[Minutes]]: ℝ(𝔽(minutes)), [[Seconds]]: ℝ(𝔽(seconds)), [[Milliseconds]]:
996 // ℝ(𝔽(milliseconds)), [[Microseconds]]: ℝ(𝔽(microseconds)), [[Nanoseconds]]:
997 // ℝ(𝔽(nanoseconds)) }.
998 return Just(record);
999}

1001// #sec-temporal-createdurationrecord
1002Maybe<DurationRecord> DurationRecord::Create(
1003 Isolate* isolate, double years, double months, double weeks, double days,
1004 double hours, double minutes, double seconds, double milliseconds,
1005 double microseconds, double nanoseconds) {
1006 // 1. If ! IsValidDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes,
1007 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is false, throw a
1008 // RangeError exception.
1009 DurationRecord record = {
1010 years,
1011 months,
1012 weeks,
1013 {days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds}};
1014 if (!IsValidDuration(isolate, record)) {
1015 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
1016 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
1017 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
1018 }
1019 // 2. Return the Record { [[Years]]: ℝ(𝔽(years)), [[Months]]: ℝ(𝔽(months)),
1020 // [[Weeks]]: ℝ(𝔽(weeks)), [[Days]]: ℝ(𝔽(days)), [[Hours]]: ℝ(𝔽(hours)),
1021 // [[Minutes]]: ℝ(𝔽(minutes)), [[Seconds]]: ℝ(𝔽(seconds)), [[Milliseconds]]:
1022 // ℝ(𝔽(milliseconds)), [[Microseconds]]: ℝ(𝔽(microseconds)), [[Nanoseconds]]:
1023 // ℝ(𝔽(nanoseconds)) }.
1024 return Just(record);
1025}

1029// #sec-temporal-createtemporalduration
1030MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> CreateTemporalDuration(
1031 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
1032 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, const DurationRecord& duration) {
1033 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1034 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
1035 // 1. If ! IsValidDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes,
1036 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is false, throw a
1037 // RangeError exception.
1038 if (!IsValidDuration(isolate, duration)) {
1039 THROW_INVALID_RANGE(JSTemporalDuration);
1040 }
1041
1042 // 2. If newTarget is not present, set it to %Temporal.Duration%.
1043 // 3. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget,
1044 // "%Temporal.Duration.prototype%", « [[InitializedTemporalDuration]],
1045 // [[Years]], [[Months]], [[Weeks]], [[Days]], [[Hours]], [[Minutes]],
1046 // [[Seconds]], [[Milliseconds]], [[Microseconds]], [[Nanoseconds]] »).
1047 const TimeDurationRecord& time_duration = duration.time_duration;
1048 DirectHandle<Number> years =
1049 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(duration.years));
1050 DirectHandle<Number> months =
1051 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(duration.months));
1052 DirectHandle<Number> weeks =
1053 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(duration.weeks));
1054 DirectHandle<Number> days =
1055 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(time_duration.days));
1056 DirectHandle<Number> hours =
1057 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(time_duration.hours));
1058 DirectHandle<Number> minutes =
1059 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(time_duration.minutes));
1060 DirectHandle<Number> seconds =
1061 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(time_duration.seconds));
1062 DirectHandle<Number> milliseconds =
1063 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(time_duration.milliseconds));
1064 DirectHandle<Number> microseconds =
1065 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(time_duration.microseconds));
1066 DirectHandle<Number> nanoseconds =
1067 factory->NewNumber(NormalizeMinusZero(time_duration.nanoseconds));
1068 ORDINARY_CREATE_FROM_CONSTRUCTOR(object, target, new_target,
1069 JSTemporalDuration)
1070 // 4. Set object.[[Years]] to ℝ(𝔽(years)).
1071 object->set_years(*years);
1072 // 5. Set object.[[Months]] to ℝ(𝔽(months)).
1073 object->set_months(*months);
1074 // 6. Set object.[[Weeks]] to ℝ(𝔽(weeks)).
1075 object->set_weeks(*weeks);
1076 // 7. Set object.[[Days]] to ℝ(𝔽(days)).
1077 object->set_days(*days);
1078 // 8. Set object.[[Hours]] to ℝ(𝔽(hours)).
1079 object->set_hours(*hours);
1080 // 9. Set object.[[Minutes]] to ℝ(𝔽(minutes)).
1081 object->set_minutes(*minutes);
1082 // 10. Set object.[[Seconds]] to ℝ(𝔽(seconds)).
1083 object->set_seconds(*seconds);
1084 // 11. Set object.[[Milliseconds]] to ℝ(𝔽(milliseconds)).
1085 object->set_milliseconds(*milliseconds);
1086 // 12. Set object.[[Microseconds]] to ℝ(𝔽(microseconds)).
1087 object->set_microseconds(*microseconds);
1088 // 13. Set object.[[Nanoseconds]] to ℝ(𝔽(nanoseconds)).
1089 object->set_nanoseconds(*nanoseconds);
1090 // 14. Return object.
1091 return object;
1092}
1093
1094MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> CreateTemporalDuration(
1095 Isolate* isolate, const DurationRecord& duration) {
1096 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1097 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, CONSTRUCTOR(duration),
1098 CONSTRUCTOR(duration), duration);
1099}

1165
1166// #sec-temporal-createtemporaltimezone
1167MaybeHandle<JSTemporalTimeZone> CreateTemporalTimeZone(
1168 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
1169 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<String> identifier) {
1170 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1171
1172 // 1. If newTarget is not present, set it to %Temporal.TimeZone%.
1173 // 2. Let object be ? OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor(newTarget,
1174 // "%Temporal.TimeZone.prototype%", « [[InitializedTemporalTimeZone]],
1175 // [[Identifier]], [[OffsetNanoseconds]] »).
1176
1177 // 3. Let offsetNanosecondsResult be ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(identifier).
1178 Maybe<int64_t> maybe_offset_nanoseconds =
1179 ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(isolate, identifier);
1180 // 4. If offsetNanosecondsResult is an abrupt completion, then
1181 if (maybe_offset_nanoseconds.IsNothing()) {
1182 DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
1183 isolate->clear_exception();
1184 // a. Assert: ! CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(identifier) is identifier.
1185 DCHECK(String::Equals(isolate, identifier,
1186 CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(isolate, identifier)));
1187
1188 // b. Set object.[[Identifier]] to identifier.
1189 // c. Set object.[[OffsetNanoseconds]] to undefined.
1190 if (IsUTC(isolate, identifier)) {
1191 return CreateTemporalTimeZoneUTC(isolate, target, new_target);
1192 }
1193#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
1194 int32_t time_zone_index = Intl::GetTimeZoneIndex(isolate, identifier);
1195 DCHECK_GE(time_zone_index, 0);
1196 return CreateTemporalTimeZoneFromIndex(isolate, target, new_target,
1197 time_zone_index);
1198#else
1199 UNREACHABLE();
1200#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
1201 // 5. Else,
1202 } else {
1203 // a. Set object.[[Identifier]] to !
1204 // FormatTimeZoneOffsetString(offsetNanosecondsResult.[[Value]]). b. Set
1205 // object.[[OffsetNanoseconds]] to offsetNanosecondsResult.[[Value]].
1206 ORDINARY_CREATE_FROM_CONSTRUCTOR(object, target, new_target,
1207 JSTemporalTimeZone)
1208 object->set_flags(0);
1209 object->set_details(0);
1210
1211 object->set_is_offset(true);
1212 object->set_offset_nanoseconds(maybe_offset_nanoseconds.FromJust());
1213 return object;
1214 }
1215 // 6. Return object.
1216}
1217
1218MaybeHandle<JSTemporalTimeZone> CreateTemporalTimeZoneDefaultTarget(
1219 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> identifier) {
1220 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1221 return CreateTemporalTimeZone(isolate, CONSTRUCTOR(time_zone),
1222 CONSTRUCTOR(time_zone), identifier);
1223}
1224
1225} // namespace

1229 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> identifier) {
1230 return CreateTemporalTimeZoneDefaultTarget(isolate, identifier);
1231}

1252
1253DateTimeRecord GetISOPartsFromEpoch(Isolate* isolate,
1254 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds) {
1255 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1256 DateTimeRecord result;
1257 // 1. Assert: ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(ℤ(epochNanoseconds)) is true.
1258 DCHECK(IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds));
1259 // 2. Let remainderNs be epochNanoseconds modulo 10^6.
1260 DirectHandle<BigInt> million = BigInt::FromUint64(isolate, 1000000);
1261 DirectHandle<BigInt> remainder_ns =
1262 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds, million).ToHandleChecked();
1263 // Need to do some remainder magic to negative remainder.
1264 if (remainder_ns->IsNegative()) {
1265 remainder_ns =
1266 BigInt::Add(isolate, remainder_ns, million).ToHandleChecked();
1267 }
1268
1269 // 3. Let epochMilliseconds be (epochNanoseconds − remainderNs) / 10^6.
1270 int64_t epoch_milliseconds =
1271 BigInt::Divide(isolate,
1272 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds, remainder_ns)
1273 .ToHandleChecked(),
1274 million)
1275 .ToHandleChecked()
1276 ->AsInt64();
1277 int year = 0;
1278 int month = 0;
1279 int day = 0;
1280 int wday = 0;
1281 int hour = 0;
1282 int min = 0;
1283 int sec = 0;
1284 int ms = 0;
1285 isolate->date_cache()->BreakDownTime(epoch_milliseconds, &year, &month, &day,
1286 &wday, &hour, &min, &sec, &ms);
1287
1288 // 4. Let year be ! YearFromTime(epochMilliseconds).
1289 result.date.year = year;
1290 // 5. Let month be ! MonthFromTime(epochMilliseconds) + 1.
1291 result.date.month = month + 1;
1292 DCHECK_GE(result.date.month, 1);
1293 DCHECK_LE(result.date.month, 12);
1294 // 6. Let day be ! DateFromTime(epochMilliseconds).
1295 result.date.day = day;
1296 DCHECK_GE(result.date.day, 1);
1297 DCHECK_LE(result.date.day, 31);
1298 // 7. Let hour be ! HourFromTime(epochMilliseconds).
1299 result.time.hour = hour;
1300 DCHECK_GE(result.time.hour, 0);
1301 DCHECK_LE(result.time.hour, 23);
1302 // 8. Let minute be ! MinFromTime(epochMilliseconds).
1303 result.time.minute = min;
1304 DCHECK_GE(result.time.minute, 0);
1305 DCHECK_LE(result.time.minute, 59);
1306 // 9. Let second be ! SecFromTime(epochMilliseconds).
1307 result.time.second = sec;
1308 DCHECK_GE(result.time.second, 0);
1309 DCHECK_LE(result.time.second, 59);
1310 // 10. Let millisecond be ! msFromTime(epochMilliseconds).
1311 result.time.millisecond = ms;
1312 DCHECK_GE(result.time.millisecond, 0);
1313 DCHECK_LE(result.time.millisecond, 999);
1314 // 11. Let microsecond be floor(remainderNs / 1000) modulo 1000.
1315 int64_t remainder = remainder_ns->AsInt64();
1316 result.time.microsecond = (remainder / 1000) % 1000;
1317 DCHECK_GE(result.time.microsecond, 0);
1318 // 12. 12. Assert: microsecond < 1000.
1319 DCHECK_LE(result.time.microsecond, 999);
1320 // 13. Let nanosecond be remainderNs modulo 1000.
1321 result.time.nanosecond = remainder % 1000;
1322 DCHECK_GE(result.time.nanosecond, 0);
1323 DCHECK_LE(result.time.nanosecond, 999);
1324 // 14. Return the Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month, [[Day]]: day,
1325 // [[Hour]]: hour, [[Minute]]: minute, [[Second]]: second, [[Millisecond]]:
1326 // millisecond, [[Microsecond]]: microsecond, [[Nanosecond]]: nanosecond }.
1327 return result;
1328}
1329
1330// #sec-temporal-balanceisodatetime
1331DateTimeRecord BalanceISODateTime(Isolate* isolate,
1332 const DateTimeRecord& date_time) {
1333 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1334 // 1. Assert: year, month, day, hour, minute, second, millisecond,
1335 // microsecond, and nanosecond are integers.
1336 // 2. Let balancedTime be ! BalanceTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond,
1337 // microsecond, nanosecond).
1338 DateTimeRecord balanced_time =
1339 BalanceTime({static_cast<double>(date_time.time.hour),
1340 static_cast<double>(date_time.time.minute),
1341 static_cast<double>(date_time.time.second),
1342 static_cast<double>(date_time.time.millisecond),
1343 static_cast<double>(date_time.time.microsecond),
1344 static_cast<double>(date_time.time.nanosecond)});
1345 // 3. Let balancedDate be ! BalanceISODate(year, month, day +
1346 // balancedTime.[[Days]]).
1347 DateRecord added_date = date_time.date;
1348 added_date.day += balanced_time.date.day;
1349 DateRecord balanced_date = BalanceISODate(isolate, added_date);
1350 // 4. Return the Record { [[Year]]: balancedDate.[[Year]], [[Month]]:
1351 // balancedDate.[[Month]], [[Day]]: balancedDate.[[Day]], [[Hour]]:
1352 // balancedTime.[[Hour]], [[Minute]]: balancedTime.[[Minute]], [[Second]]:
1353 // balancedTime.[[Second]], [[Millisecond]]: balancedTime.[[Millisecond]],
1354 // [[Microsecond]]: balancedTime.[[Microsecond]], [[Nanosecond]]:
1355 // balancedTime.[[Nanosecond]] }.
1356 return {balanced_date, balanced_time.time};
1357}
1358
1359// #sec-temporal-roundtowardszero
1360double RoundTowardsZero(double x) {
1361 // 1. Return the mathematical value that is the same sign as x and whose
1362 // magnitude is floor(abs(x)).
1363 if (x < 0) {
1364 return -std::floor(std::abs(x));
1365 } else {
1366 return std::floor(std::abs(x));
1367 }
1368}
1369
1370// #sec-temporal-temporaldurationtostring
1371Handle<String> TemporalDurationToString(Isolate* isolate,
1372 const DurationRecord& duration,
1373 Precision precision) {
1374 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
1375 DCHECK(precision != Precision::kMinute);
1376 // 1. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes,
1377 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
1378 DurationRecord dur = duration;
1379 int32_t sign = DurationRecord::Sign(dur);
1380 // Note: for the operation below, to avoid microseconds .. seconds lost
1381 // precision while the resulting value may exceed the precision limit, we use
1382 // extra double xx_add to hold the additional temp value.
1383 // 2. Set microseconds to microseconds + RoundTowardsZero(nanoseconds / 1000).
1384 double microseconds_add =
1385 RoundTowardsZero(dur.time_duration.nanoseconds / 1000);
1386 // 3. Set nanoseconds to remainder(nanoseconds, 1000).
1387 dur.time_duration.nanoseconds =
1388 std::fmod(dur.time_duration.nanoseconds, 1000);
1389 // 4. Set milliseconds to milliseconds + RoundTowardsZero(microseconds /
1390 // 1000).
1391 double milliseconds_add = RoundTowardsZero(
1392 dur.time_duration.microseconds / 1000 + microseconds_add / 1000);
1393 // 5. Set microseconds to remainder(microseconds, 1000).
1394 dur.time_duration.microseconds =
1395 std::fmod(std::fmod(dur.time_duration.microseconds, 1000) +
1396 std::fmod(microseconds_add, 1000),
1397 1000);
1398 // 6. Set seconds to seconds + RoundTowardsZero(milliseconds / 1000).
1399 double seconds_add = RoundTowardsZero(dur.time_duration.milliseconds / 1000 +
1400 milliseconds_add / 1000);
1401 // 7. Set milliseconds to remainder(milliseconds, 1000).
1402 dur.time_duration.milliseconds =
1403 std::fmod(std::fmod(dur.time_duration.milliseconds, 1000) +
1404 std::fmod(milliseconds_add, 1000),
1405 1000);
1406
1407 // 8. Let datePart be "".
1408 IncrementalStringBuilder date_part(isolate);
1409 // Number.MAX_VALUE.toString() is "1.7976931348623157e+308"
1410 // We add several more spaces to 320.
1411 base::ScopedVector<char> buf(320);
1412
1413 // 9. If years is not 0, then
1414 if (dur.years != 0) {
1415 // a. Set datePart to the string concatenation of abs(years) formatted as a
1416 // decimal number and the code unit 0x0059 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER Y).
1417 SNPrintF(buf, "%.0f", std::abs(dur.years));
1418 date_part.AppendCString(buf.data());
1419 date_part.AppendCharacter('Y');
1420 }
1421 // 10. If months is not 0, then
1422 if (dur.months != 0) {
1423 // a. Set datePart to the string concatenation of datePart,
1424 // abs(months) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit
1425 // 0x004D (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER M).
1426 SNPrintF(buf, "%.0f", std::abs(dur.months));
1427 date_part.AppendCString(buf.data());
1428 date_part.AppendCharacter('M');
1429 }
1430 // 11. If weeks is not 0, then
1431 if (dur.weeks != 0) {
1432 // a. Set datePart to the string concatenation of datePart,
1433 // abs(weeks) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit
1434 // 0x0057 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER W).
1435 SNPrintF(buf, "%.0f", std::abs(dur.weeks));
1436 date_part.AppendCString(buf.data());
1437 date_part.AppendCharacter('W');
1438 }
1439 // 12. If days is not 0, then
1440 if (dur.time_duration.days != 0) {
1441 // a. Set datePart to the string concatenation of datePart,
1442 // abs(days) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit 0x0044
1443 // (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER D).
1444 SNPrintF(buf, "%.0f", std::abs(dur.time_duration.days));
1445 date_part.AppendCString(buf.data());
1446 date_part.AppendCharacter('D');
1447 }
1448 // 13. Let timePart be "".
1449 IncrementalStringBuilder time_part(isolate);
1450 // 14. If hours is not 0, then
1451 if (dur.time_duration.hours != 0) {
1452 // a. Set timePart to the string concatenation of abs(hours) formatted as a
1453 // decimal number and the code unit 0x0048 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER H).
1454 SNPrintF(buf, "%.0f", std::abs(dur.time_duration.hours));
1455 time_part.AppendCString(buf.data());
1456 time_part.AppendCharacter('H');
1457 }
1458 // 15. If minutes is not 0, then
1459 if (dur.time_duration.minutes != 0) {
1460 // a. Set timePart to the string concatenation of timePart,
1461 // abs(minutes) formatted as a decimal number, and the code unit
1462 // 0x004D (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER M).
1463 SNPrintF(buf, "%.0f", std::abs(dur.time_duration.minutes));
1464 time_part.AppendCString(buf.data());
1465 time_part.AppendCharacter('M');
1466 }
1467 IncrementalStringBuilder seconds_part(isolate);
1468 IncrementalStringBuilder decimal_part(isolate);
1469 // 16. If any of seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds are not
1470 // 0; or years, months, weeks, days, hours, and minutes are all 0, or
1471 // precision is not "auto" then
1472 if ((dur.time_duration.seconds != 0 || seconds_add != 0 ||
1473 dur.time_duration.milliseconds != 0 ||
1474 dur.time_duration.microseconds != 0 ||
1475 dur.time_duration.nanoseconds != 0) ||
1476 (dur.years == 0 && dur.months == 0 && dur.weeks == 0 &&
1477 dur.time_duration.days == 0 && dur.time_duration.hours == 0 &&
1478 dur.time_duration.minutes == 0) ||
1479 precision != Precision::kAuto) {
1480 // a. Let fraction be abs(milliseconds) × 10^6 + abs(microseconds) × 10^3 +
1481 // abs(nanoseconds).
1482 int64_t fraction = std::abs(dur.time_duration.milliseconds) * 1e6 +
1483 std::abs(dur.time_duration.microseconds) * 1e3 +
1484 std::abs(dur.time_duration.nanoseconds);
1485 // b. Let decimalPart be fraction formatted as a nine-digit decimal number,
1486 // padded to the left with zeroes if necessary.
1487 int64_t divisor = 100000000;
1488
1489 // c. If precision is "auto", then
1490 if (precision == Precision::kAuto) {
1491 // i. Set decimalPart to the longest possible substring of decimalPart
1492 // starting at position 0 and not ending with the code unit 0x0030 (DIGIT
1493 // ZERO).
1494 while (fraction > 0) {
1495 decimal_part.AppendInt(static_cast<int32_t>(fraction / divisor));
1496 fraction %= divisor;
1497 divisor /= 10;
1498 }
1499 // d. Else if precision = 0, then
1500 } else if (precision == Precision::k0) {
1501 // i. Set decimalPart to "".
1502 // e. Else,
1503 } else {
1504 // i. Set decimalPart to the substring of decimalPart from 0 to precision.
1505 int32_t precision_len = static_cast<int32_t>(precision);
1506 DCHECK_LE(0, precision_len);
1507 DCHECK_GE(9, precision_len);
1508 for (int32_t len = 0; len < precision_len; len++) {
1509 decimal_part.AppendInt(static_cast<int32_t>(fraction / divisor));
1510 fraction %= divisor;
1511 divisor /= 10;
1512 }
1513 }
1514 // f. Let secondsPart be abs(seconds) formatted as a decimal number.
1515 if (std::abs(seconds_add + dur.time_duration.seconds) < kMaxSafeInteger) {
1516 // Fast path: The seconds_add + dur.time_duration.seconds is in the range
1517 // the double could keep the precision.
1518 dur.time_duration.seconds += seconds_add;
1519 SNPrintF(buf, "%.0f", std::abs(dur.time_duration.seconds));
1520 seconds_part.AppendCString(buf.data());
1521 } else {
1522 // Slow path: The seconds_add + dur.time_duration.seconds is out of the
1523 // range which the double could keep the precision. Format by math via
1524 // BigInt.
1525 seconds_part.AppendString(
1526 BigInt::ToString(
1527 isolate,
1528 BigInt::Add(
1529 isolate,
1530 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
1531 std::abs(seconds_add)))
1532 .ToHandleChecked(),
1533 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate,
1534 isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
1535 std::abs(dur.time_duration.seconds)))
1536 .ToHandleChecked())
1537 .ToHandleChecked())
1538 .ToHandleChecked());
1539 }
1540
1541 // g. If decimalPart is not "", then
1542 if (decimal_part.Length() != 0) {
1543 // i. Set secondsPart to the string-concatenation of secondsPart, the code
1544 // unit 0x002E (FULL STOP), and decimalPart.
1545 seconds_part.AppendCharacter('.');
1546 seconds_part.AppendString(decimal_part.Finish().ToHandleChecked());
1547 }
1548
1549 // h. Set timePart to the string concatenation of timePart, secondsPart, and
1550 // the code unit 0x0053 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER S).
1551 time_part.AppendString(seconds_part.Finish().ToHandleChecked());
1552 time_part.AppendCharacter('S');
1553 }
1554 // 17. Let signPart be the code unit 0x002D (HYPHEN-MINUS) if sign < 0, and
1555 // otherwise the empty String.
1556 if (sign < 0) {
1557 builder.AppendCharacter('-');
1558 }
1559
1560 // 18. Let result be the string concatenation of signPart, the code unit
1561 // 0x0050 (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER P) and datePart.
1562 builder.AppendCharacter('P');
1563 builder.AppendString(date_part.Finish().ToHandleChecked());
1564
1565 // 19. If timePart is not "", then
1566 if (time_part.Length() > 0) {
1567 // a. Set result to the string concatenation of result, the code unit 0x0054
1568 // (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER T), and timePart.
1569 builder.AppendCharacter('T');
1570 builder.AppendString(time_part.Finish().ToHandleChecked());
1571 }
1572 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked(), isolate);
1573}
1574
1575void ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(IncrementalStringBuilder* builder, int32_t n,
1576 int32_t min_length);
1577// #sec-temporal-formatsecondsstringpart
1578void FormatSecondsStringPart(IncrementalStringBuilder* builder, int32_t second,
1579 int32_t millisecond, int32_t microsecond,
1580 int32_t nanosecond, Precision precision) {
1581 // 1. Assert: second, millisecond, microsecond and nanosecond are integers.
1582 // 2. If precision is "minute", return "".
1583 if (precision == Precision::kMinute) {
1584 return;
1585 }
1586 // 3. Let secondsString be the string-concatenation of the code unit 0x003A
1587 // (COLON) and second formatted as a two-digit decimal number, padded to the
1588 // left with zeroes if necessary.
1589 builder->AppendCharacter(':');
1590 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(builder, second, 2);
1591 // 4. Let fraction be millisecond × 10^6 + microsecond × 10^3 + nanosecond.
1592 int64_t fraction = millisecond * 1000000 + microsecond * 1000 + nanosecond;
1593 int64_t divisor = 100000000;
1594 // 5. If precision is "auto", then
1595 if (precision == Precision::kAuto) {
1596 // a. If fraction is 0, return secondsString.
1597 if (fraction == 0) {
1598 return;
1599 }
1600 builder->AppendCharacter('.');
1601 // b. Set fraction to ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(fraction, 9).
1602 // c. Set fraction to the longest possible substring of fraction starting at
1603 // position 0 and not ending with the code unit 0x0030 (DIGIT ZERO).
1604 while (fraction > 0) {
1605 builder->AppendInt(static_cast<int32_t>(fraction / divisor));
1606 fraction %= divisor;
1607 divisor /= 10;
1608 }
1609 // 6. Else,
1610 } else {
1611 // a. If precision is 0, return secondsString.
1612 if (precision == Precision::k0) {
1613 return;
1614 }
1615 builder->AppendCharacter('.');
1616 // b. Set fraction to ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(fraction, 9).
1617 // c. Set fraction to the substring of fraction from 0 to precision.
1618 int32_t precision_len = static_cast<int32_t>(precision);
1619 DCHECK_LE(0, precision_len);
1620 DCHECK_GE(9, precision_len);
1621 for (int32_t len = 0; len < precision_len; len++) {
1622 builder->AppendInt(static_cast<int32_t>(fraction / divisor));
1623 fraction %= divisor;
1624 divisor /= 10;
1625 }
1626 }
1627 // 7. Return the string-concatenation of secondsString, the code unit 0x002E
1628 // (FULL STOP), and fraction.
1629}
1630
1631// #sec-temporal-temporaltimetostring
1632Handle<String> TemporalTimeToString(Isolate* isolate, const TimeRecord& time,
1633 Precision precision) {
1634 // 1. Assert: hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond and nanosecond
1635 // are integers.
1636 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
1637 // 2. Let hour be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(hour, 2).
1638 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, time.hour, 2);
1639 builder.AppendCharacter(':');
1640 // 3. Let minute be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(minute, 2).
1641 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, time.minute, 2);
1642 // 4. Let seconds be ! FormatSecondsStringPart(second, millisecond,
1643 // microsecond, nanosecond, precision).
1644 FormatSecondsStringPart(&builder, time.second, time.millisecond,
1645 time.microsecond, time.nanosecond, precision);
1646 // 5. Return the string-concatenation of hour, the code unit 0x003A (COLON),
1647 // minute, and seconds.
1648 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked(), isolate);
1649}
1650
1651Handle<String> TemporalTimeToString(
1652 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time,
1653 Precision precision) {
1654 return TemporalTimeToString(
1655 isolate,
1656 {temporal_time->iso_hour(), temporal_time->iso_minute(),
1657 temporal_time->iso_second(), temporal_time->iso_millisecond(),
1658 temporal_time->iso_microsecond(), temporal_time->iso_nanosecond()},
1659 precision);
1660}

1664namespace temporal {
1665MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(
1666 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone,
1667 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
1668 const char* method_name) {
1669 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1670 // 1. Let offsetNanoseconds be ? GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(timeZone, instant).
1671 int64_t offset_nanoseconds;
1672 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1673 isolate, offset_nanoseconds,
1674 GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(isolate, time_zone, instant, method_name),
1675 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
1676 // 2. Let result be ! GetISOPartsFromEpoch(instant.[[Nanoseconds]]).
1677 DateTimeRecord result = GetISOPartsFromEpoch(
1678 isolate, direct_handle(instant->nanoseconds(), isolate));
1679
1680 // 3. Set result to ! BalanceISODateTime(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
1681 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
1682 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]] +
1683 // offsetNanoseconds).
1684
1685 // Note: Since offsetNanoseconds is bounded 86400x 10^9, the
1686 // result of result.[[Nanosecond]] + offsetNanoseconds may overflow int32_t
1687 // Therefore we distribute the sum to other fields below to make sure it won't
1688 // overflow each of the int32_t fields. But it will leave each field to be
1689 // balanced by BalanceISODateTime
1690 result.time.nanosecond += offset_nanoseconds % 1000;
1691 result.time.microsecond += (offset_nanoseconds / 1000) % 1000;
1692 result.time.millisecond += (offset_nanoseconds / 1000000L) % 1000;
1693 result.time.second += (offset_nanoseconds / 1000000000L) % 60;
1694 result.time.minute += (offset_nanoseconds / 60000000000L) % 60;
1695 result.time.hour += (offset_nanoseconds / 3600000000000L) % 24;
1696 result.date.day += (offset_nanoseconds / 86400000000000L);
1697
1698 result = BalanceISODateTime(isolate, result);
1699 // 4. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
1700 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
1701 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]],
1702 // calendar).
1703 return temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(isolate, result, calendar);
1704}

1706} // namespace temporal
1707
1708namespace {
1709// #sec-temporal-getpossibleinstantsfor
1710MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetPossibleInstantsFor(
1711 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone,
1712 DirectHandle<Object> date_time) {
1713 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1714 // 1. Let possibleInstants be ? Invoke(timeZone, "getPossibleInstantsFor", «
1715 // dateTime »).
1716 DirectHandle<Object> function;
1717 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1718 isolate, function,
1719 Object::GetProperty(isolate, time_zone,
1720 isolate->factory()->getPossibleInstantsFor_string()));
1721 if (!IsCallable(*function)) {
1722 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1723 isolate,
1724 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledNonCallable,
1725 isolate->factory()->getPossibleInstantsFor_string()));
1726 }
1727 Handle<Object> possible_instants;
1728 {
1729 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {date_time};
1730 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1731 isolate, possible_instants,
1732 Execution::Call(isolate, function, time_zone, base::VectorOf(args)));
1733 }
1734
1735 // Step 4-6 of GetPossibleInstantsFor is implemented inside
1736 // temporal_instant_fixed_array_from_iterable.
1737 {
1738 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {possible_instants};
1739 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1740 isolate, possible_instants,
1741 Execution::CallBuiltin(
1742 isolate, isolate->temporal_instant_fixed_array_from_iterable(),
1743 possible_instants, base::VectorOf(args)));
1744 }
1745 DCHECK(IsFixedArray(*possible_instants));
1746 // 7. Return list.
1747 return Cast<FixedArray>(possible_instants);
1748}
1749
1750// #sec-temporal-disambiguatepossibleinstants
1751MaybeHandle<JSTemporalInstant> DisambiguatePossibleInstants(
1752 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<FixedArray> possible_instants,
1753 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone, DirectHandle<Object> date_time_obj,
1754 Disambiguation disambiguation, const char* method_name) {
1755 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1756 // 1. Assert: dateTime has an [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]] internal slot.
1757 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*date_time_obj));
1758 auto date_time = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(date_time_obj);
1759
1760 // 2. Let n be possibleInstants's length.
1761 int32_t n = possible_instants->length();
1762
1763 // 3. If n = 1, then
1764 if (n == 1) {
1765 // a. Return possibleInstants[0].
1766 Handle<Object> ret_obj(possible_instants->get(0), isolate);
1767 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalInstant(*ret_obj));
1768 return Cast<JSTemporalInstant>(ret_obj);
1769 }
1770 // 4. If n ≠ 0, then
1771 if (n != 0) {
1772 // a. If disambiguation is "earlier" or "compatible", then
1773 if (disambiguation == Disambiguation::kEarlier ||
1774 disambiguation == Disambiguation::kCompatible) {
1775 // i. Return possibleInstants[0].
1776 Handle<Object> ret_obj(possible_instants->get(0), isolate);
1777 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalInstant(*ret_obj));
1778 return Cast<JSTemporalInstant>(ret_obj);
1779 }
1780 // b. If disambiguation is "later", then
1781 if (disambiguation == Disambiguation::kLater) {
1782 // i. Return possibleInstants[n − 1].
1783 Handle<Object> ret_obj(possible_instants->get(n - 1), isolate);
1784 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalInstant(*ret_obj));
1785 return Cast<JSTemporalInstant>(ret_obj);
1786 }
1787 // c. Assert: disambiguation is "reject".
1788 DCHECK_EQ(disambiguation, Disambiguation::kReject);
1789 // d. Throw a RangeError exception.
1790 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
1791 }
1792 // 5. Assert: n = 0.
1793 DCHECK_EQ(n, 0);
1794 // 6. If disambiguation is "reject", then
1795 if (disambiguation == Disambiguation::kReject) {
1796 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
1797 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
1798 }
1799 // 7. Let epochNanoseconds be ! GetEpochFromISOParts(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
1800 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
1801 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
1802 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
1803 // dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]]).
1804 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds = GetEpochFromISOParts(
1805 isolate,
1806 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(), date_time->iso_day()},
1807 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(), date_time->iso_second(),
1808 date_time->iso_millisecond(), date_time->iso_microsecond(),
1809 date_time->iso_nanosecond()}});
1810
1811 // 8. Let dayBeforeNs be epochNanoseconds - ℤ(nsPerDay).
1812 DirectHandle<BigInt> one_day_in_ns =
1813 BigInt::FromUint64(isolate, 86400000000000ULL);
1814 DirectHandle<BigInt> day_before_ns =
1815 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds, one_day_in_ns)
1816 .ToHandleChecked();
1817 // 9. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(dayBeforeNs) is false, throw a RangeError
1818 // exception.
1819 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, day_before_ns)) {
1820 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
1821 }
1822 // 10. Let dayBefore be ! CreateTemporalInstant(dayBeforeNs).
1823 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> day_before =
1824 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, day_before_ns).ToHandleChecked();
1825 // 11. Let dayAfterNs be epochNanoseconds + ℤ(nsPerDay).
1826 DirectHandle<BigInt> day_after_ns =
1827 BigInt::Add(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds, one_day_in_ns).ToHandleChecked();
1828 // 12. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(dayAfterNs) is false, throw a RangeError
1829 // exception.
1830 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, day_after_ns)) {
1831 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
1832 }
1833 // 13. Let dayAfter be ! CreateTemporalInstant(dayAfterNs).
1834 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> day_after =
1835 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, day_after_ns).ToHandleChecked();
1836 // 10. Let offsetBefore be ? GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(timeZone, dayBefore).
1837 int64_t offset_before;
1838 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1839 isolate, offset_before,
1840 GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(isolate, time_zone, day_before, method_name),
1841 Handle<JSTemporalInstant>());
1842 // 11. Let offsetAfter be ? GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(timeZone, dayAfter).
1843 int64_t offset_after;
1844 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1845 isolate, offset_after,
1846 GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(isolate, time_zone, day_after, method_name),
1847 Handle<JSTemporalInstant>());
1848
1849 // 12. Let nanoseconds be offsetAfter − offsetBefore.
1850 double nanoseconds = offset_after - offset_before;
1851
1852 // 13. If disambiguation is "earlier", then
1853 if (disambiguation == Disambiguation::kEarlier) {
1854 // a. Let earlier be ? AddDateTime(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
1855 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
1856 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
1857 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]],
1858 // dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]], dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]],
1859 // dateTime.[[Calendar]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, −nanoseconds,
1860 // undefined).
1861 DateTimeRecord earlier;
1862 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1863 isolate, earlier,
1864 AddDateTime(
1865 isolate,
1866 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(),
1867 date_time->iso_day()},
1868 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(),
1869 date_time->iso_second(), date_time->iso_millisecond(),
1870 date_time->iso_microsecond(), date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
1871 direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate),
1872 {0, 0, 0, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, -nanoseconds}},
1873 isolate->factory()->undefined_value()),
1874 Handle<JSTemporalInstant>());
1875 // See https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/issues/1816
1876 // b. Let earlierDateTime be ? CreateTemporalDateTime(earlier.[[Year]],
1877 // earlier.[[Month]], earlier.[[Day]], earlier.[[Hour]], earlier.[[Minute]],
1878 // earlier.[[Second]], earlier.[[Millisecond]], earlier.[[Microsecond]],
1879 // earlier.[[Nanosecond]], dateTime.[[Calendar]]).
1880 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> earlier_date_time;
1881 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1882 isolate, earlier_date_time,
1883 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
1884 isolate, earlier, direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate)));
1885
1886 // c. Set possibleInstants to ? GetPossibleInstantsFor(timeZone,
1887 // earlierDateTime).
1888 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1889 isolate, possible_instants,
1890 GetPossibleInstantsFor(isolate, time_zone, earlier_date_time));
1891
1892 // d. If possibleInstants is empty, throw a RangeError exception.
1893 if (possible_instants->length() == 0) {
1894 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
1895 }
1896 // e. Return possibleInstants[0].
1897 Handle<Object> ret_obj(possible_instants->get(0), isolate);
1898 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalInstant(*ret_obj));
1899 return Cast<JSTemporalInstant>(ret_obj);
1900 }
1901 // 14. Assert: disambiguation is "compatible" or "later".
1902 DCHECK(disambiguation == Disambiguation::kCompatible ||
1903 disambiguation == Disambiguation::kLater);
1904 // 15. Let later be ? AddDateTime(dateTime.[[ISOYear]], dateTime.[[ISOMonth]],
1905 // dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]], dateTime.[[ISOMinute]],
1906 // dateTime.[[ISOSecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]],
1907 // dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]], dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]],
1908 // dateTime.[[Calendar]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, nanoseconds, undefined).
1909 DateTimeRecord later;
1910 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1911 isolate, later,
1912 AddDateTime(isolate,
1913 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(),
1914 date_time->iso_day()},
1915 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(),
1916 date_time->iso_second(), date_time->iso_millisecond(),
1917 date_time->iso_microsecond(), date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
1918 direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate),
1919 {0, 0, 0, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, nanoseconds}},
1920 isolate->factory()->undefined_value()),
1921 Handle<JSTemporalInstant>());
1922
1923 // See https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/issues/1816
1924 // 16. Let laterDateTime be ? CreateTemporalDateTime(later.[[Year]],
1925 // later.[[Month]], later.[[Day]], later.[[Hour]], later.[[Minute]],
1926 // later.[[Second]], later.[[Millisecond]], later.[[Microsecond]],
1927 // later.[[Nanosecond]], dateTime.[[Calendar]]).
1928
1929 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> later_date_time;
1930 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1931 isolate, later_date_time,
1932 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
1933 isolate, later, direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate)));
1934 // 17. Set possibleInstants to ? GetPossibleInstantsFor(timeZone,
1935 // laterDateTime).
1936 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1937 isolate, possible_instants,
1938 GetPossibleInstantsFor(isolate, time_zone, later_date_time));
1939 // 18. Set n to possibleInstants's length.
1940 n = possible_instants->length();
1941 // 19. If n = 0, throw a RangeError exception.
1942 if (n == 0) {
1943 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
1944 }
1945 // 20. Return possibleInstants[n − 1].
1946 Handle<Object> ret_obj(possible_instants->get(n - 1), isolate);
1947 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalInstant(*ret_obj));
1948 return Cast<JSTemporalInstant>(ret_obj);
1949}

1951// #sec-temporal-gettemporalcalendarwithisodefault
1952MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(
1953 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> item, const char* method_name) {
1954 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
1955
1956 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
1957 // 1. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDate]],
1958 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]], [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]],
1959 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]], [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]], or
1960 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then a. Return
1961 // item.[[Calendar]].
1962 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*item)) {
1963 return handle(Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(item)->calendar(), isolate);
1964 }
1965 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*item)) {
1966 return handle(Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(item)->calendar(), isolate);
1967 }
1968 if (IsJSTemporalPlainMonthDay(*item)) {
1969 return handle(Cast<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>(item)->calendar(), isolate);
1970 }
1971 if (IsJSTemporalPlainTime(*item)) {
1972 return handle(Cast<JSTemporalPlainTime>(item)->calendar(), isolate);
1973 }
1974 if (IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*item)) {
1975 return handle(Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(item)->calendar(), isolate);
1976 }
1977 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item)) {
1978 return handle(Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(item)->calendar(), isolate);
1979 }
1980
1981 // 2. Let calendar be ? Get(item, "calendar").
1982 Handle<Object> calendar;
1983 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1984 isolate, calendar,
1985 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, item, factory->calendar_string()));
1986 // 3. Return ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendar).
1987 return ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, calendar, method_name);
1988}
1989
1990enum class RequiredFields {
1991 kNone,
1992 kTimeZone,
1993 kTimeZoneAndOffset,
1994 kDay,
1995 kYearAndDay
1996};
1997
1998// The common part of PrepareTemporalFields and PreparePartialTemporalFields
1999// #sec-temporal-preparetemporalfields
2000// #sec-temporal-preparepartialtemporalfields
2001V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> PrepareTemporalFieldsOrPartial(
2002 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,
2003 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names, RequiredFields required,
2004 bool partial) {
2005 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2006
2007 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
2008 // 1. Let result be OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
2009 Handle<JSReceiver> result = isolate->factory()->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
2010 // 2. Let any be false.
2011 bool any = false;
2012 // 3. For each value property of fieldNames, do
2013 int length = field_names->length();
2014 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2015 DirectHandle<Object> property_obj(field_names->get(i), isolate);
2016 DirectHandle<String> property = Cast<String>(property_obj);
2017 // a. Let value be ? Get(fields, property).
2018 Handle<Object> value;
2019 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2020 isolate, value, JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, property));
2021
2022 // b. If value is undefined, then
2023 if (IsUndefined(*value)) {
2024 // This part is only for PrepareTemporalFields
2025 // Skip for the case of PreparePartialTemporalFields.
2026 if (partial) continue;
2027
2028 // i. If requiredFields contains property, then
2029 if (((required == RequiredFields::kDay ||
2030 required == RequiredFields::kYearAndDay) &&
2031 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->day_string())) ||
2032 ((required == RequiredFields::kTimeZone ||
2033 required == RequiredFields::kTimeZoneAndOffset) &&
2034 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->timeZone_string())) ||
2035 (required == RequiredFields::kTimeZoneAndOffset &&
2036 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->offset_string())) ||
2037 (required == RequiredFields::kYearAndDay &&
2038 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->year_string()))) {
2039 // 1. Throw a TypeError exception.
2040 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
2041 }
2042 // ii. Else,
2043 // 1. If property is in the Property column of Table 13, then
2044 // a. Set value to the corresponding Default value of the same row.
2045 if (String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->hour_string()) ||
2046 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->minute_string()) ||
2047 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->second_string()) ||
2048 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->millisecond_string()) ||
2049 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->microsecond_string()) ||
2050 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->nanosecond_string())) {
2051 value = Handle<Object>(Smi::zero(), isolate);
2052 }
2053 } else {
2054 // For both PrepareTemporalFields and PreparePartialTemporalFields
2055 any = partial;
2056 // c. Else,
2057 // i. If property is in the Property column of Table 13 and there is a
2058 // Conversion value in the same row, then
2059 // 1. Let Conversion represent the abstract operation named by the
2060 // Conversion value of the same row.
2061 // 2. Set value to ? Conversion(value).
2062 if (String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->month_string()) ||
2063 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->day_string())) {
2064 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, value,
2065 ToPositiveInteger(isolate, value));
2066 } else if (String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->year_string()) ||
2067 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->hour_string()) ||
2068 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->minute_string()) ||
2069 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->second_string()) ||
2070 String::Equals(isolate, property,
2071 factory->millisecond_string()) ||
2072 String::Equals(isolate, property,
2073 factory->microsecond_string()) ||
2074 String::Equals(isolate, property,
2075 factory->nanosecond_string()) ||
2076 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->eraYear_string())) {
2077 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, value,
2078 ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isolate, value));
2079 } else if (String::Equals(isolate, property,
2080 factory->monthCode_string()) ||
2081 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->offset_string()) ||
2082 String::Equals(isolate, property, factory->era_string())) {
2083 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, value,
2084 Object::ToString(isolate, value));
2085 }
2086 }
2087
2088 // d. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(result, property, value).
2089 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, result, property, value,
2090 Just(kThrowOnError))
2091 .FromJust());
2092 }
2093
2094 // Only for PreparePartialTemporalFields
2095 if (partial) {
2096 // 5. If any is false, then
2097 if (!any) {
2098 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
2099 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
2100 }
2101 }
2102 // 4. Return result.
2103 return result;
2104}

2108 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,

2120 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2121

2126// Template for DateFromFields, YearMonthFromFields, and MonthDayFromFields
2127template <typename T>
2128MaybeHandle<T> FromFields(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
2129 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,
2130 DirectHandle<Object> options,
2131 DirectHandle<String> property, InstanceType type) {
2132 DirectHandle<Object> function;
2133 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, function,
2134 Object::GetProperty(isolate, calendar, property));
2135 if (!IsCallable(*function)) {
2136 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
2137 isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledNonCallable, property));
2138 }
2139 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {fields, options};
2140 Handle<Object> result;
2141 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2142 isolate, result,
2143 Execution::Call(isolate, function, calendar, base::VectorOf(args)));
2144 if ((!IsHeapObject(*result)) ||
2145 Cast<HeapObject>(*result)->map()->instance_type() != type) {
2146 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
2147 }
2148 return Cast<T>(result);
2149}

2153 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
2154 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields, DirectHandle<Object> options) {
2155 return FromFields<JSTemporalPlainDate>(
2156 isolate, calendar, fields, options,
2157 isolate->factory()->dateFromFields_string(), JS_TEMPORAL_PLAIN_DATE_TYPE);
2158}

2195Maybe<ShowOverflow> ToTemporalOverflow(Isolate* isolate,
2196 DirectHandle<Object> options,
2197 const char* method_name) {
2198 // 1. If options is undefined, return "constrain".
2199 if (IsUndefined(*options)) return Just(ShowOverflow::kConstrain);
2200 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*options));
2201 // 2. Return ? GetOption(options, "overflow", « String », « "constrain",
2202 // "reject" », "constrain").
2203 return GetStringOption<ShowOverflow>(
2204 isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(options), "overflow", method_name,
2205 {"constrain", "reject"},

2207 ShowOverflow::kConstrain);

2221 {"prefer", "use", "ignore", "reject"},
2222 {Offset::kPrefer, Offset::kUse, Offset::kIgnore, Offset::kReject},
2223 fallback);

2243// #sec-temporal-builtintimezonegetinstantfor
2244MaybeHandle<JSTemporalInstant> BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(
2245 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone,
2246 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time,
2247 Disambiguation disambiguation, const char* method_name) {
2248 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2249 // 1. Assert: dateTime has an [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]] internal slot.
2250 // 2. Let possibleInstants be ? GetPossibleInstantsFor(timeZone, dateTime).
2251 DirectHandle<FixedArray> possible_instants;
2252 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2253 isolate, possible_instants,
2254 GetPossibleInstantsFor(isolate, time_zone, date_time));
2255 // 3. Return ? DisambiguatePossibleInstants(possibleInstants, timeZone,
2256 // dateTime, disambiguation).
2257 return DisambiguatePossibleInstants(isolate, possible_instants, time_zone,
2258 date_time, disambiguation, method_name);
2259}
2260
2261// #sec-temporal-totemporalinstant
2262MaybeHandle<JSTemporalInstant> ToTemporalInstant(Isolate* isolate,
2263 Handle<Object> item,
2264 const char* method_name) {
2265 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2266
2267 // 1. If Type(item) is Object, then
2268 // a. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalInstant]] internal slot, then
2269 if (IsJSTemporalInstant(*item)) {
2270 // i. Return item.
2271 return Cast<JSTemporalInstant>(item);
2272 }
2273 // b. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then
2274 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item)) {
2275 // i. Return ! CreateTemporalInstant(item.[[Nanoseconds]]).
2276 DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds(
2277 Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(*item)->nanoseconds(), isolate);
2278 return temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, nanoseconds)
2279 .ToHandleChecked();
2280 }
2281 // 2. Let string be ? ToString(item).
2282 DirectHandle<String> string;
2283 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, string, Object::ToString(isolate, item));
2284
2285 // 3. Let epochNanoseconds be ? ParseTemporalInstant(string).
2286 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds;
2287 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2288 isolate, epoch_nanoseconds,
2289 ParseTemporalInstant(isolate, indirect_handle(string, isolate)));
2290
2291 // 4. Return ? CreateTemporalInstant(ℤ(epochNanoseconds)).
2292 return temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds);
2293}

2298// #sec-temporal-totemporalcalendar
2299MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> ToTemporalCalendar(
2300 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> temporal_calendar_like,
2301 const char* method_name) {
2302 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
2303 // 1.If Type(temporalCalendarLike) is Object, then
2304 if (IsJSReceiver(*temporal_calendar_like)) {
2305 // a. If temporalCalendarLike has an [[InitializedTemporalDate]],
2306 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]], [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]],
2307 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]], [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]], or
2308 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then i. Return
2309 // temporalCalendarLike.[[Calendar]].
2310
2311#define EXTRACT_CALENDAR(T, obj) \
2312 if (IsJSTemporal##T(*obj)) { \
2313 return handle(Cast<JSTemporal##T>(obj)->calendar(), isolate); \
2314 }
2315
2316 EXTRACT_CALENDAR(PlainDate, temporal_calendar_like)
2317 EXTRACT_CALENDAR(PlainDateTime, temporal_calendar_like)
2318 EXTRACT_CALENDAR(PlainMonthDay, temporal_calendar_like)
2319 EXTRACT_CALENDAR(PlainTime, temporal_calendar_like)
2320 EXTRACT_CALENDAR(PlainYearMonth, temporal_calendar_like)
2321 EXTRACT_CALENDAR(ZonedDateTime, temporal_calendar_like)
2322
2323#undef EXTRACT_CALENDAR
2324 Handle<JSReceiver> obj = Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_calendar_like);
2325
2326 // b. If ? HasProperty(temporalCalendarLike, "calendar") is false, return
2327 // temporalCalendarLike.
2328 bool has;
2329 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2330 isolate, has,
2331 JSReceiver::HasProperty(isolate, obj, factory->calendar_string()),
2332 Handle<JSReceiver>());
2333 if (!has) {
2334 return obj;
2335 }
2336 // c. Set temporalCalendarLike to ? Get(temporalCalendarLike, "calendar").
2337 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2338 isolate, temporal_calendar_like,
2339 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, obj, factory->calendar_string()));
2340 // d. If Type(temporalCalendarLike) is Object
2341 if (IsJSReceiver(*temporal_calendar_like)) {
2342 obj = Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_calendar_like);
2343 // and ? HasProperty(temporalCalendarLike, "calendar") is false,
2344 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2345 isolate, has,
2346 JSReceiver::HasProperty(isolate, obj, factory->calendar_string()),
2347 Handle<JSReceiver>());
2348 if (!has) {
2349 // return temporalCalendarLike.
2350 return obj;
2351 }
2352 }
2353 }
2354
2355 // 2. Let identifier be ? ToString(temporalCalendarLike).
2356 Handle<String> identifier;
2357 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, identifier,
2358 Object::ToString(isolate, temporal_calendar_like));
2359 // 3. Let identifier be ? ParseTemporalCalendarString(identifier).
2360 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, identifier,
2361 ParseTemporalCalendarString(isolate, identifier));
2362 // 4. If IsBuiltinCalendar(identifier) is false, throw a RangeError
2363 // exception.
2364 if (!IsBuiltinCalendar(isolate, identifier)) {
2365 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
2366 isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidCalendar, identifier));
2367 }
2368 // 5. Return ? CreateTemporalCalendar(identifier).
2369 return CreateTemporalCalendar(isolate, identifier);
2370}

2435// #sec-temporal-totemporaldate
2436MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> ToTemporalDate(Isolate* isolate,
2437 Handle<Object> item_obj,
2438 DirectHandle<Object> options,
2439 const char* method_name) {
2440 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2441
2442 // 2. Assert: Type(options) is Object or Undefined.
2443 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*options) || IsUndefined(*options));
2444 // 3. If Type(item) is Object, then
2445 if (IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
2446 Handle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
2447 // a. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDate]] internal slot, then
2448 // i. Return item.
2449 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*item)) {
2450 return Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(item);
2451 }
2452 // b. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot,
2453 // then
2454 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item)) {
2455 // i. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
2456 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2457 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
2458 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
2459
2460 // ii. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(item.[[Nanoseconds]]).
2461 auto zoned_date_time = Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(item);
2462 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
2463 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(
2464 isolate, direct_handle(zoned_date_time->nanoseconds(), isolate))
2465 .ToHandleChecked();
2466 // iii. Let plainDateTime be ?
2467 // BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(item.[[TimeZone]],
2468 // instant, item.[[Calendar]]).
2469 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> plain_date_time;
2470 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2471 isolate, plain_date_time,
2472 temporal::BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(
2473 isolate,
2474 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(zoned_date_time->time_zone(), isolate),
2475 instant,
2476 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(zoned_date_time->calendar(), isolate),
2477 method_name));
2478 // iv. Return ! CreateTemporalDate(plainDateTime.[[ISOYear]],
2479 // plainDateTime.[[ISOMonth]], plainDateTime.[[ISODay]],
2480 // plainDateTime.[[Calendar]]).
2481 return CreateTemporalDate(
2482 isolate,
2483 {plain_date_time->iso_year(), plain_date_time->iso_month(),
2484 plain_date_time->iso_day()},
2485 direct_handle(plain_date_time->calendar(), isolate))
2486 .ToHandleChecked();
2487 }
2488
2489 // c. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]] internal slot, then
2490 // item.[[ISODay]], item.[[Calendar]]).
2491 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*item)) {
2492 // i. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
2493 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2494 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
2495 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
2496 // ii. Return ! CreateTemporalDate(item.[[ISOYear]], item.[[ISOMonth]],
2497 auto date_time = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(item);
2498 return CreateTemporalDate(isolate,
2499 {date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(),
2500 date_time->iso_day()},
2501 direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate))
2502 .ToHandleChecked();
2503 }
2504
2505 // d. Let calendar be ? GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(item).
2506 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
2507 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2508 isolate, calendar,
2509 GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, item, method_name));
2510 // e. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "day", "month",
2511 // "monthCode", "year" »).
2512 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names =
2513 DayMonthMonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);
2514 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
2515 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
2516 // f. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(item,
2517 // fieldNames, «»).
2518 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
2519 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, fields,
2520 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, item, field_names,
2521 RequiredFields::kNone));
2522 // g. Return ? DateFromFields(calendar, fields, options).
2523 return DateFromFields(isolate, calendar, fields, options);
2524 }
2525 // 4. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
2526 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2527 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
2528 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
2529
2530 // 5. Let string be ? ToString(item).
2531 Handle<String> string;
2532 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, string,
2533 Object::ToString(isolate, item_obj));
2534 // 6. Let result be ? ParseTemporalDateString(string).
2535 DateRecordWithCalendar result;
2536 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2537 isolate, result, ParseTemporalDateString(isolate, string),
2538 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
2539
2540 // 7. Assert: ! IsValidISODate(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
2541 // result.[[Day]]) is true.
2542 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, result.date));
2543 // 8. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(result.[[Calendar]]).
2544 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
2545 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2546 isolate, calendar,
2547 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, result.calendar, method_name));
2548 // 9. Return ? CreateTemporalDate(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
2549 // result.[[Day]], calendar).
2550 return CreateTemporalDate(isolate, result.date, calendar);
2551}
2552
2553MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> ToTemporalDate(Isolate* isolate,
2554 Handle<Object> item_obj,
2555 const char* method_name) {
2556 // 1. If options is not present, set options to undefined.
2557 return ToTemporalDate(isolate, item_obj,
2558 isolate->factory()->undefined_value(), method_name);
2559}

2561// #sec-isintegralnumber
2562bool IsIntegralNumber(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> argument) {
2563 // 1. If Type(argument) is not Number, return false.
2564 if (!IsNumber(*argument)) return false;
2565 // 2. If argument is NaN, +∞𝔽, or -∞𝔽, return false.
2566 double number = Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*argument));
2567 if (!std::isfinite(number)) return false;
2568 // 3. If floor(abs(ℝ(argument))) ≠ abs(ℝ(argument)), return false.
2569 if (std::floor(std::abs(number)) != std::abs(number)) return false;
2570 // 4. Return true.
2571 return true;
2572}
2573
2574// #sec-temporal-tointegerwithoutrounding
2575Maybe<double> ToIntegerWithoutRounding(Isolate* isolate,
2576 Handle<Object> argument) {
2577 // 1. Let number be ? ToNumber(argument).
2578 DirectHandle<Number> number;
2579 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2580 isolate, number, Object::ToNumber(isolate, argument), Nothing<double>());
2581 // 2. If number is NaN, +0𝔽, or −0𝔽 return 0.
2582 if (IsNaN(*number) || Object::NumberValue(*number) == 0) {
2583 return Just(static_cast<double>(0));
2584 }
2585 // 3. If IsIntegralNumber(number) is false, throw a RangeError exception.
2586 if (!IsIntegralNumber(isolate, number)) {
2587 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
2588 isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(), Nothing<double>());
2589 }
2590 // 4. Return ℝ(number).
2591 return Just(Object::NumberValue(*number));
2592}
