2597
2598// #sec-temporal-regulatetime
2599Maybe<TimeRecord> RegulateTime(Isolate* isolate, const TimeRecord& time,
2600 ShowOverflow overflow) {
2601 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2602
2603 // 1. Assert: hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond and nanosecond
2604 // are integers.
2605 // 2. Assert: overflow is either "constrain" or "reject".
2606 switch (overflow) {
2607 case ShowOverflow::kConstrain: {
2608 TimeRecord result(time);
2609 // 3. If overflow is "constrain", then
2610 // a. Return ! ConstrainTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond,
2611 // microsecond, nanosecond).
2612 result.hour = std::max(std::min(result.hour, 23), 0);
2613 result.minute = std::max(std::min(result.minute, 59), 0);
2614 result.second = std::max(std::min(result.second, 59), 0);
2615 result.millisecond = std::max(std::min(result.millisecond, 999), 0);
2616 result.microsecond = std::max(std::min(result.microsecond, 999), 0);
2617 result.nanosecond = std::max(std::min(result.nanosecond, 999), 0);
2618 return Just(result);
2619 }
2620 case ShowOverflow::kReject:
2621 // 4. If overflow is "reject", then
2622 // a. If ! IsValidTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond,
2623 // nanosecond) is false, throw a RangeError exception.
2624 if (!IsValidTime(isolate, time)) {
2625 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
2626 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
2627 Nothing<TimeRecord>());
2628 }
2629 // b. Return the new Record { [[Hour]]: hour, [[Minute]]: minute,
2630 // [[Second]]: second, [[Millisecond]]: millisecond, [[Microsecond]]:
2631 // microsecond, [[Nanosecond]]: nanosecond }.
2632 return Just(time);
2633 }
2634}
2635
2636// #sec-temporal-totemporaltime
2637MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> ToTemporalTime(
2638 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, const char* method_name,
2639 ShowOverflow overflow = ShowOverflow::kConstrain) {
2640 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
2641 TimeRecordWithCalendar result;
2642 // 2. Assert: overflow is either "constrain" or "reject".
2643 // 3. If Type(item) is Object, then
2644 if (IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
2645 Handle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
2646 // a. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalTime]] internal slot, then
2647 // i. Return item.
2648 if (IsJSTemporalPlainTime(*item)) {
2649 return Cast<JSTemporalPlainTime>(item);
2650 }
2651 // b. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot,
2652 // then
2653 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item)) {
2654 // i. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(item.[[Nanoseconds]]).
2655 auto zoned_date_time = Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(item);
2656 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
2657 CreateTemporalInstant(
2658 isolate, direct_handle(zoned_date_time->nanoseconds(), isolate))
2659 .ToHandleChecked();
2660 // ii. Set plainDateTime to ?
2661 // BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(item.[[TimeZone]],
2662 // instant, item.[[Calendar]]).
2663 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> plain_date_time;
2664 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2665 isolate, plain_date_time,
2666 BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(
2667 isolate,
2668 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(zoned_date_time->time_zone(), isolate),
2669 instant,
2670 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(zoned_date_time->calendar(), isolate),
2671 method_name));
2672 // iii. Return !
2673 // CreateTemporalTime(plainDateTime.[[ISOHour]],
2674 // plainDateTime.[[ISOMinute]], plainDateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
2675 // plainDateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], plainDateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
2676 // plainDateTime.[[ISONanosecond]]).
2677 return CreateTemporalTime(isolate, {plain_date_time->iso_hour(),
2678 plain_date_time->iso_minute(),
2679 plain_date_time->iso_second(),
2680 plain_date_time->iso_millisecond(),
2681 plain_date_time->iso_microsecond(),
2682 plain_date_time->iso_nanosecond()})
2683 .ToHandleChecked();
2684 }
2685 // c. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]] internal slot, then
2686 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*item)) {
2687 // i. Return ! CreateTemporalTime(item.[[ISOHour]], item.[[ISOMinute]],
2688 // item.[[ISOSecond]], item.[[ISOMillisecond]], item.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
2689 // item.[[ISONanosecond]]).
2690 auto date_time = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(item);
2691 return CreateTemporalTime(
2692 isolate,
2693 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(),
2694 date_time->iso_second(), date_time->iso_millisecond(),
2695 date_time->iso_microsecond(), date_time->iso_nanosecond()})
2696 .ToHandleChecked();
2697 }
2698 // d. Let calendar be ? GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(item).
2699 Handle<JSReceiver> calendar;
2700 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2701 isolate, calendar,
2702 GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, item, method_name));
2703 // e. If ? ToString(calendar) is not "iso8601", then
2704 DirectHandle<String> identifier;
2705 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, identifier,
2706 Object::ToString(isolate, calendar));
2707 if (!String::Equals(isolate, factory->iso8601_string(), identifier)) {
2708 // i. Throw a RangeError exception.
2709 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
2710 }
2711 // f. Let result be ? ToTemporalTimeRecord(item).
2712 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2713 isolate, result.time, ToTemporalTimeRecord(isolate, item, method_name),
2714 Handle<JSTemporalPlainTime>());
2715 // g. Set result to ? RegulateTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
2716 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
2717 // result.[[Nanosecond]], overflow).
2718 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2719 isolate, result.time, RegulateTime(isolate, result.time, overflow),
2720 Handle<JSTemporalPlainTime>());
2721 } else {
2722 // 4. Else,
2723 // a. Let string be ? ToString(item).
2724 Handle<String> string;
2725 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, string,
2726 Object::ToString(isolate, item_obj));
2727 // b. Let result be ? ParseTemporalTimeString(string).
2728 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2729 isolate, result, ParseTemporalTimeString(isolate, string),
2730 Handle<JSTemporalPlainTime>());
2731 // c. Assert: ! IsValidTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
2732 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
2733 // result.[[Nanosecond]]) is true.
2734 DCHECK(IsValidTime(isolate, result.time));
2735 // d. If result.[[Calendar]] is not one of undefined or "iso8601", then
2736 DCHECK(IsUndefined(*result.calendar) || IsString(*result.calendar));
2737 if (!IsUndefined(*result.calendar) &&
2738 !String::Equals(isolate, Cast<String>(result.calendar),
2739 isolate->factory()->iso8601_string())) {
2740 // i. Throw a RangeError exception.
2741 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
2742 }
2743 }
2744 // 5. Return ? CreateTemporalTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
2745 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
2746 // result.[[Nanosecond]]).
2747 return CreateTemporalTime(isolate, result.time);
2748}
2749
2750// Helper function to loop through Table 8 Duration Record Fields
2751// This function implement
2752// "For each row of Table 8, except the header row, in table order, do"
2753// loop. It is designed to be used to implement the common part of
2754// ToPartialDuration, ToTemporalDurationRecord
2755Maybe<bool> IterateDurationRecordFieldsTable(
2756 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_duration_like,
2757 Maybe<bool> (*RowFunction)(Isolate*,
2758 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_duration_like,
2759 DirectHandle<String>, double*),
2760 DurationRecord* record) {
2761 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
2762 std::array<std::pair<DirectHandle<String>, double*>, 10> table8 = {
2763 {{factory->days_string(), &record->time_duration.days},
2764 {factory->hours_string(), &record->time_duration.hours},
2765 {factory->microseconds_string(), &record->time_duration.microseconds},
2766 {factory->milliseconds_string(), &record->time_duration.milliseconds},
2767 {factory->minutes_string(), &record->time_duration.minutes},
2768 {factory->months_string(), &record->months},
2769 {factory->nanoseconds_string(), &record->time_duration.nanoseconds},
2770 {factory->seconds_string(), &record->time_duration.seconds},
2771 {factory->weeks_string(), &record->weeks},
2772 {factory->years_string(), &record->years}}};
2773
2774 // x. Let any be false.
2775 bool any = false;
2776 // x+1. For each row of Table 8, except the header row, in table order, do
2777 for (const auto& row : table8) {
2778 bool result;
2779 // row.first is prop: the Property Name value of the current row
2780 // row.second is the address of result's field whose name is the Field Name
2781 // value of the current row
2782 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2783 isolate, result,
2784 RowFunction(isolate, temporal_duration_like, row.first, row.second),
2785 Nothing<bool>());
2786 any |= result;
2787 }
2788 return Just(any);
2789}
2790
2791// #sec-temporal-totemporaldurationrecord
2792Maybe<DurationRecord> ToTemporalDurationRecord(
2793 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> temporal_duration_like_obj,
2794 const char* method_name) {
2795 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2796
2797 // 1. If Type(temporalDurationLike) is not Object, then
2798 if (!IsJSReceiver(*temporal_duration_like_obj)) {
2799 // a. Let string be ? ToString(temporalDurationLike).
2800 Handle<String> string;
2801 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2802 isolate, string, Object::ToString(isolate, temporal_duration_like_obj),
2803 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
2804 // b. Let result be ? ParseTemporalDurationString(string).
2805 return ParseTemporalDurationString(isolate, string);
2806 }
2807 Handle<JSReceiver> temporal_duration_like =
2808 Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_duration_like_obj);
2809 // 2. If temporalDurationLike has an [[InitializedTemporalDuration]] internal
2810 // slot, then
2811 if (IsJSTemporalDuration(*temporal_duration_like)) {
2812 // a. Return ! CreateDurationRecord(temporalDurationLike.[[Years]],
2813 // temporalDurationLike.[[Months]], temporalDurationLike.[[Weeks]],
2814 // temporalDurationLike.[[Days]], temporalDurationLike.[[Hours]],
2815 // temporalDurationLike.[[Minutes]], temporalDurationLike.[[Seconds]],
2816 // temporalDurationLike.[[Milliseconds]],
2817 // temporalDurationLike.[[Microseconds]],
2818 // temporalDurationLike.[[Nanoseconds]]).
2819 auto duration = Cast<JSTemporalDuration>(temporal_duration_like);
2820 return DurationRecord::Create(isolate,
2821 Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),
2822 Object::NumberValue(duration->months()),
2823 Object::NumberValue(duration->weeks()),
2824 Object::NumberValue(duration->days()),
2825 Object::NumberValue(duration->hours()),
2826 Object::NumberValue(duration->minutes()),
2827 Object::NumberValue(duration->seconds()),
2828 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
2829 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
2830 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds()));
2831 }
2832 // 3. Let result be a new Record with all the internal slots given in the
2833 // Internal Slot column in Table 8.
2834 DurationRecord result;
2835 // 4. Let any be false.
2836 bool any = false;
2837
2838 // 5. For each row of Table 8, except the header row, in table order, do
2839 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2840 isolate, any,
2841 IterateDurationRecordFieldsTable(
2842 isolate, temporal_duration_like,
2843 [](Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_duration_like,
2844 DirectHandle<String> prop, double* field) -> Maybe<bool> {
2845 bool not_undefined = false;
2846 // a. Let prop be the Property value of the current row.
2847 Handle<Object> val;
2848 // b. Let val be ? Get(temporalDurationLike, prop).
2849 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2850 isolate, val,
2851 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, temporal_duration_like, prop),
2852 Nothing<bool>());
2853 // c. If val is undefined, then
2854 if (IsUndefined(*val)) {
2855 // i. Set result's internal slot whose name is the Internal Slot
2856 // value of the current row to 0.
2857 *field = 0;
2858 // d. Else,
2859 } else {
2860 // i. Set any to true.
2861 not_undefined = true;
2862 // ii. Let val be 𝔽(? ToIntegerWithoutRounding(val)).
2863 // iii. Set result's field whose name is the Field Name value of
2864 // the current row to val.
2865 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2866 isolate, *field, ToIntegerWithoutRounding(isolate, val),
2867 Nothing<bool>());
2868 }
2869 return Just(not_undefined);
2870 },
2871 &result),
2872 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
2873
2874 // 6. If any is false, then
2875 if (!any) {
2876 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
2877 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
2878 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
2879 }
2880 // 7. If ! IsValidDuration(result.[[Years]], result.[[Months]],
2881 // result.[[Weeks]] result.[[Days]], result.[[Hours]], result.[[Minutes]],
2882 // result.[[Seconds]], result.[[Milliseconds]], result.[[Microseconds]],
2883 // result.[[Nanoseconds]]) is false, then
2884 if (!IsValidDuration(isolate, result)) {
2885 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
2886 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
2887 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
2888 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
2889 }
2890 // 8. Return result.
2891 return Just(result);
2892}

2894// #sec-temporal-totemporalduration
2895MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> ToTemporalDuration(Isolate* isolate,
2896 Handle<Object> item,
2897 const char* method_name) {
2898 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2899
2900 DurationRecord result;
2901 // 1. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalDuration]]
2902 // internal slot, then
2903 if (IsJSTemporalDuration(*item)) {
2904 // a. Return item.
2905 return Cast<JSTemporalDuration>(item);
2906 }
2907 // 2. Let result be ? ToTemporalDurationRecord(item).
2908 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2909 isolate, result, ToTemporalDurationRecord(isolate, item, method_name),
2910 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
2911
2912 // 3. Return ? CreateTemporalDuration(result.[[Years]], result.[[Months]],
2913 // result.[[Weeks]], result.[[Days]], result.[[Hours]], result.[[Minutes]],
2914 // result.[[Seconds]], result.[[Milliseconds]], result.[[Microseconds]],
2915 // result.[[Nanoseconds]]).
2916 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, result);
2917}

2919// #sec-temporal-totemporaltimezone
2920MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> ToTemporalTimeZone(
2921 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> temporal_time_zone_like,
2922 const char* method_name) {
2923 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
2924
2925 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
2926 // 1. If Type(temporalTimeZoneLike) is Object, then
2927 if (IsJSReceiver(*temporal_time_zone_like)) {
2928 // a. If temporalTimeZoneLike has an [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]]
2929 // internal slot, then
2930 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*temporal_time_zone_like)) {
2931 // i. Return temporalTimeZoneLike.[[TimeZone]].
2932 auto zoned_date_time =
2933 Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(temporal_time_zone_like);
2934 return handle(zoned_date_time->time_zone(), isolate);
2935 }
2936 Handle<JSReceiver> obj = Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_time_zone_like);
2937 // b. If ? HasProperty(temporalTimeZoneLike, "timeZone") is false,
2938 bool has;
2939 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2940 isolate, has,
2941 JSReceiver::HasProperty(isolate, obj, factory->timeZone_string()),
2942 Handle<JSReceiver>());
2943 if (!has) {
2944 // return temporalTimeZoneLike.
2945 return obj;
2946 }
2947 // c. Set temporalTimeZoneLike to ?
2948 // Get(temporalTimeZoneLike, "timeZone").
2949 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2950 isolate, temporal_time_zone_like,
2951 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, obj, factory->timeZone_string()));
2952 // d. If Type(temporalTimeZoneLike)
2953 if (IsJSReceiver(*temporal_time_zone_like)) {
2954 // is Object and ? HasProperty(temporalTimeZoneLike, "timeZone") is false,
2955 obj = Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_time_zone_like);
2956 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2957 isolate, has,
2958 JSReceiver::HasProperty(isolate, obj, factory->timeZone_string()),
2959 Handle<JSReceiver>());
2960 if (!has) {
2961 // return temporalTimeZoneLike.
2962 return obj;
2963 }
2964 }
2965 }
2966 Handle<String> identifier;
2967 // 2. Let identifier be ? ToString(temporalTimeZoneLike).
2968 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2969 isolate, identifier, Object::ToString(isolate, temporal_time_zone_like));
2970
2971 // 3. Let parseResult be ? ParseTemporalTimeZoneString(identifier).
2972 TimeZoneRecord parse_result;
2973 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2974 isolate, parse_result, ParseTemporalTimeZoneString(isolate, identifier),
2975 Handle<JSReceiver>());
2976
2977 // 4. If parseResult.[[Name]] is not undefined, then
2978 if (!IsUndefined(*parse_result.name)) {
2979 DCHECK(IsString(*parse_result.name));
2980 // a. Let name be parseResult.[[Name]].
2981 Handle<String> name = Cast<String>(parse_result.name);
2982 // b. If ParseText(StringToCodePoints(name, TimeZoneNumericUTCOffset)) is
2983 // a List of errors, then
2984 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed_offset =
2985 TemporalParser::ParseTimeZoneNumericUTCOffset(isolate, name);
2986 if (!parsed_offset.has_value()) {
2987 // i. If ! IsValidTimeZoneName(name) is false, throw a RangeError
2988 // exception.
2989 if (!IsValidTimeZoneName(isolate, name)) {
2990 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
2991 }
2992 // ii. Set name to ! CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(name).
2993 name = CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(isolate, name);
2994 }
2995 // c. Return ! CreateTemporalTimeZone(name).
2996 return temporal::CreateTemporalTimeZone(isolate, name);
2997 }
2998 // 5. If parseResult.[[Z]] is true, return ! CreateTemporalTimeZone("UTC").
2999 if (parse_result.z) {
3000 return CreateTemporalTimeZoneUTC(isolate);
3001 }
3002 // 6. Return ! CreateTemporalTimeZone(parseResult.[[OffsetString]]).
3003 DCHECK(IsString(*parse_result.offset_string));
3004 return temporal::CreateTemporalTimeZone(
3005 isolate, Cast<String>(parse_result.offset_string));
3006}

3076
3077// #sec-temporal-formattimezoneoffsetstring
3078Handle<String> FormatTimeZoneOffsetString(Isolate* isolate,
3079 int64_t offset_nanoseconds) {
3080 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
3081 // 1. Assert: offsetNanoseconds is an integer.
3082 // 2. If offsetNanoseconds ≥ 0, let sign be "+"; otherwise, let sign be "-".
3083 builder.AppendCharacter((offset_nanoseconds >= 0) ? '+' : '-');
3084 // 3. Let offsetNanoseconds be abs(offsetNanoseconds).
3085 offset_nanoseconds = std::abs(offset_nanoseconds);
3086 // 4. Let nanoseconds be offsetNanoseconds modulo 10^9.
3087 int64_t nanoseconds = offset_nanoseconds % 1000000000;
3088 // 5. Let seconds be floor(offsetNanoseconds / 10^9) modulo 60.
3089 int32_t seconds = (offset_nanoseconds / 1000000000) % 60;
3090 // 6. Let minutes be floor(offsetNanoseconds / (6 × 10^10)) modulo 60.
3091 int32_t minutes = (offset_nanoseconds / 60000000000) % 60;
3092 // 7. Let hours be floor(offsetNanoseconds / (3.6 × 10^12)).
3093 int32_t hours = offset_nanoseconds / 3600000000000;
3094 // 8. Let h be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(hours, 2).
3095 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, hours, 2);
3096
3097 // 9. Let m be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(minutes, 2).
3098 builder.AppendCharacter(':');
3099 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, minutes, 2);
3100
3101 // 10. Let s be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(seconds, 2).
3102 // 11. If nanoseconds ≠ 0, then
3103 if (nanoseconds != 0) {
3104 // a. Let fraction be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(nanoseconds, 9).
3105 // b. Set fraction to the longest possible substring of fraction starting at
3106 // position 0 and not ending with the code unit 0x0030 (DIGIT ZERO). c. Let
3107 // post be the string-concatenation of the code unit 0x003A (COLON), s, the
3108 // code unit 0x002E (FULL STOP), and fraction.
3109 builder.AppendCharacter(':');
3110 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, seconds, 2);
3111 builder.AppendCharacter('.');
3112 int64_t divisor = 100000000;
3113 do {
3114 builder.AppendInt(static_cast<int>(nanoseconds / divisor));
3115 nanoseconds %= divisor;
3116 divisor /= 10;
3117 } while (nanoseconds > 0);
3118 // 11. Else if seconds ≠ 0, then
3119 } else if (seconds != 0) {
3120 // a. Let post be the string-concatenation of the code unit 0x003A (COLON)
3121 // and s.
3122 builder.AppendCharacter(':');
3123 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, seconds, 2);
3124 }
3125 // 12. Return the string-concatenation of sign, h, the code unit 0x003A
3126 // (COLON), m, and post.
3127 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked(), isolate);
3128}
3129
3130double RoundNumberToIncrement(Isolate* isolate, double x, double increment,
3131 RoundingMode rounding_mode);
3132
3133// #sec-temporal-formatisotimezoneoffsetstring
3134Handle<String> FormatISOTimeZoneOffsetString(Isolate* isolate,
3135 int64_t offset_nanoseconds) {
3136 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
3137 // 1. Assert: offsetNanoseconds is an integer.
3138 // 2. Set offsetNanoseconds to ! RoundNumberToIncrement(offsetNanoseconds, 60
3139 // × 10^9, "halfExpand").
3140 offset_nanoseconds = RoundNumberToIncrement(
3141 isolate, offset_nanoseconds, 60000000000, RoundingMode::kHalfExpand);
3142 // 3. If offsetNanoseconds ≥ 0, let sign be "+"; otherwise, let sign be "-".
3143 builder.AppendCharacter((offset_nanoseconds >= 0) ? '+' : '-');
3144 // 4. Set offsetNanoseconds to abs(offsetNanoseconds).
3145 offset_nanoseconds = std::abs(offset_nanoseconds);
3146 // 5. Let minutes be offsetNanoseconds / (60 × 10^9) modulo 60.
3147 int32_t minutes = (offset_nanoseconds / 60000000000) % 60;
3148 // 6. Let hours be floor(offsetNanoseconds / (3600 × 10^9)).
3149 int32_t hours = offset_nanoseconds / 3600000000000;
3150 // 7. Let h be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(hours, 2).
3151 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, hours, 2);
3152
3153 // 8. Let m be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(minutes, 2).
3154 builder.AppendCharacter(':');
3155 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, minutes, 2);
3156 // 9. Return the string-concatenation of sign, h, the code unit 0x003A
3157 // (COLON), and m.
3158 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked(), isolate);
3159}
3160
3161int32_t DecimalLength(int32_t n) {
3162 int32_t i = 1;
3163 while (n >= 10) {
3164 n /= 10;
3165 i++;
3166 }
3167 return i;
3168}
3169
3170// #sec-tozeropaddeddecimalstring
3171void ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(IncrementalStringBuilder* builder, int32_t n,
3172 int32_t min_length) {
3173 for (int32_t pad = min_length - DecimalLength(n); pad > 0; pad--) {
3174 builder->AppendCharacter('0');
3175 }
3176 builder->AppendInt(n);
3177}

3179// #sec-temporal-padisoyear
3180void PadISOYear(IncrementalStringBuilder* builder, int32_t y) {
3181 // 1. Assert: y is an integer.
3182 // 2. If y ≥ 0 and y ≤ 9999, then
3183 if (y >= 0 && y <= 9999) {
3184 // a. Return ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(y, 4).
3185 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(builder, y, 4);
3186 return;
3187 }
3188 // 3. If y > 0, let yearSign be "+"; otherwise, let yearSign be "-".
3189 if (y > 0) {
3190 builder->AppendCharacter('+');
3191 } else {
3192 builder->AppendCharacter('-');
3193 }
3194 // 4. Let year be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(abs(y), 6).
3195 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(builder, std::abs(y), 6);
3196 // 5. Return the string-concatenation of yearSign and year.
3197}

3199// #sec-temporal-formatcalendarannotation
3200Handle<String> FormatCalendarAnnotation(Isolate* isolate,
3201 DirectHandle<String> id,
3202 ShowCalendar show_calendar) {
3203 // 1.Assert: showCalendar is "auto", "always", or "never".
3204 // 2. If showCalendar is "never", return the empty String.
3205 if (show_calendar == ShowCalendar::kNever) {
3206 return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
3207 }
3208 // 3. If showCalendar is "auto" and id is "iso8601", return the empty String.
3209 if (show_calendar == ShowCalendar::kAuto &&
3210 String::Equals(isolate, id, isolate->factory()->iso8601_string())) {
3211 return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
3212 }
3213 // 4. Return the string-concatenation of "[u-ca=", id, and "]".
3214 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
3215 builder.AppendCStringLiteral("[u-ca=");
3216 builder.AppendString(id);
3217 builder.AppendCharacter(']');
3218 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked(), isolate);
3219}

3233 // 3. Return FormatCalendarAnnotation(calendarID, showCalendar).

3317 // (HYPHEN-MINUS), and month.
3318 builder.AppendCharacter('-');
3319 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, year_month->iso_month(), 2);
3320 // 6. Let calendarID be ? ToString(yearMonth.[[Calendar]]).
3321 DirectHandle<String> calendar_id;
3322 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(

3325 // 7. If showCalendar is "always" or if *_calendarID_ is not *"iso8601", then
3326 if (show_calendar == ShowCalendar::kAlways ||
3327 !String::Equals(isolate, calendar_id,
3328 isolate->factory()->iso8601_string())) {
3329 // a. Let day be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(yearMonth.[[ISODay]], 2).
3330 // b. Set result to the string-concatenation of result, the code unit 0x002D
3331 // (HYPHEN-MINUS), and day.
3332 builder.AppendCharacter('-');
3333 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, year_month->iso_day(), 2);
3334 }
3335 // 8. Let calendarString be ! FormatCalendarAnnotation(calendarID,
3336 // showCalendar).
3337 DirectHandle<String> calendar_string =
3338 FormatCalendarAnnotation(isolate, calendar_id, show_calendar);
3339 // 9. Set result to the string-concatenation of result and calendarString.
3340 builder.AppendString(calendar_string);
3341 // 10. Return result.
3342 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked(), isolate);
3343}
3344
3345// #sec-temporal-builtintimezonegetoffsetstringfor
3346MaybeHandle<String> BuiltinTimeZoneGetOffsetStringFor(
3347 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone,
3348 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant, const char* method_name) {
3349 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3350 // 1. Let offsetNanoseconds be ? GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(timeZone, instant).
3351 int64_t offset_nanoseconds;
3352 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3353 isolate, offset_nanoseconds,
3354 GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(isolate, time_zone, instant, method_name),
3355 Handle<String>());
3356
3357 // 2. Return ! FormatTimeZoneOffsetString(offsetNanoseconds).
3358 return FormatTimeZoneOffsetString(isolate, offset_nanoseconds);
3359}
3360
3361// #sec-temporal-parseisodatetime
3362Maybe<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar> ParseISODateTime(
3363 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string,
3364 const ParsedISO8601Result& parsed);
3365// Note: We split ParseISODateTime to two function because the spec text
3366// repeates some parsing unnecessary. If a function is calling ParseISODateTime
3367// from a AO which already call ParseText() for TemporalDateTimeString,
3368// TemporalInstantString, TemporalMonthDayString, TemporalTimeString,
3369// TemporalYearMonthString, TemporalZonedDateTimeString. But for the usage in
3370// ParseTemporalTimeZoneString, we use the following version.
3371Maybe<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar> ParseISODateTime(Isolate* isolate,
3372 Handle<String> iso_string) {
3373 // 2. For each nonterminal goal of « TemporalDateTimeString,
3374 // TemporalInstantString, TemporalMonthDayString, TemporalTimeString,
3375 // TemporalYearMonthString, TemporalZonedDateTimeString », do
3376
3377 // a. If parseResult is not a Parse Node, set parseResult to
3378 // ParseText(StringToCodePoints(isoString), goal).
3379 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed;
3380 if ((parsed =
3381 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalDateTimeString(isolate, iso_string))
3382 .has_value() ||
3383 (parsed = TemporalParser::ParseTemporalInstantString(isolate, iso_string))
3384 .has_value() ||
3385 (parsed =
3386 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalMonthDayString(isolate, iso_string))
3387 .has_value() ||
3388 (parsed = TemporalParser::ParseTemporalTimeString(isolate, iso_string))
3389 .has_value() ||
3390 (parsed =
3391 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalYearMonthString(isolate, iso_string))
3392 .has_value() ||
3393 (parsed = TemporalParser::ParseTemporalZonedDateTimeString(isolate,
3394 iso_string))
3395 .has_value()) {
3396 return ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed);
3397 }
3398
3399 // 3. If parseResult is not a Parse Node, throw a RangeError exception.
3400 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3401 Nothing<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3402}
3403
3404Maybe<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar> ParseISODateTime(
3405 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string,
3406 const ParsedISO8601Result& parsed) {
3407 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3408
3409 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar result;
3410 // 6. Set yearMV to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(year).
3411 result.date.year = parsed.date_year;
3412 // 7. If month is undefined, then
3413 if (parsed.date_month_is_undefined()) {
3414 // a. Set monthMV to 1.
3415 result.date.month = 1;
3416 // 8. Else,
3417 } else {
3418 // a. Set monthMV to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(month).
3419 result.date.month = parsed.date_month;
3420 }
3421
3422 // 9. If day is undefined, then
3423 if (parsed.date_day_is_undefined()) {
3424 // a. Set dayMV to 1.
3425 result.date.day = 1;
3426 // 10. Else,
3427 } else {
3428 // a. Set dayMV to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(day).
3429 result.date.day = parsed.date_day;
3430 }
3431 // 11. Set hourMV to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(hour).
3432 result.time.hour = parsed.time_hour_is_undefined() ? 0 : parsed.time_hour;
3433 // 12. Set minuteMV to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(minute).
3434 result.time.minute =
3435 parsed.time_minute_is_undefined() ? 0 : parsed.time_minute;
3436 // 13. Set secondMV to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(second).
3437 result.time.second =
3438 parsed.time_second_is_undefined() ? 0 : parsed.time_second;
3439 // 14. If secondMV is 60, then
3440 if (result.time.second == 60) {
3441 // a. Set secondMV to 59.
3442 result.time.second = 59;
3443 }
3444 // 15. If fSeconds is not empty, then
3445 if (!parsed.time_nanosecond_is_undefined()) {
3446 // a. Let fSecondsDigits be the substring of CodePointsToString(fSeconds)
3447 // from 1.
3448 //
3449 // b. Let fSecondsDigitsExtended be the string-concatenation of
3450 // fSecondsDigits and "000000000".
3451 //
3452 // c. Let millisecond be the substring of fSecondsDigitsExtended from 0 to
3453 // 3.
3454 //
3455 // d. Let microsecond be the substring of fSecondsDigitsExtended from 3 to
3456 // 6.
3457 //
3458 // e. Let nanosecond be the substring of fSecondsDigitsExtended from 6 to 9.
3459 //
3460 // f. Let millisecondMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(millisecond).
3461 result.time.millisecond = parsed.time_nanosecond / 1000000;
3462 // g. Let microsecondMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(microsecond).
3463 result.time.microsecond = (parsed.time_nanosecond / 1000) % 1000;
3464 // h. Let nanosecondMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(nanosecond).
3465 result.time.nanosecond = (parsed.time_nanosecond % 1000);
3466 // 16. Else,
3467 } else {
3468 // a. Let millisecondMV be 0.
3469 result.time.millisecond = 0;
3470 // b. Let microsecondMV be 0.
3471 result.time.microsecond = 0;
3472 // c. Let nanosecondMV be 0.
3473 result.time.nanosecond = 0;
3474 }
3475 // 17. If ! IsValidISODate(yearMV, monthMV, dayMV) is false, throw a
3476 // RangeError exception.
3477 if (!IsValidISODate(isolate, result.date)) {
3478 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3479 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3480 Nothing<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3481 }
3482 // 18. If ! IsValidTime(hourMV, minuteMV, secondMV, millisecondMV,
3483 // microsecondMV, nanosecond) is false, throw a RangeError exception.
3484 if (!IsValidTime(isolate, result.time)) {
3485 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3486 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3487 Nothing<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3488 }
3489
3490 // 19. Let timeZoneResult be the Record { [[Z]]: false, [[OffsetString]]:
3491 // undefined, [[Name]]: undefined }.
3492 result.time_zone = {false, isolate->factory()->undefined_value(),
3493 isolate->factory()->undefined_value()};
3494 // 20. If parseResult contains a TimeZoneIdentifier Parse Node, then
3495 if (parsed.tzi_name_length != 0) {
3496 // a. Let name be the source text matched by the TimeZoneIdentifier Parse
3497 // Node contained within parseResult.
3498 //
3499 // b. Set timeZoneResult.[[Name]] to CodePointsToString(name).
3500 result.time_zone.name = isolate->factory()->NewSubString(
3501 iso_string, parsed.tzi_name_start,
3502 parsed.tzi_name_start + parsed.tzi_name_length);
3503 }
3504 // 21. If parseResult contains a UTCDesignator Parse Node, then
3505 if (parsed.utc_designator) {
3506 // a. Set timeZoneResult.[[Z]] to true.
3507 result.time_zone.z = true;
3508 // 22. Else,
3509 } else {
3510 // a. If parseResult contains a TimeZoneNumericUTCOffset Parse Node, then
3511 if (parsed.offset_string_length != 0) {
3512 // i. Let offset be the source text matched by the
3513 // TimeZoneNumericUTCOffset Parse Node contained within parseResult.
3514 // ii. Set timeZoneResult.[[OffsetString]] to CodePointsToString(offset).
3515 result.time_zone.offset_string = isolate->factory()->NewSubString(
3516 iso_string, parsed.offset_string_start,
3517 parsed.offset_string_start + parsed.offset_string_length);
3518 }
3519 }
3520
3521 // 23. If calendar is empty, then
3522 if (parsed.calendar_name_length == 0) {
3523 // a. Let calendarVal be undefined.
3524 result.calendar = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
3525 // 24. Else,
3526 } else {
3527 // a. Let calendarVal be CodePointsToString(calendar).
3528 result.calendar = isolate->factory()->NewSubString(
3529 iso_string, parsed.calendar_name_start,
3530 parsed.calendar_name_start + parsed.calendar_name_length);
3531 }
3532 // 24. Return the Record { [[Year]]: yearMV, [[Month]]: monthMV, [[Day]]:
3533 // dayMV, [[Hour]]: hourMV, [[Minute]]: minuteMV, [[Second]]: secondMV,
3534 // [[Millisecond]]: millisecondMV, [[Microsecond]]: microsecondMV,
3535 // [[Nanosecond]]: nanosecondMV, [[TimeZone]]: timeZoneResult,
3536 // [[Calendar]]: calendarVal, }.
3537 return Just(result);
3538}
3539
3540// #sec-temporal-parsetemporaldatestring
3541Maybe<DateRecordWithCalendar> ParseTemporalDateString(
3542 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string) {
3543 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3544 // 1. Let parts be ? ParseTemporalDateTimeString(isoString).
3545 // 2. Return the Record { [[Year]]: parts.[[Year]], [[Month]]:
3546 // parts.[[Month]], [[Day]]: parts.[[Day]], [[Calendar]]: parts.[[Calendar]]
3547 // }.
3548 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar record;
3549 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3550 isolate, record, ParseTemporalDateTimeString(isolate, iso_string),
3551 Nothing<DateRecordWithCalendar>());
3552 DateRecordWithCalendar result = {record.date, record.calendar};
3553 return Just(result);
3554}
3555
3556// #sec-temporal-parsetemporaltimestring
3557Maybe<TimeRecordWithCalendar> ParseTemporalTimeString(
3558 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string) {
3559 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3560
3561 // 1. Assert: Type(isoString) is String.
3562 // 2. If isoString does not satisfy the syntax of a TemporalTimeString
3563 // (see 13.33), then
3564 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
3565 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalTimeString(isolate, iso_string);
3566 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
3567 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
3568 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3569 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3570 Nothing<TimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3571 }
3572
3573 // 3. If _isoString_ contains a |UTCDesignator|, then
3574 if (parsed->utc_designator) {
3575 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
3576 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3577 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3578 Nothing<TimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3579 }
3580
3581 // 3. Let result be ? ParseISODateTime(isoString).
3582 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar result;
3583 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3584 isolate, result, ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed),
3585 Nothing<TimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3586 // 4. Return the Record { [[Hour]]: result.[[Hour]], [[Minute]]:
3587 // result.[[Minute]], [[Second]]: result.[[Second]], [[Millisecond]]:
3588 // result.[[Millisecond]], [[Microsecond]]: result.[[Microsecond]],
3589 // [[Nanosecond]]: result.[[Nanosecond]], [[Calendar]]: result.[[Calendar]] }.
3590 TimeRecordWithCalendar ret = {result.time, result.calendar};
3591 return Just(ret);
3592}
3593
3594// #sec-temporal-parsetemporalinstantstring
3595Maybe<InstantRecord> ParseTemporalInstantString(Isolate* isolate,
3596 Handle<String> iso_string) {
3597 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3598
3599 // 1. If ParseText(StringToCodePoints(isoString), TemporalInstantString) is a
3600 // List of errors, throw a RangeError exception.
3601 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
3602 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalInstantString(isolate, iso_string);
3603 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
3604 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3605 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3606 Nothing<InstantRecord>());
3607 }
3608
3609 // 2. Let result be ? ParseISODateTime(isoString).
3610 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar result;
3611 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3612 isolate, result, ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed),
3613 Nothing<InstantRecord>());
3614
3615 // 3. Let offsetString be result.[[TimeZone]].[[OffsetString]].
3616 Handle<Object> offset_string = result.time_zone.offset_string;
3617
3618 // 4. If result.[[TimeZone]].[[Z]] is true, then
3619 if (result.time_zone.z) {
3620 // a. Set offsetString to "+00:00".
3621 offset_string = isolate->factory()->NewStringFromStaticChars("+00:00");
3622 }
3623 // 5. Assert: offsetString is not undefined.
3624 DCHECK(!IsUndefined(*offset_string));
3625
3626 // 6. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: result.[[Year]],
3627 // [[Month]]: result.[[Month]], [[Day]]: result.[[Day]],
3628 // [[Hour]]: result.[[Hour]], [[Minute]]: result.[[Minute]],
3629 // [[Second]]: result.[[Second]],
3630 // [[Millisecond]]: result.[[Millisecond]],
3631 // [[Microsecond]]: result.[[Microsecond]],
3632 // [[Nanosecond]]: result.[[Nanosecond]],
3633 // [[TimeZoneOffsetString]]: offsetString }.
3634 InstantRecord record({result.date, result.time, offset_string});
3635 return Just(record);
3636}

3638// #sec-temporal-parsetemporalrelativetostring
3639Maybe<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar> ParseTemporalRelativeToString(
3640 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string) {
3641 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3642
3643 // 1. If ParseText(StringToCodePoints(isoString), TemporalDateTimeString) is a
3644 // List of errors, throw a RangeError exception.
3645 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
3646 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalDateTimeString(isolate, iso_string);
3647 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
3648 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
3649 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3650 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3651 Nothing<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3652 }
3653 // 2. Returns ? ParseISODateTime(isoString).
3654 return ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed);
3655}

3657// #sec-temporal-parsetemporalinstant
3658MaybeHandle<BigInt> ParseTemporalInstant(Isolate* isolate,
3659 Handle<String> iso_string) {
3660 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3661
3662 // 1. Assert: Type(isoString) is String.
3663 // 2. Let result be ? ParseTemporalInstantString(isoString).
3664 InstantRecord result;
3665 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3666 isolate, result, ParseTemporalInstantString(isolate, iso_string),
3667 Handle<BigInt>());
3668
3669 // 3. Let offsetString be result.[[TimeZoneOffsetString]].
3670 // 4. Assert: offsetString is not undefined.
3671 DCHECK(!IsUndefined(*result.offset_string));
3672
3673 // 5. Let utc be ? GetEpochFromISOParts(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
3674 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
3675 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]]).
3676 DirectHandle<BigInt> utc =
3677 GetEpochFromISOParts(isolate, {result.date, result.time});
3678
3679 // 6. Let offsetNanoseconds be ? ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(offsetString).
3680 int64_t offset_nanoseconds;
3681 DCHECK(IsString(*result.offset_string));
3682 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3683 isolate, offset_nanoseconds,
3684 ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(isolate, Cast<String>(result.offset_string)),
3685 Handle<BigInt>());
3686
3687 // 7. Let result be utc - ℤ(offsetNanoseconds).
3688 Handle<BigInt> result_value =
3689 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, utc,
3690 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, offset_nanoseconds))
3691 .ToHandleChecked();
3692 // 8. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(result) is false, then
3693 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, result_value)) {
3694 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
3695 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
3696 }
3697 // 9. Return result.
3698 return result_value;
3699}
3700
3701// #sec-temporal-parsetemporalzoneddatetimestring
3702Maybe<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar> ParseTemporalZonedDateTimeString(
3703 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string) {
3704 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3705 // 1. If ParseText(StringToCodePoints(isoString), TemporalZonedDateTimeString)
3706 // is a List of errors, throw a RangeError exception.
3707 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
3708 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalZonedDateTimeString(isolate, iso_string);
3709 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
3710 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3711 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3712 Nothing<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar>());
3713 }
3714
3715 // 2. Return ? ParseISODateTime(isoString).
3716 return ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed);
3717}
3718
3719// #sec-temporal-createdurationrecord
3720Maybe<DurationRecord> CreateDurationRecord(Isolate* isolate,
3721 const DurationRecord& duration) {
3722 // 1. If ! IsValidDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes,
3723 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds) is false, throw a
3724 // RangeError exception.
3725 if (!IsValidDuration(isolate, duration)) {
3726 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3727 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3728 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
3729 }
3730 // 2. Return the Record { [[Years]]: ℝ(𝔽(years)), [[Months]]: ℝ(𝔽(months)),
3731 // [[Weeks]]: ℝ(𝔽(weeks)), [[Days]]: ℝ(𝔽(days)), [[Hours]]: ℝ(𝔽(hours)),
3732 // [[Minutes]]: ℝ(𝔽(minutes)), [[Seconds]]: ℝ(𝔽(seconds)), [[Milliseconds]]:
3733 // ℝ(𝔽(milliseconds)), [[Microseconds]]: ℝ(𝔽(microseconds)), [[Nanoseconds]]:
3734 // ℝ(𝔽(nanoseconds)) }.
3735 return Just(duration);
3736}
3737
3738inline double IfEmptyReturnZero(double value) {
3739 return value == ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty ? 0 : value;
3740}
3741
3742// #sec-temporal-parsetemporaldurationstring
3743Maybe<DurationRecord> ParseTemporalDurationString(Isolate* isolate,
3744 Handle<String> iso_string) {
3745 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3746 // In this funciton, we use 'double' as type for all mathematical values
3747 // because in
3748 // https://tc39.es/proposal-temporal/#sec-properties-of-temporal-duration-instances
3749 // they are "A float64-representable integer representing the number" in the
3750 // internal slots.
3751 // 1. Let duration be ParseText(StringToCodePoints(isoString),
3752 // TemporalDurationString).
3753 // 2. If duration is a List of errors, throw a RangeError exception.
3754 // 3. Let each of sign, years, months, weeks, days, hours, fHours, minutes,
3755 // fMinutes, seconds, and fSeconds be the source text matched by the
3756 // respective Sign, DurationYears, DurationMonths, DurationWeeks,
3757 // DurationDays, DurationWholeHours, DurationHoursFraction,
3758 // DurationWholeMinutes, DurationMinutesFraction, DurationWholeSeconds, and
3759 // DurationSecondsFraction Parse Node enclosed by duration, or an empty
3760 // sequence of code points if not present.
3761 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Duration> parsed =
3762 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalDurationString(isolate, iso_string);
3763 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
3764 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3765 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3766 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
3767 }
3768 // 4. Let yearsMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(CodePointsToString(years)).
3769 double years_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->years);
3770 // 5. Let monthsMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(CodePointsToString(months)).
3771 double months_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->months);
3772 // 6. Let weeksMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(CodePointsToString(weeks)).
3773 double weeks_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->weeks);
3774 // 7. Let daysMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(CodePointsToString(days)).
3775 double days_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->days);
3776 // 8. Let hoursMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(CodePointsToString(hours)).
3777 double hours_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->whole_hours);
3778 // 9. If fHours is not empty, then
3779 double minutes_mv;
3780 if (parsed->hours_fraction != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty) {
3781 // a. If any of minutes, fMinutes, seconds, fSeconds is not empty, throw a
3782 // RangeError exception.
3783 if (parsed->whole_minutes != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty ||
3784 parsed->minutes_fraction != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty ||
3785 parsed->whole_seconds != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty ||
3786 parsed->seconds_fraction != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty) {
3787 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3788 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3789 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
3790 }
3791 // b. Let fHoursDigits be the substring of CodePointsToString(fHours)
3792 // from 1.
3793 //
3794 // c. Let fHoursScale be the length of fHoursDigits.
3795 //
3796 // d. Let
3797 // minutesMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(fHoursDigits) / 10^fHoursScale × 60.
3798 minutes_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->hours_fraction) * 60.0 / 1e9;
3799 // 10. Else,
3800 } else {
3801 // a. Let minutesMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(CodePointsToString(minutes)).
3802 minutes_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->whole_minutes);
3803 }
3804 double seconds_mv;
3805 // 11. If fMinutes is not empty, then
3806 if (parsed->minutes_fraction != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty) {
3807 // a. If any of seconds, fSeconds is not empty, throw a RangeError
3808 // exception.
3809 if (parsed->whole_seconds != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty ||
3810 parsed->seconds_fraction != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty) {
3811 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3812 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3813 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
3814 }
3815 // b. Let fMinutesDigits be the substring of CodePointsToString(fMinutes)
3816 // from 1.
3817 //
3818 // c. Let fMinutesScale be the length of fMinutesDigits.
3819 //
3820 // d. Let secondsMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(fMinutesDigits) /
3821 // 10^fMinutesScale × 60.
3822 seconds_mv = IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->minutes_fraction) * 60.0 / 1e9;
3823 // 12. Else if seconds is not empty, then
3824 } else if (parsed->whole_seconds != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty) {
3825 // a. Let secondsMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(CodePointsToString(seconds)).
3826 seconds_mv = parsed->whole_seconds;
3827 // 13. Else,
3828 } else {
3829 // a. Let secondsMV be remainder(minutesMV, 1) × 60.
3830 seconds_mv = (minutes_mv - std::floor(minutes_mv)) * 60.0;
3831 }
3832 double milliseconds_mv, microseconds_mv, nanoseconds_mv;
3833 // Note: In step 14-17, we calculate from nanoseconds_mv to miilliseconds_mv
3834 // in the reversee order of the spec text to avoid numerical errors would be
3835 // introduced by multiple division inside the remainder operations. If we
3836 // strickly follow the order by using double, the end result of nanoseconds_mv
3837 // will be wrong due to numerical errors.
3838 //
3839 // 14. If fSeconds is not empty, then
3840 if (parsed->seconds_fraction != ParsedISO8601Duration::kEmpty) {
3841 // a. Let fSecondsDigits be the substring of CodePointsToString(fSeconds)
3842 // from 1.
3843 //
3844 // b. Let fSecondsScale be the length of fSecondsDigits.
3845 //
3846 // c. Let millisecondsMV be ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(fSecondsDigits) /
3847 // 10^fSecondsScale × 1000.
3848 DCHECK_LE(IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->seconds_fraction), 1e9);
3849 nanoseconds_mv = std::round(IfEmptyReturnZero(parsed->seconds_fraction));
3850 // 15. Else,
3851 } else {
3852 // a. Let millisecondsMV be remainder(secondsMV, 1) × 1000.
3853 nanoseconds_mv = std::round((seconds_mv - std::floor(seconds_mv)) * 1e9);
3854 }
3855 milliseconds_mv = std::floor(nanoseconds_mv / 1000000);
3856 // 16. Let microsecondsMV be remainder(millisecondsMV, 1) × 1000.
3857 microseconds_mv = std::floor(nanoseconds_mv / 1000) -
3858 std::floor(nanoseconds_mv / 1000000) * 1000;
3859 // 17. Let nanosecondsMV be remainder(microsecondsMV, 1) × 1000.
3860 nanoseconds_mv -= std::floor(nanoseconds_mv / 1000) * 1000;
3861
3862 // 18. If sign contains the code point 0x002D (HYPHEN-MINUS) or 0x2212 (MINUS
3863 // SIGN), then a. Let factor be −1.
3864 // 19. Else,
3865 // a. Let factor be 1.
3866 double factor = parsed->sign;
3867
3868 // 20. Return ? CreateDurationRecord(yearsMV × factor, monthsMV × factor,
3869 // weeksMV × factor, daysMV × factor, hoursMV × factor, floor(minutesMV) ×
3870 // factor, floor(secondsMV) × factor, floor(millisecondsMV) × factor,
3871 // floor(microsecondsMV) × factor, floor(nanosecondsMV) × factor).
3872
3873 return CreateDurationRecord(
3874 isolate,
3875 {years_mv * factor,
3876 months_mv * factor,
3877 weeks_mv * factor,
3878 {days_mv * factor, hours_mv * factor, std::floor(minutes_mv) * factor,
3879 std::floor(seconds_mv) * factor, milliseconds_mv * factor,
3880 microseconds_mv * factor, nanoseconds_mv * factor}});
3881}
3882
3883// #sec-temporal-parsetemporaltimezonestring
3884Maybe<TimeZoneRecord> ParseTemporalTimeZoneString(
3885 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> time_zone_string) {
3886 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3887
3888 // 1. Let parseResult be ParseText(StringToCodePoints(timeZoneString),
3889 // TimeZoneIdentifier).
3890 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
3891 TemporalParser::ParseTimeZoneIdentifier(isolate, time_zone_string);
3892 // 2. If parseResult is a Parse Node, then
3893 if (parsed.has_value()) {
3894 // a. Return the Record { [[Z]]: false, [[OffsetString]]: undefined,
3895 // [[Name]]: timeZoneString }.
3896 return Just(TimeZoneRecord(
3897 {false, isolate->factory()->undefined_value(), time_zone_string}));
3898 }
3899
3900 // 3. Let result be ? ParseISODateTime(timeZoneString).
3901 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar result;
3902 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3903 isolate, result, ParseISODateTime(isolate, time_zone_string),
3904 Nothing<TimeZoneRecord>());
3905
3906 // 4. Let timeZoneResult be result.[[TimeZone]].
3907 // 5. If timeZoneResult.[[Z]] is false, timeZoneResult.[[OffsetString]] is
3908 // undefined, and timeZoneResult.[[Name]] is undefined, throw a RangeError
3909 // exception.
3910 if (!result.time_zone.z && IsUndefined(*result.time_zone.offset_string) &&
3911 IsUndefined(*result.time_zone.name)) {
3912 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
3913 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
3914 Nothing<TimeZoneRecord>());
3915 }
3916 // 6. Return timeZoneResult.
3917 return Just(result.time_zone);
3918}
3919
3920Maybe<int64_t> ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(Isolate* isolate,
3921 Handle<String> iso_string) {
3922 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3923
3924 // 1. Assert: Type(offsetString) is String.
3925 // 2. If offsetString does not satisfy the syntax of a
3926 // TimeZoneNumericUTCOffset (see 13.33), then
3927 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
3928 TemporalParser::ParseTimeZoneNumericUTCOffset(isolate, iso_string);
3929 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
3930 /* a. Throw a RangeError exception. */
3931 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
3932 isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(), Nothing<int64_t>());
3933 }
3934 // 3. Let sign, hours, minutes, seconds, and fraction be the parts of
3935 // offsetString produced respectively by the TimeZoneUTCOffsetSign,
3936 // TimeZoneUTCOffsetHour, TimeZoneUTCOffsetMinute, TimeZoneUTCOffsetSecond,
3937 // and TimeZoneUTCOffsetFraction productions, or undefined if not present.
3938 // 4. If either hours or sign are undefined, throw a RangeError exception.
3939 if (parsed->tzuo_hour_is_undefined() || parsed->tzuo_sign_is_undefined()) {
3940 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
3941 isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(), Nothing<int64_t>());
3942 }
3943 // 5. If sign is the code unit 0x002D (HYPHEN-MINUS) or 0x2212 (MINUS SIGN),
3944 // then a. Set sign to −1.
3945 // 6. Else,
3946 // a. Set sign to 1.
3947 int64_t sign = parsed->tzuo_sign;
3948
3949 // 7. Set hours to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(hours).
3950 int64_t hours = parsed->tzuo_hour;
3951 // 8. Set minutes to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(minutes).
3952 int64_t minutes =
3953 parsed->tzuo_minute_is_undefined() ? 0 : parsed->tzuo_minute;
3954 // 9. Set seconds to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(seconds).
3955 int64_t seconds =
3956 parsed->tzuo_second_is_undefined() ? 0 : parsed->tzuo_second;
3957 // 10. If fraction is not undefined, then
3958 int64_t nanoseconds;
3959 if (!parsed->tzuo_nanosecond_is_undefined()) {
3960 // a. Set fraction to the string-concatenation of the previous value of
3961 // fraction and the string "000000000".
3962 // b. Let nanoseconds be the String value equal to the substring of fraction
3963 // consisting of the code units with indices 0 (inclusive) through 9
3964 // (exclusive). c. Set nanoseconds to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(nanoseconds).
3965 nanoseconds = parsed->tzuo_nanosecond;
3966 // 11. Else,
3967 } else {
3968 // a. Let nanoseconds be 0.
3969 nanoseconds = 0;
3970 }
3971 // 12. Return sign × (((hours × 60 + minutes) × 60 + seconds) × 10^9 +
3972 // nanoseconds).
3973 return Just(sign * (((hours * 60 + minutes) * 60 + seconds) * 1000000000 +
3974 nanoseconds));
3975}
3976
3977bool IsValidTimeZoneNumericUTCOffsetString(Isolate* isolate,
3978 Handle<String> iso_string) {
3979 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3980
3981 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
3982 TemporalParser::ParseTimeZoneNumericUTCOffset(isolate, iso_string);
3983 return parsed.has_value();
3984}

3986// #sec-temporal-parsetemporalcalendarstring
3987MaybeHandle<String> ParseTemporalCalendarString(Isolate* isolate,
3988 Handle<String> iso_string) {
3989 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
3990
3991 // 1. Let parseResult be Completion(ParseISODateTime(isoString)).
3992 Maybe<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar> parse_result =
3993 ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string);
3994 // 2. If parseResult is a normal completion, then
3995 if (parse_result.IsJust()) {
3996 // a. Let calendar be parseResult.[[Value]].[[Calendar]].
3997 Handle<Object> calendar = parse_result.FromJust().calendar;
3998 // b. If calendar is undefined, return "iso8601".
3999 if (IsUndefined(*calendar)) {
4000 return isolate->factory()->iso8601_string();
4001 // c. Else, return calendar.
4002 } else {
4003 CHECK(IsString(*calendar));
4004 return Cast<String>(calendar);
4005 }
4006 // 3. Else,
4007 } else {
4008 DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
4009 isolate->clear_exception();
4010 // a. Set parseResult to ParseText(StringToCodePoints(isoString),
4011 // CalendarName).
4012 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
4013 TemporalParser::ParseCalendarName(isolate, iso_string);
4014 // b. If parseResult is a List of errors, throw a RangeError exception.
4015 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
4016 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidCalendar,
4017 iso_string));
4018 }
4019 // c. Else, return isoString.
4020 return iso_string;
4021 }
4022}

4024// #sec-temporal-calendarequals
4025Maybe<bool> CalendarEqualsBool(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSReceiver> one,
4026 Handle<JSReceiver> two) {
4027 // 1. If one and two are the same Object value, return true.
4028 if (one.is_identical_to(two)) {
4029 return Just(true);
4030 }
4031 // 2. Let calendarOne be ? ToString(one).
4032 DirectHandle<String> calendar_one;
4033 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4034 isolate, calendar_one, Object::ToString(isolate, one), Nothing<bool>());
4035 // 3. Let calendarTwo be ? ToString(two).
4036 DirectHandle<String> calendar_two;
4037 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4038 isolate, calendar_two, Object::ToString(isolate, two), Nothing<bool>());
4039 // 4. If calendarOne is calendarTwo, return true.
4040 if (String::Equals(isolate, calendar_one, calendar_two)) {
4041 return Just(true);
4042 }
4043 // 5. Return false.
4044 return Just(false);
4045}
4046MaybeHandle<Oddball> CalendarEquals(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSReceiver> one,
4047 Handle<JSReceiver> two) {
4048 bool result;
4049 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, result,
4050 CalendarEqualsBool(isolate, one, two),
4051 Handle<Oddball>());
4052 return isolate->factory()->ToBoolean(result);
4053}

4165// #sec-temporal-defaultmergefields
4166MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> DefaultMergeFields(
4167 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,
4168 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> additional_fields) {
4169 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
4170 // 1. Let merged be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
4171 Handle<JSObject> merged =
4172 isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function());
4173
4174 // 2. Let originalKeys be ? EnumerableOwnPropertyNames(fields, key).
4175 DirectHandle<FixedArray> original_keys;
4176 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4177 isolate, original_keys,
4178 KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, fields, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
4179 ENUMERABLE_STRINGS,
4180 GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString));
4181 // 3. For each element nextKey of originalKeys, do
4182 for (int i = 0; i < original_keys->length(); i++) {
4183 // a. If nextKey is not "month" or "monthCode", then
4184 DirectHandle<Object> next_key(original_keys->get(i), isolate);
4185 DCHECK(IsString(*next_key));
4186 DirectHandle<String> next_key_string = Cast<String>(next_key);
4187 if (!(String::Equals(isolate, factory->month_string(), next_key_string) ||
4188 String::Equals(isolate, factory->monthCode_string(),
4189 next_key_string))) {
4190 // i. Let propValue be ? Get(fields, nextKey).
4191 DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
4192 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4193 isolate, prop_value,
4194 Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate, fields, next_key_string));
4195 // ii. If propValue is not undefined, then
4196 if (!IsUndefined(*prop_value)) {
4197 // 1. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(merged, nextKey,
4198 // propValue).
4199 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, merged, next_key_string,
4200 prop_value, Just(kDontThrow))
4201 .FromJust());
4202 }
4203 }
4204 }
4205 // 4. Let newKeys be ? EnumerableOwnPropertyNames(additionalFields, key).
4206 DirectHandle<FixedArray> new_keys;
4207 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4208 isolate, new_keys,
4209 KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, additional_fields,
4210 KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly, ENUMERABLE_STRINGS,
4211 GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString));
4212 bool new_keys_has_month_or_month_code = false;
4213 // 5. For each element nextKey of newKeys, do
4214 for (int i = 0; i < new_keys->length(); i++) {
4215 DirectHandle<Object> next_key(new_keys->get(i), isolate);
4216 DCHECK(IsString(*next_key));
4217 DirectHandle<String> next_key_string = Cast<String>(next_key);
4218 // a. Let propValue be ? Get(additionalFields, nextKey).
4219 DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
4220 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4221 isolate, prop_value,
4222 Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate, additional_fields,
4223 next_key_string));
4224 // b. If propValue is not undefined, then
4225 if (!IsUndefined(*prop_value)) {
4226 // 1. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(merged, nextKey, propValue).
4227 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, merged, next_key_string,
4228 prop_value, Just(kDontThrow))
4229 .FromJust());
4230 }
4231 new_keys_has_month_or_month_code |=
4232 String::Equals(isolate, factory->month_string(), next_key_string) ||
4233 String::Equals(isolate, factory->monthCode_string(), next_key_string);
4234 }
4235 // 6. If newKeys does not contain either "month" or "monthCode", then
4236 if (!new_keys_has_month_or_month_code) {
4237 // a. Let month be ? Get(fields, "month").
4238 DirectHandle<Object> month;
4239 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4240 isolate, month,
4241 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->month_string()));
4242 // b. If month is not undefined, then
4243 if (!IsUndefined(*month)) {
4244 // i. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(merged, "month", month).
4245 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, merged,
4246 factory->month_string(), month,
4247 Just(kDontThrow))
4248 .FromJust());
4249 }
4250 // c. Let monthCode be ? Get(fields, "monthCode").
4251 DirectHandle<Object> month_code;
4252 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4253 isolate, month_code,
4254 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->monthCode_string()));
4255 // d. If monthCode is not undefined, then
4256 if (!IsUndefined(*month_code)) {
4257 // i. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(merged, "monthCode", monthCode).
4258 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, merged,
4259 factory->monthCode_string(),
4260 month_code, Just(kDontThrow))
4261 .FromJust());
4262 }
4263 }
4264 // 7. Return merged.
4265 return merged;
4266}

4268// #sec-temporal-getoffsetnanosecondsfor
4269Maybe<int64_t> GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(Isolate* isolate,
4270 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone_obj,
4271 DirectHandle<Object> instant,
4272 const char* method_name) {
4273 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
4274 // 1. Let getOffsetNanosecondsFor be ? GetMethod(timeZone,
4275 // "getOffsetNanosecondsFor").
4276 DirectHandle<Object> get_offset_nanoseconds_for;
4277 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4278 isolate, get_offset_nanoseconds_for,
4279 Object::GetMethod(isolate, time_zone_obj,
4280 isolate->factory()->getOffsetNanosecondsFor_string()),
4281 Nothing<int64_t>());
4282 if (!IsCallable(*get_offset_nanoseconds_for)) {
4283 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
4284 isolate,
4285 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledNonCallable,
4286 isolate->factory()->getOffsetNanosecondsFor_string()),
4287 Nothing<int64_t>());
4288 }
4289 DirectHandle<Object> offset_nanoseconds_obj;
4290 // 3. Let offsetNanoseconds be ? Call(getOffsetNanosecondsFor, timeZone, «
4291 // instant »).
4292 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {instant};
4293 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4294 isolate, offset_nanoseconds_obj,
4295 Execution::Call(isolate, get_offset_nanoseconds_for, time_zone_obj,
4296 base::VectorOf(args)),
4297 Nothing<int64_t>());
4298
4299 // 4. If Type(offsetNanoseconds) is not Number, throw a TypeError exception.
4300 if (!IsNumber(*offset_nanoseconds_obj)) {
4301 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
4302 Nothing<int64_t>());
4303 }
4304
4305 // 5. If ! IsIntegralNumber(offsetNanoseconds) is false, throw a RangeError
4306 // exception.
4307 if (!IsIntegralNumber(isolate, offset_nanoseconds_obj)) {
4308 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
4309 isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(), Nothing<int64_t>());
4310 }
4311 double offset_nanoseconds =
4312 Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*offset_nanoseconds_obj));
4313
4314 // 6. Set offsetNanoseconds to ℝ(offsetNanoseconds).
4315 int64_t offset_nanoseconds_int = static_cast<int64_t>(offset_nanoseconds);
4316 // 7. If abs(offsetNanoseconds) >= 86400 × 10^9, throw a RangeError exception.
4317 if (std::abs(offset_nanoseconds_int) >= 86400e9) {
4318 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
4319 isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(), Nothing<int64_t>());
4320 }
4321 // 8. Return offsetNanoseconds.
4322 return Just(offset_nanoseconds_int);
4323}

4325// #sec-temporal-topositiveinteger
4326MaybeHandle<Number> ToPositiveInteger(Isolate* isolate,
4327 Handle<Object> argument) {
4328 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
4329
4330 // 1. Let integer be ? ToInteger(argument).
4331 Handle<Number> integer;
4332 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, integer,
4333 ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isolate, argument));
4334 // 2. If integer ≤ 0, then
4335 if (NumberToInt32(*integer) <= 0) {
4336 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
4337 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
4338 }
4339 return integer;
4340}

4345MaybeHandle<Object> InvokeCalendarMethod(Isolate* isolate,
4346 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
4347 DirectHandle<String> name,
4348 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> date_like) {
4349 Handle<Object> result;
4350 /* 1. Assert: Type(calendar) is Object. */
4351 DCHECK(calendar->TaggedImpl::IsObject());
4352 /* 2. Let result be ? Invoke(calendar, #name, « dateLike »). */
4353 DirectHandle<Object> function;
4354 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, function,
4355 Object::GetProperty(isolate, calendar, name));
4356 if (!IsCallable(*function)) {
4357 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
4358 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledNonCallable, name));
4359 }
4360 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {date_like};
4361 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4362 isolate, result,
4363 Execution::Call(isolate, function, calendar, base::VectorOf(args)));
4364 return result;
4365}

4367#define CALENDAR_ABSTRACT_OPERATION_INT_ACTION(Name, name, Action) \
4368 MaybeHandle<Smi> Calendar##Name(Isolate* isolate, \
4369 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar, \
4370 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> date_like) { \
4371 /* 1. Assert: Type(calendar) is Object. */ \
4372 /* 2. Let result be ? Invoke(calendar, property, « dateLike »). */ \
4373 Handle<Object> result; \
4374 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION( \
4375 isolate, result, \
4376 InvokeCalendarMethod(isolate, calendar, \
4377 isolate->factory()->name##_string(), date_like)); \
4378 /* 3. If result is undefined, throw a RangeError exception. */ \
4379 if (IsUndefined(*result)) { \
4380 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR()); \
4381 } \
4382 /* 4. Return ? Action(result). */ \
4383 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result, Action(isolate, result)); \
4384 return handle(Smi::FromInt(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*result))), \
4385 isolate); \
4386 }
4387
4388#define CALENDAR_ABSTRACT_OPERATION(Name, property) \
4389 MaybeHandle<Object> Calendar##Name(Isolate* isolate, \
4390 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar, \
4391 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> date_like) { \
4392 return InvokeCalendarMethod(isolate, calendar, \
4393 isolate->factory()->property##_string(), \
4394 date_like); \
4395 }

4397// #sec-temporal-calendaryear

4406 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> date_like) {

4411 isolate, result,
4412 InvokeCalendarMethod(isolate, calendar,

4417 }
4418 // 4. Return ? ToString(result).
4419 return Object::ToString(isolate, result);
4420}

4492bool IsUTC(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> time_zone) {
4493 // 1. Assert: Type(timeZone) is String.
4494 // 2. Let tzText be ! StringToCodePoints(timeZone).
4495 // 3. Let tzUpperText be the result of toUppercase(tzText), according to the
4496 // Unicode Default Case Conversion algorithm.
4497 // 4. Let tzUpper be ! CodePointsToString(tzUpperText).
4498 // 5. If tzUpper and "UTC" are the same sequence of code points, return true.
4499 // 6. Return false.
4500 if (time_zone->length() != 3) return false;
4501 time_zone = String::Flatten(isolate, time_zone);
4502 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4503 const String::FlatContent& flat = time_zone->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
4504 return (flat.Get(0) == u'U' || flat.Get(0) == u'u') &&
4505 (flat.Get(1) == u'T' || flat.Get(1) == u't') &&
4506 (flat.Get(2) == u'C' || flat.Get(2) == u'c');
4507}
4508
4509#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
4510class CalendarMap final {
4511 public:
4512 CalendarMap() {
4513 icu::Locale locale("und");
4514 UErrorCode status = U_ZERO_ERROR;
4515 std::unique_ptr<icu::StringEnumeration> enumeration(
4516 icu::Calendar::getKeywordValuesForLocale("ca", locale, false, status));
4517 calendar_ids.push_back("iso8601");
4518 calendar_id_indices.insert({"iso8601", 0});
4519 int32_t i = 1;
4520 for (const char* item = enumeration->next(nullptr, status);
4521 U_SUCCESS(status) && item != nullptr;
4522 item = enumeration->next(nullptr, status)) {
4523 if (strcmp(item, "iso8601") != 0) {
4524 const char* type = uloc_toUnicodeLocaleType("ca", item);
4525 calendar_ids.push_back(type);
4526 calendar_id_indices.insert({type, i++});
4527 }
4528 }
4529 }
4530 bool Contains(const std::string& id) const {
4531 return calendar_id_indices.find(id) != calendar_id_indices.end();
4532 }
4533
4534 std::string Id(int32_t index) const {
4535 DCHECK_LT(index, calendar_ids.size());
4536 return calendar_ids[index];
4537 }
4538
4539 int32_t Index(const char* id) const {
4540 return calendar_id_indices.find(id)->second;
4541 }
4542
4543 private:
4544 std::map<std::string, int32_t> calendar_id_indices;
4545 std::vector<std::string> calendar_ids;
4546};
4547
4548DEFINE_LAZY_LEAKY_OBJECT_GETTER(CalendarMap, GetCalendarMap)

4552 // 2. If calendars contains the ASCII-lowercase of id, return true.
4553 // 3. Return false.
4554 id = Intl::ConvertToLower(isolate, String::Flatten(isolate, id))
4555 .ToHandleChecked();
4556 return GetCalendarMap()->Contains(id->ToCString().get());
4557}

4585// #sec-temporal-isbuiltincalendar
4586bool IsBuiltinCalendar(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> id) {
4587 // Note: For build without intl support, the only item in AvailableCalendars()
4588 // is "iso8601".
4589 // 1. Let calendars be AvailableCalendars().
4590 // 2. If calendars contains the ASCII-lowercase of id, return true.
4591 // 3. Return false.
4592
4593 // Fast path
4594 if (isolate->factory()->iso8601_string()->Equals(*id)) return true;
4595 if (id->length() != 7) return false;
4596 id = String::Flatten(isolate, id);
4597
4598 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4599 const String::FlatContent& flat = id->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
4600 // Return true if id is case insensitive equals to "iso8601".
4601 return AsciiAlphaToLower(flat.Get(0)) == 'i' &&
4602 AsciiAlphaToLower(flat.Get(1)) == 's' &&
4603 AsciiAlphaToLower(flat.Get(2)) == 'o' && flat.Get(3) == '8' &&
4604 flat.Get(4) == '6' && flat.Get(5) == '0' && flat.Get(6) == '1';
4605}
4606
4607int32_t CalendarIndex(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> id) { return 0; }

4621// Common routine shared by ToTemporalTimeRecord and ToPartialTime
4622// #sec-temporal-topartialtime
4623// #sec-temporal-totemporaltimerecord
4624Maybe<TimeRecord> ToTemporalTimeRecordOrPartialTime(
4625 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_time_like,
4626 const TimeRecord& time, bool skip_undefined, const char* method_name) {
4627 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
4628
4629 TimeRecord result(time);
4630 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
4631 // 1. Assert: Type(temporalTimeLike) is Object.
4632 // 2. Let result be the new Record { [[Hour]]: undefined, [[Minute]]:
4633 // undefined, [[Second]]: undefined, [[Millisecond]]: undefined,
4634 // [[Microsecond]]: undefined, [[Nanosecond]]: undefined }.
4635 // See https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/pull/1862
4636 // 3. Let _any_ be *false*.
4637 bool any = false;
4638 // 4. For each row of Table 4, except the header row, in table order, do
4639 std::array<std::pair<Handle<String>, int32_t*>, 6> table4 = {
4640 {{factory->hour_string(), &result.hour},
4641 {factory->microsecond_string(), &result.microsecond},
4642 {factory->millisecond_string(), &result.millisecond},
4643 {factory->minute_string(), &result.minute},
4644 {factory->nanosecond_string(), &result.nanosecond},
4645 {factory->second_string(), &result.second}}};
4646 for (const auto& row : table4) {
4647 Handle<Object> value;
4648 // a. Let property be the Property value of the current row.
4649 // b. Let value be ? Get(temporalTimeLike, property).
4650 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4651 isolate, value,
4652 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, temporal_time_like, row.first),
4653 Nothing<TimeRecord>());
4654 // c. If value is not undefined, then
4655 if (!IsUndefined(*value)) {
4656 // i. Set _any_ to *true*.
4657 any = true;
4658 // If it is inside ToPartialTime, we only continue if it is not undefined.
4659 } else if (skip_undefined) {
4660 continue;
4661 }
4662 // d. / ii. Set value to ? ToIntegerThrowOnOInfinity(value).
4663 DirectHandle<Number> value_number;
4664 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, value_number,
4665 ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isolate, value),
4666 Nothing<TimeRecord>());
4667 // e. / iii. Set result's internal slot whose name is the Internal Slot
4668 // value of the current row to value.
4669 *(row.second) = Object::NumberValue(*value_number);
4670 }
4671
4672 // 5. If _any_ is *false*, then
4673 if (!any) {
4674 // a. Throw a *TypeError* exception.
4675 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
4676 Nothing<TimeRecord>());
4677 }
4678 // 4. Return result.
4679 return Just(result);
4680}

4683Maybe<TimeRecord> ToPartialTime(Isolate* isolate,
4684 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_time_like,
4685 const TimeRecord& time,
4686 const char* method_name) {
4687 return ToTemporalTimeRecordOrPartialTime(isolate, temporal_time_like, time,
4688 true, method_name);
4689}

4691// #sec-temporal-totemporaltimerecord
4692Maybe<TimeRecord> ToTemporalTimeRecord(
4693 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_time_like,
4694 const char* method_name) {
4695 return ToTemporalTimeRecordOrPartialTime(
4696 isolate, temporal_time_like,
4697 {kMinInt31, kMinInt31, kMinInt31, kMinInt31, kMinInt31, kMinInt31}, false,
4698 method_name);
4699}
