4701// #sec-temporal-gettemporalunit
4702// In the spec text, the extraValues is defined as an optional argument of
4703// "a List of ECMAScript language values". Most of the caller does not pass in
4704// value for extraValues, which is represented by the default Unit::kNotPresent.
4705// For the three places in the spec text calling GetTemporalUnit with
4706// an extraValues argument:
4707// << "day" >> is passed in as in the algorithm of
4708// Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.round() and
4709// Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.round();
4710// << "auto" >> is passed in as in the algorithm of
4711// Temporal.Duration.prototype.round().
4712// Therefore we can simply use a Unit of three possible value, the default
4713// Unit::kNotPresent, Unit::kDay, and Unit::kAuto to cover all the possible
4714// value for extraValues.
4715Maybe<Unit> GetTemporalUnit(Isolate* isolate,
4716 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> normalized_options,
4717 const char* key, UnitGroup unit_group,
4718 Unit default_value, bool default_is_required,
4719 const char* method_name,
4720 Unit extra_values = Unit::kNotPresent) {
4721 std::vector<const char*> str_values;
4722 std::vector<Unit> enum_values;
4723 switch (unit_group) {
4724 case UnitGroup::kDate:
4725 if (default_value == Unit::kAuto || extra_values == Unit::kAuto) {
4726 str_values = {"year", "month", "week", "day", "auto",
4727 "years", "months", "weeks", "days"};
4728 enum_values = {Unit::kYear, Unit::kMonth, Unit::kWeek,
4729 Unit::kDay, Unit::kAuto, Unit::kYear,
4730 Unit::kMonth, Unit::kWeek, Unit::kDay};
4731 } else {
4732 DCHECK(default_value == Unit::kNotPresent ||
4733 default_value == Unit::kYear || default_value == Unit::kMonth ||
4734 default_value == Unit::kWeek || default_value == Unit::kDay);
4735 str_values = {"year", "month", "week", "day",
4736 "years", "months", "weeks", "days"};
4737 enum_values = {Unit::kYear, Unit::kMonth, Unit::kWeek, Unit::kDay,
4738 Unit::kYear, Unit::kMonth, Unit::kWeek, Unit::kDay};
4739 }
4740 break;
4741 case UnitGroup::kTime:
4742 if (default_value == Unit::kAuto || extra_values == Unit::kAuto) {
4743 str_values = {"hour", "minute", "second",
4744 "millisecond", "microsecond", "nanosecond",
4745 "auto", "hours", "minutes",
4746 "seconds", "milliseconds", "microseconds",
4747 "nanoseconds"};
4748 enum_values = {
4749 Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute, Unit::kSecond,
4750 Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond, Unit::kNanosecond,
4751 Unit::kAuto, Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute,
4752 Unit::kSecond, Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond,
4753 Unit::kNanosecond};
4754 } else if (default_value == Unit::kDay || extra_values == Unit::kDay) {
4755 str_values = {"hour", "minute", "second",
4756 "millisecond", "microsecond", "nanosecond",
4757 "day", "hours", "minutes",
4758 "seconds", "milliseconds", "microseconds",
4759 "nanoseconds", "days"};
4760 enum_values = {
4761 Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute, Unit::kSecond,
4762 Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond, Unit::kNanosecond,
4763 Unit::kDay, Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute,
4764 Unit::kSecond, Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond,
4765 Unit::kNanosecond, Unit::kDay};
4766 } else {
4767 DCHECK(default_value == Unit::kNotPresent ||
4768 default_value == Unit::kHour || default_value == Unit::kMinute ||
4769 default_value == Unit::kSecond ||
4770 default_value == Unit::kMillisecond ||
4771 default_value == Unit::kMicrosecond ||
4772 default_value == Unit::kNanosecond);
4773 str_values = {"hour", "minute", "second",
4774 "millisecond", "microsecond", "nanosecond",
4775 "hours", "minutes", "seconds",
4776 "milliseconds", "microseconds", "nanoseconds"};
4777 enum_values = {
4778 Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute, Unit::kSecond,
4779 Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond, Unit::kNanosecond,
4780 Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute, Unit::kSecond,
4781 Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond, Unit::kNanosecond};
4782 }
4783 break;
4784 case UnitGroup::kDateTime:
4785 if (default_value == Unit::kAuto || extra_values == Unit::kAuto) {
4786 str_values = {"year", "month", "week",
4787 "day", "hour", "minute",
4788 "second", "millisecond", "microsecond",
4789 "nanosecond", "auto", "years",
4790 "months", "weeks", "days",
4791 "hours", "minutes", "seconds",
4792 "milliseconds", "microseconds", "nanoseconds"};
4793 enum_values = {
4794 Unit::kYear, Unit::kMonth, Unit::kWeek,
4795 Unit::kDay, Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute,
4796 Unit::kSecond, Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond,
4797 Unit::kNanosecond, Unit::kAuto, Unit::kYear,
4798 Unit::kMonth, Unit::kWeek, Unit::kDay,
4799 Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute, Unit::kSecond,
4800 Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond, Unit::kNanosecond};
4801 } else {
4802 str_values = {
4803 "year", "month", "week", "day",
4804 "hour", "minute", "second", "millisecond",
4805 "microsecond", "nanosecond", "years", "months",
4806 "weeks", "days", "hours", "minutes",
4807 "seconds", "milliseconds", "microseconds", "nanoseconds"};
4808 enum_values = {
4809 Unit::kYear, Unit::kMonth, Unit::kWeek,
4810 Unit::kDay, Unit::kHour, Unit::kMinute,
4811 Unit::kSecond, Unit::kMillisecond, Unit::kMicrosecond,
4812 Unit::kNanosecond, Unit::kYear, Unit::kMonth,
4813 Unit::kWeek, Unit::kDay, Unit::kHour,
4814 Unit::kMinute, Unit::kSecond, Unit::kMillisecond,
4815 Unit::kMicrosecond, Unit::kNanosecond};
4816 }
4817 break;
4818 }
4819
4820 // 4. If default is required, then
4821 if (default_is_required) default_value = Unit::kNotPresent;
4822 // a. Let defaultValue be undefined.
4823 // 5. Else,
4824 // a. Let defaultValue be default.
4825 // b. If defaultValue is not undefined and singularNames does not contain
4826 // defaultValue, then i. Append defaultValue to singularNames.
4827
4828 // 9. Let value be ? GetOption(normalizedOptions, key, "string",
4829 // allowedValues, defaultValue).
4830 Unit value;
4831 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4832 isolate, value,
4833 GetStringOption<Unit>(isolate, normalized_options, key, method_name,
4834 str_values, enum_values, default_value),
4835 Nothing<Unit>());
4836
4837 // 10. If value is undefined and default is required, throw a RangeError
4838 // exception.
4839 if (default_is_required && value == Unit::kNotPresent) {
4840 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
4841 isolate,
4842 NewRangeError(
4843 MessageTemplate::kValueOutOfRange,
4844 isolate->factory()->undefined_value(),
4845 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(method_name),
4846 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(key)),
4847 Nothing<Unit>());
4848 }
4849 // 12. Return value.
4850 return Just(value);
4851}
4852
4853// #sec-temporal-mergelargestunitoption
4854MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> MergeLargestUnitOption(Isolate* isolate,
4855 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options,
4856 Unit largest_unit) {
4857 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
4858 // 1. Let merged be OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
4859 Handle<JSReceiver> merged = isolate->factory()->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
4860 // 2. Let keys be ? EnumerableOwnPropertyNames(options, key).
4861 // 3. For each element nextKey of keys, do
4862 // a. Let propValue be ? Get(options, nextKey).
4863 // b. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(merged, nextKey, propValue).
4864 JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
4865 isolate, merged, options, PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder,
4866 {}, false)
4867 .Check();
4868
4869 // 4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(merged, "largestUnit", largestUnit).
4870 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
4871 isolate, merged, isolate->factory()->largestUnit_string(),
4872 UnitToString(isolate, largest_unit), Just(kThrowOnError))
4873 .FromJust());
4874 // 5. Return merged.
4875 return merged;
4876}
4877
4878// #sec-temporal-tointegerthrowoninfinity
4879MaybeHandle<Number> ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(Isolate* isolate,
4880 Handle<Object> argument) {
4881 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
4882
4883 // 1. Let integer be ? ToIntegerOrInfinity(argument).
4884 Handle<Number> integer;
4885 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, integer,
4886 Object::ToInteger(isolate, argument));
4887 // 2. If integer is +∞ or -∞, throw a RangeError exception.
4888 if (!std::isfinite(Object::NumberValue(*integer))) {
4889 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
4890 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
4891 }
4892 return integer;
4893}
4894
4895// #sec-temporal-largeroftwotemporalunits
4896Unit LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(Unit u1, Unit u2) {
4897 // 1. If either u1 or u2 is "year", return "year".
4898 if (u1 == Unit::kYear || u2 == Unit::kYear) return Unit::kYear;
4899 // 2. If either u1 or u2 is "month", return "month".
4900 if (u1 == Unit::kMonth || u2 == Unit::kMonth) return Unit::kMonth;
4901 // 3. If either u1 or u2 is "week", return "week".
4902 if (u1 == Unit::kWeek || u2 == Unit::kWeek) return Unit::kWeek;
4903 // 4. If either u1 or u2 is "day", return "day".
4904 if (u1 == Unit::kDay || u2 == Unit::kDay) return Unit::kDay;
4905 // 5. If either u1 or u2 is "hour", return "hour".
4906 if (u1 == Unit::kHour || u2 == Unit::kHour) return Unit::kHour;
4907 // 6. If either u1 or u2 is "minute", return "minute".
4908 if (u1 == Unit::kMinute || u2 == Unit::kMinute) return Unit::kMinute;
4909 // 7. If either u1 or u2 is "second", return "second".
4910 if (u1 == Unit::kSecond || u2 == Unit::kSecond) return Unit::kSecond;
4911 // 8. If either u1 or u2 is "millisecond", return "millisecond".
4912 if (u1 == Unit::kMillisecond || u2 == Unit::kMillisecond)
4913 return Unit::kMillisecond;
4914 // 9. If either u1 or u2 is "microsecond", return "microsecond".
4915 if (u1 == Unit::kMicrosecond || u2 == Unit::kMicrosecond)
4916 return Unit::kMicrosecond;
4917 // 10. Return "nanosecond".
4918 return Unit::kNanosecond;
4919}
4920
4921Handle<String> UnitToString(Isolate* isolate, Unit unit) {
4922 switch (unit) {
4923 case Unit::kYear:
4924 return isolate->factory()->year_string();
4925 case Unit::kMonth:
4926 return isolate->factory()->month_string();
4927 case Unit::kWeek:
4928 return isolate->factory()->week_string();
4929 case Unit::kDay:
4930 return isolate->factory()->day_string();
4931 case Unit::kHour:
4932 return isolate->factory()->hour_string();
4933 case Unit::kMinute:
4934 return isolate->factory()->minute_string();
4935 case Unit::kSecond:
4936 return isolate->factory()->second_string();
4937 case Unit::kMillisecond:
4938 return isolate->factory()->millisecond_string();
4939 case Unit::kMicrosecond:
4940 return isolate->factory()->microsecond_string();
4941 case Unit::kNanosecond:
4942 return isolate->factory()->nanosecond_string();
4943 case Unit::kNotPresent:
4944 case Unit::kAuto:
4945 UNREACHABLE();
4946 }
4947}
4948
4949// #sec-temporal-create-iso-date-record
4950DateRecord CreateISODateRecord(Isolate* isolate, const DateRecord& date) {
4951 // 1. Assert: IsValidISODate(year, month, day) is true.
4952 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, date));
4953 // 2. Return the Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month, [[Day]]: day }.
4954 return date;
4955}
4956
4957// #sec-temporal-balanceisodate
4958DateRecord BalanceISODate(Isolate* isolate, const DateRecord& date) {
4959 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
4960 // 1. Let epochDays be MakeDay(𝔽(year), 𝔽(month - 1), 𝔽(day)).
4961 double epoch_days = MakeDay(date.year, date.month - 1, date.day);
4962 // 2. Assert: epochDays is finite.
4963 DCHECK(std::isfinite(epoch_days));
4964 // 3. Let ms be MakeDate(epochDays, +0𝔽).
4965 double ms = MakeDate(epoch_days, 0);
4966 // 4. Return CreateISODateRecordWithCalendar(ℝ(YearFromTime(ms)),
4967 // ℝ(MonthFromTime(ms)) + 1, ℝ(DateFromTime(ms))).
4968 int year = 0;
4969 int month = 0;
4970 int day = 0;
4971 int wday = 0;
4972 int hour = 0;
4973 int minute = 0;
4974 int second = 0;
4975 int millisecond = 0;
4976
4977 DCHECK(std::isfinite(ms));
4978 DCHECK_LT(ms, static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max()));
4979 DCHECK_GT(ms, static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()));
4980 isolate->date_cache()->BreakDownTime(ms, &year, &month, &day, &wday, &hour,
4981 &minute, &second, &millisecond);
4982
4983 return CreateISODateRecord(isolate, {year, month + 1, day});
4984}
4985
4986// #sec-temporal-adddatetime
4987Maybe<DateTimeRecord> AddDateTime(Isolate* isolate,
4988 const DateTimeRecord& date_time,
4989 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
4990 const DurationRecord& dur,
4991 DirectHandle<Object> options) {
4992 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
4993
4994 // 1. Assert: ISODateTimeWithinLimits(year, month, day, hour, minute, second,
4995 // millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond) is true.
4996 DCHECK(ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isolate, date_time));
4997 // 2. Let timeResult be ! AddTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond,
4998 // microsecond, nanosecond, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds,
4999 // microseconds, nanoseconds).
5000 const TimeDurationRecord& time = dur.time_duration;
5001 DateTimeRecord time_result =
5002 AddTime(isolate, date_time.time,
5003 {0, time.hours, time.minutes, time.seconds, time.milliseconds,
5004 time.microseconds, time.nanoseconds});
5005
5006 // 3. Let datePart be ? CreateTemporalDate(year, month, day, calendar).
5007 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> date_part;
5008 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5009 isolate, date_part, CreateTemporalDate(isolate, date_time.date, calendar),
5010 Nothing<DateTimeRecord>());
5011 // 4. Let dateDuration be ? CreateTemporalDuration(years, months, weeks, days
5012 // + timeResult.[[Days]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
5013 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> date_duration;
5014 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5015 isolate, date_duration,
5016 CreateTemporalDuration(
5017 isolate,
5018 {dur.years,
5019 dur.months,
5020 dur.weeks,
5021 {dur.time_duration.days + time_result.date.day, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}),
5022 Nothing<DateTimeRecord>());
5023 // 5. Let addedDate be ? CalendarDateAdd(calendar, datePart, dateDuration,
5024 // options).
5025 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> added_date;
5026 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5027 isolate, added_date,
5028 CalendarDateAdd(isolate, calendar, date_part, date_duration, options),
5029 Nothing<DateTimeRecord>());
5030 // 6. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: addedDate.[[ISOYear]], [[Month]]:
5031 // addedDate.[[ISOMonth]], [[Day]]: addedDate.[[ISODay]], [[Hour]]:
5032 // timeResult.[[Hour]], [[Minute]]: timeResult.[[Minute]], [[Second]]:
5033 // timeResult.[[Second]], [[Millisecond]]: timeResult.[[Millisecond]],
5034 // [[Microsecond]]: timeResult.[[Microsecond]], [[Nanosecond]]:
5035 // timeResult.[[Nanosecond]], }.
5036 time_result.date = {added_date->iso_year(), added_date->iso_month(),
5037 added_date->iso_day()};
5038 return Just(time_result);
5039}

5041// #sec-temporal-balanceduration
5042Maybe<TimeDurationRecord> BalanceDuration(Isolate* isolate, Unit largest_unit,
5043 const TimeDurationRecord& duration,
5044 const char* method_name) {
5045 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5046
5047 // 1. If relativeTo is not present, set relativeTo to undefined.
5048 return BalanceDuration(isolate, largest_unit,
5049 isolate->factory()->undefined_value(), duration,
5050 method_name);
5051}
5052
5053Maybe<TimeDurationRecord> BalanceDuration(Isolate* isolate, Unit largest_unit,
5054 DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds,
5055 const char* method_name) {
5056 // 1. Let balanceResult be ? BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(days, hours,
5057 // minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, largestUnit,
5058 // relativeTo).
5059 BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult balance_result;
5060 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5061 isolate, balance_result,
5062 BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(isolate, largest_unit, 0, nanoseconds,
5063 method_name),
5064 Nothing<TimeDurationRecord>());
5065
5066 // 2. If balanceResult is positive overflow or negative overflow, then
5067 if (balance_result.overflow != BalanceOverflow::kNone) {
5068 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
5069 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
5070 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
5071 Nothing<TimeDurationRecord>());
5072 // 3. Else,
5073 } else {
5074 // a. Return balanceResult.
5075 return Just(balance_result.value);
5076 }
5077}
5078
5079Maybe<TimeDurationRecord> BalanceDuration(Isolate* isolate, Unit largest_unit,
5080 const TimeDurationRecord& dur1,
5081 const TimeDurationRecord& dur2,
5082 const char* method_name) {
5083 // Add the two TimeDurationRecord as BigInt in nanoseconds.
5084 DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds =
5085 BigInt::Add(isolate, TotalDurationNanoseconds(isolate, dur1, 0),
5086 TotalDurationNanoseconds(isolate, dur2, 0))
5087 .ToHandleChecked();
5088 return BalanceDuration(isolate, largest_unit, nanoseconds, method_name);
5089}

5091// #sec-temporal-balanceduration
5092Maybe<TimeDurationRecord> BalanceDuration(Isolate* isolate, Unit largest_unit,
5093 Handle<Object> relative_to_obj,
5094 const TimeDurationRecord& value,
5095 const char* method_name) {
5096 // 1. Let balanceResult be ? BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(days, hours,
5097 // minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, largestUnit,
5098 // relativeTo).
5099 BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult balance_result;
5100 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5101 isolate, balance_result,
5102 BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(isolate, largest_unit, relative_to_obj,
5103 value, method_name),
5104 Nothing<TimeDurationRecord>());
5105
5106 // 2. If balanceResult is positive overflow or negative overflow, then
5107 if (balance_result.overflow != BalanceOverflow::kNone) {
5108 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
5109 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
5110 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
5111 Nothing<TimeDurationRecord>());
5112 // 3. Else,
5113 } else {
5114 // a. Return balanceResult.
5115 return Just(balance_result.value);
5116 }
5117}

5119// sec-temporal-balancepossiblyinfiniteduration
5120Maybe<BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult> BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(
5121 Isolate* isolate, Unit largest_unit, Handle<Object> relative_to_obj,
5122 const TimeDurationRecord& value, const char* method_name) {
5123 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5124 TimeDurationRecord duration = value;
5125 DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds;
5126
5127 // 2. If Type(relativeTo) is Object and relativeTo has an
5128 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then
5129 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*relative_to_obj)) {
5130 auto relative_to = Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(relative_to_obj);
5131 // a. Let endNs be ? AddZonedDateTime(relativeTo.[[Nanoseconds]],
5132 // relativeTo.[[TimeZone]], relativeTo.[[Calendar]], 0, 0, 0, days, hours,
5133 // minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
5134 DirectHandle<BigInt> end_ns;
5135 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5136 isolate, end_ns,
5137 AddZonedDateTime(isolate,
5138 direct_handle(relative_to->nanoseconds(), isolate),
5139 direct_handle(relative_to->time_zone(), isolate),
5140 direct_handle(relative_to->calendar(), isolate),
5141 {0, 0, 0, duration}, method_name),
5142 Nothing<BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult>());
5143 // b. Set nanoseconds to endNs − relativeTo.[[Nanoseconds]].
5144 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5145 isolate, nanoseconds,
5146 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, end_ns,
5147 direct_handle(relative_to->nanoseconds(), isolate)),
5148 Nothing<BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult>());
5149 // 3. Else,
5150 } else {
5151 // a. Set nanoseconds to ℤ(! TotalDurationNanoseconds(days, hours, minutes,
5152 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, 0)).
5153 nanoseconds = TotalDurationNanoseconds(isolate, duration, 0);
5154 }
5155
5156 // Call the BigInt version for the same process after step 4
5157 // The only value need to pass in is nanoseconds and days because
5158 // 1) step 4 and 5 use nanoseconds and days only, and
5159 // 2) step 6 is "Set hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, and microseconds
5160 // to 0."
5161 return BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(isolate, largest_unit, relative_to_obj,
5162 duration.days, nanoseconds,
5163 method_name);
5164}
5165
5166// The special case of BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration while the nanosecond is a
5167// large value and days contains non-zero values but the rest are 0.
5168// This version has no relative_to.
5169Maybe<BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult> BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(
5170 Isolate* isolate, Unit largest_unit, Handle<Object> relative_to_obj,
5171 double days, DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds, const char* method_name) {
5172 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5173
5174 // 4. If largestUnit is one of "year", "month", "week", or "day", then
5175 if (largest_unit == Unit::kYear || largest_unit == Unit::kMonth ||
5176 largest_unit == Unit::kWeek || largest_unit == Unit::kDay) {
5177 // a. Let result be ? NanosecondsToDays(nanoseconds, relativeTo).
5178 NanosecondsToDaysResult result;
5179 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5180 isolate, result,
5181 NanosecondsToDays(isolate, nanoseconds, relative_to_obj, method_name),
5182 Nothing<BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult>());
5183 // b. Set days to result.[[Days]].
5184 days = result.days;
5185 // c. Set nanoseconds to result.[[Nanoseconds]].
5186 nanoseconds = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, result.nanoseconds);
5187 // 5. Else,
5188 } else {
5189 // a. Set days to 0.
5190 days = 0;
5191 }
5192 // 6. Set hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, and microseconds to 0.
5193 DirectHandle<BigInt> thousand = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 1000);
5194 DirectHandle<BigInt> sixty = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 60);
5195 DirectHandle<BigInt> zero = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 0);
5196 DirectHandle<BigInt> hours = zero;
5197 DirectHandle<BigInt> minutes = zero;
5198 DirectHandle<BigInt> seconds = zero;
5199 DirectHandle<BigInt> milliseconds = zero;
5200 DirectHandle<BigInt> microseconds = zero;
5201
5202 // 7. If nanoseconds < 0, let sign be −1; else, let sign be 1.
5203 // 8. Set nanoseconds to abs(nanoseconds).
5204 int32_t sign = 1;
5205 if (nanoseconds->IsNegative()) {
5206 sign = -1;
5207 nanoseconds = BigInt::UnaryMinus(isolate, nanoseconds);
5208 }
5209
5210 // 9 If largestUnit is "year", "month", "week", "day", or "hour", then
5211 switch (largest_unit) {
5212 case Unit::kYear:
5213 case Unit::kMonth:
5214 case Unit::kWeek:
5215 case Unit::kDay:
5216 case Unit::kHour:
5217 // a. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
5218 microseconds =
5219 BigInt::Divide(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5220 // b. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
5221 nanoseconds =
5222 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5223 // c. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
5224 milliseconds =
5225 BigInt::Divide(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5226 // d. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
5227 microseconds =
5228 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5229 // e. Set seconds to floor(milliseconds / 1000).
5230 seconds =
5231 BigInt::Divide(isolate, milliseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5232 // f. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
5233 milliseconds =
5234 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, milliseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5235 // g. Set minutes to floor(seconds, 60).
5236 minutes = BigInt::Divide(isolate, seconds, sixty).ToHandleChecked();
5237 // h. Set seconds to seconds modulo 60.
5238 seconds = BigInt::Remainder(isolate, seconds, sixty).ToHandleChecked();
5239 // i. Set hours to floor(minutes / 60).
5240 hours = BigInt::Divide(isolate, minutes, sixty).ToHandleChecked();
5241 // j. Set minutes to minutes modulo 60.
5242 minutes = BigInt::Remainder(isolate, minutes, sixty).ToHandleChecked();
5243 break;
5244 // 10. Else if largestUnit is "minute", then
5245 case Unit::kMinute:
5246 // a. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
5247 microseconds =
5248 BigInt::Divide(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5249 // b. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
5250 nanoseconds =
5251 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5252 // c. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
5253 milliseconds =
5254 BigInt::Divide(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5255 // d. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
5256 microseconds =
5257 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5258 // e. Set seconds to floor(milliseconds / 1000).
5259 seconds =
5260 BigInt::Divide(isolate, milliseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5261 // f. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
5262 milliseconds =
5263 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, milliseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5264 // g. Set minutes to floor(seconds / 60).
5265 minutes = BigInt::Divide(isolate, seconds, sixty).ToHandleChecked();
5266 // h. Set seconds to seconds modulo 60.
5267 seconds = BigInt::Remainder(isolate, seconds, sixty).ToHandleChecked();
5268 break;
5269 // 11. Else if largestUnit is "second", then
5270 case Unit::kSecond:
5271 // a. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
5272 microseconds =
5273 BigInt::Divide(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5274 // b. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
5275 nanoseconds =
5276 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5277 // c. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
5278 milliseconds =
5279 BigInt::Divide(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5280 // d. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
5281 microseconds =
5282 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5283 // e. Set seconds to floor(milliseconds / 1000).
5284 seconds =
5285 BigInt::Divide(isolate, milliseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5286 // f. Set milliseconds to milliseconds modulo 1000.
5287 milliseconds =
5288 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, milliseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5289 break;
5290 // 12. Else if largestUnit is "millisecond", then
5291 case Unit::kMillisecond:
5292 // a. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
5293 microseconds =
5294 BigInt::Divide(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5295 // b. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
5296 nanoseconds =
5297 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5298 // c. Set milliseconds to floor(microseconds / 1000).
5299 milliseconds =
5300 BigInt::Divide(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5301 // d. Set microseconds to microseconds modulo 1000.
5302 microseconds =
5303 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, microseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5304 break;
5305 // 13. Else if largestUnit is "microsecond", then
5306 case Unit::kMicrosecond:
5307 // a. Set microseconds to floor(nanoseconds / 1000).
5308 microseconds =
5309 BigInt::Divide(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5310 // b. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds modulo 1000.
5311 nanoseconds =
5312 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, nanoseconds, thousand).ToHandleChecked();
5313 break;
5314 // 14. Else,
5315 case Unit::kNanosecond:
5316 // a. Assert: largestUnit is "nanosecond".
5317 break;
5318 case Unit::kAuto:
5319 case Unit::kNotPresent:
5320 UNREACHABLE();
5321 }
5322 // 15. For each value v of « days, hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds,
5323 // microseconds, nanoseconds », do a. If 𝔽(v) is not finite, then i. If sign
5324 // = 1, then
5325 // 1. Return positive overflow.
5326 // ii. Else if sign = -1, then
5327 // 1. Return negative overflow.
5328 double hours_value = Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, hours));
5329 double minutes_value =
5330 Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, minutes));
5331 double seconds_value =
5332 Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, seconds));
5333 double milliseconds_value =
5334 Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, milliseconds));
5335 double microseconds_value =
5336 Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, microseconds));
5337 double nanoseconds_value =
5338 Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, nanoseconds));
5339 if (std::isinf(days) || std::isinf(hours_value) ||
5340 std::isinf(minutes_value) || std::isinf(seconds_value) ||
5341 std::isinf(milliseconds_value) || std::isinf(microseconds_value) ||
5342 std::isinf(nanoseconds_value)) {
5343 return Just(BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult(
5344 {{0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0},
5345 sign == 1 ? BalanceOverflow::kPositive : BalanceOverflow::kNegative}));
5346 }
5347
5348 // 16. Return ? CreateTimeDurationRecord(days, hours × sign, minutes × sign,
5349 // seconds × sign, milliseconds × sign, microseconds × sign, nanoseconds ×
5350 // sign).
5351 TimeDurationRecord result;
5352 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5353 isolate, result,
5354 TimeDurationRecord::Create(
5355 isolate, days, hours_value * sign, minutes_value * sign,
5356 seconds_value * sign, milliseconds_value * sign,
5357 microseconds_value * sign, nanoseconds_value * sign),
5358 Nothing<BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult>());
5359 return Just(
5360 BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult({result, BalanceOverflow::kNone}));
5361}

5363// #sec-temporal-addzoneddatetime
5364MaybeHandle<BigInt> AddZonedDateTime(Isolate* isolate,
5365 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds,
5366 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone,
5367 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
5368 const DurationRecord& duration,
5369 const char* method_name) {
5370 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5371
5372 // 1. If options is not present, set options to undefined.
5373 return AddZonedDateTime(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds, time_zone, calendar,
5374 duration, isolate->factory()->undefined_value(),
5375 method_name);
5376}
5377
5378// #sec-temporal-addzoneddatetime
5379MaybeHandle<BigInt> AddZonedDateTime(Isolate* isolate,
5380 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds,
5381 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone,
5382 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
5383 const DurationRecord& duration,
5384 DirectHandle<Object> options,
5385 const char* method_name) {
5386 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5387
5388 TimeDurationRecord time_duration = duration.time_duration;
5389 // 2. If all of years, months, weeks, and days are 0, then
5390 if (duration.years == 0 && duration.months == 0 && duration.weeks == 0 &&
5391 time_duration.days == 0) {
5392 // a. Return ? AddInstant(epochNanoseconds, hours, minutes, seconds,
5393 // milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
5394 return AddInstant(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds, time_duration);
5395 }
5396 // 3. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(epochNanoseconds).
5397 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
5398 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)
5399 .ToHandleChecked();
5400
5401 // 4. Let temporalDateTime be ?
5402 // BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(timeZone, instant, calendar).
5403 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> temporal_date_time;
5404 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
5405 isolate, temporal_date_time,
5406 temporal::BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(isolate, time_zone, instant,
5407 calendar, method_name));
5408 // 5. Let datePart be ? CreateTemporalDate(temporalDateTime.[[ISOYear]],
5409 // temporalDateTime.[[ISOMonth]], temporalDateTime.[[ISODay]], calendar).
5410 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> date_part;
5411 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
5412 isolate, date_part,
5413 CreateTemporalDate(
5414 isolate,
5415 {temporal_date_time->iso_year(), temporal_date_time->iso_month(),
5416 temporal_date_time->iso_day()},
5417 calendar));
5418 // 6. Let dateDuration be ? CreateTemporalDuration(years, months, weeks, days,
5419 // 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
5420 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> date_duration;
5421 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
5422 isolate, date_duration,
5423 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate,
5424 {duration.years,
5425 duration.months,
5426 duration.weeks,
5427 {time_duration.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}));
5428 // 7. Let addedDate be ? CalendarDateAdd(calendar, datePart, dateDuration,
5429 // options).
5430 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> added_date;
5431 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
5432 isolate, added_date,
5433 CalendarDateAdd(isolate, calendar, date_part, date_duration, options));
5434 // 8. Let intermediateDateTime be ?
5435 // CreateTemporalDateTime(addedDate.[[ISOYear]], addedDate.[[ISOMonth]],
5436 // addedDate.[[ISODay]], temporalDateTime.[[ISOHour]],
5437 // temporalDateTime.[[ISOMinute]], temporalDateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
5438 // temporalDateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], temporalDateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
5439 // temporalDateTime.[[ISONanosecond]], calendar).
5440 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> intermediate_date_time;
5441 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
5442 isolate, intermediate_date_time,
5443 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
5444 isolate,
5445 {{added_date->iso_year(), added_date->iso_month(),
5446 added_date->iso_day()},
5447 {temporal_date_time->iso_hour(), temporal_date_time->iso_minute(),
5448 temporal_date_time->iso_second(),
5449 temporal_date_time->iso_millisecond(),
5450 temporal_date_time->iso_microsecond(),
5451 temporal_date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
5452 calendar));
5453 // 9. Let intermediateInstant be ? BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(timeZone,
5454 // intermediateDateTime, "compatible").
5455 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> intermediate_instant;
5456 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
5457 isolate, intermediate_instant,
5458 BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(isolate, time_zone, intermediate_date_time,
5459 Disambiguation::kCompatible, method_name));
5460 // 10. Return ? AddInstant(intermediateInstant.[[Nanoseconds]], hours,
5461 // minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
5462 time_duration.days = 0;
5463 return AddInstant(isolate,
5464 direct_handle(intermediate_instant->nanoseconds(), isolate),
5465 time_duration);
5466}
5467
5468Maybe<NanosecondsToDaysResult> NanosecondsToDays(
5469 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds,
5470 Handle<Object> relative_to_obj, const char* method_name) {
5471 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5472 // 1. Let dayLengthNs be nsPerDay.
5473 constexpr int64_t kDayLengthNs = 86400000000000LLU;
5474 DirectHandle<BigInt> day_length_ns = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, kDayLengthNs);
5475 double sign;
5476 switch (BigInt::CompareToNumber(nanoseconds,
5477 direct_handle(Smi::zero(), isolate))) {
5478 // 2. If nanoseconds = 0, then
5479 case ComparisonResult::kEqual:
5480 // a. Return the Record { [[Days]]: 0, [[Nanoseconds]]: 0, [[DayLength]]:
5481 // dayLengthNs }.
5482 return Just(NanosecondsToDaysResult({0, 0, kDayLengthNs}));
5483 // 3. If nanoseconds < 0, let sign be -1; else, let sign be 1.
5484 case ComparisonResult::kLessThan:
5485 sign = -1;
5486 break;
5487 case ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan:
5488 sign = 1;
5489 break;
5490 default:
5491 UNREACHABLE();
5492 }
5493
5494 // 4. If Type(relativeTo) is not Object or relativeTo does not have an
5495 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then
5496 if (!IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*relative_to_obj)) {
5497 // a. Return the Record { [[Days]]: RoundTowardsZero(nanoseconds /
5498 // dayLengthNs), [[Nanoseconds]]: (abs(nanoseconds) modulo dayLengthNs) ×
5499 // sign, [[DayLength]]: dayLengthNs }.
5500 if (sign == -1) {
5501 nanoseconds = BigInt::UnaryMinus(isolate, nanoseconds);
5502 }
5503 DirectHandle<BigInt> days_bigint;
5504 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5505 isolate, days_bigint,
5506 BigInt::Divide(isolate, nanoseconds, day_length_ns),
5507 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5508 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5509 isolate, nanoseconds,
5510 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, nanoseconds, day_length_ns),
5511 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5512 if (sign == -1) {
5513 days_bigint = BigInt::UnaryMinus(isolate, days_bigint);
5514 nanoseconds = BigInt::UnaryMinus(isolate, nanoseconds);
5515 }
5516 return Just(NanosecondsToDaysResult(
5517 {Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, days_bigint)),
5518 Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, nanoseconds)),
5519 kDayLengthNs}));
5520 }
5521 auto relative_to = Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(relative_to_obj);
5522 // 5. Let startNs be ℝ(relativeTo.[[Nanoseconds]]).
5523 DirectHandle<BigInt> start_ns(relative_to->nanoseconds(), isolate);
5524 // 6. Let startInstant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(ℤ(sartNs)).
5525 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> start_instant =
5526 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(
5527 isolate, direct_handle(relative_to->nanoseconds(), isolate))
5528 .ToHandleChecked();
5529
5530 // 7. Let startDateTime be ?
5531 // BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(relativeTo.[[TimeZone]],
5532 // startInstant, relativeTo.[[Calendar]]).
5533 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone(relative_to->time_zone(), isolate);
5534 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(relative_to->calendar(), isolate);
5535 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> start_date_time;
5536 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5537 isolate, start_date_time,
5538 temporal::BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(
5539 isolate, time_zone, start_instant, calendar, method_name),
5540 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5541
5542 // 8. Let endNs be startNs + nanoseconds.
5543 DirectHandle<BigInt> end_ns;
5544 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, end_ns,
5545 BigInt::Add(isolate, start_ns, nanoseconds),
5546 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5547
5548 // 9. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(ℤ(endNs)) is false, throw a RangeError
5549 // exception.
5550 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, end_ns)) {
5551 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
5552 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
5553 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5554 }
5555
5556 // 10. Let endInstant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(ℤ(endNs)).
5557 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> end_instant =
5558 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, end_ns).ToHandleChecked();
5559 // 11. Let endDateTime be ?
5560 // BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(relativeTo.[[TimeZone]],
5561 // endInstant, relativeTo.[[Calendar]]).
5562 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> end_date_time;
5563 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5564 isolate, end_date_time,
5565 temporal::BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(
5566 isolate, time_zone, end_instant, calendar, method_name),
5567 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5568
5569 // 12. Let dateDifference be ?
5570 // DifferenceISODateTime(startDateTime.[[ISOYear]],
5571 // startDateTime.[[ISOMonth]], startDateTime.[[ISODay]],
5572 // startDateTime.[[ISOHour]], startDateTime.[[ISOMinute]],
5573 // startDateTime.[[ISOSecond]], startDateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]],
5574 // startDateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]], startDateTime.[[ISONanosecond]],
5575 // endDateTime.[[ISOYear]], endDateTime.[[ISOMonth]], endDateTime.[[ISODay]],
5576 // endDateTime.[[ISOHour]], endDateTime.[[ISOMinute]],
5577 // endDateTime.[[ISOSecond]], endDateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]],
5578 // endDateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]], endDateTime.[[ISONanosecond]],
5579 // relativeTo.[[Calendar]], "day", OrdinaryObjectCreate(null)).
5580 DurationRecord date_difference;
5581 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5582 isolate, date_difference,
5583 DifferenceISODateTime(
5584 isolate,
5585 {{start_date_time->iso_year(), start_date_time->iso_month(),
5586 start_date_time->iso_day()},
5587 {start_date_time->iso_hour(), start_date_time->iso_minute(),
5588 start_date_time->iso_second(), start_date_time->iso_millisecond(),
5589 start_date_time->iso_microsecond(),
5590 start_date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
5591 {{end_date_time->iso_year(), end_date_time->iso_month(),
5592 end_date_time->iso_day()},
5593 {end_date_time->iso_hour(), end_date_time->iso_minute(),
5594 end_date_time->iso_second(), end_date_time->iso_millisecond(),
5595 end_date_time->iso_microsecond(), end_date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
5596 calendar, Unit::kDay, isolate->factory()->NewJSObjectWithNullProto(),
5597 method_name),
5598 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5599
5600 // 13. Let days be dateDifference.[[Days]].
5601 double days = date_difference.time_duration.days;
5602
5603 // 14. Let intermediateNs be ℝ(? AddZonedDateTime(ℤ(startNs),
5604 // relativeTo.[[TimeZone]], relativeTo.[[Calendar]], 0, 0, 0, days, 0, 0, 0,
5605 // 0, 0, 0)).
5606 DirectHandle<BigInt> intermediate_ns;
5607 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5608 isolate, intermediate_ns,
5609 AddZonedDateTime(isolate, start_ns, time_zone, calendar,
5610 {0, 0, 0, {days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}, method_name),
5611 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5612
5613 // 15. If sign is 1, then
5614 if (sign == 1) {
5615 // a. Repeat, while days > 0 and intermediateNs > endNs,
5616 while (days > 0 && BigInt::CompareToBigInt(intermediate_ns, end_ns) ==
5617 ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan) {
5618 // i. Set days to days − 1.
5619 days -= 1;
5620 // ii. Set intermediateNs to ℝ(? AddZonedDateTime(ℤ(startNs),
5621 // relativeTo.[[TimeZone]], relativeTo.[[Calendar]], 0, 0, 0, days, 0, 0,
5622 // 0, 0, 0, 0)).
5623 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5624 isolate, intermediate_ns,
5625 AddZonedDateTime(isolate, start_ns, time_zone, calendar,
5626 {0, 0, 0, {days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}, method_name),
5627 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5628 }
5629 }
5630
5631 // 16. Set nanoseconds to endNs − intermediateNs.
5632 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5633 isolate, nanoseconds, BigInt::Subtract(isolate, end_ns, intermediate_ns),
5634 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5635
5636 // 17. Let done be false.
5637 bool done = false;
5638
5639 // 18. Repeat, while done is false,
5640 while (!done) {
5641 // a. Let oneDayFartherNs be ℝ(? AddZonedDateTime(ℤ(intermediateNs),
5642 // relativeTo.[[TimeZone]], relativeTo.[[Calendar]], 0, 0, 0, sign, 0, 0, 0,
5643 // 0, 0, 0)).
5644 DirectHandle<BigInt> one_day_farther_ns;
5645 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5646 isolate, one_day_farther_ns,
5647 AddZonedDateTime(isolate, intermediate_ns, time_zone, calendar,
5648 {0, 0, 0, {sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}, method_name),
5649 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5650
5651 // b. Set dayLengthNs to oneDayFartherNs − intermediateNs.
5652 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5653 isolate, day_length_ns,
5654 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, one_day_farther_ns, intermediate_ns),
5655 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5656
5657 // c. If (nanoseconds − dayLengthNs) × sign ≥ 0, then
5658 if (sign * CompareResultToSign(
5659 BigInt::CompareToBigInt(nanoseconds, day_length_ns)) >=
5660 0) {
5661 // i. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds − dayLengthNs.
5662 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5663 isolate, nanoseconds,
5664 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, nanoseconds, day_length_ns),
5665 Nothing<NanosecondsToDaysResult>());
5666
5667 // ii. Set intermediateNs to oneDayFartherNs.
5668 intermediate_ns = one_day_farther_ns;
5669
5670 // iii. Set days to days + sign.
5671 days += sign;
5672 // d. Else,
5673 } else {
5674 // i. Set done to true.
5675 done = true;
5676 }
5677 }
5678
5679 // 20. Return the new Record { [[Days]]: days, [[Nanoseconds]]: nanoseconds,
5680 // [[DayLength]]: abs(dayLengthNs) }.
5681 NanosecondsToDaysResult result(
5682 {days, Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(isolate, nanoseconds)),
5683 std::abs(day_length_ns->AsInt64())});
5684 return Just(result);
5685}
5686
5687// #sec-temporal-differenceisodatetime
5688Maybe<DurationRecord> DifferenceISODateTime(Isolate* isolate,
5689 const DateTimeRecord& date_time1,
5690 const DateTimeRecord& date_time2,
5691 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
5692 Unit largest_unit,
5693 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options,
5694 const char* method_name) {
5695 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5696 // 1. Assert: ISODateTimeWithinLimits(y1, mon1, d1, h1, min1, s1, ms1, mus1,
5697 // ns1) is true.
5698 DCHECK(ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isolate, date_time1));
5699 // 2. Assert: ISODateTimeWithinLimits(y2, mon2, d2, h2, min2, s2, ms2, mus2,
5700 // ns2) is true.
5701 DCHECK(ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isolate, date_time2));
5702 // 3. Let timeDifference be ! DifferenceTime(h1, min1, s1, ms1, mus1, ns1, h2,
5703 // min2, s2, ms2, mus2, ns2).
5704 TimeDurationRecord time_difference =
5705 DifferenceTime(isolate, date_time1.time, date_time2.time).ToChecked();
5706
5707 // 4. Let timeSign be ! DurationSign(0, 0, 0, 0, timeDifference.[[Hours]],
5708 // timeDifference.[[Minutes]], timeDifference.[[Seconds]],
5709 // timeDifference.[[Milliseconds]], timeDifference.[[Microseconds]],
5710 // timeDifference.[[Nanoseconds]]).
5711 time_difference.days = 0;
5712 double time_sign = DurationRecord::Sign({0, 0, 0, time_difference});
5713
5714 // 5. Let dateSign be ! CompareISODate(y2, mon2, d2, y1, mon1, d1).
5715 double date_sign = CompareISODate(date_time2.date, date_time1.date);
5716
5717 // 6. Let adjustedDate be CreateISODateRecordWithCalendar(y1, mon1, d1).
5718 DateRecord adjusted_date = date_time1.date;
5719 CHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, adjusted_date));
5720
5721 // 7. If timeSign is -dateSign, then
5722 if (time_sign == -date_sign) {
5723 adjusted_date.day -= time_sign;
5724 // a. Set adjustedDate to BalanceISODate(adjustedDate.[[Year]],
5725 // adjustedDate.[[Month]], adjustedDate.[[Day]] - timeSign).
5726 adjusted_date = BalanceISODate(isolate, adjusted_date);
5727 // b. Set timeDifference to ! BalanceDuration(-timeSign,
5728 // timeDifference.[[Hours]], timeDifference.[[Minutes]],
5729 // timeDifference.[[Seconds]], timeDifference.[[Milliseconds]],
5730 // timeDifference.[[Microseconds]], timeDifference.[[Nanoseconds]],
5731 // largestUnit).
5732 time_difference.days = -time_sign;
5733 time_difference =
5734 BalanceDuration(isolate, largest_unit, time_difference, method_name)
5735 .ToChecked();
5736 }
5737
5738 // 8. Let date1 be ! CreateTemporalDate(adjustedDate.[[Year]],
5739 // adjustedDate.[[Month]], adjustedDate.[[Day]], calendar).
5740 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> date1 =
5741 CreateTemporalDate(isolate, adjusted_date, calendar).ToHandleChecked();
5742
5743 // 9. Let date2 be ! CreateTemporalDate(y2, mon2, d2, calendar).
5744 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> date2 =
5745 CreateTemporalDate(isolate, date_time2.date, calendar).ToHandleChecked();
5746 // 10. Let dateLargestUnit be ! LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits("day", largestUnit).
5747 Unit date_largest_unit = LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(Unit::kDay, largest_unit);
5748
5749 // 11. Let untilOptions be ? MergeLargestUnitOption(options, dateLargestUnit).
5750 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> until_options;
5751 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5752 isolate, until_options,
5753 MergeLargestUnitOption(isolate, options, date_largest_unit),
5754 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
5755 // 12. Let dateDifference be ? CalendarDateUntil(calendar, date1, date2,
5756 // untilOptions).
5757 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> date_difference;
5758 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5759 isolate, date_difference,
5760 CalendarDateUntil(isolate, calendar, date1, date2, until_options),
5761 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
5762 // 13. Let balanceResult be ? BalanceDuration(dateDifference.[[Days]],
5763 // timeDifference.[[Hours]], timeDifference.[[Minutes]],
5764 // timeDifference.[[Seconds]], timeDifference.[[Milliseconds]],
5765 // timeDifference.[[Microseconds]], timeDifference.[[Nanoseconds]],
5766 // largestUnit).
5767
5768 time_difference.days = Object::NumberValue(date_difference->days());
5769 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5770 isolate, time_difference,
5771 BalanceDuration(isolate, largest_unit, time_difference, method_name),
5772 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
5773
5774 // 14. Return ! CreateDurationRecord(dateDifference.[[Years]],
5775 // dateDifference.[[Months]], dateDifference.[[Weeks]],
5776 // balanceResult.[[Days]], balanceResult.[[Hours]], balanceResult.[[Minutes]],
5777 // balanceResult.[[Seconds]], balanceResult.[[Milliseconds]],
5778 // balanceResult.[[Microseconds]], balanceResult.[[Nanoseconds]]).
5779
5780 return Just(CreateDurationRecord(
5781 isolate, {Object::NumberValue(date_difference->years()),
5782 Object::NumberValue(date_difference->months()),
5783 Object::NumberValue(date_difference->weeks()),
5784 time_difference})
5785 .ToChecked());
5786}
5787
5788// #sec-temporal-addinstant
5789MaybeHandle<BigInt> AddInstant(Isolate* isolate,
5790 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds,
5791 const TimeDurationRecord& addend) {
5792 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5793 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
5794
5795 // 1. Assert: hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and
5796 // nanoseconds are integer Number values.
5797 // 2. Let result be epochNanoseconds + ℤ(nanoseconds) +
5798 // ℤ(microseconds) × 1000ℤ + ℤ(milliseconds) × 10^6ℤ + ℤ(seconds) × 10^9ℤ +
5799 // ℤ(minutes) × 60ℤ × 10^9ℤ + ℤ(hours) × 3600ℤ × 10^9ℤ.
5800
5801 // epochNanoseconds + ℤ(nanoseconds)
5802 Handle<BigInt> result =
5803 BigInt::Add(
5804 isolate, epoch_nanoseconds,
5805 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, factory->NewNumber(addend.nanoseconds))
5806 .ToHandleChecked())
5807 .ToHandleChecked();
5808
5809 // + ℤ(microseconds) × 1000ℤ
5810 DirectHandle<BigInt> temp =
5811 BigInt::Multiply(
5812 isolate,
5813 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, factory->NewNumber(addend.microseconds))
5814 .ToHandleChecked(),
5815 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 1000))
5816 .ToHandleChecked();
5817 result = BigInt::Add(isolate, result, temp).ToHandleChecked();
5818
5819 // + ℤ(milliseconds) × 10^6ℤ
5820 temp = BigInt::Multiply(isolate,
5821 BigInt::FromNumber(
5822 isolate, factory->NewNumber(addend.milliseconds))
5823 .ToHandleChecked(),
5824 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 1000000))
5825 .ToHandleChecked();
5826 result = BigInt::Add(isolate, result, temp).ToHandleChecked();
5827
5828 // + ℤ(seconds) × 10^9ℤ
5829 temp = BigInt::Multiply(
5830 isolate,
5831 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, factory->NewNumber(addend.seconds))
5832 .ToHandleChecked(),
5833 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 1000000000))
5834 .ToHandleChecked();
5835 result = BigInt::Add(isolate, result, temp).ToHandleChecked();
5836
5837 // + ℤ(minutes) × 60ℤ × 10^9ℤ.
5838 temp = BigInt::Multiply(
5839 isolate,
5840 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, factory->NewNumber(addend.minutes))
5841 .ToHandleChecked(),
5842 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 60000000000))
5843 .ToHandleChecked();
5844 result = BigInt::Add(isolate, result, temp).ToHandleChecked();
5845
5846 // + ℤ(hours) × 3600ℤ × 10^9ℤ.
5847 temp = BigInt::Multiply(
5848 isolate,
5849 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, factory->NewNumber(addend.hours))
5850 .ToHandleChecked(),
5851 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 3600000000000))
5852 .ToHandleChecked();
5853 result = BigInt::Add(isolate, result, temp).ToHandleChecked();
5854
5855 // 3. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(result) is false, throw a RangeError
5856 // exception.
5857 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, result)) {
5858 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
5859 }
5860 // 4. Return result.
5861 return result;
5862}
5863
5864// #sec-temporal-isvalidepochnanoseconds
5865bool IsValidEpochNanoseconds(Isolate* isolate,
5866 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds) {
5867 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5868 // nsMinInstant = -nsMaxInstant = -8.64 × 10^21
5869 constexpr double kNsMinInstant = -8.64e21;
5870 // nsMaxInstant = 10^8 × nsPerDay = 8.64 × 1021
5871 constexpr double kNsMaxInstant = 8.64e21;
5872
5873 // 1. Assert: Type(epochNanoseconds) is BigInt.
5874 // 2. If ℝ(epochNanoseconds) < nsMinInstant or ℝ(epochNanoseconds) >
5875 // nsMaxInstant, then
5876 if (BigInt::CompareToNumber(epoch_nanoseconds,
5877 isolate->factory()->NewNumber(kNsMinInstant)) ==
5878 ComparisonResult::kLessThan ||
5879 BigInt::CompareToNumber(epoch_nanoseconds,
5880 isolate->factory()->NewNumber(kNsMaxInstant)) ==
5881 ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan) {
5882 // a. Return false.
5883 return false;
5884 }
5885 return true;
5886}
5887
5888Handle<BigInt> GetEpochFromISOParts(Isolate* isolate,
5889 const DateTimeRecord& date_time) {
5890 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5891 // 1. Assert: year, month, day, hour, minute, second, millisecond,
5892 // microsecond, and nanosecond are integers.
5893 // 2. Assert: ! IsValidISODate(year, month, day) is true.
5894 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, date_time.date));
5895 // 3. Assert: ! IsValidTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond,
5896 // nanosecond) is true.
5897 DCHECK(IsValidTime(isolate, date_time.time));
5898 // 4. Let date be ! MakeDay(𝔽(year), 𝔽(month − 1), 𝔽(day)).
5899 double date = MakeDay(date_time.date.year, date_time.date.month - 1,
5900 date_time.date.day);
5901 // 5. Let time be ! MakeTime(𝔽(hour), 𝔽(minute), 𝔽(second), 𝔽(millisecond)).
5902 double time = MakeTime(date_time.time.hour, date_time.time.minute,
5903 date_time.time.second, date_time.time.millisecond);
5904 // 6. Let ms be ! MakeDate(date, time).
5905 double ms = MakeDate(date, time);
5906 // 7. Assert: ms is finite.
5907 // 8. Return ℝ(ms) × 10^6 + microsecond × 10^3 + nanosecond.
5908 return BigInt::Add(
5909 isolate,
5910 BigInt::Add(
5911 isolate,
5912 BigInt::Multiply(
5913 isolate,
5914 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate,
5915 isolate->factory()->NewNumber(ms))
5916 .ToHandleChecked(),
5917 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 1000000))
5918 .ToHandleChecked(),
5919 BigInt::Multiply(
5920 isolate,
5921 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, date_time.time.microsecond),
5922 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 1000))
5923 .ToHandleChecked())
5924 .ToHandleChecked(),
5925 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, date_time.time.nanosecond))
5926 .ToHandleChecked();
5927}

5932
5933// #sec-temporal-durationsign
5934int32_t DurationRecord::Sign(const DurationRecord& dur) {
5935 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5936
5937 // 1. For each value v of « years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes,
5938 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds », do a. If v < 0, return
5939 // −1. b. If v > 0, return 1.
5940 // 2. Return 0.
5941 if (dur.years < 0) return -1;
5942 if (dur.years > 0) return 1;
5943 if (dur.months < 0) return -1;
5944 if (dur.months > 0) return 1;
5945 if (dur.weeks < 0) return -1;
5946 if (dur.weeks > 0) return 1;
5947 const TimeDurationRecord& time = dur.time_duration;
5948 if (time.days < 0) return -1;
5949 if (time.days > 0) return 1;
5950 if (time.hours < 0) return -1;
5951 if (time.hours > 0) return 1;
5952 if (time.minutes < 0) return -1;
5953 if (time.minutes > 0) return 1;
5954 if (time.seconds < 0) return -1;
5955 if (time.seconds > 0) return 1;
5956 if (time.milliseconds < 0) return -1;
5957 if (time.milliseconds > 0) return 1;
5958 if (time.microseconds < 0) return -1;
5959 if (time.microseconds > 0) return 1;
5960 if (time.nanoseconds < 0) return -1;
5961 if (time.nanoseconds > 0) return 1;
5962 return 0;
5963}
5964
5965// #sec-temporal-isvalidduration
5966bool IsValidDuration(Isolate* isolate, const DurationRecord& dur) {
5967 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
5968
5969 // 1. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes,
5970 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
5971 int32_t sign = DurationRecord::Sign(dur);
5972 // 2. For each value v of « years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes,
5973 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds », do a. If v is not
5974 // finite, return false. b. If v < 0 and sign > 0, return false. c. If v > 0
5975 // and sign < 0, return false.
5976 // 3. Return true.
5977 const TimeDurationRecord& time = dur.time_duration;
5978
5979 if (!(std::isfinite(dur.years) && std::isfinite(dur.months) &&
5980 std::isfinite(dur.weeks) && std::isfinite(time.days) &&
5981 std::isfinite(time.hours) && std::isfinite(time.minutes) &&
5982 std::isfinite(time.seconds) && std::isfinite(time.milliseconds) &&
5983 std::isfinite(time.microseconds) && std::isfinite(time.nanoseconds))) {
5984 return false;
5985 }
5986 if ((sign > 0 && (dur.years < 0 || dur.months < 0 || dur.weeks < 0 ||
5987 time.days < 0 || time.hours < 0 || time.minutes < 0 ||
5988 time.seconds < 0 || time.milliseconds < 0 ||
5989 time.microseconds < 0 || time.nanoseconds < 0)) ||
5990 (sign < 0 && (dur.years > 0 || dur.months > 0 || dur.weeks > 0 ||
5991 time.days > 0 || time.hours > 0 || time.minutes > 0 ||
5992 time.seconds > 0 || time.milliseconds > 0 ||
5993 time.microseconds > 0 || time.nanoseconds > 0))) {
5994 return false;
5995 }
5996 static const double kPower32Of2 = static_cast<double>(int64_t(1) << 32);
5997 static const int64_t kPower53Of2 = int64_t(1) << 53;
5998 // 3. If abs(years) ≥ 2**32, return false.
5999 if (std::abs(dur.years) >= kPower32Of2) {
6000 return false;
6001 }
6002 // 4. If abs(months) ≥ 2**32, return false.
6003 if (std::abs(dur.months) >= kPower32Of2) {
6004 return false;
6005 }
6006 // 5. If abs(weeks) ≥ 2**32, return false.
6007 if (std::abs(dur.weeks) >= kPower32Of2) {
6008 return false;
6009 }
6010 // 6. Let normalizedSeconds be days × 86,400 + hours × 3600 + minutes × 60 +
6011 // seconds + ℝ(𝔽(milliseconds)) × 10**-3 + ℝ(𝔽(microseconds)) × 10**-6 +
6012 // ℝ(𝔽(nanoseconds)) × 10**-9.
6013 // 7. NOTE: The above step cannot be implemented directly using floating-point
6014 // arithmetic. Multiplying by 10**-3, 10**-6, and 10**-9 respectively may be
6015 // imprecise when milliseconds, microseconds, or nanoseconds is an unsafe
6016 // integer. This multiplication can be implemented in C++ with an
6017 // implementation of std::remquo() with sufficient bits in the quotient.
6018 // String manipulation will also give an exact result, since the
6019 // multiplication is by a power of 10.
6020 // 8. If abs(normalizedSeconds) ≥ 2**53, return false.
6021
6022 int64_t allowed = kPower53Of2;
6023 double in_seconds = std::abs(time.days * 86400.0 + time.hours * 3600.0 +
6024 time.minutes * 60.0 + time.seconds);
6025
6026 if (in_seconds >= allowed) {
6027 return false;
6028 }
6029 allowed -= in_seconds;
6030
6031 // Check the part > 1 seconds.
6032 in_seconds = std::floor(std::abs(time.milliseconds / 1e3)) +
6033 std::floor(std::abs(time.microseconds / 1e6)) +
6034 std::floor(std::abs(time.nanoseconds / 1e9));
6035 if (in_seconds >= allowed) {
6036 return false;
6037 }
6038 allowed -= in_seconds;
6039
6040 // Sum of the three remainings will surely < 3
6041 if (allowed > 3) {
6042 return true;
6043 }
6044
6045 allowed *= 1000000000; // convert to ns
6046 int64_t remainders = std::abs(fmod(time.milliseconds, 1e3)) * 1000000 +
6047 std::abs(fmod(time.microseconds, 1e6)) * 1000 +
6048 std::abs(fmod(time.nanoseconds, 1e9));
6049 if (remainders >= allowed) {
6050 return false;
6051 }
6052 return true;
6053}

6059// #sec-temporal-isisoleapyear
6060bool IsISOLeapYear(Isolate* isolate, int32_t year) {
6061 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6062
6063 // 1. Assert: year is an integer.
6064 // 2. If year modulo 4 ≠ 0, return false.
6065 // 3. If year modulo 400 = 0, return true.
6066 // 4. If year modulo 100 = 0, return false.
6067 // 5. Return true.
6068 return isolate->date_cache()->IsLeap(year);
6069}

6071// #sec-temporal-isodaysinmonth
6072int32_t ISODaysInMonth(Isolate* isolate, int32_t year, int32_t month) {
6073 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6074
6075 // 1. Assert: year is an integer.
6076 // 2. Assert: month is an integer, month ≥ 1, and month ≤ 12.
6077 DCHECK_GE(month, 1);
6078 DCHECK_LE(month, 12);
6079 // 3. If month is 1, 3, 5, 7, 8, 10, or 12, return 31.
6080 if (month % 2 == ((month < 8) ? 1 : 0)) return 31;
6081 // 4. If month is 4, 6, 9, or 11, return 30.
6082 DCHECK(month == 2 || month == 4 || month == 6 || month == 9 || month == 11);
6083 if (month != 2) return 30;
6084 // 5. If ! IsISOLeapYear(year) is true, return 29.
6085 return IsISOLeapYear(isolate, year) ? 29 : 28;
6086 // 6. Return 28.
6087}

6089// #sec-temporal-isodaysinyear
6090int32_t ISODaysInYear(Isolate* isolate, int32_t year) {
6091 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6092
6093 // 1. Assert: year is an integer.
6094 // 2. If ! IsISOLeapYear(year) is true, then
6095 // a. Return 366.
6096 // 3. Return 365.
6097 return IsISOLeapYear(isolate, year) ? 366 : 365;
6098}

6100bool IsValidTime(Isolate* isolate, const TimeRecord& time) {
6101 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6102
6103 // 2. If hour < 0 or hour > 23, then
6104 // a. Return false.
6105 if (time.hour < 0 || time.hour > 23) return false;
6106 // 3. If minute < 0 or minute > 59, then
6107 // a. Return false.
6108 if (time.minute < 0 || time.minute > 59) return false;
6109 // 4. If second < 0 or second > 59, then
6110 // a. Return false.
6111 if (time.second < 0 || time.second > 59) return false;
6112 // 5. If millisecond < 0 or millisecond > 999, then
6113 // a. Return false.
6114 if (time.millisecond < 0 || time.millisecond > 999) return false;
6115 // 6. If microsecond < 0 or microsecond > 999, then
6116 // a. Return false.
6117 if (time.microsecond < 0 || time.microsecond > 999) return false;
6118 // 7. If nanosecond < 0 or nanosecond > 999, then
6119 // a. Return false.
6120 if (time.nanosecond < 0 || time.nanosecond > 999) return false;
6121 // 8. Return true.
6122 return true;
6123}

6125// #sec-temporal-isvalidisodate
6126bool IsValidISODate(Isolate* isolate, const DateRecord& date) {
6127 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6128
6129 // 1. Assert: year, month, and day are integers.
6130 // 2. If month < 1 or month > 12, then
6131 // a. Return false.
6132 if (date.month < 1 || date.month > 12) return false;
6133 // 3. Let daysInMonth be ! ISODaysInMonth(year, month).
6134 // 4. If day < 1 or day > daysInMonth, then
6135 // a. Return false.
6136 if (date.day < 1 ||
6137 date.day > ISODaysInMonth(isolate, date.year, date.month)) {
6138 return false;
6139 }
6140 // 5. Return true.
6141 return true;
6142}

6144// #sec-temporal-compareisodate
6145int32_t CompareISODate(const DateRecord& one, const DateRecord& two) {
6146 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6147
6148 // 1. Assert: y1, m1, d1, y2, m2, and d2 are integers.
6149 // 2. If y1 > y2, return 1.
6150 if (one.year > two.year) return 1;
6151 // 3. If y1 < y2, return -1.
6152 if (one.year < two.year) return -1;
6153 // 4. If m1 > m2, return 1.
6154 if (one.month > two.month) return 1;
6155 // 5. If m1 < m2, return -1.
6156 if (one.month < two.month) return -1;
6157 // 6. If d1 > d2, return 1.
6158 if (one.day > two.day) return 1;
6159 // 7. If d1 < d2, return -1.
6160 if (one.day < two.day) return -1;
6161 // 8. Return 0.
6162 return 0;
6163}

6167// #sec-temporal-compareisodatetime
6168int32_t CompareISODateTime(const DateTimeRecord& one,
6169 const DateTimeRecord& two) {
6170 // 2. Let dateResult be ! CompareISODate(y1, mon1, d1, y2, mon2, d2).
6171 int32_t date_result = CompareISODate(one.date, two.date);
6172 // 3. If dateResult is not 0, then
6173 if (date_result != 0) {
6174 // a. Return dateResult.
6175 return date_result;
6176 }
6177 // 4. Return ! CompareTemporalTime(h1, min1, s1, ms1, mus1, ns1, h2, min2, s2,
6178 // ms2, mus2, ns2).
6179 return CompareTemporalTime(one.time, two.time);
6180}
6181
6182inline int32_t floor_divid(int32_t a, int32_t b) {
6183 return (((a) / (b)) + ((((a) < 0) && (((a) % (b)) != 0)) ? -1 : 0));
6184}
6185// #sec-temporal-balanceisoyearmonth
6186void BalanceISOYearMonth(Isolate* isolate, int32_t* year, int32_t* month) {
6187 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6188
6189 // 1. Assert: year and month are integers.
6190 // 2. Set year to year + floor((month - 1) / 12).
6191 *year += floor_divid((*month - 1), 12);
6192 // 3. Set month to (month − 1) modulo 12 + 1.
6193 *month = static_cast<int32_t>(modulo(*month - 1, 12)) + 1;
6194
6195 // 4. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month }.
6196}
6197// #sec-temporal-balancetime
6198DateTimeRecord BalanceTime(const UnbalancedTimeRecord& input) {
6199 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6200 UnbalancedTimeRecord time(input);
6201 TimeRecord result;
6202
6203 // 1. Assert: hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, and nanosecond
6204 // are integers.
6205 // 2. Set microsecond to microsecond + floor(nanosecond / 1000).
6206 time.microsecond += std::floor(time.nanosecond / 1000.0);
6207 // 3. Set nanosecond to nanosecond modulo 1000.
6208 result.nanosecond = modulo(time.nanosecond, 1000);
6209 // 4. Set millisecond to millisecond + floor(microsecond / 1000).
6210 time.millisecond += std::floor(time.microsecond / 1000.0);
6211 // 5. Set microsecond to microsecond modulo 1000.
6212 result.microsecond = modulo(time.microsecond, 1000);
6213 // 6. Set second to second + floor(millisecond / 1000).
6214 time.second += std::floor(time.millisecond / 1000.0);
6215 // 7. Set millisecond to millisecond modulo 1000.
6216 result.millisecond = modulo(time.millisecond, 1000);
6217 // 8. Set minute to minute + floor(second / 60).
6218 time.minute += std::floor(time.second / 60.0);
6219 // 9. Set second to second modulo 60.
6220 result.second = modulo(time.second, 60);
6221 // 10. Set hour to hour + floor(minute / 60).
6222 time.hour += std::floor(time.minute / 60.0);
6223 // 11. Set minute to minute modulo 60.
6224 result.minute = modulo(time.minute, 60);
6225 // 12. Let days be floor(hour / 24).
6226 int32_t days = std::floor(time.hour / 24.0);
6227 // 13. Set hour to hour modulo 24.
6228 result.hour = modulo(time.hour, 24);
6229 // 14. Return the new Record { [[Days]]: days, [[Hour]]: hour, [[Minute]]:
6230 // minute, [[Second]]: second, [[Millisecond]]: millisecond, [[Microsecond]]:
6231 // microsecond, [[Nanosecond]]: nanosecond }.
6232 return {{0, 0, days}, result};
6233}
6234
6235// #sec-temporal-differencetime
6236Maybe<TimeDurationRecord> DifferenceTime(Isolate* isolate,
6237 const TimeRecord& time1,
6238 const TimeRecord& time2) {
6239 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6240
6241 // 1. Assert: h1, min1, s1, ms1, mus1, ns1, h2, min2, s2, ms2, mus2, and ns2
6242 // are integers.
6243 TimeDurationRecord dur;
6244 // 2. Let hours be h2 − h1.
6245 dur.hours = time2.hour - time1.hour;
6246 // 3. Let minutes be min2 − min1.
6247 dur.minutes = time2.minute - time1.minute;
6248 // 4. Let seconds be s2 − s1.
6249 dur.seconds = time2.second - time1.second;
6250 // 5. Let milliseconds be ms2 − ms1.
6251 dur.milliseconds = time2.millisecond - time1.millisecond;
6252 // 6. Let microseconds be mus2 − mus1.
6253 dur.microseconds = time2.microsecond - time1.microsecond;
6254 // 7. Let nanoseconds be ns2 − ns1.
6255 dur.nanoseconds = time2.nanosecond - time1.nanosecond;
6256 // 8. Let sign be ! DurationSign(0, 0, 0, 0, hours, minutes, seconds,
6257 // milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
6258 double sign = DurationRecord::Sign(
6259 {0,
6260 0,
6261 0,
6262 {0, dur.hours, dur.minutes, dur.seconds, dur.milliseconds,
6263 dur.microseconds, dur.nanoseconds}});
6264
6265 // 9. Let bt be ! BalanceTime(hours × sign, minutes × sign, seconds × sign,
6266 // milliseconds × sign, microseconds × sign, nanoseconds × sign).
6267 DateTimeRecord bt =
6268 BalanceTime({dur.hours * sign, dur.minutes * sign, dur.seconds * sign,
6269 dur.milliseconds * sign, dur.microseconds * sign,
6270 dur.nanoseconds * sign});
6271
6272 // 9. Return ! CreateTimeDurationRecord(bt.[[Days]] × sign, bt.[[Hour]] ×
6273 // sign, bt.[[Minute]] × sign, bt.[[Second]] × sign, bt.[[Millisecond]] ×
6274 // sign, bt.[[Microsecond]] × sign, bt.[[Nanosecond]] × sign).
6275 return TimeDurationRecord::Create(
6276 isolate, bt.date.day * sign, bt.time.hour * sign, bt.time.minute * sign,
6277 bt.time.second * sign, bt.time.millisecond * sign,
6278 bt.time.microsecond * sign, bt.time.nanosecond * sign);
6279}
6280
6281// #sec-temporal-addtime
6282DateTimeRecord AddTime(Isolate* isolate, const TimeRecord& time,
6283 const TimeDurationRecord& addend) {
6284 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6285
6286 DCHECK_EQ(addend.days, 0);
6287 // 1. Assert: hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond,
6288 // hours, minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, and nanoseconds are
6289 // integers.
6290 // 2. Let hour be hour + hours.
6291 return BalanceTime({time.hour + addend.hours,
6292 // 3. Let minute be minute + minutes.
6293 time.minute + addend.minutes,
6294 // 4. Let second be second + seconds.
6295 time.second + addend.seconds,
6296 // 5. Let millisecond be millisecond + milliseconds.
6297 time.millisecond + addend.milliseconds,
6298 // 6. Let microsecond be microsecond + microseconds.
6299 time.microsecond + addend.microseconds,
6300 // 7. Let nanosecond be nanosecond + nanoseconds.
6301 time.nanosecond + addend.nanoseconds});
6302 // 8. Return ! BalanceTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond,
6303 // nanosecond).
6304}

6306// #sec-temporal-totaldurationnanoseconds
6307Handle<BigInt> TotalDurationNanoseconds(Isolate* isolate,
6308 const TimeDurationRecord& value,
6309 double offset_shift) {
6310 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6311
6312 TimeDurationRecord duration(value);
6313
6314 DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds =
6315 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate,
6316 isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value.nanoseconds))
6317 .ToHandleChecked();
6318
6319 // 1. Assert: offsetShift is an integer.
6320 // 2. Set nanoseconds to ℝ(nanoseconds).
6321 // 3. If days ≠ 0, then
6322 if (duration.days != 0) {
6323 // a. Set nanoseconds to nanoseconds − offsetShift.
6324 nanoseconds = BigInt::Subtract(
6325 isolate, nanoseconds,
6326 BigInt::FromNumber(
6327 isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(offset_shift))
6328 .ToHandleChecked())
6329 .ToHandleChecked();
6330 }
6331
6332 DirectHandle<BigInt> thousand = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 1000);
6333 DirectHandle<BigInt> sixty = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 60);
6334 DirectHandle<BigInt> twentyfour = BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 24);
6335 // 4. Set hours to ℝ(hours) + ℝ(days) × 24.
6336
6337 Handle<BigInt> x =
6338 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value.days))
6339 .ToHandleChecked();
6340 x = BigInt::Multiply(isolate, twentyfour, x).ToHandleChecked();
6341 x = BigInt::Add(isolate, x,
6342 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate,
6343 isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value.hours))
6344 .ToHandleChecked())
6345 .ToHandleChecked();
6346
6347 // 5. Set minutes to ℝ(minutes) + hours × 60.
6348 x = BigInt::Multiply(isolate, sixty, x).ToHandleChecked();
6349 x = BigInt::Add(isolate, x,
6350 BigInt::FromNumber(
6351 isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value.minutes))
6352 .ToHandleChecked())
6353 .ToHandleChecked();
6354 // 6. Set seconds to ℝ(seconds) + minutes × 60.
6355 x = BigInt::Multiply(isolate, sixty, x).ToHandleChecked();
6356 x = BigInt::Add(isolate, x,
6357 BigInt::FromNumber(
6358 isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value.seconds))
6359 .ToHandleChecked())
6360 .ToHandleChecked();
6361 // 7. Set milliseconds to ℝ(milliseconds) + seconds × 1000.
6362 x = BigInt::Multiply(isolate, thousand, x).ToHandleChecked();
6363 x = BigInt::Add(isolate, x,
6364 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
6365 value.milliseconds))
6366 .ToHandleChecked())
6367 .ToHandleChecked();
6368 // 8. Set microseconds to ℝ(microseconds) + milliseconds × 1000.
6369 x = BigInt::Multiply(isolate, thousand, x).ToHandleChecked();
6370 x = BigInt::Add(isolate, x,
6371 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
6372 value.microseconds))
6373 .ToHandleChecked())
6374 .ToHandleChecked();
6375 // 9. Return nanoseconds + microseconds × 1000.
6376 x = BigInt::Multiply(isolate, thousand, x).ToHandleChecked();
6377 x = BigInt::Add(isolate, x, nanoseconds).ToHandleChecked();
6378 return x;
6379}

6386// #sec-temporal-isomonthdayfromfields
6387Maybe<DateRecord> ISOMonthDayFromFields(Isolate* isolate,
6388 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,
6389 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options,
6390 const char* method_name) {
6391 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
6392 // 1. Assert: Type(fields) is Object.
6393 // 2. Set fields to ? PrepareTemporalFields(fields, « "day", "month",
6394 // "monthCode", "year" », «"day"»).
6395 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names =
6396 DayMonthMonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);
6397 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6398 isolate, fields,
6399 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, fields, field_names, RequiredFields::kDay),
6400 Nothing<DateRecord>());
6401 // 3. Let overflow be ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
6402 ShowOverflow overflow;
6403 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6404 isolate, overflow, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
6405 Nothing<DateRecord>());
6406 // 4. Let month be ! Get(fields, "month").
6407 DirectHandle<Object> month_obj =
6408 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->month_string())
6409 .ToHandleChecked();
6410 // 5. Let monthCode be ! Get(fields, "monthCode").
6411 DirectHandle<Object> month_code_obj =
6412 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->monthCode_string())
6413 .ToHandleChecked();
6414 // 6. Let year be ! Get(fields, "year").
6415 DirectHandle<Object> year_obj =
6416 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->year_string())
6417 .ToHandleChecked();
6418 // 7. If month is not undefined, and monthCode and year are both undefined,
6419 // then
6420 if (!IsUndefined(*month_obj, isolate) &&
6421 IsUndefined(*month_code_obj, isolate) &&
6422 IsUndefined(*year_obj, isolate)) {
6423 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
6424 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
6425 Nothing<DateRecord>());
6426 }
6427 // 8. Set month to ? ResolveISOMonth(fields).
6428 DateRecord result;
6429 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, result.month,
6430 ResolveISOMonth(isolate, fields),
6431 Nothing<DateRecord>());
6432
6433 // 9. Let day be ! Get(fields, "day").
6434 DirectHandle<Object> day_obj =
6435 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->day_string())
6436 .ToHandleChecked();
6437 // 10. Assert: Type(day) is Number.
6438 // Note: "day" in fields is always converted by
6439 // ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity inside the PrepareTemporalFields above.
6440 // Therefore the day_obj is always an integer.
6441 result.day = FastD2I(floor(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*day_obj))));
6442 // 11. Let referenceISOYear be 1972 (the first leap year after the Unix
6443 // epoch).
6444 int32_t reference_iso_year = 1972;
6445 // 12. If monthCode is undefined, then
6446 if (IsUndefined(*month_code_obj, isolate)) {
6447 result.year = FastD2I(floor(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*year_obj))));
6448 // a. Let result be ? RegulateISODate(year, month, day, overflow).
6449 } else {
6450 // 13. Else,
6451 // a. Let result be ? RegulateISODate(referenceISOYear, month, day,
6452 // overflow).
6453 result.year = reference_iso_year;
6454 }
6455 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6456 isolate, result, RegulateISODate(isolate, overflow, result),
6457 Nothing<DateRecord>());
6458 // 14. Return the new Record { [[Month]]: result.[[Month]], [[Day]]:
6459 // result.[[Day]], [[ReferenceISOYear]]: referenceISOYear }.
6460 result.year = reference_iso_year;
6461 return Just(result);
6462}

6467MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> JSTemporalDuration::Constructor(

6551// #sec-temporal-torelativetemporalobject
6552MaybeHandle<Object> ToRelativeTemporalObject(Isolate* isolate,
6553 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options,
6554 const char* method_name);
