6585// #sec-temporal-adjustroundeddurationdays
6586Maybe<DurationRecord> AdjustRoundedDurationDays(Isolate* isolate,
6587 const DurationRecord& duration,
6588 double increment, Unit unit,
6589 RoundingMode rounding_mode,
6590 Handle<Object> relative_to_obj,
6591 const char* method_name) {
6592 // 1. If Type(relativeTo) is not Object; or relativeTo does not have an
6593 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot; or unit is one of
6594 // "year", "month", "week", or "day"; or unit is "nanosecond" and increment is
6595 // 1, then
6596 if (!IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*relative_to_obj) ||
6597 (unit == Unit::kYear || unit == Unit::kMonth || unit == Unit::kWeek ||
6598 unit == Unit::kDay) ||
6599 (unit == Unit::kNanosecond && increment == 1)) {
6600 // a. Return ! CreateDurationRecord(years, months, weeks, days, hours,
6601 // minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
6602 return Just(CreateDurationRecord(isolate, duration).ToChecked());
6603 }
6604 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> relative_to =
6605 Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(relative_to_obj);
6606 // 2. Let timeRemainderNs be ! TotalDurationNanoseconds(0, hours, minutes,
6607 // seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds, 0).
6608 DirectHandle<BigInt> time_remainder_ns = TotalDurationNanoseconds(
6609 isolate,
6610 {0, duration.time_duration.hours, duration.time_duration.minutes,
6611 duration.time_duration.seconds, duration.time_duration.milliseconds,
6612 duration.time_duration.microseconds, duration.time_duration.nanoseconds},
6613 0);
6614
6615 ComparisonResult compare = BigInt::CompareToNumber(
6616 time_remainder_ns, direct_handle(Smi::zero(), isolate));
6617 double direction;
6618 // 3. If timeRemainderNs = 0, let direction be 0.
6619 if (compare == ComparisonResult::kEqual) {
6620 direction = 0;
6621 // 4. Else if timeRemainderNs < 0, let direction be -1.
6622 } else if (compare == ComparisonResult::kLessThan) {
6623 direction = -1;
6624 // 5. Else, let direction be 1.
6625 } else {
6626 direction = 1;
6627 }
6628
6629 // 6. Let dayStart be ? AddZonedDateTime(relativeTo.[[Nanoseconds]],
6630 // relativeTo.[[TimeZone]], relativeTo.[[Calendar]], years, months, weeks,
6631 // days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
6632 DirectHandle<BigInt> day_start;
6633 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6634 isolate, day_start,
6635 AddZonedDateTime(isolate,
6636 direct_handle(relative_to->nanoseconds(), isolate),
6637 direct_handle(relative_to->time_zone(), isolate),
6638 direct_handle(relative_to->calendar(), isolate),
6639 {duration.years,
6640 duration.months,
6641 duration.weeks,
6642 {duration.time_duration.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
6643 method_name),
6644 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
6645 // 7. Let dayEnd be ? AddZonedDateTime(dayStart, relativeTo.[[TimeZone]],
6646 // relativeTo.[[Calendar]], 0, 0, 0, direction, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
6647 DirectHandle<BigInt> day_end;
6648 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6649 isolate, day_end,
6650 AddZonedDateTime(isolate, day_start,
6651 direct_handle(relative_to->time_zone(), isolate),
6652 direct_handle(relative_to->calendar(), isolate),
6653 {0, 0, 0, {direction, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}, method_name),
6654 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
6655 // 8. Let dayLengthNs be ℝ(dayEnd - dayStart).
6656 DirectHandle<BigInt> day_length_ns =
6657 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, day_end, day_start).ToHandleChecked();
6658 // 9. If (timeRemainderNs - dayLengthNs) × direction < 0, then
6659 DirectHandle<BigInt> time_remainder_ns_minus_day_length_ns =
6660 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, time_remainder_ns, day_length_ns)
6661 .ToHandleChecked();
6662
6663 if (time_remainder_ns_minus_day_length_ns->AsInt64() * direction < 0) {
6664 // a. Return ! CreateDurationRecord(years, months, weeks, days, hours,
6665 // minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
6666 return Just(CreateDurationRecord(isolate, duration).ToChecked());
6667 }
6668 // 10. Set timeRemainderNs to ! RoundTemporalInstant(ℤ(timeRemainderNs -
6669 // dayLengthNs), increment, unit, roundingMode).
6670 time_remainder_ns =
6671 RoundTemporalInstant(isolate, time_remainder_ns_minus_day_length_ns,
6672 increment, unit, rounding_mode);
6673 // 11. Let adjustedDateDuration be ? AddDuration(years, months, weeks, days,
6674 // 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, direction, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, relativeTo).
6675 DurationRecord adjusted_date_duration;
6676 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6677 isolate, adjusted_date_duration,
6678 AddDuration(isolate,
6679 {duration.years,
6680 duration.months,
6681 duration.weeks,
6682 {duration.time_duration.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
6683 {0, 0, 0, {direction, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}, relative_to,
6684 method_name),
6685 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
6686 // 12. Let adjustedTimeDuration be ? BalanceDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
6687 // timeRemainderNs, "hour").
6688 TimeDurationRecord adjusted_time_duration;
6689 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6690 isolate, adjusted_time_duration,
6691 BalanceDuration(isolate, Unit::kHour, time_remainder_ns, method_name),
6692 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
6693 // 13. Return ! CreateDurationRecord(adjustedDateDuration.[[Years]],
6694 // adjustedDateDuration.[[Months]], adjustedDateDuration.[[Weeks]],
6695 // adjustedDateDuration.[[Days]], adjustedTimeDuration.[[Hours]],
6696 // adjustedTimeDuration.[[Minutes]], adjustedTimeDuration.[[Seconds]],
6697 // adjustedTimeDuration.[[Milliseconds]],
6698 // adjustedTimeDuration.[[Microseconds]],
6699 // adjustedTimeDuration.[[Nanoseconds]]).
6700 adjusted_time_duration.days = adjusted_date_duration.time_duration.days;
6701 return Just(
6702 CreateDurationRecord(
6703 isolate, {adjusted_date_duration.years, adjusted_date_duration.months,
6704 adjusted_date_duration.weeks, adjusted_time_duration})
6705 .ToChecked());
6706}
6707
6708// #sec-temporal-calculateoffsetshift
6709Maybe<int64_t> CalculateOffsetShift(Isolate* isolate,
6710 Handle<Object> relative_to_obj,
6711 const DateDurationRecord& dur,
6712 const char* method_name) {
6713 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6714
6715 // 1. If Type(relativeTo) is not Object or relativeTo does not have an
6716 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, return 0.
6717 if (!IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*relative_to_obj)) {
6718 return Just(static_cast<int64_t>(0));
6719 }
6720 auto relative_to = Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(relative_to_obj);
6721 // 2. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(relativeTo.[[Nanoseconds]]).
6722 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
6723 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(
6724 isolate, direct_handle(relative_to->nanoseconds(), isolate))
6725 .ToHandleChecked();
6726 // 3. Let offsetBefore be ? GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(relativeTo.[[TimeZone]],
6727 // instant).
6728 int64_t offset_before;
6729 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6730 isolate, offset_before,
6731 GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(isolate,
6732 direct_handle(relative_to->time_zone(), isolate),
6733 instant, method_name),
6734 Nothing<int64_t>());
6735 // 4. Let after be ? AddZonedDateTime(relativeTo.[[Nanoseconds]],
6736 // relativeTo.[[TimeZone]], relativeTo.[[Calendar]], y, mon, w, d, 0, 0, 0, 0,
6737 // 0, 0).
6738 DirectHandle<BigInt> after;
6739 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6740 isolate, after,
6741 AddZonedDateTime(
6742 isolate, direct_handle(relative_to->nanoseconds(), isolate),
6743 direct_handle(relative_to->time_zone(), isolate),
6744 direct_handle(relative_to->calendar(), isolate),
6745 {dur.years, dur.months, dur.weeks, {dur.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
6746 method_name),
6747 Nothing<int64_t>());
6748 // 5. Let instantAfter be ! CreateTemporalInstant(after).
6749 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant_after =
6750 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, after).ToHandleChecked();
6751 // 6. Let offsetAfter be ? GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(relativeTo.[[TimeZone]],
6752 // instantAfter).
6753 int64_t offset_after;
6754 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6755 isolate, offset_after,
6756 GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(isolate,
6757 direct_handle(relative_to->time_zone(), isolate),
6758 instant_after, method_name),
6759 Nothing<int64_t>());
6760 // 7. Return offsetAfter − offsetBefore
6761 return Just(offset_after - offset_before);
6762}

6766 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate> relative_to;
6767 double days;
6768};

6771 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> relative_to,
6772 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> duration, const char* method_name);

6774// #sec-temporal-unbalancedurationrelative
6775Maybe<DateDurationRecord> UnbalanceDurationRelative(
6776 Isolate* isolate, const DateDurationRecord& dur, Unit largest_unit,
6777 Handle<Object> relative_to_obj, const char* method_name) {
6778 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
6779
6780 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
6781 // 1. If largestUnit is "year", or years, months, weeks, and days are all 0,
6782 // then
6783 if (largest_unit == Unit::kYear ||
6784 (dur.years == 0 && dur.months == 0 && dur.weeks == 0 && dur.days == 0)) {
6785 // a. Return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(years, months, weeks, days).
6786 return Just(DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, dur.years, dur.months,
6787 dur.weeks, dur.days)
6788 .ToChecked());
6789 }
6790 // 2. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
6791 // 0).
6792 double sign = DurationRecord::Sign(
6793 {dur.years, dur.months, dur.weeks, {dur.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}});
6794 // 3. Assert: sign ≠ 0.
6795 DCHECK_NE(sign, 0);
6796 // 4. Let oneYear be ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
6797 // 0).
6798 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> one_year =
6799 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {sign, 0, 0, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
6800 .ToHandleChecked();
6801 // 5. Let oneMonth be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
6802 // 0).
6803 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> one_month =
6804 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {0, sign, 0, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
6805 .ToHandleChecked();
6806 // 6. Let oneWeek be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
6807 // 0).
6808 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> one_week =
6809 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {0, 0, sign, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
6810 .ToHandleChecked();
6811 // 7. If relativeTo is not undefined, then
6812 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> relative_to;
6813 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
6814 if (!IsUndefined(*relative_to_obj)) {
6815 // a. Set relativeTo to ? ToTemporalDate(relativeTo).
6816 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6817 isolate, relative_to,
6818 ToTemporalDate(isolate, relative_to_obj, method_name),
6819 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6820 // b. Let calendar be relativeTo.[[Calendar]].
6821 calendar = direct_handle(relative_to->calendar(), isolate);
6822 // 8. Else,
6823 } else {
6824 // a. Let calendar be undefined.
6825 }
6826 DateDurationRecord result = dur;
6827 // 9. If largestUnit is "month", then
6828 if (largest_unit == Unit::kMonth) {
6829 // a. If calendar is undefined, then
6830 if (calendar.is_null()) {
6831 // i. Throw a RangeError exception.
6832 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
6833 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
6834 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6835 }
6836 // b. Let dateAdd be ? GetMethod(calendar, "dateAdd").
6837 DirectHandle<Object> date_add;
6838 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6839 isolate, date_add,
6840 Object::GetMethod(isolate, calendar, factory->dateAdd_string()),
6841 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6842 // c. Let dateUntil be ? GetMethod(calendar, "dateUntil").
6843 DirectHandle<Object> date_until;
6844 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6845 isolate, date_until,
6846 Object::GetMethod(isolate, calendar, factory->dateUntil_string()),
6847 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6848 // d. Repeat, while years ≠ 0,
6849 while (result.years != 0) {
6850 // i. Let newRelativeTo be ? CalendarDateAdd(calendar, relativeTo,
6851 // oneYear, undefined, dateAdd).
6852 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> new_relative_to;
6853 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6854 isolate, new_relative_to,
6855 CalendarDateAdd(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_year,
6856 factory->undefined_value(), date_add),
6857 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6858 // ii. Let untilOptions be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
6859 DirectHandle<JSObject> until_options =
6860 factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
6861 // iii. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(untilOptions, "largestUnit",
6862 // "month").
6863 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
6864 isolate, until_options, factory->largestUnit_string(),
6865 factory->month_string(), Just(kThrowOnError))
6866 .FromJust());
6867 // iv. Let untilResult be ? CalendarDateUntil(calendar, relativeTo,
6868 // newRelativeTo, untilOptions, dateUntil).
6869 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> until_result;
6870 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6871 isolate, until_result,
6872 CalendarDateUntil(isolate, calendar, relative_to, new_relative_to,
6873 until_options, date_until),
6874 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6875 // v. Let oneYearMonths be untilResult.[[Months]].
6876 double one_year_months = Object::NumberValue(until_result->months());
6877 // vi. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
6878 relative_to = new_relative_to;
6879 // vii. Set years to years − sign.
6880 result.years -= sign;
6881 // viii. Set months to months + oneYearMonths.
6882 result.months += one_year_months;
6883 }
6884 // 10. Else if largestUnit is "week", then
6885 } else if (largest_unit == Unit::kWeek) {
6886 // a. If calendar is undefined, then
6887 if (calendar.is_null()) {
6888 // i. Throw a RangeError exception.
6889 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
6890 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
6891 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6892 }
6893 // b. Repeat, while years ≠ 0,
6894 while (result.years != 0) {
6895 // i. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneYear).
6896 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
6897 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6898 isolate, move_result,
6899 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_year,
6900 method_name),
6901 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6902 // ii. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
6903 relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
6904 // iii. Set days to days + moveResult.[[Days]].
6905 result.days += move_result.days;
6906 // iv. Set years to years - sign.
6907 result.years -= sign;
6908 }
6909 // c. Repeat, while months ≠ 0,
6910 while (result.months != 0) {
6911 // i. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
6912 // oneMonth).
6913 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
6914 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6915 isolate, move_result,
6916 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_month,
6917 method_name),
6918 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6919 // ii. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
6920 relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
6921 // iii. Set days to days + moveResult.[[Days]].
6922 result.days += move_result.days;
6923 // iv. Set months to months - sign.
6924 result.months -= sign;
6925 }
6926 // 11. Else,
6927 } else {
6928 // a. If any of years, months, and weeks are not zero, then
6929 if ((result.years != 0) || (result.months != 0) || (result.weeks != 0)) {
6930 // i. If calendar is undefined, then
6931 if (calendar.is_null()) {
6932 // i. Throw a RangeError exception.
6933 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
6934 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
6935 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6936 }
6937 // b. Repeat, while years ≠ 0,
6938 while (result.years != 0) {
6939 // i. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
6940 // oneYear).
6941 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
6942 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6943 isolate, move_result,
6944 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_year,
6945 method_name),
6946 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6947 // ii. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
6948 relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
6949 // iii. Set days to days + moveResult.[[Days]].
6950 result.days += move_result.days;
6951 // iv. Set years to years - sign.
6952 result.years -= sign;
6953 }
6954 // c. Repeat, while months ≠ 0,
6955 while (result.months != 0) {
6956 // i. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
6957 // oneMonth).
6958 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
6959 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6960 isolate, move_result,
6961 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_month,
6962 method_name),
6963 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6964 // ii. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
6965 relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
6966 // iii. Set days to days + moveResult.[[Days]].
6967 result.days += move_result.days;
6968 // iv. Set months to years - sign.
6969 result.months -= sign;
6970 }
6971 // d. Repeat, while weeks ≠ 0,
6972 while (result.weeks != 0) {
6973 // i. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
6974 // oneWeek).
6975 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
6976 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
6977 isolate, move_result,
6978 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_week,
6979 method_name),
6980 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
6981 // ii. Set relativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
6982 relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
6983 // iii. Set days to days + moveResult.[[Days]].
6984 result.days += move_result.days;
6985 // iv. Set weeks to years - sign.
6986 result.weeks -= sign;
6987 }
6988 }
6989 }
6990 // 12. Return ? CreateDateDurationRecord(years, months, weeks, days).
6991 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, result.years, result.months,
6992 result.weeks, result.days);
6993}
6994
6995// #sec-temporal-balancedurationrelative
6996Maybe<DateDurationRecord> BalanceDurationRelative(
6997 Isolate* isolate, const DateDurationRecord& dur, Unit largest_unit,
6998 Handle<Object> relative_to_obj, const char* method_name) {
6999 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
7000
7001 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
7002 // 1. If largestUnit is not one of "year", "month", or "week", or years,
7003 // months, weeks, and days are all 0, then
7004
7005 if ((largest_unit != Unit::kYear && largest_unit != Unit::kMonth &&
7006 largest_unit != Unit::kWeek) ||
7007 (dur.years == 0 && dur.months == 0 && dur.weeks == 0 && dur.days == 0)) {
7008 // a. Return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(years, months, weeks, days).
7009 return Just(DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, dur.years, dur.months,
7010 dur.weeks, dur.days)
7011 .ToChecked());
7012 }
7013 // 2. If relativeTo is undefined, then
7014 if (IsUndefined(*relative_to_obj)) {
7015 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
7016 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
7017 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
7018 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7019 }
7020
7021 // 3. Let sign be ! DurationSign(years, months, weeks, days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
7022 // 0).
7023 double sign = DurationRecord::Sign(
7024 {dur.years, dur.months, dur.weeks, {dur.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}});
7025 // 4. Assert: sign ≠ 0.
7026 DCHECK_NE(sign, 0);
7027 // 5. Let oneYear be ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
7028 // 0).
7029 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> one_year =
7030 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {sign, 0, 0, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
7031 .ToHandleChecked();
7032 // 6. Let oneMonth be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
7033 // 0).
7034 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> one_month =
7035 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {0, sign, 0, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
7036 .ToHandleChecked();
7037 // 7. Let oneWeek be ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, sign, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
7038 // 0).
7039 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> one_week =
7040 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {0, 0, sign, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
7041 .ToHandleChecked();
7042 // 8. Set relativeTo to ? ToTemporalDate(relativeTo).
7043 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> relative_to;
7044 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7045 isolate, relative_to,
7046 ToTemporalDate(isolate, relative_to_obj, method_name),
7047 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7048 // 9. Let calendar be relativeTo.[[Calendar]].
7049 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(relative_to->calendar(), isolate);
7050
7051 DateDurationRecord result = dur;
7052 // 10. If largestUnit is "year", then
7053 if (largest_unit == Unit::kYear) {
7054 // a. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneYear).
7055 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
7056 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7057 isolate, move_result,
7058 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_year, method_name),
7059 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7060 // b. Let newRelativeTo be moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7061 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7062 // c. Let oneYearDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
7063 double one_year_days = move_result.days;
7064 // d. Repeat, while abs(days) ≥ abs(oneYearDays),
7065 while (std::abs(result.days) >= std::abs(one_year_days)) {
7066 // i. Set days to days - oneYearDays.
7067 result.days -= one_year_days;
7068 // ii. Set years to years + sign.
7069 result.years += sign;
7070 // iii. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
7071 relative_to = new_relative_to;
7072 // iv. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
7073 // oneYear).
7074 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7075 isolate, move_result,
7076 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_year,
7077 method_name),
7078 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7079
7080 // iv. Set newRelativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7081 new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7082 // v. Set oneYearDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
7083 one_year_days = move_result.days;
7084 }
7085 // e. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneMonth).
7086 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7087 isolate, move_result,
7088 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_month,
7089 method_name),
7090 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7091 // f. Set newRelativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7092 new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7093 // g. Let oneMonthDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
7094 double one_month_days = move_result.days;
7095 // h. Repeat, while abs(days) ≥ abs(oneMonthDays),
7096 while (std::abs(result.days) >= std::abs(one_month_days)) {
7097 // i. Set days to days - oneMonthDays.
7098 result.days -= one_month_days;
7099 // ii. Set months to months + sign.
7100 result.months += sign;
7101 // iii. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
7102 relative_to = new_relative_to;
7103 // iv. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
7104 // oneMonth).
7105 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7106 isolate, move_result,
7107 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_month,
7108 method_name),
7109 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7110 // iv. Set newRrelativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7111 new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7112 // v. Set oneMonthDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
7113 one_month_days = move_result.days;
7114 }
7115 // i. Let dateAdd be ? GetMethod(calendar, "dateAdd").
7116 DirectHandle<Object> date_add;
7117 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7118 isolate, date_add,
7119 Object::GetMethod(isolate, calendar, factory->dateAdd_string()),
7120 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7121 // j. Set newRelativeTo be ? CalendarDateAdd(calendar, relativeTo, oneYear,
7122 // undefined, dateAdd).
7123 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7124 isolate, new_relative_to,
7125 CalendarDateAdd(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_year,
7126 factory->undefined_value(), date_add),
7127 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7128 // k. Let dateUntil be ? GetMethod(calendar, "dateUntil").
7129 DirectHandle<Object> date_until;
7130 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7131 isolate, date_until,
7132 Object::GetMethod(isolate, calendar, factory->dateUntil_string()),
7133 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7134 // l. Let untilOptions be OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
7135 DirectHandle<JSObject> until_options = factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
7136 // m. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(untilOptions, "largestUnit",
7137 // "month").
7138 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
7139 isolate, until_options, factory->largestUnit_string(),
7140 factory->month_string(), Just(kThrowOnError))
7141 .FromJust());
7142 // n. Let untilResult be ? CalendarDateUntil(calendar, relativeTo,
7143 // newRelativeTo, untilOptions, dateUntil).
7144 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> until_result;
7145 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7146 isolate, until_result,
7147 CalendarDateUntil(isolate, calendar, relative_to, new_relative_to,
7148 until_options, date_until),
7149 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7150 // o. Let oneYearMonths be untilResult.[[Months]].
7151 double one_year_months = Object::NumberValue(until_result->months());
7152 // p. Repeat, while abs(months) ≥ abs(oneYearMonths),
7153 while (std::abs(result.months) >= std::abs(one_year_months)) {
7154 // i. Set months to months - oneYearMonths.
7155 result.months -= one_year_months;
7156 // ii. Set years to years + sign.
7157 result.years += sign;
7158 // iii. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
7159 relative_to = new_relative_to;
7160 // iv. Set newRelativeTo to ? CalendarDateAdd(calendar, relativeTo,
7161 // oneYear, undefined, dateAdd).
7162 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7163 isolate, new_relative_to,
7164 CalendarDateAdd(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_year,
7165 factory->undefined_value(), date_add),
7166 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7167 // v. Set untilOptions to OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
7168 until_options = factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
7169 // vi. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(untilOptions, "largestUnit",
7170 // "month").
7171 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
7172 isolate, until_options, factory->largestUnit_string(),
7173 factory->month_string(), Just(kThrowOnError))
7174 .FromJust());
7175 // vii. Set untilResult to ? CalendarDateUntil(calendar, relativeTo,
7176 // newRelativeTo, untilOptions, dateUntil).
7177 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7178 isolate, until_result,
7179 CalendarDateUntil(isolate, calendar, relative_to, new_relative_to,
7180 until_options, date_until),
7181 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7182 // viii. Set oneYearMonths to untilResult.[[Months]].
7183 one_year_months = Object::NumberValue(until_result->months());
7184 }
7185 // 11. Else if largestUnit is "month", then
7186 } else if (largest_unit == Unit::kMonth) {
7187 // a. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneMonth).
7188 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
7189 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7190 isolate, move_result,
7191 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_month,
7192 method_name),
7193 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7194 // b. Let newRelativeTo be moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7195 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7196 // c. Let oneMonthDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
7197 double one_month_days = move_result.days;
7198 // d. Repeat, while abs(days) ≥ abs(oneMonthDays),
7199 while (std::abs(result.days) >= std::abs(one_month_days)) {
7200 // i. Set days to days - oneMonthDays.
7201 result.days -= one_month_days;
7202 // ii. Set months to months + sign.
7203 result.months += sign;
7204 // iii. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
7205 relative_to = new_relative_to;
7206 // iv. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
7207 // oneMonth).
7208 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7209 isolate, move_result,
7210 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_month,
7211 method_name),
7212 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7213 // v. Set newRelativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7214 new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7215 // vi. Set oneMonthDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
7216 one_month_days = move_result.days;
7217 }
7218 // 12. Else
7219 } else {
7220 // a. Assert: largestUnit is "week".
7221 DCHECK_EQ(largest_unit, Unit::kWeek);
7222 // b. Let moveResult be ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo, oneWeek).
7223 MoveRelativeDateResult move_result;
7224 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7225 isolate, move_result,
7226 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_week, method_name),
7227 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7228 // c. Let newRelativeTo be moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7229 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7230 // d. Let oneWeekDays be moveResult.[[Days]].
7231 double one_week_days = move_result.days;
7232 // e. Repeat, while abs(days) ≥ abs(oneWeekDays),
7233 while (std::abs(result.days) >= std::abs(one_week_days)) {
7234 // i. Set days to days - oneWeekDays.
7235 result.days -= one_week_days;
7236 // ii. Set weeks to weeks + sign.
7237 result.weeks += sign;
7238 // iii. Set relativeTo to newRelativeTo.
7239 relative_to = new_relative_to;
7240 // v. Set moveResult to ? MoveRelativeDate(calendar, relativeTo,
7241 // oneWeek).
7242 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7243 isolate, move_result,
7244 MoveRelativeDate(isolate, calendar, relative_to, one_week,
7245 method_name),
7246 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
7247 // v. Set newRelativeTo to moveResult.[[RelativeTo]].
7248 new_relative_to = move_result.relative_to;
7249 // vi. Set oneWeekDays to moveResult.[[Days]].
7250 one_week_days = move_result.days;
7251 }
7252 }
7253 // 12. Return ? CreateDateDurationRecord(years, months, weeks, days).
7254 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, result.years, result.months,
7255 result.weeks, result.days);
7256}
7257
7258} // namespace

7260// #sec-temporal.duration.compare
7261MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalDuration::Compare(Isolate* isolate,
7262 Handle<Object> one_obj,
7263 Handle<Object> two_obj,
7264 DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
7265 const char* method_name = "Temporal.Duration.compare";
7266 // 1. Set one to ? ToTemporalDuration(one).
7267 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> one;
7268 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7269 isolate, one,
7270 temporal::ToTemporalDuration(isolate, one_obj, method_name));
7271 // 2. Set two to ? ToTemporalDuration(two).
7272 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> two;
7273 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7274 isolate, two,
7275 temporal::ToTemporalDuration(isolate, two_obj, method_name));
7276 // 3. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
7277 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
7278 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7279 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
7280 // 4. Let relativeTo be ? ToRelativeTemporalObject(options).
7281 Handle<Object> relative_to;
7282 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7283 isolate, relative_to,
7284 ToRelativeTemporalObject(isolate, options, method_name));
7285 // 5. LetCalculateOffsetShift shift1 be ? CalculateOffsetShift(relativeTo,
7286 // one.[[Years]], one.[[Months]], one.[[Weeks]], one.[[Days]]).
7287 int64_t shift1;
7288 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7289 isolate, shift1,
7290 CalculateOffsetShift(
7291 isolate, relative_to,
7292 {Object::NumberValue(one->years()),
7293 Object::NumberValue(one->months()),
7294 Object::NumberValue(one->weeks()), Object::NumberValue(one->days())},
7295 method_name),
7296 Handle<Smi>());
7297 // 6. Let shift2 be ? CalculateOffsetShift(relativeTo, two.[[Years]],
7298 // two.[[Months]], two.[[Weeks]], two.[[Days]]).
7299 int64_t shift2;
7300 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7301 isolate, shift2,
7302 CalculateOffsetShift(
7303 isolate, relative_to,
7304 {Object::NumberValue(two->years()),
7305 Object::NumberValue(two->months()),
7306 Object::NumberValue(two->weeks()), Object::NumberValue(two->days())},
7307 method_name),
7308 Handle<Smi>());
7309 // 7. If any of one.[[Years]], two.[[Years]], one.[[Months]], two.[[Months]],
7310 // one.[[Weeks]], or two.[[Weeks]] are not 0, then
7311 double days1, days2;
7312 if (Object::NumberValue(one->years()) != 0 ||
7313 Object::NumberValue(two->years()) != 0 ||
7314 Object::NumberValue(one->months()) != 0 ||
7315 Object::NumberValue(two->months()) != 0 ||
7316 Object::NumberValue(one->weeks()) != 0 ||
7317 Object::NumberValue(two->weeks()) != 0) {
7318 // a. Let unbalanceResult1 be ? UnbalanceDurationRelative(one.[[Years]],
7319 // one.[[Months]], one.[[Weeks]], one.[[Days]], "day", relativeTo).
7320 DateDurationRecord unbalance_result1;
7321 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7322 isolate, unbalance_result1,
7323 UnbalanceDurationRelative(isolate,
7324 {Object::NumberValue(one->years()),
7325 Object::NumberValue(one->months()),
7326 Object::NumberValue(one->weeks()),
7327 Object::NumberValue(one->days())},
7328 Unit::kDay, relative_to, method_name),
7329 Handle<Smi>());
7330 // b. Let unbalanceResult2 be ? UnbalanceDurationRelative(two.[[Years]],
7331 // two.[[Months]], two.[[Weeks]], two.[[Days]], "day", relativeTo).
7332 DateDurationRecord unbalance_result2;
7333 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7334 isolate, unbalance_result2,
7335 UnbalanceDurationRelative(isolate,
7336 {Object::NumberValue(two->years()),
7337 Object::NumberValue(two->months()),
7338 Object::NumberValue(two->weeks()),
7339 Object::NumberValue(two->days())},
7340 Unit::kDay, relative_to, method_name),
7341 Handle<Smi>());
7342 // c. Let days1 be unbalanceResult1.[[Days]].
7343 days1 = unbalance_result1.days;
7344 // d. Let days2 be unbalanceResult2.[[Days]].
7345 days2 = unbalance_result2.days;
7346 // 8. Else,
7347 } else {
7348 // a. Let days1 be one.[[Days]].
7349 days1 = Object::NumberValue(one->days());
7350 // b. Let days2 be two.[[Days]].
7351 days2 = Object::NumberValue(two->days());
7352 }
7353 // 9. Let ns1 be ! TotalDurationNanoseconds(days1, one.[[Hours]],
7354 // one.[[Minutes]], one.[[Seconds]], one.[[Milliseconds]],
7355 // one.[[Microseconds]], one.[[Nanoseconds]], shift1).
7356 DirectHandle<BigInt> ns1 = TotalDurationNanoseconds(
7357 isolate,
7358 {days1, Object::NumberValue(one->hours()),
7359 Object::NumberValue(one->minutes()), Object::NumberValue(one->seconds()),
7360 Object::NumberValue(one->milliseconds()),
7361 Object::NumberValue(one->microseconds()),
7362 Object::NumberValue(one->nanoseconds())},
7363 shift1);
7364 // 10. Let ns2 be ! TotalDurationNanoseconds(days2, two.[[Hours]],
7365 // two.[[Minutes]], two.[[Seconds]], two.[[Milliseconds]],
7366 // two.[[Microseconds]], two.[[Nanoseconds]], shift2).
7367 DirectHandle<BigInt> ns2 = TotalDurationNanoseconds(
7368 isolate,
7369 {days2, Object::NumberValue(two->hours()),
7370 Object::NumberValue(two->minutes()), Object::NumberValue(two->seconds()),
7371 Object::NumberValue(two->milliseconds()),
7372 Object::NumberValue(two->microseconds()),
7373 Object::NumberValue(two->nanoseconds())},
7374 shift2);
7375 switch (BigInt::CompareToBigInt(ns1, ns2)) {
7376 // 11. If ns1 > ns2, return 1𝔽.
7377 case ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan:
7378 return handle(Smi::FromInt(1), isolate);
7379 // 12. If ns1 < ns2, return -1𝔽.
7380 case ComparisonResult::kLessThan:
7381 return handle(Smi::FromInt(-1), isolate);
7382 // 13. Return +0𝔽.
7383 default:
7384 return handle(Smi::FromInt(0), isolate);
7385 }
7386}

7388// #sec-temporal.duration.from
7389MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> JSTemporalDuration::From(Isolate* isolate,
7390 Handle<Object> item) {
7391 // 1. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalDuration]]
7392 // internal slot, then
7393 if (IsJSTemporalDuration(*item)) {
7394 // a. Return ? CreateTemporalDuration(item.[[Years]], item.[[Months]],
7395 // item.[[Weeks]], item.[[Days]], item.[[Hours]], item.[[Minutes]],
7396 // item.[[Seconds]], item.[[Milliseconds]], item.[[Microseconds]],
7397 // item.[[Nanoseconds]]).
7398 auto duration = Cast<JSTemporalDuration>(item);
7399 return CreateTemporalDuration(
7400 isolate, {Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),
7401 Object::NumberValue(duration->months()),
7402 Object::NumberValue(duration->weeks()),
7403 {Object::NumberValue(duration->days()),
7404 Object::NumberValue(duration->hours()),
7405 Object::NumberValue(duration->minutes()),
7406 Object::NumberValue(duration->seconds()),
7407 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
7408 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
7409 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds())}});
7410 }
7411 // 2. Return ? ToTemporalDuration(item).
7412 return temporal::ToTemporalDuration(isolate, item, "Temporal.Duration.from");
7413}

7441// #sec-temporal.duration.prototype.round
7442MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> JSTemporalDuration::Round(
7443 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> duration,
7444 DirectHandle<Object> round_to_obj) {
7445 const char* method_name = "Temporal.Duration.prototype.round";
7446 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
7447 // 1. Let duration be the this value.
7448 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(duration,
7449 // [[InitializedTemporalDuration]]).
7450 // 3. If roundTo is undefined, then
7451 if (IsUndefined(*round_to_obj)) {
7452 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
7453 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
7454 }
7455 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> round_to;
7456 // 4. If Type(roundTo) is String, then
7457 if (IsString(*round_to_obj)) {
7458 // a. Let paramString be roundTo.
7459 DirectHandle<String> param_string = Cast<String>(round_to_obj);
7460 // b. Set roundTo to ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
7461 round_to = factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
7462 // c. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(roundTo, "_smallestUnit_",
7463 // paramString).
7464 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, round_to,
7465 factory->smallestUnit_string(),
7466 param_string, Just(kThrowOnError))
7467 .FromJust());
7468 } else {
7469 // a. Set roundTo to ? GetOptionsObject(roundTo).
7470 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7471 isolate, round_to,
7472 GetOptionsObject(isolate, round_to_obj, method_name));
7473 }
7474 // 6. Let smallestUnitPresent be true.
7475 bool smallest_unit_present = true;
7476 // 7. Let largestUnitPresent be true.
7477 bool largest_unit_present = true;
7478 // 8. Let smallestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(roundTo, "smallestUnit", datetime,
7479 // undefined).
7480 Unit smallest_unit;
7481 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7482 isolate, smallest_unit,
7483 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, round_to, "smallestUnit", UnitGroup::kDateTime,
7484 Unit::kNotPresent, false, method_name),
7485 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7486 // 9. If smallestUnit is undefined, then
7487 if (smallest_unit == Unit::kNotPresent) {
7488 // a. Set smallestUnitPresent to false.
7489 smallest_unit_present = false;
7490 // b. Set smallestUnit to "nanosecond".
7491 smallest_unit = Unit::kNanosecond;
7492 }
7493 // 10. Let defaultLargestUnit be !
7494 // DefaultTemporalLargestUnit(duration.[[Years]], duration.[[Months]],
7495 // duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], duration.[[Hours]],
7496 // duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]], duration.[[Milliseconds]],
7497 // duration.[[Microseconds]]).
7498 Unit default_largest_unit = DefaultTemporalLargestUnit(
7499 {Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),
7500 Object::NumberValue(duration->months()),
7501 Object::NumberValue(duration->weeks()),
7502 {Object::NumberValue(duration->days()),
7503 Object::NumberValue(duration->hours()),
7504 Object::NumberValue(duration->minutes()),
7505 Object::NumberValue(duration->seconds()),
7506 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
7507 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
7508 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds())}});
7509
7510 // 11. Set defaultLargestUnit to !
7511 // LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(defaultLargestUnit, smallestUnit).
7512 default_largest_unit =
7513 LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(default_largest_unit, smallest_unit);
7514 // 12. Let largestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(roundTo, "largestUnit", datetime,
7515 // undefined, « "auto" »).
7516 Unit largest_unit;
7517 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7518 isolate, largest_unit,
7519 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, round_to, "largestUnit", UnitGroup::kDateTime,
7520 Unit::kNotPresent, false, method_name, Unit::kAuto),
7521 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7522 // 13. If largestUnit is undefined, then
7523 if (largest_unit == Unit::kNotPresent) {
7524 // a. Set largestUnitPresent to false.
7525 largest_unit_present = false;
7526 // b. Set largestUnit to defaultLargestUnit.
7527 largest_unit = default_largest_unit;
7528 // 14. Else if largestUnit is "auto", then
7529 } else if (largest_unit == Unit::kAuto) {
7530 // a. Set largestUnit to defaultLargestUnit.
7531 largest_unit = default_largest_unit;
7532 }
7533 // 15. If smallestUnitPresent is false and largestUnitPresent is false, then
7534 if (!smallest_unit_present && !largest_unit_present) {
7535 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
7536 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
7537 }
7538 // 16. If LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(largestUnit, smallestUnit) is not
7539 // largestUnit, throw a RangeError exception.
7540 if (LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(largest_unit, smallest_unit) != largest_unit) {
7541 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
7542 }
7543 // 17. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(roundTo, "halfExpand").
7544 RoundingMode rounding_mode;
7545 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7546 isolate, rounding_mode,
7547 ToTemporalRoundingMode(isolate, round_to, RoundingMode::kHalfExpand,
7548 method_name),
7549 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7550 // 18. Let maximum be !
7551 // MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallestUnit).
7552 Maximum maximum = MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallest_unit);
7553
7554 // 19. Let roundingIncrement be ? ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(roundTo,
7555 // maximum, false).
7556 double rounding_increment;
7557 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7558 isolate, rounding_increment,
7559 ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(isolate, round_to, maximum.value,
7560 maximum.defined, false),
7561 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7562 // 20. Let relativeTo be ? ToRelativeTemporalObject(roundTo).
7563 Handle<Object> relative_to;
7564 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7565 isolate, relative_to,
7566 ToRelativeTemporalObject(isolate, round_to, method_name));
7567 // 21. Let unbalanceResult be ? UnbalanceDurationRelative(duration.[[Years]],
7568 // duration.[[Months]], duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], largestUnit,
7569 // relativeTo).
7570 DateDurationRecord unbalance_result;
7571 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7572 isolate, unbalance_result,
7573 UnbalanceDurationRelative(isolate,
7574 {Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),
7575 Object::NumberValue(duration->months()),
7576 Object::NumberValue(duration->weeks()),
7577 Object::NumberValue(duration->days())},
7578 largest_unit, relative_to, method_name),
7579 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7580 // 22. Let roundResult be (? RoundDuration(unbalanceResult.[[Years]],
7581 // unbalanceResult.[[Months]], unbalanceResult.[[Weeks]],
7582 // unbalanceResult.[[Days]], duration.[[Hours]], duration.[[Minutes]],
7583 // duration.[[Seconds]], duration.[[Milliseconds]], duration.[[Microseconds]],
7584 // duration.[[Nanoseconds]], roundingIncrement, smallestUnit, roundingMode,
7585 // relativeTo)).[[DurationRecord]].
7586 DurationRecordWithRemainder round_result;
7587 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7588 isolate, round_result,
7589 RoundDuration(
7590 isolate,
7591 {unbalance_result.years,
7592 unbalance_result.months,
7593 unbalance_result.weeks,
7594 {unbalance_result.days, Object::NumberValue(duration->hours()),
7595 Object::NumberValue(duration->minutes()),
7596 Object::NumberValue(duration->seconds()),
7597 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
7598 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
7599 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds())}},
7600 rounding_increment, smallest_unit, rounding_mode, relative_to,
7601 method_name),
7602 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7603
7604 // 23. Let adjustResult be ? AdjustRoundedDurationDays(roundResult.[[Years]],
7605 // roundResult.[[Months]], roundResult.[[Weeks]], roundResult.[[Days]],
7606 // roundResult.[[Hours]], roundResult.[[Minutes]], roundResult.[[Seconds]],
7607 // roundResult.[[Milliseconds]], roundResult.[[Microseconds]],
7608 // roundResult.[[Nanoseconds]], roundingIncrement, smallestUnit, roundingMode,
7609 // relativeTo).
7610 DurationRecord adjust_result;
7611 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7612 isolate, adjust_result,
7613 AdjustRoundedDurationDays(isolate, round_result.record,
7614 rounding_increment, smallest_unit,
7615 rounding_mode, relative_to, method_name),
7616 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7617 // 24. Let balanceResult be ? BalanceDurationRelative(adjustResult.[[Years]],
7618 // adjustResult.[[Months]], adjustResult.[[Weeks]], adjustResult.[[Days]],
7619 // largestUnit, relativeTo).
7620 DateDurationRecord balance_result;
7621 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7622 isolate, balance_result,
7623 BalanceDurationRelative(
7624 isolate,
7625 {adjust_result.years, adjust_result.months, adjust_result.weeks,
7626 adjust_result.time_duration.days},
7627 largest_unit, relative_to, method_name),
7628 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7629 // 25. If Type(relativeTo) is Object and relativeTo has an
7630 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then
7631 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*relative_to)) {
7632 // a. Set relativeTo to ? MoveRelativeZonedDateTime(relativeTo,
7633 // balanceResult.[[Years]], balanceResult.[[Months]],
7634 // balanceResult.[[Weeks]], 0).
7635 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7636 isolate, relative_to,
7637 MoveRelativeZonedDateTime(isolate,
7638 Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(relative_to),
7639 {balance_result.years, balance_result.months,
7640 balance_result.weeks, 0},
7641 method_name));
7642 }
7643 // 26. Let result be ? BalanceDuration(balanceResult.[[Days]],
7644 // adjustResult.[[Hours]], adjustResult.[[Minutes]], adjustResult.[[Seconds]],
7645 // adjustResult.[[Milliseconds]], adjustResult.[[Microseconds]],
7646 // adjustResult.[[Nanoseconds]], largestUnit, relativeTo).
7647 TimeDurationRecord result;
7648 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7649 isolate, result,
7650 BalanceDuration(isolate, largest_unit, relative_to,
7651 {balance_result.days, adjust_result.time_duration.hours,
7652 adjust_result.time_duration.minutes,
7653 adjust_result.time_duration.seconds,
7654 adjust_result.time_duration.milliseconds,
7655 adjust_result.time_duration.microseconds,
7656 adjust_result.time_duration.nanoseconds},
7657 method_name),
7658 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7659 // 27. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(balanceResult.[[Years]],
7660 // balanceResult.[[Months]], balanceResult.[[Weeks]], result.[[Days]],
7661 // result.[[Hours]], result.[[Minutes]], result.[[Seconds]],
7662 // result.[[Milliseconds]], result.[[Microseconds]], result.[[Nanoseconds]]).
7663 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate,
7664 {balance_result.years, balance_result.months,
7665 balance_result.weeks, result})
7666 .ToHandleChecked();
7667}
7668
7669// #sec-temporal.duration.prototype.total
7670MaybeHandle<Object> JSTemporalDuration::Total(
7671 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> duration,
7672 DirectHandle<Object> total_of_obj) {
7673 const char* method_name = "Temporal.Duration.prototype.total";
7674 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
7675 // 1. Let duration be the this value.
7676 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(duration,
7677 // [[InitializedTemporalDuration]]).
7678 // 3. If totalOf is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
7679 if (IsUndefined(*total_of_obj, isolate)) {
7680 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
7681 }
7682
7683 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> total_of;
7684 // 4. If Type(totalOf) is String, then
7685 if (IsString(*total_of_obj)) {
7686 // a. Let paramString be totalOf.
7687 DirectHandle<String> param_string = Cast<String>(total_of_obj);
7688 // b. Set totalOf to ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
7689 total_of = factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
7690 // c. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(total_of, "unit", paramString).
7691 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, total_of,
7692 factory->unit_string(), param_string,
7693 Just(kThrowOnError))
7694 .FromJust());
7695 } else {
7696 // 5. Set totalOf to ? GetOptionsObject(totalOf).
7697 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7698 isolate, total_of,
7699 GetOptionsObject(isolate, total_of_obj, method_name));
7700 }
7701
7702 // 6. Let relativeTo be ? ToRelativeTemporalObject(totalOf).
7703 Handle<Object> relative_to;
7704 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7705 isolate, relative_to,
7706 ToRelativeTemporalObject(isolate, total_of, method_name));
7707 // 7. Let unit be ? GetTemporalUnit(totalOf, "unit", datetime, required).
7708 Unit unit;
7709 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7710 isolate, unit,
7711 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, total_of, "unit", UnitGroup::kDateTime,
7712 Unit::kNotPresent, true, method_name),
7713 Handle<Object>());
7714 // 8. Let unbalanceResult be ? UnbalanceDurationRelative(duration.[[Years]],
7715 // duration.[[Months]], duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], unit,
7716 // relativeTo).
7717 DateDurationRecord unbalance_result;
7718 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7719 isolate, unbalance_result,
7720 UnbalanceDurationRelative(isolate,
7721 {Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),
7722 Object::NumberValue(duration->months()),
7723 Object::NumberValue(duration->weeks()),
7724 Object::NumberValue(duration->days())},
7725 unit, relative_to, method_name),
7726 Handle<Object>());
7727
7728 // 9. Let intermediate be undefined.
7729 Handle<Object> intermediate = factory->undefined_value();
7730
7731 // 8. If relativeTo has an [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot,
7732 // then
7733 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*relative_to)) {
7734 // a. Set intermediate to ? MoveRelativeZonedDateTime(relativeTo,
7735 // unbalanceResult.[[Years]], unbalanceResult.[[Months]],
7736 // unbalanceResult.[[Weeks]], 0).
7737 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
7738 isolate, intermediate,
7739 MoveRelativeZonedDateTime(
7740 isolate, Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(relative_to),
7741 {unbalance_result.years, unbalance_result.months,
7742 unbalance_result.weeks, 0},
7743 method_name));
7744 }
7745
7746 // 11. Let balanceResult be ?
7747 // BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(unbalanceResult.[[Days]],
7748 // duration.[[Hours]], duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]],
7749 // duration.[[Milliseconds]], duration.[[Microseconds]],
7750 // duration.[[Nanoseconds]], unit, intermediate).
7751 BalancePossiblyInfiniteDurationResult balance_result;
7752 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7753 isolate, balance_result,
7754 BalancePossiblyInfiniteDuration(
7755 isolate, unit, intermediate,
7756 {unbalance_result.days, Object::NumberValue(duration->hours()),
7757 Object::NumberValue(duration->minutes()),
7758 Object::NumberValue(duration->seconds()),
7759 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
7760 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
7761 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds())},
7762 method_name),
7763 Handle<Object>());
7764 // 12. If balanceResult is positive overflow, return +∞𝔽.
7765 if (balance_result.overflow == BalanceOverflow::kPositive) {
7766 return factory->infinity_value();
7767 }
7768 // 13. If balanceResult is negative overflow, return -∞𝔽.
7769 if (balance_result.overflow == BalanceOverflow::kNegative) {
7770 return factory->minus_infinity_value();
7771 }
7772 // 14. Assert: balanceResult is a Time Duration Record.
7773 DCHECK_EQ(balance_result.overflow, BalanceOverflow::kNone);
7774 // 15. Let roundRecord be ? RoundDuration(unbalanceResult.[[Years]],
7775 // unbalanceResult.[[Months]], unbalanceResult.[[Weeks]],
7776 // balanceResult.[[Days]], balanceResult.[[Hours]], balanceResult.[[Minutes]],
7777 // balanceResult.[[Seconds]], balanceResult.[[Milliseconds]],
7778 // balanceResult.[[Microseconds]], balanceResult.[[Nanoseconds]], 1, unit,
7779 // "trunc", relativeTo).
7780 DurationRecordWithRemainder round_record;
7781 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7782 isolate, round_record,
7783 RoundDuration(isolate,
7784 {unbalance_result.years, unbalance_result.months,
7785 unbalance_result.weeks, balance_result.value},
7786 1, unit, RoundingMode::kTrunc, relative_to, method_name),
7787 Handle<Object>());
7788 // 16. Let roundResult be roundRecord.[[DurationRecord]].
7789 DurationRecord& round_result = round_record.record;
7790
7791 double whole;
7792 switch (unit) {
7793 // 17. If unit is "year", then
7794 case Unit::kYear:
7795 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Years]].
7796 whole = round_result.years;
7797 break;
7798 // 18. If unit is "month", then
7799 case Unit::kMonth:
7800 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Months]].
7801 whole = round_result.months;
7802 break;
7803 // 19. If unit is "week", then
7804 case Unit::kWeek:
7805 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Weeks]].
7806 whole = round_result.weeks;
7807 break;
7808 // 20. If unit is "day", then
7809 case Unit::kDay:
7810 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Days]].
7811 whole = round_result.time_duration.days;
7812 break;
7813 // 21. If unit is "hour", then
7814 case Unit::kHour:
7815 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Hours]].
7816 whole = round_result.time_duration.hours;
7817 break;
7818 // 22. If unit is "minute", then
7819 case Unit::kMinute:
7820 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Minutes]].
7821 whole = round_result.time_duration.minutes;
7822 break;
7823 // 23. If unit is "second", then
7824 case Unit::kSecond:
7825 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Seconds]].
7826 whole = round_result.time_duration.seconds;
7827 break;
7828 // 24. If unit is "millisecond", then
7829 case Unit::kMillisecond:
7830 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Milliseconds]].
7831 whole = round_result.time_duration.milliseconds;
7832 break;
7833 // 25. If unit is "microsecond", then
7834 case Unit::kMicrosecond:
7835 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Microseconds]].
7836 whole = round_result.time_duration.microseconds;
7837 break;
7838 // 26. If unit is "naoosecond", then
7839 case Unit::kNanosecond:
7840 // a. Let whole be roundResult.[[Nanoseconds]].
7841 whole = round_result.time_duration.nanoseconds;
7842 break;
7843 default:
7844 UNREACHABLE();
7845 }
7846 // 27. Return 𝔽(whole + roundRecord.[[Remainder]]).
7847 return factory->NewNumber(whole + round_record.remainder);
7848}

7850namespace temporal {
7851// #sec-temporal-topartialduration
7852Maybe<DurationRecord> ToPartialDuration(
7853 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> temporal_duration_like_obj,
7854 const DurationRecord& input) {
7855 // 1. If Type(temporalDurationLike) is not Object, then
7856 if (!IsJSReceiver(*temporal_duration_like_obj)) {
7857 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
7858 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
7859 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
7860 }
7861 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_duration_like =
7862 Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_duration_like_obj);
7863
7864 // 2. Let result be a new partial Duration Record with each field set to
7865 // undefined.
7866 DurationRecord result = input;
7867
7868 // 3. Let any be false.
7869 bool any = false;
7870
7871 // Table 8: Duration Record Fields
7872 // #table-temporal-duration-record-fields
7873 // 4. For each row of Table 8, except the header row, in table order, do
7874 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7875 isolate, any,
7876 IterateDurationRecordFieldsTable(
7877 isolate, temporal_duration_like,
7878 [](Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_duration_like,
7879 DirectHandle<String> prop, double* field) -> Maybe<bool> {
7880 bool not_undefined = false;
7881 // a. Let prop be the Property value of the current row.
7882 Handle<Object> val;
7883 // b. Let val be ? Get(temporalDurationLike, prop).
7884 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7885 isolate, val,
7886 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, temporal_duration_like, prop),
7887 Nothing<bool>());
7888 // c. If val is not undefined, then
7889 if (!IsUndefined(*val)) {
7890 // i. Set any to true.
7891 not_undefined = true;
7892 // ii. Let val be 𝔽(? ToIntegerWithoutRounding(val)).
7893 // iii. Set result's field whose name is the Field Name value of
7894 // the current row to val.
7895 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7896 isolate, *field, ToIntegerWithoutRounding(isolate, val),
7897 Nothing<bool>());
7898 }
7899 return Just(not_undefined);
7900 },
7901 &result),
7902 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
7903
7904 // 5. If any is false, then
7905 if (!any) {
7906 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
7907 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
7908 Nothing<DurationRecord>());
7909 }
7910 // 6. Return result.
7911 return Just(result);
7912}

7917MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> JSTemporalDuration::With(
7918 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> duration,
7919 DirectHandle<Object> temporal_duration_like) {
7920 DurationRecord partial;
7921 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7922 isolate, partial,
7923 temporal::ToPartialDuration(
7924 isolate, temporal_duration_like,
7925 {Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),
7926 Object::NumberValue(duration->months()),
7927 Object::NumberValue(duration->weeks()),
7928 {Object::NumberValue(duration->days()),
7929 Object::NumberValue(duration->hours()),
7930 Object::NumberValue(duration->minutes()),
7931 Object::NumberValue(duration->seconds()),
7932 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
7933 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
7934 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds())}}),
7935 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
7936
7937 // 24. Return ? CreateTemporalDuration(years, months, weeks, days, hours,
7938 // minutes, seconds, milliseconds, microseconds, nanoseconds).
7939 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, partial);
7940}

7967MaybeHandle<Oddball> JSTemporalDuration::Blank(
7968 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> duration) {

7970 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(duration,
7971 // [[InitializedTemporalDuration]]).

7973 // duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], duration.[[Hours]],
7974 // duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]], duration.[[Milliseconds]],
7975 // duration.[[Microseconds]], duration.[[Nanoseconds]]).

7979 DurationRecord::Sign({Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),

7986 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
7987 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
7988 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds())}});
7989 return isolate->factory()->ToBoolean(sign == 0);
7990}
