9539// #sec-temporal-toisodayofyear
9540int32_t ToISODayOfYear(Isolate* isolate, const DateRecord& date) {
9541 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
9542 // 1. Assert: IsValidISODate(year, month, day) is *true*.
9543 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, date));
9544 // 2. Let _epochDays_ be MakeDay(𝔽(year), 𝔽(month - 1), 𝔽(day)).
9545 // 3. Assert: _epochDays_ is finite.
9546 // 4. Return ℝ(DayWithinYear(MakeDate(_epochDays_, *+0*<sub>𝔽</sub>))) + 1.
9547 // Note: In ISO 8601, Jan: month=1, Dec: month=12,
9548 // In DateCache API, Jan: month=0, Dec: month=11 so we need to - 1 for month.
9549 return date.day +
9550 isolate->date_cache()->DaysFromYearMonth(date.year, date.month - 1) -
9551 isolate->date_cache()->DaysFromYearMonth(date.year, 0);
9552}
9553
9554bool IsPlainDatePlainDateTimeOrPlainYearMonth(
9555 DirectHandle<Object> temporal_date_like) {
9556 return IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*temporal_date_like) ||
9557 IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*temporal_date_like) ||
9558 IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*temporal_date_like);
9559}
9560
9561// #sec-temporal-toisodayofweek
9562int32_t ToISODayOfWeek(Isolate* isolate, const DateRecord& date) {
9563 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
9564
9565 // 1. Assert: IsValidISODate(year, month, day) is *true*.
9566 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, date));
9567 // 2. Let _epochDays_ be MakeDay(𝔽(year), 𝔽(month - 1), 𝔽(day)).
9568 // Note: "- 1" after "date.day" came from the MakeyDay AO in
9569 // "9. Return Day(t) + dt - 1𝔽."
9570 int32_t epoch_days =
9571 isolate->date_cache()->DaysFromYearMonth(date.year, date.month - 1) +
9572 date.day - 1;
9573 // 3. Assert: _epochDays_ is finite.
9574 // 4. Let _dayOfWeek_ be WeekDay(MakeDate(_epochDays_, *+0*<sub>𝔽</sub>)).
9575 int32_t weekday = isolate->date_cache()->Weekday(epoch_days);
9576 // 5. If _dayOfWeek_ = *+0*<sub>𝔽</sub>, return 7.
9577
9578 // Note: In ISO 8601, Jan: month=1, Dec: month=12.
9579 // In DateCache API, Jan: month=0, Dec: month=11 so we need to - 1 for month.
9580 // Weekday() expect "the number of days since the epoch" as input and the
9581 // value of day is 1-based so we need to minus 1 to calculate "the number of
9582 // days" because the number of days on the epoch (1970/1/1) should be 0,
9583 // not 1
9584 // Note: In ISO 8601, Sun: weekday=7 Mon: weekday=1
9585 // In DateCache API, Sun: weekday=0 Mon: weekday=1
9586 // 6. Return ℝ(_dayOfWeek_).
9587 return weekday == 0 ? 7 : weekday;
9588}
9589
9590// #sec-temporal-regulateisodate
9591Maybe<DateRecord> RegulateISODate(Isolate* isolate, ShowOverflow overflow,
9592 const DateRecord& date) {
9593 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
9594
9595 // 1. Assert: year, month, and day are integers.
9596 // 2. Assert: overflow is either "constrain" or "reject".
9597 switch (overflow) {
9598 // 3. If overflow is "reject", then
9599 case ShowOverflow::kReject:
9600 // a. If ! IsValidISODate(year, month, day) is false, throw a RangeError
9601 // exception.
9602 if (!IsValidISODate(isolate, date)) {
9603 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
9604 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
9605 Nothing<DateRecord>());
9606 }
9607 // b. Return the Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month, [[Day]]: day
9608 // }.
9609 return Just(date);
9610 // 4. If overflow is "constrain", then
9611 case ShowOverflow::kConstrain:
9612 DateRecord result(date);
9613 // a. Set month to ! ConstrainToRange(month, 1, 12).
9614 result.month = std::max(std::min(result.month, 12), 1);
9615 // b. Set day to ! ConstrainToRange(day, 1, ! ISODaysInMonth(year,
9616 // month)).
9617 result.day =
9618 std::max(std::min(result.day,
9619 ISODaysInMonth(isolate, result.year, result.month)),
9620 1);
9621 // c. Return the Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month, [[Day]]: day
9622 // }.
9623 return Just(result);
9624 }
9625}
9626
9627// #sec-temporal-regulateisoyearmonth
9628Maybe<int32_t> RegulateISOYearMonth(Isolate* isolate, ShowOverflow overflow,
9629 int32_t month) {
9630 // 1. Assert: year and month are integers.
9631 // 2. Assert: overflow is either "constrain" or "reject".
9632 switch (overflow) {
9633 // 3. If overflow is "constrain", then
9634 case ShowOverflow::kConstrain:
9635 // a. Return ! ConstrainISOYearMonth(year, month).
9636 return Just(std::max(std::min(month, 12), 1));
9637 // 4. If overflow is "reject", then
9638 case ShowOverflow::kReject:
9639 // a. If ! IsValidISOMonth(month) is false, throw a RangeError exception.
9640 if (month < 1 || 12 < month) {
9641 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
9642 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
9643 Nothing<int32_t>());
9644 }
9645 // b. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: month }.
9646 return Just(month);
9647 default:
9648 UNREACHABLE();
9649 }
9650}
9651
9652// #sec-temporal-resolveisomonth
9653Maybe<int32_t> ResolveISOMonth(Isolate* isolate,
9654 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields) {
9655 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
9656 // 1. Let month be ! Get(fields, "month").
9657 DirectHandle<Object> month_obj =
9658 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->month_string())
9659 .ToHandleChecked();
9660 // 2. Let monthCode be ! Get(fields, "monthCode").
9661 Handle<Object> month_code_obj =
9662 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->monthCode_string())
9663 .ToHandleChecked();
9664 // 3. If monthCode is undefined, then
9665 if (IsUndefined(*month_code_obj, isolate)) {
9666 // a. If month is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
9667 if (IsUndefined(*month_obj, isolate)) {
9668 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
9669 isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(), Nothing<int32_t>());
9670 }
9671 // b. Return month.
9672 // Note: In Temporal spec, "month" in fields is always converted by
9673 // ToPositiveInteger inside PrepareTemporalFields before calling
9674 // ResolveISOMonth. Therefore the month_obj is always a positive integer.
9675 DCHECK(IsSmi(*month_obj) || IsHeapNumber(*month_obj));
9676 return Just(FastD2I(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*month_obj))));
9677 }
9678 // 4. Assert: Type(monthCode) is String.
9679 DCHECK(IsString(*month_code_obj));
9680 DirectHandle<String> month_code;
9681 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, month_code,
9682 Object::ToString(isolate, month_code_obj),
9683 Nothing<int32_t>());
9684 // 5. Let monthLength be the length of monthCode.
9685 // 6. If monthLength is not 3, throw a RangeError exception.
9686 if (month_code->length() != 3) {
9687 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
9688 isolate,
9689 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyValueOutOfRange,
9690 factory->monthCode_string()),
9691 Nothing<int32_t>());
9692 }
9693 // 7. Let numberPart be the substring of monthCode from 1.
9694 // 8. Set numberPart to ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(numberPart).
9695 // 9. If numberPart < 1 or numberPart > 12, throw a RangeError exception.
9696 uint16_t m0 = month_code->Get(0);
9697 uint16_t m1 = month_code->Get(1);
9698 uint16_t m2 = month_code->Get(2);
9699 if (!((m0 == 'M') && ((m1 == '0' && '1' <= m2 && m2 <= '9') ||
9700 (m1 == '1' && '0' <= m2 && m2 <= '2')))) {
9701 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
9702 isolate,
9703 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyValueOutOfRange,
9704 factory->monthCode_string()),
9705 Nothing<int32_t>());
9706 }
9707 int32_t number_part =
9708 10 * static_cast<int32_t>(m1 - '0') + static_cast<int32_t>(m2 - '0');
9709 // 10. If month is not undefined, and month ≠ numberPart, then
9710 // 11. If ! SameValueNonNumeric(monthCode, ! BuildISOMonthCode(numberPart)) is
9711 // false, then a. Throw a RangeError exception.
9712 // Note: In Temporal spec, "month" in fields is always converted by
9713 // ToPositiveInteger inside PrepareTemporalFields before calling
9714 // ResolveISOMonth. Therefore the month_obj is always a positive integer.
9715 if (!IsUndefined(*month_obj) &&
9716 FastD2I(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*month_obj))) != number_part) {
9717 // a. Throw a RangeError exception.
9718 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
9719 isolate,
9720 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyValueOutOfRange,
9721 factory->month_string()),
9722 Nothing<int32_t>());
9723 }
9724
9725 // 12. Return numberPart.
9726 return Just(number_part);
9727}
9728
9729// #sec-temporal-isodatefromfields
9730Maybe<DateRecord> ISODateFromFields(Isolate* isolate,
9731 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,
9732 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options,
9733 const char* method_name) {
9734 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
9735
9736 // 1. Assert: Type(fields) is Object.
9737 // 2. Set fields to ? PrepareTemporalFields(fields, « "day", "month",
9738 // "monthCode", "year" », «"year", "day"»).
9739 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names =
9740 DayMonthMonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);
9741 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
9742 isolate, fields,
9743 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, fields, field_names,
9744 RequiredFields::kYearAndDay),
9745 Nothing<DateRecord>());
9746 // 3. Let overflow be ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
9747 ShowOverflow overflow;
9748 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
9749 isolate, overflow, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
9750 Nothing<DateRecord>());
9751
9752 // 4. Let year be ! Get(fields, "year").
9753 DirectHandle<Object> year_obj =
9754 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->year_string())
9755 .ToHandleChecked();
9756 // 5. Assert: Type(year) is Number.
9757 // Note: "year" in fields is always converted by
9758 // ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity inside the PrepareTemporalFields above.
9759 // Therefore the year_obj is always an integer.
9760 DCHECK(IsSmi(*year_obj) || IsHeapNumber(*year_obj));
9761
9762 // 6. Let month be ? ResolveISOMonth(fields).
9763 int32_t month;
9764 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
9765 isolate, month, ResolveISOMonth(isolate, fields), Nothing<DateRecord>());
9766
9767 // 7. Let day be ! Get(fields, "day").
9768 DirectHandle<Object> day_obj =
9769 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->day_string())
9770 .ToHandleChecked();
9771 // 8. Assert: Type(day) is Number.
9772 // Note: "day" in fields is always converted by
9773 // ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity inside the PrepareTemporalFields above.
9774 // Therefore the day_obj is always an integer.
9775 DCHECK(IsSmi(*day_obj) || IsHeapNumber(*day_obj));
9776 // 9. Return ? RegulateISODate(year, month, day, overflow).
9777 return RegulateISODate(
9778 isolate, overflow,
9779 {FastD2I(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*year_obj))), month,
9780 FastD2I(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*day_obj)))});
9781}
9782
9783// #sec-temporal-addisodate
9784Maybe<DateRecord> AddISODate(Isolate* isolate, const DateRecord& date,
9785 const DateDurationRecord& duration,
9786 ShowOverflow overflow) {
9787 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
9788
9789 // 1. Assert: year, month, day, years, months, weeks, and days are integers.
9790 // 2. Assert: overflow is either "constrain" or "reject".
9791 DCHECK(overflow == ShowOverflow::kConstrain ||
9792 overflow == ShowOverflow::kReject);
9793 // 3. Let intermediate be ! BalanceISOYearMonth(year + years, month + months).
9794 DateRecord intermediate = date;
9795 intermediate.year += static_cast<int32_t>(duration.years);
9796 intermediate.month += static_cast<int32_t>(duration.months);
9797 BalanceISOYearMonth(isolate, &intermediate.year, &intermediate.month);
9798 // 4. Let intermediate be ? RegulateISODate(intermediate.[[Year]],
9799 // intermediate.[[Month]], day, overflow).
9800 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
9801 isolate, intermediate, RegulateISODate(isolate, overflow, intermediate),
9802 Nothing<DateRecord>());
9803
9804 // 5. Set days to days + 7 × weeks.
9805 // 6. Let d be intermediate.[[Day]] + days.
9806 intermediate.day += duration.days + 7 * duration.weeks;
9807 // 7. Return BalanceISODate(intermediate.[[Year]], intermediate.[[Month]], d).
9808 return Just(BalanceISODate(isolate, intermediate));
9809}
9810
9811// #sec-temporal-differenceisodate
9812Maybe<DateDurationRecord> DifferenceISODate(Isolate* isolate,
9813 const DateRecord& date1,
9814 const DateRecord& date2,
9815 Unit largest_unit,
9816 const char* method_name) {
9817 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
9818
9819 // 1. Assert: largestUnit is one of "year", "month", "week", or "day".
9820 DCHECK(largest_unit == Unit::kYear || largest_unit == Unit::kMonth ||
9821 largest_unit == Unit::kWeek || largest_unit == Unit::kDay);
9822 // 2. If largestUnit is "year" or "month", then
9823 switch (largest_unit) {
9824 case Unit::kYear:
9825 case Unit::kMonth: {
9826 // a. Let sign be -(! CompareISODate(y1, m1, d1, y2, m2, d2)).
9827 int32_t sign = -CompareISODate(date1, date2);
9828 // b. If sign is 0, return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(0, 0, 0, 0).
9829 if (sign == 0) {
9830 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, 0, 0, 0, 0);
9831 }
9832
9833 // c. Let start be the new Record { [[Year]]: y1, [[Month]]: m1, [[Day]]:
9834 // d1
9835 // }.
9836 DateRecord start = date1;
9837 // d. Let end be the new Record { [[Year]]: y2, [[Month]]: m2, [[Day]]:
9838 // d2 }.
9839 DateRecord end = date2;
9840 // e. Let years be end.[[Year]] − start.[[Year]].
9841 double years = end.year - start.year;
9842 // f. Let mid be ! AddISODate(y1, m1, d1, years, 0, 0, 0, "constrain").
9843 DateRecord mid;
9844 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
9845 isolate, mid,
9846 AddISODate(isolate, date1, {years, 0, 0, 0},
9847 ShowOverflow::kConstrain),
9848 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
9849
9850 // g. Let midSign be -(! CompareISODate(mid.[[Year]], mid.[[Month]],
9851 // mid.[[Day]], y2, m2, d2)).
9852 int32_t mid_sign = -CompareISODate(mid, date2);
9853
9854 // h. If midSign is 0, then
9855 if (mid_sign == 0) {
9856 // i. If largestUnit is "year", return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(years,
9857 // 0, 0, 0).
9858 if (largest_unit == Unit::kYear) {
9859 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, years, 0, 0, 0);
9860 }
9861 // ii. Return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(0, years × 12, 0, 0).
9862 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, 0, years * 12, 0, 0);
9863 }
9864 // i. Let months be end.[[Month]] − start.[[Month]].
9865 double months = end.month - start.month;
9866 // j. If midSign is not equal to sign, then
9867 if (mid_sign != sign) {
9868 // i. Set years to years - sign.
9869 years -= sign;
9870 // ii. Set months to months + sign × 12.
9871 months += sign * 12;
9872 }
9873 // k. Set mid be ! AddISODate(y1, m1, d1, years, months, 0, 0,
9874 // "constrain").
9875 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
9876 isolate, mid,
9877 AddISODate(isolate, date1, {years, months, 0, 0},
9878 ShowOverflow::kConstrain),
9879 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
9880 // l. Let midSign be -(! CompareISODate(mid.[[Year]], mid.[[Month]],
9881 // mid.[[Day]], y2, m2, d2)).
9882 mid_sign = -CompareISODate(mid, date2);
9883 // m. If midSign is 0, then
9884 if (mid_sign == 0) {
9885 // 1. i. If largestUnit is "year", return !
9886 // CreateDateDurationRecord(years, months, 0, 0).
9887 if (largest_unit == Unit::kYear) {
9888 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, years, months, 0, 0);
9889 }
9890 // ii. Return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(0, months + years × 12, 0, 0).
9891 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, 0, months + years * 12, 0,
9892 0);
9893 }
9894 // n. If midSign is not equal to sign, then
9895 if (mid_sign != sign) {
9896 // i. Set months to months - sign.
9897 months -= sign;
9898 // ii. If months is equal to -sign, then
9899 if (months == -sign) {
9900 // 1. Set years to years - sign.
9901 years -= sign;
9902 // 2. Set months to 11 × sign.
9903 months = 11 * sign;
9904 }
9905 // iii. Set mid be ! AddISODate(y1, m1, d1, years, months, 0, 0,
9906 // "constrain").
9907 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
9908 isolate, mid,
9909 AddISODate(isolate, date1, {years, months, 0, 0},
9910 ShowOverflow::kConstrain),
9911 Nothing<DateDurationRecord>());
9912 // iv. Let midSign be -(! CompareISODate(mid.[[Year]], mid.[[Month]],
9913 // mid.[[Day]], y2, m2, d2)).
9914 mid_sign = -CompareISODate(mid, date2);
9915 }
9916 // o. Let days be 0.
9917 double days = 0;
9918 // p. If mid.[[Month]] = end.[[Month]], then
9919 if (mid.month == end.month) {
9920 // i. Assert: mid.[[Year]] = end.[[Year]].
9921 DCHECK_EQ(mid.year, end.year);
9922 // ii. Set days to end.[[Day]] - mid.[[Day]].
9923 days = end.day - mid.day;
9924 } else if (sign < 0) {
9925 // q. Else if sign < 0, set days to -mid.[[Day]] - (!
9926 // ISODaysInMonth(end.[[Year]], end.[[Month]]) - end.[[Day]]).
9927 days =
9928 -mid.day - (ISODaysInMonth(isolate, end.year, end.month) - end.day);
9929 } else {
9930 // r. Else, set days to end.[[Day]] + (! ISODaysInMonth(mid.[[Year]],
9931 // mid.[[Month]]) - mid.[[Day]]).
9932 days =
9933 end.day + (ISODaysInMonth(isolate, mid.year, mid.month) - mid.day);
9934 }
9935 // s. If largestUnit is "month", then
9936 if (largest_unit == Unit::kMonth) {
9937 // i. Set months to months + years × 12.
9938 months += years * 12;
9939 // ii. Set years to 0.
9940 years = 0;
9941 }
9942 // t. Return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(years, months, 0, days).
9943 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, years, months, 0, days);
9944 }
9945 // 3. If largestUnit is "day" or "week", then
9946 case Unit::kDay:
9947 case Unit::kWeek: {
9948 DateRecord smaller, greater;
9949 // a. If ! CompareISODate(y1, m1, d1, y2, m2, d2) < 0, then
9950 int32_t sign;
9951 if (CompareISODate(date1, date2) < 0) {
9952 // i. Let smaller be the Record { [[Year]]: y1, [[Month]]: m1, [[Day]]:
9953 // d1
9954 // }.
9955 smaller = date1;
9956 // ii. Let greater be the Record { [[Year]]: y2, [[Month]]: m2, [[Day]]:
9957 // d2
9958 // }.
9959 greater = date2;
9960 // iii. Let sign be 1.
9961 sign = 1;
9962 } else {
9963 // b. Else,
9964 // i. Let smaller be the new Record { [[Year]]: y2, [[Month]]: m2,
9965 // [[Day]]: d2 }.
9966 smaller = date2;
9967 // ii. Let greater be the new Record { [[Year]]: y1, [[Month]]: m1,
9968 // [[Day]]: d1 }.
9969 greater = date1;
9970 // iii. Let sign be −1.
9971 sign = -1;
9972 }
9973 // c. Let days be ! ToISODayOfYear(greater.[[Year]], greater.[[Month]],
9974 // greater.[[Day]]) − ! ToISODayOfYear(smaller.[[Year]],
9975 // smaller.[[Month]], smaller.[[Day]]).
9976 int32_t days =
9977 ToISODayOfYear(isolate, greater) - ToISODayOfYear(isolate, smaller);
9978 // d. Let year be smaller.[[Year]].
9979 // e. Repeat, while year < greater.[[Year]],
9980 for (int32_t year = smaller.year; year < greater.year; year++) {
9981 // i. Set days to days + ! ISODaysInYear(year).
9982 // ii. Set year to year + 1.
9983 days += ISODaysInYear(isolate, year);
9984 }
9985 // f. Let weeks be 0.
9986 int32_t weeks = 0;
9987 // g. If largestUnit is "week", then
9988 if (largest_unit == Unit::kWeek) {
9989 // i. Set weeks to floor(days / 7).
9990 weeks = days / 7;
9991 // ii. Set days to days mod 7.
9992 days = days % 7;
9993 }
9994 // h. Return ! CreateDateDurationRecord(0, 0, weeks × sign, days × sign).
9995 return DateDurationRecord::Create(isolate, 0, 0, weeks * sign,
9996 days * sign);
9997 }
9998 default:
9999 UNREACHABLE();
10000 }
10001}
10002
10003// #sec-temporal-isoyearmonthfromfields
10004Maybe<DateRecord> ISOYearMonthFromFields(Isolate* isolate,
10005 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,
10006 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options,
10007 const char* method_name) {
10008 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
10009 // 1. Assert: Type(fields) is Object.
10010 // 2. Set fields to ? PrepareTemporalFields(fields, « "month", "monthCode",
10011 // "year" », «»).
10012 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names = factory->NewFixedArray(3);
10013 field_names->set(0, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).month_string());
10014 field_names->set(1, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).monthCode_string());
10015 field_names->set(2, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).year_string());
10016 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10017 isolate, fields,
10018 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, fields, field_names,
10019 RequiredFields::kNone),
10020 Nothing<DateRecord>());
10021 // 3. Let overflow be ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
10022 ShowOverflow overflow;
10023 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10024 isolate, overflow, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
10025 Nothing<DateRecord>());
10026
10027 // 4. Let year be ! Get(fields, "year").
10028 DirectHandle<Object> year_obj =
10029 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->year_string())
10030 .ToHandleChecked();
10031 // 5. If year is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
10032 if (IsUndefined(*year_obj, isolate)) {
10033 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
10034 Nothing<DateRecord>());
10035 }
10036 DateRecord result;
10037 result.year = FastD2I(floor(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*year_obj))));
10038 // 6. Let month be ? ResolveISOMonth(fields).
10039 int32_t month;
10040 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10041 isolate, month, ResolveISOMonth(isolate, fields), Nothing<DateRecord>());
10042 // 7. Let result be ? RegulateISOYearMonth(year, month, overflow).
10043 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10044 isolate, result.month, RegulateISOYearMonth(isolate, overflow, month),
10045 Nothing<DateRecord>());
10046 // 8. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: result.[[Year]], [[Month]]:
10047 // result.[[Month]], [[ReferenceISODay]]: 1 }.
10048 result.day = 1;
10049 return Just(result);
10050}
10051
10052// #sec-temporal-toisoweekofyear
10053int32_t ToISOWeekOfYear(Isolate* isolate, const DateRecord& date) {
10054 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
10055 // 1. Assert: IsValidISODate(year, month, day) is *true*.
10056 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, date));
10057
10058 // 2. Let wednesday be 3.
10059 constexpr int32_t kWednesday = 3;
10060 // 3. Let thursday_ be 4.
10061 constexpr int32_t kThursday = 4;
10062 // 4. Let friday be 5.
10063 constexpr int32_t kFriday = 5;
10064 // 5. Let saturday be 6.
10065 constexpr int32_t kSaturday = 6;
10066 // 6. Let daysInWeek be 7.
10067 constexpr int32_t kDaysInWeek = 7;
10068 // 7. Let maxWeekNumber be 53.
10069 constexpr int32_t kMaxWeekNumber = 53;
10070 // 8. Let dayOfYear be ToISODayOfYear(year, month, day).
10071 int32_t day_of_year = ToISODayOfYear(isolate, date);
10072 // 9. Let dayOfWeek be ToISODayOfWeek(year, month, day).
10073 int32_t day_of_week = ToISODayOfWeek(isolate, date);
10074 // 10. Let week be floor((dayOfYear + daysInWeek - dayOfWeek + wednesday ) /
10075 // daysInWeek).
10076 int32_t week =
10077 (day_of_year + kDaysInWeek - day_of_week + kWednesday) / kDaysInWeek;
10078 // 11. If week < 1, then
10079 if (week < 1) {
10080 // a. NOTE: This is the last week of the previous year.
10081 // b. Let dayOfJan1st be ToISODayOfWeek(year, 1, 1).
10082 int32_t day_of_jan_1st = ToISODayOfWeek(isolate, {date.year, 1, 1});
10083 // c. If dayOfJan1st is friday, then
10084 if (day_of_jan_1st == kFriday) {
10085 // a. Return maxWeekNumber.
10086 return kMaxWeekNumber;
10087 }
10088 // d. If dayOfJan1st is saturday, and InLeapYear(TimeFromYear(𝔽(year - 1)))
10089 // is *1*<sub>𝔽</sub>, then
10090 if (day_of_jan_1st == kSaturday && IsISOLeapYear(isolate, date.year - 1)) {
10091 // i. Return maxWeekNumber.
10092 return kMaxWeekNumber;
10093 }
10094 // e. Return maxWeekNumber - 1.
10095 return kMaxWeekNumber - 1;
10096 }
10097 // 12. If week is maxWeekNumber, then
10098 if (week == kMaxWeekNumber) {
10099 // a. Let daysInYear be DaysInYear(𝔽(year)).
10100 int32_t days_in_year = ISODaysInYear(isolate, date.year);
10101 // b. Let daysLaterInYear be daysInYear - dayOfYear.
10102 int32_t days_later_in_year = days_in_year - day_of_year;
10103 // c. Let daysAfterThursday be thursday - dayOfWeek.
10104 int32_t days_after_thursday = kThursday - day_of_week;
10105 // d. If daysLaterInYear &lt; daysAfterThursday, then
10106 if (days_later_in_year < days_after_thursday) {
10107 // 1. Return 1.
10108 return 1;
10109 }
10110 }
10111 // 13. Return week.
10112 return week;
10113}
10114
10115} // namespace

10117// #sec-temporal.calendar.prototype.dateadd
10118MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> JSTemporalCalendar::DateAdd(
10119 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> calendar,
10120 Handle<Object> date_obj, Handle<Object> duration_obj,
10121 DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
10122 const char* method_name = "Temporal.Calendar.prototype.dateAdd";
10123 // 1. Let calendar be the this value.
10124 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(calendar,
10125 // [[InitializedTemporalCalendar]]).
10126 // 3. Assert: calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601".
10127 // 4. Set date to ? ToTemporalDate(date).
10128 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> date;
10129 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, date,
10130 ToTemporalDate(isolate, date_obj, method_name));
10131
10132 // 5. Set duration to ? ToTemporalDuration(duration).
10133 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> duration;
10134 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10135 isolate, duration,
10136 temporal::ToTemporalDuration(isolate, duration_obj, method_name));
10137
10138 // 6. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
10139 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
10140 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10141 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
10142
10143 // 7. Let overflow be ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
10144 ShowOverflow overflow;
10145 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10146 isolate, overflow, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
10147 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
10148
10149 // 8. Let balanceResult be ? BalanceDuration(duration.[[Days]],
10150 // duration.[[Hours]], duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]],
10151 // duration.[[Milliseconds]], duration.[[Microseconds]],
10152 // duration.[[Nanoseconds]], "day").
10153 TimeDurationRecord balance_result;
10154 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10155 isolate, balance_result,
10156 BalanceDuration(isolate, Unit::kDay,
10157 {Object::NumberValue(duration->days()),
10158 Object::NumberValue(duration->hours()),
10159 Object::NumberValue(duration->minutes()),
10160 Object::NumberValue(duration->seconds()),
10161 Object::NumberValue(duration->milliseconds()),
10162 Object::NumberValue(duration->microseconds()),
10163 Object::NumberValue(duration->nanoseconds())},
10164 method_name),
10165 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
10166
10167 DateRecord result;
10168 // If calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601", then
10169 if (calendar->calendar_index() == 0) {
10170 // 9. Let result be ? AddISODate(date.[[ISOYear]], date.[[ISOMonth]],
10171 // date.[[ISODay]], duration.[[Years]], duration.[[Months]],
10172 // duration.[[Weeks]], balanceResult.[[Days]], overflow).
10173 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10174 isolate, result,
10175 AddISODate(
10176 isolate, {date->iso_year(), date->iso_month(), date->iso_day()},
10177 {Object::NumberValue(duration->years()),
10178 Object::NumberValue(duration->months()),
10179 Object::NumberValue(duration->weeks()), balance_result.days},
10180 overflow),
10181 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
10182 } else {
10183#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
10184 // TODO(ftang) add code for other calendar.
10185 UNIMPLEMENTED();
10186#else // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
10187 UNREACHABLE();
10188#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
10189 }
10190 // 10. Return ? CreateTemporalDate(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
10191 // result.[[Day]], calendar).
10192 return CreateTemporalDate(isolate, result, calendar);
10193}

10195// #sec-temporal.calendar.prototype.daysinyear
10196MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalCalendar::DaysInYear(
10197 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> calendar,
10198 Handle<Object> temporal_date_like) {
10199 // 1. Let calendar be the this value.
10200 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(calendar,
10201 // [[InitializedTemporalCalendar]]).
10202 // 3. Assert: calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601".
10203 // 4. If Type(temporalDateLike) is not Object or temporalDateLike does not
10204 // have an [[InitializedTemporalDate]], [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]] or
10205 // [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]] internal slot, then
10206 if (!IsPlainDatePlainDateTimeOrPlainYearMonth(temporal_date_like)) {
10207 // a. Set temporalDateLike to ? ToTemporalDate(temporalDateLike).
10208 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10209 isolate, temporal_date_like,
10210 ToTemporalDate(isolate, temporal_date_like,
10211 "Temporal.Calendar.prototype.daysInYear"));
10212 }
10213
10214 // a. Let daysInYear be ! ISODaysInYear(temporalDateLike.[[ISOYear]]).
10215 int32_t year;
10216 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*temporal_date_like)) {
10217 year = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(temporal_date_like)->iso_year();
10218 } else if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*temporal_date_like)) {
10219 year = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(temporal_date_like)->iso_year();
10220 } else {
10221 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*temporal_date_like));
10222 year = Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(temporal_date_like)->iso_year();
10223 }
10224 int32_t days_in_year = ISODaysInYear(isolate, year);
10225 // 6. Return 𝔽(daysInYear).
10226 return handle(Smi::FromInt(days_in_year), isolate);
10227}

10229// #sec-temporal.calendar.prototype.daysinmonth
10230MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalCalendar::DaysInMonth(
10231 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> calendar,
10232 Handle<Object> temporal_date_like) {
10233 // 1 Let calendar be the this value.
10234 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(calendar,
10235 // [[InitializedTemporalCalendar]]).
10236 // 3. Assert: calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601".
10237 // 4. If Type(temporalDateLike) is not Object or temporalDateLike does not
10238 // have an [[InitializedTemporalDate]], [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]] or
10239 // [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]] internal slot, then
10240 if (!IsPlainDatePlainDateTimeOrPlainYearMonth(temporal_date_like)) {
10241 // a. Set temporalDateLike to ? ToTemporalDate(temporalDateLike).
10242 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10243 isolate, temporal_date_like,
10244 ToTemporalDate(isolate, temporal_date_like,
10245 "Temporal.Calendar.prototype.daysInMonth"));
10246 }
10247
10248 // 5. Return 𝔽(! ISODaysInMonth(temporalDateLike.[[ISOYear]],
10249 // temporalDateLike.[[ISOMonth]])).
10250 int32_t year;
10251 int32_t month;
10252 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*temporal_date_like)) {
10253 year = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(temporal_date_like)->iso_year();
10254 month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(temporal_date_like)->iso_month();
10255 } else if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*temporal_date_like)) {
10256 year = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(temporal_date_like)->iso_year();
10257 month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(temporal_date_like)->iso_month();
10258 } else {
10259 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*temporal_date_like));
10260 year = Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(temporal_date_like)->iso_year();
10261 month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(temporal_date_like)->iso_month();
10262 }
10263 return handle(Smi::FromInt(ISODaysInMonth(isolate, year, month)), isolate);
10264}
10265
10266// #sec-temporal.calendar.prototype.year
10267MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalCalendar::Year(
10268 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> calendar,
10269 Handle<Object> temporal_date_like) {
10270 // 1. Let calendar be the this value.
10271 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(calendar,
10272 // [[InitializedTemporalCalendar]]).
10273 // 3. Assert: calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601".
10274 // 4. If Type(temporalDateLike) is not Object or temporalDateLike does not
10275 // have an [[InitializedTemporalDate]], [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]],
10276 // or [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]]
10277 // internal slot, then
10278 if (!IsPlainDatePlainDateTimeOrPlainYearMonth(temporal_date_like)) {
10279 // a. Set temporalDateLike to ? ToTemporalDate(temporalDateLike).
10280 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10281 isolate, temporal_date_like,
10282 ToTemporalDate(isolate, temporal_date_like,

10486// #sec-temporal.calendar.prototype.dateuntil
10487MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> JSTemporalCalendar::DateUntil(
10488 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> calendar,
10489 Handle<Object> one_obj, Handle<Object> two_obj,
10490 DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
10491 const char* method_name = "Temporal.Calendar.prototype.dateUntil";
10492 // 1. Let calendar be the this value.
10493 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(calendar,
10494 // [[InitializedTemporalCalendar]]).
10495 // 3. Assert: calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601".
10496 // 4. Set one to ? ToTemporalDate(one).
10497 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> one;
10498 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, one,
10499 ToTemporalDate(isolate, one_obj, method_name));
10500 // 5. Set two to ? ToTemporalDate(two).
10501 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> two;
10502 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, two,
10503 ToTemporalDate(isolate, two_obj, method_name));
10504 // 6. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
10505 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
10506 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10507 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
10508
10509 // 7. Let largestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(options, "largestUnit", date,
10510 // "auto").
10511 Unit largest_unit;
10512 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10513 isolate, largest_unit,
10514 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, options, "largestUnit", UnitGroup::kDate,
10515 Unit::kAuto, false, method_name),
10516 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
10517 // 8. If largestUnit is "auto", set largestUnit to "day".
10518 if (largest_unit == Unit::kAuto) largest_unit = Unit::kDay;
10519
10520 // 9. Let result be ! DifferenceISODate(one.[[ISOYear]], one.[[ISOMonth]],
10521 // one.[[ISODay]], two.[[ISOYear]], two.[[ISOMonth]], two.[[ISODay]],
10522 // largestUnit).
10523 DateDurationRecord result;
10524 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10525 isolate, result,
10526 DifferenceISODate(isolate,
10527 {one->iso_year(), one->iso_month(), one->iso_day()},
10528 {two->iso_year(), two->iso_month(), two->iso_day()},
10529 largest_unit, method_name),
10530 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
10531
10532 // 10. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(result.[[Years]], result.[[Months]],
10533 // result.[[Weeks]], result.[[Days]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
10534 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {result.years,
10535 result.months,
10536 result.weeks,
10537 {result.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
10538 .ToHandleChecked();
10539}

10577// #sec-temporal.calendar.prototype.monthcode
10578MaybeHandle<String> JSTemporalCalendar::MonthCode(
10579 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> calendar,
10580 Handle<Object> temporal_date_like) {
10581 // 1. Let calendar be the this value.
10582 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(calendar,
10583 // [[InitializedTemporalCalendar]]).
10584 // 3. Assert: calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601".
10585 // 4. If Type(temporalDateLike) is not Object or temporalDateLike does not
10586 // have an [[InitializedTemporalDate]], [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]],
10587 // [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]], or
10588 // [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]] internal slot, then
10589 if (!(IsPlainDatePlainDateTimeOrPlainYearMonth(temporal_date_like) ||
10590 IsJSTemporalPlainMonthDay(*temporal_date_like))) {
10591 // a. Set temporalDateLike to ? ToTemporalDate(temporalDateLike).
10592 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10593 isolate, temporal_date_like,
10594 ToTemporalDate(isolate, temporal_date_like,
10595 "Temporal.Calendar.prototype.monthCode"));
10596 }
10597
10598 // 5. Return ! ISOMonthCode(temporalDateLike).
10599 int32_t month;
10600 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*temporal_date_like)) {
10601 month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(temporal_date_like)->iso_month();
10602 } else if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*temporal_date_like)) {
10603 month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(temporal_date_like)->iso_month();
10604 } else if (IsJSTemporalPlainMonthDay(*temporal_date_like)) {
10605 month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>(temporal_date_like)->iso_month();
10606 } else {
10607 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*temporal_date_like));
10608 month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(temporal_date_like)->iso_month();
10609 }
10610 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
10611 builder.AppendCharacter('M');
10612 if (month < 10) {
10613 builder.AppendCharacter('0');
10614 }
10615 builder.AppendInt(month);
10616
10617 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish(), isolate);
10618}

10801 // 3. Assert: calendar.[[Identifier]] is "iso8601".
10802 // 4. Let temporalDate be ? ToTemporalDate(temporalDateLike).
10803 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> temporal_date;
10804 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10805 isolate, temporal_date,
10806 ToTemporalDate(isolate, temporal_date_like,
10807 "Temporal.Calendar.prototype.weekOfYear"));
10808 // a. Let value be ! ToISOWeekOfYear(temporalDate.[[ISOYear]],
10809 // temporalDate.[[ISOMonth]], temporalDate.[[ISODay]]).
10810 int32_t value = ToISOWeekOfYear(
10811 isolate, {temporal_date->iso_year(), temporal_date->iso_month(),
10812 temporal_date->iso_day()});
10813 return handle(Smi::FromInt(value), isolate);
10814}

10828// #sec-temporal.timezone
10829MaybeHandle<JSTemporalTimeZone> JSTemporalTimeZone::Constructor(
10830 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
10831 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<Object> identifier_obj) {
10832 // 1. If NewTarget is undefined, then
10833 if (IsUndefined(*new_target, isolate)) {
10834 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
10835 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
10836 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kConstructorNotFunction,
10837 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
10838 "Temporal.TimeZone")));
10839 }
10840 // 2. Set identifier to ? ToString(identifier).
10841 Handle<String> identifier;
10842 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, identifier,
10843 Object::ToString(isolate, identifier_obj));
10844 Handle<String> canonical;
10845 // 3. If identifier satisfies the syntax of a TimeZoneNumericUTCOffset
10846 // (see 13.33), then
10847 if (IsValidTimeZoneNumericUTCOffsetString(isolate, identifier)) {
10848 // a. Let offsetNanoseconds be ? ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(identifier).
10849 int64_t offset_nanoseconds;
10850 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
10851 isolate, offset_nanoseconds,
10852 ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(isolate, identifier),
10853 Handle<JSTemporalTimeZone>());
10854
10855 // b. Let canonical be ! FormatTimeZoneOffsetString(offsetNanoseconds).
10856 canonical = FormatTimeZoneOffsetString(isolate, offset_nanoseconds);
10857 } else {
10858 // 4. Else,
10859 // a. If ! IsValidTimeZoneName(identifier) is false, then
10860 if (!IsValidTimeZoneName(isolate, identifier)) {
10861 // i. Throw a RangeError exception.
10862 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidTimeZone,
10863 identifier));
10864 }
10865 // b. Let canonical be ! CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(identifier).
10866 canonical = CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(isolate, identifier);
10867 }
10868 // 5. Return ? CreateTemporalTimeZone(canonical, NewTarget).
10869 return CreateTemporalTimeZone(isolate, target, new_target, canonical);
10870}

10984 Handle<Object> instant_obj, Handle<Object> calendar_like) {

10987 // 1. 1. Let timeZone be the this value.
10988 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(timeZone,
10989 // [[InitializedTemporalTimeZone]]).
10990 // 3. Set instant to ? ToTemporalInstant(instant).
10991 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant;
10992 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
10993 isolate, instant, ToTemporalInstant(isolate, instant_obj, method_name));

11006// template for shared code of Temporal.TimeZone.prototype.getNextTransition and
11007// Temporal.TimeZone.prototype.getPreviousTransition
11008template <DirectHandle<Object> (*iana_func)(Isolate*, DirectHandle<BigInt>,
11009 int32_t)>
11010MaybeHandle<Object> GetTransition(Isolate* isolate,
11011 DirectHandle<JSTemporalTimeZone> time_zone,
11012 Handle<Object> starting_point_obj,
11013 const char* method_name) {
11014 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
11015 // 1. Let timeZone be the this value.
11016 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(timeZone,
11017 // [[InitializedTemporalTimeZone]]).
11018 // 3. Set startingPoint to ? ToTemporalInstant(startingPoint).
11019 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> starting_point;
11020 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11021 isolate, starting_point,
11022 ToTemporalInstant(isolate, starting_point_obj, method_name));
11023 // 4. If timeZone.[[OffsetNanoseconds]] is not undefined, return null.
11024 if (time_zone->is_offset()) {
11025 return isolate->factory()->null_value();
11026 }
11027 // 5. Let transition be ?
11028 // GetIANATimeZoneNextTransition(startingPoint.[[Nanoseconds]],
11029 // timeZone.[[Identifier]]).
11030 DirectHandle<Object> transition_obj =
11031 iana_func(isolate, direct_handle(starting_point->nanoseconds(), isolate),
11032 time_zone->time_zone_index());
11033 // 6. If transition is null, return null.
11034 if (IsNull(*transition_obj)) {
11035 return isolate->factory()->null_value();
11036 }
11037 DCHECK(IsBigInt(*transition_obj));
11038 DirectHandle<BigInt> transition = Cast<BigInt>(transition_obj);
11039 // 7. Return ! CreateTemporalInstant(transition).
11040 return temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, transition).ToHandleChecked();
11041}

11044MaybeHandle<Object> JSTemporalTimeZone::GetNextTransition(

11048 isolate, time_zone, starting_point_obj,
11049 "Temporal.TimeZone.prototype.getNextTransition");

11051// #sec-temporal.timezone.prototype.getprevioustransition
11052MaybeHandle<Object> JSTemporalTimeZone::GetPreviousTransition(

11057 "Temporal.TimeZone.prototype.getPreviousTransition");

11060// #sec-temporal.timezone.prototype.getpossibleinstantsfor
11061// #sec-temporal-getianatimezoneepochvalue
11062MaybeHandle<JSArray> GetIANATimeZoneEpochValueAsArrayOfInstantForUTC(
11063 Isolate* isolate, const DateTimeRecord& date_time) {
11064 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11065 // 6. Let possibleInstants be a new empty List.
11066 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds =
11067 GetEpochFromISOParts(isolate, date_time);
11068 DirectHandle<FixedArray> fixed_array = factory->NewFixedArray(1);
11069 // 7. For each value epochNanoseconds in possibleEpochNanoseconds, do
11070 // a. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(epochNanoseconds) is false, throw a
11071 // RangeError exception.
11072 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)) {
11073 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
11074 }
11075 // b. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(epochNanoseconds).
11076 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
11077 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)
11078 .ToHandleChecked();
11079 // c. Append instant to possibleInstants.
11080 fixed_array->set(0, *instant);
11081 // 8. Return ! CreateArrayFromList(possibleInstants).
11082 return factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(fixed_array);
11083}
11084
11085#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
11086MaybeHandle<JSArray> GetIANATimeZoneEpochValueAsArrayOfInstant(
11087 Isolate* isolate, int32_t time_zone_index,
11088 const DateTimeRecord& date_time) {
11089 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11090 if (time_zone_index == JSTemporalTimeZone::kUTCTimeZoneIndex) {
11091 return GetIANATimeZoneEpochValueAsArrayOfInstantForUTC(isolate, date_time);
11092 }
11093
11094 // For TimeZone other than UTC, call ICU indirectly from Intl
11095 DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds_in_local_time =
11096 GetEpochFromISOParts(isolate, date_time);
11097
11098 DirectHandleVector<BigInt> possible_offset =
11099 Intl::GetTimeZonePossibleOffsetNanoseconds(isolate, time_zone_index,
11100 nanoseconds_in_local_time);
11101
11102 int32_t array_length = static_cast<int32_t>(possible_offset.size());
11103 DirectHandle<FixedArray> fixed_array = factory->NewFixedArray(array_length);
11104
11105 for (int32_t i = 0; i < array_length; i++) {
11106 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds =
11107 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, nanoseconds_in_local_time, possible_offset[i])
11108 .ToHandleChecked();
11109 // a. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(epochNanoseconds) is false, throw a
11110 // RangeError exception.
11111 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)) {
11112 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
11113 }
11114 // b. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(epochNanoseconds).
11115 Handle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
11116 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)
11117 .ToHandleChecked();
11118 // b. Append instant to possibleInstants.
11119 fixed_array->set(i, *(instant));
11120 }
11121
11122 // 8. Return ! CreateArrayFromList(possibleInstants).
11123 return factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(fixed_array);
11124}
11125
11126#else // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
11127
11128MaybeHandle<JSArray> GetIANATimeZoneEpochValueAsArrayOfInstant(
11129 Isolate* isolate, int32_t time_zone_index,
11130 const DateTimeRecord& date_time) {
11131 DCHECK_EQ(time_zone_index, JSTemporalTimeZone::kUTCTimeZoneIndex);
11132 return GetIANATimeZoneEpochValueAsArrayOfInstantForUTC(isolate, date_time);
11133}
11134#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT

11136// #sec-temporal.timezone.prototype.getpossibleinstantsfor
11137MaybeHandle<JSArray> JSTemporalTimeZone::GetPossibleInstantsFor(
11138 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalTimeZone> time_zone,
11139 Handle<Object> date_time_obj) {
11140 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11141 // 1. Let timeZone be the this value.
11142 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(timeZone,
11143 // [[InitializedTemporalTimezone]]).
11144 // 3. Set dateTime to ? ToTemporalDateTime(dateTime).
11145 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time;
11146 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11147 isolate, date_time,
11148 ToTemporalDateTime(isolate, date_time_obj,
11149 "Temporal.TimeZone.prototype.getPossibleInstantsFor"));
11150 DateTimeRecord date_time_record = {
11151 {date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(), date_time->iso_day()},
11152 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(), date_time->iso_second(),
11153 date_time->iso_millisecond(), date_time->iso_microsecond(),
11154 date_time->iso_nanosecond()}};
11155 // 4. If timeZone.[[OffsetNanoseconds]] is not undefined, then
11156 if (time_zone->is_offset()) {
11157 // a. Let epochNanoseconds be ! GetEpochFromISOParts(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
11158 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
11159 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
11160 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
11161 // dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]]).
11162 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds =
11163 GetEpochFromISOParts(isolate, date_time_record);
11164 // b. Let possibleEpochNanoseconds be « epochNanoseconds -
11165 // ℤ(timeZone.[[OffsetNanoseconds]]) ».
11166 epoch_nanoseconds =
11167 BigInt::Subtract(
11168 isolate, epoch_nanoseconds,
11169 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, time_zone->offset_nanoseconds()))
11170 .ToHandleChecked();
11171
11172 // The following is the step 7 and 8 for the case of step 4 under the if
11173 // block.
11174
11175 // a. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(epochNanoseconds) is false, throw a
11176 // RangeError exception.
11177 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)) {
11178 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
11179 }
11180
11181 // b. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(epochNanoseconds).
11182
11183 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
11184 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)
11185 .ToHandleChecked();
11186 // c. Return ! CreateArrayFromList(« instant »).
11187 DirectHandle<FixedArray> fixed_array = factory->NewFixedArray(1);
11188 fixed_array->set(0, *instant);
11189 return factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(fixed_array);
11190 }
11191
11192 // 5. Let possibleEpochNanoseconds be ?
11193 // GetIANATimeZoneEpochValue(timeZone.[[Identifier]], dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
11194 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
11195 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
11196 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
11197 // dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]]).
11198
11199 // ... Step 5-8 put into GetIANATimeZoneEpochValueAsArrayOfInstant
11200 // 8. Return ! CreateArrayFromList(possibleInstants).
11201 return GetIANATimeZoneEpochValueAsArrayOfInstant(
11202 isolate, time_zone->time_zone_index(), date_time_record);
11203}

11205// #sec-temporal.timezone.prototype.getoffsetnanosecondsfor
11206MaybeHandle<Object> JSTemporalTimeZone::GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(
11207 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalTimeZone> time_zone,
11208 Handle<Object> instant_obj) {
11209 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
11210 // 1. Let timeZone be the this value.
11211 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(timeZone,
11212 // [[InitializedTemporalTimeZone]]).
11213 // 3. Set instant to ? ToTemporalInstant(instant).
11214 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant;
11215 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11216 isolate, instant,
11217 ToTemporalInstant(isolate, instant_obj,
11218 "Temporal.TimeZone.prototype.getOffsetNanosecondsFor"));

11220 // timeZone.[[OffsetNanoseconds]].
11221 if (time_zone->is_offset()) {

11223 time_zone->offset_nanoseconds());

11225 // 5. Return ! GetIANATimeZoneOffsetNanoseconds(instant.[[Nanoseconds]],
11226 // timeZone.[[Identifier]]).

11250// #sec-temporal.timezone.prototype.tostring
11251MaybeHandle<Object> JSTemporalTimeZone::ToString(
11252 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalTimeZone> time_zone,
11253 const char* method_name) {
11254 return time_zone->id(isolate);
11255}
11256
11257int32_t JSTemporalTimeZone::time_zone_index() const {
11258 DCHECK(is_offset() == false);
11259 return offset_milliseconds_or_time_zone_index();
11260}
11261
11262int64_t JSTemporalTimeZone::offset_nanoseconds() const {
11263 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
11264 DCHECK(is_offset());
11265 return static_cast<int64_t>(offset_milliseconds()) * 1000000 +
11266 static_cast<int64_t>(offset_sub_milliseconds());
11267}
11268
11269void JSTemporalTimeZone::set_offset_nanoseconds(int64_t ns) {
11270 this->set_offset_milliseconds(static_cast<int32_t>(ns / 1000000));
11271 this->set_offset_sub_milliseconds(static_cast<int32_t>(ns % 1000000));
11272}
11273
11274MaybeHandle<String> JSTemporalTimeZone::id(Isolate* isolate) const {
11275 if (is_offset()) {
11276 return FormatTimeZoneOffsetString(isolate, offset_nanoseconds());
11277 }
11278#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
11279 std::string id =
11280 Intl::TimeZoneIdFromIndex(offset_milliseconds_or_time_zone_index());
11281 return isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(id.c_str());
11282#else // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
11283 DCHECK_EQ(kUTCTimeZoneIndex, offset_milliseconds_or_time_zone_index());
11284 return isolate->factory()->UTC_string();
11285#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
11286}
11287
11288MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> JSTemporalPlainDate::Constructor(
11289 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
11290 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<Object> iso_year_obj,
11291 Handle<Object> iso_month_obj, Handle<Object> iso_day_obj,
11292 Handle<Object> calendar_like) {
11293 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDate";
11294 // 1. If NewTarget is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
11295 if (IsUndefined(*new_target)) {
11296 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
11297 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kMethodInvokedOnWrongType,
11298 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
11299 method_name)));
11300 }
11301#define TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(name, T) \
11302 int32_t name; \
11303 { \
11304 DirectHandle<Object> number_##name; \
11305 /* x. Let name be ? ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(name). */ \
11306 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, number_##name, \
11307 ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isolate, name##_obj)); \
11308 name = NumberToInt32(*number_##name); \
11309 }
11310
11311 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_year, JSTemporalPlainDate);
11312 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_month, JSTemporalPlainDate);
11313 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_day, JSTemporalPlainDate);
11314
11315 // 8. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendarLike).
11316 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
11317 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11318 isolate, calendar,
11319 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, calendar_like, method_name));
11320
11321 // 9. Return ? CreateTemporalDate(y, m, d, calendar, NewTarget).
11322 return CreateTemporalDate(isolate, target, new_target,
11323 {iso_year, iso_month, iso_day}, calendar);
11324}
11325
11326// #sec-temporal.plaindate.compare
11327MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalPlainDate::Compare(Isolate* isolate,
11328 Handle<Object> one_obj,
11329 Handle<Object> two_obj) {
11330 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDate.compare";
11331 // 1. Set one to ? ToTemporalDate(one).
11332 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> one;
11333 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, one,
11334 ToTemporalDate(isolate, one_obj, method_name));
11335 // 2. Set two to ? ToTemporalDate(two).
11336 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> two;
11337 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, two,
11338 ToTemporalDate(isolate, two_obj, method_name));
11339 // 3. Return 𝔽(! CompareISODate(one.[[ISOYear]], one.[[ISOMonth]],
11340 // one.[[ISODay]], two.[[ISOYear]], two.[[ISOMonth]], two.[[ISODay]])).
11341 return Handle<Smi>(Smi::FromInt(CompareISODate(
11342 {one->iso_year(), one->iso_month(), one->iso_day()},
11343 {two->iso_year(), two->iso_month(), two->iso_day()})),
11344 isolate);
11345}

11347// #sec-temporal.plaindate.prototype.equals
11348MaybeHandle<Oddball> JSTemporalPlainDate::Equals(
11349 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> temporal_date,
11350 Handle<Object> other_obj) {
11351 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11352 // 1. Let temporalDate be the this value.
11353 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalDate,
11354 // [[InitializedTemporalDate]]).
11355 // 3. Set other to ? ToTemporalDate(other).
11356 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> other;
11357 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11358 isolate, other,
11359 ToTemporalDate(isolate, other_obj,
11360 "Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.equals"));
11361 // 4. If temporalDate.[[ISOYear]] ≠ other.[[ISOYear]], return false.
11362 if (temporal_date->iso_year() != other->iso_year()) {
11363 return factory->false_value();
11364 }
11365 // 5. If temporalDate.[[ISOMonth]] ≠ other.[[ISOMonth]], return false.
11366 if (temporal_date->iso_month() != other->iso_month()) {
11367 return factory->false_value();
11368 }
11369 // 6. If temporalDate.[[ISODay]] ≠ other.[[ISODay]], return false.
11370 if (temporal_date->iso_day() != other->iso_day()) {
11371 return factory->false_value();
11372 }
11373 // 7. Return ? CalendarEquals(temporalDate.[[Calendar]], other.[[Calendar]]).
11374 return CalendarEquals(isolate, handle(temporal_date->calendar(), isolate),
11375 handle(other->calendar(), isolate));
11376}

11400// Template for common code shared by
11401// Temporal.PlainDate(Timne)?.prototype.toPlain(YearMonth|MonthDay)
11402// #sec-temporal.plaindate.prototype.toplainmonthday
11403// #sec-temporal.plaindate.prototype.toplainyearmonth
11404// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.prototype.toplainmonthday
11405// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.prototype.toplainyearmonth
11406template <typename T, typename R,
11407 MaybeHandle<R> (*from_fields)(Isolate*, DirectHandle<JSReceiver>,
11408 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>,
11409 DirectHandle<Object>)>
11410MaybeHandle<R> ToPlain(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<T> t,
11411 DirectHandle<String> f1, DirectHandle<String> f2) {
11412 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11413 // 1. Let temporalDate be the this value.
11414 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(t, [[InitializedTemporalDate]]).
11415 // 3. Let calendar be t.[[Calendar]].
11416 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(t->calendar(), isolate);
11417 // 4. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « f1 , f2 »).
11418 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names = factory->NewFixedArray(2);
11419 field_names->set(0, *f1);
11420 field_names->set(1, *f2);
11421 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
11422 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
11423 // 5. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(t, fieldNames, «»).
11424 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
11425 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11426 isolate, fields,
11427 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, t, field_names, RequiredFields::kNone));
11428 // 6. Return ? FromFields(calendar, fields).
11429 return from_fields(isolate, calendar, fields,
11430 isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
11431}

11494// #sec-temporal-rejectobjectwithcalendarortimezone
11495Maybe<bool> RejectObjectWithCalendarOrTimeZone(
11496 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object) {
11497 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
11498
11499 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11500 // 1. Assert: Type(object) is Object.
11501 // 2. If object has an [[InitializedTemporalDate]],
11502 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]], [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]],
11503 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]], [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]], or
11504 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then
11505 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*object) || IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*object) ||
11506 IsJSTemporalPlainMonthDay(*object) || IsJSTemporalPlainTime(*object) ||
11507 IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*object) ||
11508 IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*object)) {
11509 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
11510 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
11511 Nothing<bool>());
11512 }
11513 // 3. Let calendarProperty be ? Get(object, "calendar").
11514 DirectHandle<Object> calendar_property;
11515 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11516 isolate, calendar_property,
11517 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, object, factory->calendar_string()),
11518 Nothing<bool>());
11519 // 4. If calendarProperty is not undefined, then
11520 if (!IsUndefined(*calendar_property)) {
11521 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
11522 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
11523 Nothing<bool>());
11524 }
11525 // 5. Let timeZoneProperty be ? Get(object, "timeZone").
11526 DirectHandle<Object> time_zone_property;
11527 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11528 isolate, time_zone_property,
11529 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, object, factory->timeZone_string()),
11530 Nothing<bool>());
11531 // 6. If timeZoneProperty is not undefined, then
11532 if (!IsUndefined(*time_zone_property)) {
11533 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
11534 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR(),
11535 Nothing<bool>());
11536 }
11537 return Just(true);
11538}

11540// #sec-temporal-calendarmergefields
11541MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> CalendarMergeFields(
11542 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
11543 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields,
11544 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> additional_fields) {
11545 // 1. Let mergeFields be ? GetMethod(calendar, "mergeFields").
11546 DirectHandle<Object> merge_fields;
11547 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11548 isolate, merge_fields,
11549 Object::GetMethod(isolate, calendar,
11550 isolate->factory()->mergeFields_string()));
11551 // 2. If mergeFields is undefined, then
11552 if (IsUndefined(*merge_fields)) {
11553 // a. Return ? DefaultMergeFields(fields, additionalFields).
11554 return DefaultMergeFields(isolate, fields, additional_fields);
11555 }
11556 // 3. Return ? Call(mergeFields, calendar, « fields, additionalFields »).
11557 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {fields, additional_fields};
11558 Handle<Object> result;
11559 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11560 isolate, result,
11561 Execution::Call(isolate, merge_fields, calendar, base::VectorOf(args)));
11562 // 4. If Type(result) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
11563 if (!IsJSReceiver(*result)) {
11564 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
11565 }
11566 return Cast<JSReceiver>(result);
11567}

11569// Common code shared by Temporal.Plain(Date|YearMonth|MonthDay).prototype.with
11570template <typename T, MaybeHandle<T> (*from_fields_func)(
11571 Isolate*, DirectHandle<JSReceiver>,
11572 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>, DirectHandle<Object>)>
11573MaybeHandle<T> PlainDateOrYearMonthOrMonthDayWith(
11574 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<T> temporal,
11575 DirectHandle<Object> temporal_like_obj, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj,
11576 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names, const char* method_name) {
11577 // 1. Let temporalDate be the this value.
11578 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalDate,
11579 // [[InitializedTemporalXXX]]).
11580 // 3. If Type(temporalXXXLike) is not Object, then
11581 if (!IsJSReceiver(*temporal_like_obj)) {
11582 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
11583 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
11584 }
11585 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_like = Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_like_obj);
11586 // 4. Perform ? RejectObjectWithCalendarOrTimeZone(temporalXXXLike).
11587 MAYBE_RETURN(RejectObjectWithCalendarOrTimeZone(isolate, temporal_like),
11588 Handle<T>());
11589
11590 // 5. Let calendar be temporalXXX.[[Calendar]].
11591 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(temporal->calendar(), isolate);
11592
11593 // 6. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, fieldNames).
11594 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
11595 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
11596 // 7. Let partialDate be ? PreparePartialTemporalFields(temporalXXXLike,
11597 // fieldNames).
11598 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> partial_date;
11599 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11600 isolate, partial_date,
11601 PreparePartialTemporalFields(isolate, temporal_like, field_names));
11602 // 8. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
11603 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
11604 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11605 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
11606 // 9. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(temporalXXX, fieldNames, «»).
11607 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
11608 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11609 isolate, fields,
11610 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, temporal, field_names,
11611 RequiredFields::kNone));
11612 // 10. Set fields to ? CalendarMergeFields(calendar, fields, partialDate).
11613 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11614 isolate, fields,
11615 CalendarMergeFields(isolate, calendar, fields, partial_date));
11616 // 11. Set fields to ? PrepareTemporalFields(fields, fieldNames, «»).
11617 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, fields,
11618 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, fields, field_names,
11619 RequiredFields::kNone));
11620 // 12. Return ? XxxFromFields(calendar, fields, options).
11621 return from_fields_func(isolate, calendar, fields, options);
11622}

11641// #sec-temporal.plaindate.prototype.tozoneddatetime
11642MaybeHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> JSTemporalPlainDate::ToZonedDateTime(
11643 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> temporal_date,
11644 Handle<Object> item_obj) {
11645 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.toZonedDateTime";
11646 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11647 // 1. Let temporalDate be the this value.
11648 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalDate,
11649 // [[InitializedTemporalDate]]).
11650 // 3. If Type(item) is Object, then
11651 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone;
11652 Handle<Object> temporal_time_obj;
11653 if (IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
11654 Handle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
11655 // a. Let timeZoneLike be ? Get(item, "timeZone").
11656 Handle<Object> time_zone_like;
11657 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11658 isolate, time_zone_like,
11659 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, item, factory->timeZone_string()));
11660 // b. If timeZoneLike is undefined, then
11661 if (IsUndefined(*time_zone_like)) {
11662 // i. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(item).
11663 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11664 isolate, time_zone,
11665 temporal::ToTemporalTimeZone(isolate, item, method_name));
11666 // ii. Let temporalTime be undefined.
11667 temporal_time_obj = factory->undefined_value();
11668 // c. Else,
11669 } else {
11670 // i. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(timeZoneLike).
11671 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11672 isolate, time_zone,
11673 temporal::ToTemporalTimeZone(isolate, time_zone_like, method_name));
11674 // ii. Let temporalTime be ? Get(item, "plainTime").
11675 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11676 isolate, temporal_time_obj,
11677 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, item, factory->plainTime_string()));
11678 }
11679 // 4. Else,
11680 } else {
11681 // a. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(item).
11682 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11683 isolate, time_zone,
11684 temporal::ToTemporalTimeZone(isolate, item_obj, method_name));
11685 // b. Let temporalTime be undefined.
11686 temporal_time_obj = factory->undefined_value();
11687 }
11688 // 5. If temporalTime is undefined, then
11689 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> temporal_date_time;
11690 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(temporal_date->calendar(), isolate);
11691 if (IsUndefined(*temporal_time_obj)) {
11692 // a. Let temporalDateTime be ?
11693 // CreateTemporalDateTime(temporalDate.[[ISOYear]],
11694 // temporalDate.[[ISOMonth]], temporalDate.[[ISODay]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
11695 // temporalDate.[[Calendar]]).
11696 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11697 isolate, temporal_date_time,
11698 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
11699 isolate,
11700 {{temporal_date->iso_year(), temporal_date->iso_month(),
11701 temporal_date->iso_day()},
11702 {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
11703 calendar));
11704 // 6. Else,
11705 } else {
11706 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time;
11707 // a. Set temporalTime to ? ToTemporalTime(temporalTime).
11708 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11709 isolate, temporal_time,
11710 temporal::ToTemporalTime(isolate, temporal_time_obj, method_name));
11711 // b. Let temporalDateTime be ?
11712 // CreateTemporalDateTime(temporalDate.[[ISOYear]],
11713 // temporalDate.[[ISOMonth]], temporalDate.[[ISODay]],
11714 // temporalTime.[[ISOHour]], temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]],
11715 // temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]], temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]],
11716 // temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]], temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]],
11717 // temporalDate.[[Calendar]]).
11718 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11719 isolate, temporal_date_time,
11720 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
11721 isolate,
11722 {{temporal_date->iso_year(), temporal_date->iso_month(),
11723 temporal_date->iso_day()},
11724 {temporal_time->iso_hour(), temporal_time->iso_minute(),
11725 temporal_time->iso_second(), temporal_time->iso_millisecond(),
11726 temporal_time->iso_microsecond(),
11727 temporal_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
11728 calendar));
11729 }
11730 // 7. Let instant be ? BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(timeZone,
11731 // temporalDateTime, "compatible").
11732 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant;
11733 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11734 isolate, instant,
11735 BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(isolate, time_zone, temporal_date_time,
11736 Disambiguation::kCompatible, method_name));
11737 // 8. Return ? CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(instant.[[Nanoseconds]], timeZone,
11738 // temporalDate.[[Calendar]]).
11739 return CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(
11740 isolate, direct_handle(instant->nanoseconds(), isolate), time_zone,
11741 calendar);
11742}

11800// #sec-temporal-differencetemporalplandate
11801MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> DifferenceTemporalPlainDate(
11802 Isolate* isolate, TimePreposition operation,
11803 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate> temporal_date, Handle<Object> other_obj,
11804 DirectHandle<Object> options, const char* method_name) {
11805 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
11806 // 1. If operation is since, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
11807 double sign = operation == TimePreposition::kSince ? -1 : 1;
11808 // 2. Set other to ? ToTemporalDate(other).
11809 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> other;
11810 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, other,
11811 ToTemporalDate(isolate, other_obj, method_name));
11812 // 3. If ? CalendarEquals(temporalDate.[[Calendar]], other.[[Calendar]]) is
11813 // false, throw a RangeError exception.
11814 bool calendar_equals;
11815 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11816 isolate, calendar_equals,
11817 CalendarEqualsBool(isolate, handle(temporal_date->calendar(), isolate),
11818 handle(other->calendar(), isolate)),
11819 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
11820 if (!calendar_equals) {
11821 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
11822 }
11823
11824 // 4. Let settings be ? GetDifferenceSettings(operation, options, date, « »,
11825 // "day", "day").
11826 DifferenceSettings settings;
11827 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11828 isolate, settings,
11829 GetDifferenceSettings(isolate, operation, options, UnitGroup::kDate,
11830 DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings::kNone,
11831 Unit::kDay, Unit::kDay, method_name),
11832 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
11833 // 5. Let untilOptions be ? MergeLargestUnitOption(settings.[[Options]],
11834 // settings.[[LargestUnit]]).
11835 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> until_options;
11836 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11837 isolate, until_options,
11838 MergeLargestUnitOption(isolate, settings.options, settings.largest_unit),
11839 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
11840 // 6. Let result be ? CalendarDateUntil(temporalDate.[[Calendar]],
11841 // temporalDate, other, untilOptions).
11842 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> result;
11843 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11844 isolate, result,
11845 CalendarDateUntil(isolate,
11846 direct_handle(temporal_date->calendar(), isolate),
11847 temporal_date, other, until_options),
11848 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
11849 // 7. If settings.[[SmallestUnit]] is not "day" or
11850 // settings.[[RoundingIncrement]] ≠ 1, then
11851 if (settings.smallest_unit != Unit::kDay ||
11852 settings.rounding_increment != 1) {
11853 // a. Set result to (? RoundDuration(result.[[Years]], result.[[Months]],
11854 // result.[[Weeks]], result.[[Days]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
11855 // settings.[[RoundingIncrement]], settings.[[SmallestUnit]],
11856 // settings.[[RoundingMode]], temporalDate)).[[DurationRecord]].
11857 DurationRecordWithRemainder round_result;
11858 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11859 isolate, round_result,
11860 RoundDuration(isolate,
11861 {Object::NumberValue(result->years()),
11862 Object::NumberValue(result->months()),
11863 Object::NumberValue(result->weeks()),
11864 {Object::NumberValue(result->days()), 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
11865 settings.rounding_increment, settings.smallest_unit,
11866 settings.rounding_mode, temporal_date, method_name),
11867 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
11868 // 8. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign × result.[[Years]], sign ×
11869 // result.[[Months]], sign × result.[[Weeks]], sign × result.[[Days]], 0, 0,
11870 // 0, 0, 0, 0).
11871 round_result.record.years *= sign;
11872 round_result.record.months *= sign;
11873 round_result.record.weeks *= sign;
11874 round_result.record.time_duration.days *= sign;
11875 round_result.record.time_duration.hours =
11876 round_result.record.time_duration.minutes =
11877 round_result.record.time_duration.seconds =
11878 round_result.record.time_duration.milliseconds =
11879 round_result.record.time_duration.microseconds =
11880 round_result.record.time_duration.nanoseconds = 0;
11881 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, round_result.record)
11882 .ToHandleChecked();
11883 }
11884 // 8. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign × result.[[Years]], sign ×
11885 // result.[[Months]], sign × result.[[Weeks]], sign × result.[[Days]], 0, 0,
11886 // 0, 0, 0, 0).
11887 return CreateTemporalDuration(
11888 isolate,
11889 {sign * Object::NumberValue(result->years()),
11890 sign * Object::NumberValue(result->months()),
11891 sign * Object::NumberValue(result->weeks()),
11892 {sign * Object::NumberValue(result->days()), 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
11893 .ToHandleChecked();
11894}
11895
11896} // namespace

11959// #sec-temporal.plaindate.from
11960MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> JSTemporalPlainDate::From(
11961 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
11962 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDate.from";
11963 // 1. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
11964 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
11965 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
11966 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
11967 // 2. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalDate]]
11968 // internal slot, then
11969 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*item)) {
11970 // a. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
11971 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
11972 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
11973 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate>());
11974 // b. Return ? CreateTemporalDate(item.[[ISOYear]], item.[[ISOMonth]],
11975 // item.[[ISODay]], item.[[Calendar]]).
11976 auto date = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(item);
11977 return CreateTemporalDate(
11978 isolate, {date->iso_year(), date->iso_month(), date->iso_day()},
11979 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(date->calendar(), isolate));
11980 }
11981 // 3. Return ? ToTemporalDate(item, options).
11982 return ToTemporalDate(isolate, item, options, method_name);
11983}
11984
11985#define DEFINE_INT_FIELD(obj, str, field, item) \
11986 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty( \
11987 isolate, obj, factory->str##_string(), \
11988 DirectHandle<Smi>(Smi::FromInt(item->field()), isolate), \
11989 Just(kThrowOnError)) \
11990 .FromJust());
11991
11992// #sec-temporal.plaindate.prototype.getisofields
11993MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> JSTemporalPlainDate::GetISOFields(
11994 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> temporal_date) {
11995 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
11996 // 1. Let temporalDate be the this value.
11997 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalDate,
11998 // [[InitializedTemporalDate]]).
11999 // 3. Let fields be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
12000 Handle<JSObject> fields =
12001 isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function());
12002 // 4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "calendar",
12003 // temporalDate.[[Calendar]]).
12004 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
12005 isolate, fields, factory->calendar_string(),
12006 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(temporal_date->calendar(), isolate),
12007 Just(kThrowOnError))
12008 .FromJust());
12009 // 5. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoDay",
12010 // 𝔽(temporalDate.[[ISODay]])).
12011 // 6. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMonth",
12012 // 𝔽(temporalDate.[[ISOMonth]])).
12013 // 7. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoYear",
12014 // 𝔽(temporalDate.[[ISOYear]])).
12015 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoDay, iso_day, temporal_date)
12016 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMonth, iso_month, temporal_date)
12017 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoYear, iso_year, temporal_date)
12018 // 8. Return fields.
12019 return fields;
12020}

12049MaybeHandle<String> TemporalToString(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<T> temporal,
12050 DirectHandle<Object> options_obj,
12051 const char* method_name) {

12053 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalDate,

12055 // 3. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).

12057 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12058 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
12059 // 4. Let showCalendar be ? ToShowCalendarOption(options).
12060 ShowCalendar show_calendar;
12061 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12062 isolate, show_calendar,
12063 ToShowCalendarOption(isolate, options, method_name), Handle<String>());
12064 // 5. Return ? TemporalDateToString(temporalDate, showCalendar).
12065 return F(isolate, temporal, show_calendar);
12066}

12090// #sec-temporal-createtemporaldatetime
12091MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::Constructor(
12092 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
12093 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<Object> iso_year_obj,
12094 Handle<Object> iso_month_obj, Handle<Object> iso_day_obj,
12095 Handle<Object> hour_obj, Handle<Object> minute_obj,
12096 Handle<Object> second_obj, Handle<Object> millisecond_obj,
12097 Handle<Object> microsecond_obj, Handle<Object> nanosecond_obj,
12098 Handle<Object> calendar_like) {
12099 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDateTime";
12100 // 1. If NewTarget is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
12101 if (IsUndefined(*new_target)) {
12102 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
12103 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kMethodInvokedOnWrongType,
12104 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
12105 method_name)));
12106 }
12107
12108 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_year, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12109 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_month, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12110 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_day, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12111 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(hour, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12112 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(minute, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12113 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(second, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12114 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(millisecond, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12115 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(microsecond, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12116 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(nanosecond, JSTemporalPlainDateTime);
12117
12118 // 20. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendarLike).
12119 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
12120 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12121 isolate, calendar,
12122 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, calendar_like, method_name));
12123
12124 // 21. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(isoYear, isoMonth, isoDay, hour,
12125 // minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond, calendar, NewTarget).
12126 return CreateTemporalDateTime(
12127 isolate, target, new_target,
12128 {{iso_year, iso_month, iso_day},
12129 {hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond}},
12130 calendar);
12131}
