12135// #sec-temporal-interprettemporaldatetimefields
12136Maybe<temporal::DateTimeRecord> InterpretTemporalDateTimeFields(
12137 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar,
12138 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields, DirectHandle<Object> options,
12139 const char* method_name) {
12140 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
12141
12142 // 1. Let timeResult be ? ToTemporalTimeRecord(fields).
12143 TimeRecord time_result;
12144 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12145 isolate, time_result, ToTemporalTimeRecord(isolate, fields, method_name),
12146 Nothing<temporal::DateTimeRecord>());
12147
12148 // 2. Let temporalDate be ? DateFromFields(calendar, fields, options).
12149 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> temporal_date;
12150 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12151 isolate, temporal_date,
12152 DateFromFields(isolate, calendar, fields, options),
12153 Nothing<temporal::DateTimeRecord>());
12154
12155 // 3. Let overflow be ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
12156 ShowOverflow overflow;
12157 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12158 isolate, overflow, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
12159 Nothing<temporal::DateTimeRecord>());
12160
12161 // 4. Let timeResult be ? RegulateTime(timeResult.[[Hour]],
12162 // timeResult.[[Minute]], timeResult.[[Second]], timeResult.[[Millisecond]],
12163 // timeResult.[[Microsecond]], timeResult.[[Nanosecond]], overflow).
12164 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12165 isolate, time_result,
12166 temporal::RegulateTime(isolate, time_result, overflow),
12167 Nothing<temporal::DateTimeRecord>());
12168 // 5. Return the new Record { [[Year]]: temporalDate.[[ISOYear]], [[Month]]:
12169 // temporalDate.[[ISOMonth]], [[Day]]: temporalDate.[[ISODay]], [[Hour]]:
12170 // timeResult.[[Hour]], [[Minute]]: timeResult.[[Minute]], [[Second]]:
12171 // timeResult.[[Second]], [[Millisecond]]: timeResult.[[Millisecond]],
12172 // [[Microsecond]]: timeResult.[[Microsecond]], [[Nanosecond]]:
12173 // timeResult.[[Nanosecond]] }.
12174
12175 temporal::DateTimeRecord result = {
12176 {temporal_date->iso_year(), temporal_date->iso_month(),
12177 temporal_date->iso_day()},
12178 time_result};
12179 return Just(result);
12180}
12181
12182// #sec-temporal-parsetemporaldatetimestring
12183Maybe<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar> ParseTemporalDateTimeString(
12184 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string) {
12185 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
12186 // 1. Assert: Type(isoString) is String.
12187 // 2. If isoString does not satisfy the syntax of a TemporalDateTimeString
12188 // (see 13.33), then
12189 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
12190 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalDateTimeString(isolate, iso_string);
12191 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
12192 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
12193 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
12194 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
12195 Nothing<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar>());
12196 }
12197
12198 // 3. If _isoString_ contains a |UTCDesignator|, then
12199 if (parsed->utc_designator) {
12200 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
12201 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
12202 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
12203 Nothing<DateTimeRecordWithCalendar>());
12204 }
12205
12206 // 3. Let result be ? ParseISODateTime(isoString).
12207 // 4. Return result.
12208 return ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed);
12209}
12210
12211// #sec-temporal-totemporaldatetime
12212MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> ToTemporalDateTime(
12213 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, DirectHandle<Object> options,
12214 const char* method_name) {
12215 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
12216 // 2. Assert: Type(options) is Object or Undefined.
12217 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*options) || IsUndefined(*options));
12218
12219 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
12220 temporal::DateTimeRecord result;
12221 // 2. If Type(item) is Object, then
12222 if (IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
12223 Handle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
12224 // a. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]] internal slot, then
12225 // i. Return item.
12226 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*item)) {
12227 return Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(item);
12228 }
12229 // b. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot,
12230 // then
12231 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item)) {
12232 // i. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
12233 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12234 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
12235 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12236 // ii. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(item.[[Nanoseconds]]).
12237 auto zoned_date_time = Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(item);
12238 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
12239 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(
12240 isolate, direct_handle(zoned_date_time->nanoseconds(), isolate))
12241 .ToHandleChecked();
12242 // iii. Return ?
12243 // temporal::BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(item.[[TimeZone]],
12244 // instant, item.[[Calendar]]).
12245 return temporal::BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(
12246 isolate, direct_handle(zoned_date_time->time_zone(), isolate),
12247 instant, direct_handle(zoned_date_time->calendar(), isolate),
12248 method_name);
12249 }
12250 // c. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDate]] internal slot, then
12251 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*item)) {
12252 // i. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
12253 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12254 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
12255 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12256 // ii. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(item.[[ISOYear]],
12257 // item.[[ISOMonth]], item.[[ISODay]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
12258 // item.[[Calendar]]).
12259 auto date = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(item);
12260 return temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
12261 isolate,
12262 {{date->iso_year(), date->iso_month(), date->iso_day()},
12263 {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
12264 direct_handle(date->calendar(), isolate));
12265 }
12266 // d. Let calendar be ? GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(item).
12267 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12268 isolate, calendar,
12269 GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, item, method_name));
12270 // e. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "day", "hour",
12271 // "microsecond", "millisecond", "minute", "month", "monthCode",
12272 // "nanosecond", "second", "year" »).
12273 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names = All10UnitsInFixedArray(isolate);
12274 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
12275 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
12276 // f. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(item,
12277 // PrepareTemporalFields(item, fieldNames, «»).
12278 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
12279 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, fields,
12280 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, item, field_names,
12281 RequiredFields::kNone));
12282 // g. Let result be ?
12283 // InterpretTemporalDateTimeFields(calendar, fields, options).
12284 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12285 isolate, result,
12286 InterpretTemporalDateTimeFields(isolate, calendar, fields, options,
12287 method_name),
12288 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12289 } else {
12290 // 3. Else,
12291 // a. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
12292 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12293 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
12294 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12295
12296 // b. Let string be ? ToString(item).
12297 Handle<String> string;
12298 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, string,
12299 Object::ToString(isolate, item_obj));
12300 // c. Let result be ? ParseTemporalDateTimeString(string).
12301 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar parsed_result;
12302 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12303 isolate, parsed_result, ParseTemporalDateTimeString(isolate, string),
12304 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12305 result = {parsed_result.date, parsed_result.time};
12306 // d. Assert: ! IsValidISODate(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
12307 // result.[[Day]]) is true.
12308 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, result.date));
12309 // e. Assert: ! IsValidTime(result.[[Hour]],
12310 // result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]],
12311 // result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]]) is true.
12312 DCHECK(IsValidTime(isolate, result.time));
12313 // f. Let calendar
12314 // be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(result.[[Calendar]]).
12315 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12316 isolate, calendar,
12317 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, parsed_result.calendar,
12318 method_name));
12319 }
12320 // 4. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
12321 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
12322 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]],
12323 // calendar).
12324 return temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(isolate, {result.date, result.time},
12325 calendar);
12326}

12328} // namespace

12330// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.from
12331MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::From(
12332 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
12333 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDateTime.from";
12334 // 1. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
12335 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
12336 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12337 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
12338 // 2. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]]
12339 // internal slot, then
12340 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*item)) {
12341 // a. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
12342 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12343 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
12344 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12345 // b. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(item.[[ISYear]], item.[[ISOMonth]],
12346 // item.[[ISODay]], item.[[ISOHour]], item.[[ISOMinute]],
12347 // item.[[ISOSecond]], item.[[ISOMillisecond]], item.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
12348 // item.[[ISONanosecond]], item.[[Calendar]]).
12349 auto date_time = Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(item);
12350 return temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
12351 isolate,
12352 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(), date_time->iso_day()},
12353 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(),
12354 date_time->iso_second(), date_time->iso_millisecond(),
12355 date_time->iso_microsecond(), date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
12356 direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate));
12357 }
12358 // 3. Return ? ToTemporalDateTime(item, options).
12359 return ToTemporalDateTime(isolate, item, options, method_name);
12360}
12361
12362// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.compare
12363MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::Compare(Isolate* isolate,
12364 Handle<Object> one_obj,
12365 Handle<Object> two_obj) {
12366 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDateTime.compare";
12367 // 1. Set one to ? ToTemporalDateTime(one).
12368 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> one;
12369 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, one,
12370 ToTemporalDateTime(isolate, one_obj, method_name));
12371 // 2. Set two to ? ToTemporalDateTime(two).
12372 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> two;
12373 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, two,
12374 ToTemporalDateTime(isolate, two_obj, method_name));
12375 // 3. Return 𝔽(! CompareISODateTime(one.[[ISOYear]], one.[[ISOMonth]],
12376 // one.[[ISODay]], one.[[ISOHour]], one.[[ISOMinute]], one.[[ISOSecond]],
12377 // one.[[ISOMillisecond]], one.[[ISOMicrosecond]], one.[[ISONanosecond]],
12378 // two.[[ISOYear]], two.[[ISOMonth]], two.[[ISODay]], two.[[ISOHour]],
12379 // two.[[ISOMinute]], two.[[ISOSecond]], two.[[ISOMillisecond]],
12380 // two.[[ISOMicrosecond]], two.[[ISONanosecond]])).
12381 return Handle<Smi>(
12382 Smi::FromInt(CompareISODateTime(
12383 {
12384 {one->iso_year(), one->iso_month(), one->iso_day()},
12385 {one->iso_hour(), one->iso_minute(), one->iso_second(),
12386 one->iso_millisecond(), one->iso_microsecond(),
12387 one->iso_nanosecond()},
12388 },
12389 {
12390 {two->iso_year(), two->iso_month(), two->iso_day()},
12391 {two->iso_hour(), two->iso_minute(), two->iso_second(),
12392 two->iso_millisecond(), two->iso_microsecond(),
12393 two->iso_nanosecond()},
12394 })),
12395 isolate);
12396}

12398// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.prototype.equals
12399MaybeHandle<Oddball> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::Equals(
12400 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time,
12401 Handle<Object> other_obj) {
12402 // 1. Let dateTime be the this value.
12403 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(dateTime,
12404 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]]).
12405 // 3. Set other to ? ToTemporalDateTime(other).
12406 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> other;
12407 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12408 isolate, other,
12409 ToTemporalDateTime(isolate, other_obj,
12410 "Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.equals"));
12411 // 4. Let result be ! CompareISODateTime(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
12412 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
12413 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
12414 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
12415 // dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]], other.[[ISOYear]], other.[[ISOMonth]],
12416 // other.[[ISODay]], other.[[ISOHour]], other.[[ISOMinute]],
12417 // other.[[ISOSecond]], other.[[ISOMillisecond]], other.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
12418 // other.[[ISONanosecond]]).
12419 int32_t result = CompareISODateTime(
12420 {
12421 {date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(), date_time->iso_day()},
12422 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(),
12423 date_time->iso_second(), date_time->iso_millisecond(),
12424 date_time->iso_microsecond(), date_time->iso_nanosecond()},
12425 },
12426 {
12427 {other->iso_year(), other->iso_month(), other->iso_day()},
12428 {other->iso_hour(), other->iso_minute(), other->iso_second(),
12429 other->iso_millisecond(), other->iso_microsecond(),
12430 other->iso_nanosecond()},
12431 });
12432 // 5. If result is not 0, return false.
12433 if (result != 0) return isolate->factory()->false_value();
12434 // 6. Return ? CalendarEquals(dateTime.[[Calendar]], other.[[Calendar]]).
12435 return CalendarEquals(isolate, handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate),
12436 handle(other->calendar(), isolate));
12437}

12439// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.prototype.with
12440MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::With(
12441 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time,
12442 DirectHandle<Object> temporal_date_time_like_obj,
12443 DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
12444 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.with";
12445 // 1. Let dateTime be the this value.
12446 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(dateTime,
12447 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]]).
12448 // 3. If Type(temporalDateTimeLike) is not Object, then
12449 if (!IsJSReceiver(*temporal_date_time_like_obj)) {
12450 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
12451 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
12452 }
12453 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> temporal_date_time_like =
12454 Cast<JSReceiver>(temporal_date_time_like_obj);
12455 // 4. Perform ? RejectObjectWithCalendarOrTimeZone(temporalTimeLike).
12456 MAYBE_RETURN(
12457 RejectObjectWithCalendarOrTimeZone(isolate, temporal_date_time_like),
12458 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12459 // 5. Let calendar be dateTime.[[Calendar]].
12460 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(date_time->calendar(), isolate);
12461 // 6. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "day", "hour",
12462 // "microsecond", "millisecond", "minute", "month", "monthCode", "nanosecond",
12463 // "second", "year" »).
12464 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names = All10UnitsInFixedArray(isolate);
12465 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
12466 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
12467
12468 // 7. Let partialDateTime be ?
12469 // PreparePartialTemporalFields(temporalDateTimeLike, fieldNames).
12470 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> partial_date_time;
12471 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12472 isolate, partial_date_time,
12473 PreparePartialTemporalFields(isolate, temporal_date_time_like,
12474 field_names));
12475
12476 // 8. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
12477 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
12478 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12479 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
12480 // 9. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(dateTime, fieldNames, «»).
12481 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
12482 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12483 isolate, fields,
12484 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, date_time, field_names,
12485 RequiredFields::kNone));
12486
12487 // 10. Set fields to ? CalendarMergeFields(calendar, fields, partialDateTime).
12488 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12489 isolate, fields,
12490 CalendarMergeFields(isolate, calendar, fields, partial_date_time));
12491 // 11. Set fields to ? PrepareTemporalFields(fields, fieldNames, «»).
12492 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, fields,
12493 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, fields, field_names,
12494 RequiredFields::kNone));
12495 // 12. Let result be ? InterpretTemporalDateTimeFields(calendar, fields,
12496 // options).
12497 temporal::DateTimeRecord result;
12498 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12499 isolate, result,
12500 InterpretTemporalDateTimeFields(isolate, calendar, fields, options,
12501 method_name),
12502 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12503 // 13. Assert: ! IsValidISODate(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
12504 // result.[[Day]]) is true.
12505 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, result.date));
12506 // 14. Assert: ! IsValidTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
12507 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
12508 // result.[[Nanosecond]]) is true.
12509 DCHECK(IsValidTime(isolate, result.time));
12510 // 15. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
12511 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
12512 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]],
12513 // calendar).
12514 return temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(isolate, {result.date, result.time},
12515 calendar);
12516}

12644namespace {
12645
12646// #sec-temporal-consolidatecalendars
12647MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> ConsolidateCalendars(Isolate* isolate,
12648 Handle<JSReceiver> one,
12649 Handle<JSReceiver> two) {
12650 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
12651 // 1. If one and two are the same Object value, return two.
12652 if (one.is_identical_to(two)) return two;
12653
12654 // 2. Let calendarOne be ? ToString(one).
12655 DirectHandle<String> calendar_one;
12656 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, calendar_one,
12657 Object::ToString(isolate, one));
12658 // 3. Let calendarTwo be ? ToString(two).
12659 DirectHandle<String> calendar_two;
12660 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, calendar_two,
12661 Object::ToString(isolate, two));
12662 // 4. If calendarOne is calendarTwo, return two.
12663 if (String::Equals(isolate, calendar_one, calendar_two)) {
12664 return two;
12665 }
12666 // 5. If calendarOne is "iso8601", return two.
12667 if (String::Equals(isolate, calendar_one, factory->iso8601_string())) {
12668 return two;
12669 }
12670 // 6. If calendarTwo is "iso8601", return one.
12671 if (String::Equals(isolate, calendar_two, factory->iso8601_string())) {
12672 return one;
12673 }
12674 // 7. Throw a RangeError exception.
12675 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
12676}

12698 ConsolidateCalendars(isolate, handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate),

12700 // 5. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(plainDate.[[ISOYear]],

12702 // temporalDateTime.[[ISOMinute]], temporalDateTime.[[ISOSecond]],

12714namespace {
12715MaybeHandle<String> TemporalDateTimeToString(Isolate* isolate,
12716 const DateTimeRecord& date_time,
12717 Handle<JSReceiver> calendar,
12718 Precision precision,
12719 ShowCalendar show_calendar) {
12720 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
12721 // 1. Assert: isoYear, isoMonth, isoDay, hour, minute, second, millisecond,
12722 // microsecond, and nanosecond are integers.
12723 // 2. Let year be ! PadISOYear(isoYear).
12724 PadISOYear(&builder, date_time.date.year);
12725
12726 // 3. Let month be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(isoMonth, 2).
12727 builder.AppendCharacter('-');
12728 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, date_time.date.month, 2);
12729
12730 // 4. Let day be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(isoDay, 2).
12731 builder.AppendCharacter('-');
12732 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, date_time.date.day, 2);
12733 // 5. Let hour be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(hour, 2).
12734 builder.AppendCharacter('T');
12735 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, date_time.time.hour, 2);
12736
12737 // 6. Let minute be ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(minute, 2).
12738 builder.AppendCharacter(':');
12739 ToZeroPaddedDecimalString(&builder, date_time.time.minute, 2);
12740
12741 // 7. Let seconds be ! FormatSecondsStringPart(second, millisecond,
12742 // microsecond, nanosecond, precision).
12743 FormatSecondsStringPart(
12744 &builder, date_time.time.second, date_time.time.millisecond,
12745 date_time.time.microsecond, date_time.time.nanosecond, precision);
12746 // 8. Let calendarString be ? MaybeFormatCalendarAnnotation(calendar,
12747 // showCalendar).
12748 DirectHandle<String> calendar_string;
12749 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12750 isolate, calendar_string,
12751 MaybeFormatCalendarAnnotation(isolate, calendar, show_calendar));
12752
12753 // 9. Return the string-concatenation of year, the code unit 0x002D
12754 // (HYPHEN-MINUS), month, the code unit 0x002D (HYPHEN-MINUS), day, 0x0054
12755 // (LATIN CAPITAL LETTER T), hour, the code unit 0x003A (COLON), minute,
12756 builder.AppendString(calendar_string);
12757 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked(), isolate);
12758}
12759} // namespace

12794namespace {
12795
12796constexpr double kNsPerDay = 8.64e13;
12797
12798DateTimeRecord RoundTime(
12799 Isolate* isolate, const TimeRecord& time, double increment, Unit unit,
12800 RoundingMode rounding_mode,
12801 // 3.a a. If dayLengthNs is not present, set dayLengthNs to nsPerDay.
12802 double day_length_ns = kNsPerDay);
12803
12804// #sec-temporal-roundisodatetime
12805DateTimeRecord RoundISODateTime(
12806 Isolate* isolate, const DateTimeRecord& date_time, double increment,
12807 Unit unit, RoundingMode rounding_mode,
12808 // 3. If dayLength is not present, set dayLength to nsPerDay.
12809 double day_length_ns = kNsPerDay) {
12810 // 1. Assert: year, month, day, hour, minute, second, millisecond,
12811 // microsecond, and nanosecond are integers.
12812 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
12813 // 2. Assert: ISODateTimeWithinLimits(year, month, day, hour, minute, second,
12814 // millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond) is true.
12815 DCHECK(ISODateTimeWithinLimits(isolate, date_time));
12816
12817 // 4. Let roundedTime be ! RoundTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond,
12818 // microsecond, nanosecond, increment, unit, roundingMode, dayLength).
12819 DateTimeRecord rounded_time = RoundTime(isolate, date_time.time, increment,
12820 unit, rounding_mode, day_length_ns);
12821 // 5. Let balanceResult be ! BalanceISODate(year, month, day +
12822 // roundedTime.[[Days]]).
12823 rounded_time.date.year = date_time.date.year;
12824 rounded_time.date.month = date_time.date.month;
12825 rounded_time.date.day += date_time.date.day;
12826 DateRecord balance_result = BalanceISODate(isolate, rounded_time.date);
12827
12828 // 6. Return the Record { [[Year]]: balanceResult.[[Year]], [[Month]]:
12829 // balanceResult.[[Month]], [[Day]]: balanceResult.[[Day]], [[Hour]]:
12830 // roundedTime.[[Hour]], [[Minute]]: roundedTime.[[Minute]], [[Second]]:
12831 // roundedTime.[[Second]], [[Millisecond]]: roundedTime.[[Millisecond]],
12832 // [[Microsecond]]: roundedTime.[[Microsecond]], [[Nanosecond]]:
12833 // roundedTime.[[Nanosecond]] }.
12834 return {balance_result, rounded_time.time};
12835}

12837} // namespace

12839// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.prototype.tostring
12840MaybeHandle<String> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::ToString(
12841 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time,
12842 DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
12843 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.toString";
12844 // 1. Let dateTime be the this value.
12845 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(dateTime,
12846 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]]).
12847 // 3. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
12848 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
12849 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12850 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
12851
12852 // 4. Let precision be ? ToSecondsStringPrecision(options).
12853 StringPrecision precision;
12854 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12855 isolate, precision,
12856 ToSecondsStringPrecision(isolate, options, method_name),
12857 Handle<String>());
12858
12859 // 5. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(options, "trunc").
12860 RoundingMode rounding_mode;
12861 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12862 isolate, rounding_mode,
12863 ToTemporalRoundingMode(isolate, options, RoundingMode::kTrunc,
12864 method_name),
12865 Handle<String>());
12866
12867 // 6. Let showCalendar be ? ToShowCalendarOption(options).
12868 ShowCalendar show_calendar;
12869 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12870 isolate, show_calendar,
12871 ToShowCalendarOption(isolate, options, method_name), Handle<String>());
12872
12873 // 7. Let result be ! RoundISODateTime(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
12874 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
12875 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
12876 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
12877 // dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]], precision.[[Increment]], precision.[[Unit]],
12878 // roundingMode).
12879 DateTimeRecord result = RoundISODateTime(
12880 isolate,
12881 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(), date_time->iso_day()},
12882 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(), date_time->iso_second(),
12883 date_time->iso_millisecond(), date_time->iso_microsecond(),
12884 date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
12885 precision.increment, precision.unit, rounding_mode);
12886 // 8. Return ? TemporalDateTimeToString(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
12887 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
12888 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]],
12889 // dateTime.[[Calendar]], precision.[[Precision]], showCalendar).
12890 return TemporalDateTimeToString(isolate, result,
12891 handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate),
12892 precision.precision, show_calendar);
12893}

12918// #sec-temporal-totemporaldatetimeroundingincrement
12919Maybe<double> ToTemporalDateTimeRoundingIncrement(
12920 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> normalized_option,
12921 Unit smallest_unit) {
12922 Maximum maximum;
12923 // 1. If smallestUnit is "day", then
12924 if (smallest_unit == Unit::kDay) {
12925 // a. Let maximum be 1.
12926 maximum.value = 1;
12927 maximum.defined = true;
12928 // 2. Else,
12929 } else {
12930 // a. Let maximum be !
12931 // MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallestUnit).
12932 maximum = MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallest_unit);
12933 // b. Assert: maximum is not undefined.
12934 DCHECK(maximum.defined);
12935 }
12936 // 3. Return ? ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(normalizedOptions, maximum, false).
12937 return ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(isolate, normalized_option, maximum.value,
12938 maximum.defined, false);
12939}

12943// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.prototype.round
12944MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::Round(
12945 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time,
12946 DirectHandle<Object> round_to_obj) {
12947 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.round";
12948 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
12949 // 1. Let temporalTime be the this value.
12950 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(dateTime,
12951 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]]).
12952 // 3. If roundTo is undefined, then
12953 if (IsUndefined(*round_to_obj)) {
12954 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
12955 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
12956 }
12957
12958 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> round_to;
12959 // 4. If Type(roundTo) is String, then
12960 if (IsString(*round_to_obj)) {
12961 // a. Let paramString be roundTo.
12962 DirectHandle<String> param_string = Cast<String>(round_to_obj);
12963 // b. Set roundTo to ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
12964 round_to = factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
12965 // c. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(roundTo, "smallestUnit",
12966 // paramString).
12967 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, round_to,
12968 factory->smallestUnit_string(),
12969 param_string, Just(kThrowOnError))
12970 .FromJust());
12971 // 5. Else
12972 } else {
12973 // a. Set roundTo to ? GetOptionsObject(roundTo).
12974 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
12975 isolate, round_to,
12976 GetOptionsObject(isolate, round_to_obj, method_name));
12977 }
12978
12979 // 6. Let smallestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(roundTo, "smallestUnit", time,
12980 // required).
12981 Unit smallest_unit;
12982 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12983 isolate, smallest_unit,
12984 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, round_to, "smallestUnit", UnitGroup::kTime,
12985 Unit::kDay, true, method_name),
12986 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12987
12988 // 7. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(roundTo, "halfExpand").
12989 RoundingMode rounding_mode;
12990 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
12991 isolate, rounding_mode,
12992 ToTemporalRoundingMode(isolate, round_to, RoundingMode::kHalfExpand,
12993 method_name),
12994 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
12995
12996 // 8. Let roundingIncrement be ? ToTemporalDateTimeRoundingIncrement(roundTo,
12997 // smallestUnit).
12998 double rounding_increment;
12999 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13000 isolate, rounding_increment,
13001 ToTemporalDateTimeRoundingIncrement(isolate, round_to, smallest_unit),
13002 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
13003
13004 // 9. Let result be ! RoundISODateTime(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
13005 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
13006 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
13007 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
13008 // dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]], roundingIncrement, smallestUnit, roundingMode).
13009 DateTimeRecord result = RoundISODateTime(
13010 isolate,
13011 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(), date_time->iso_day()},
13012 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(), date_time->iso_second(),
13013 date_time->iso_millisecond(), date_time->iso_microsecond(),
13014 date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
13015 rounding_increment, smallest_unit, rounding_mode);
13016
13017 // 10. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
13018 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
13019 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]],
13020 // dateTime.[[Calendar]]).
13021 return temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
13022 isolate, result, direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate));
13023}

13025namespace {
13026
13027MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>
13028AddDurationToOrSubtractDurationFromPlainDateTime(
13029 Isolate* isolate, Arithmetic operation,
13030 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time,
13031 Handle<Object> temporal_duration_like, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj,
13032 const char* method_name) {
13033 // 1. If operation is subtract, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
13034 double sign = operation == Arithmetic::kSubtract ? -1.0 : 1.0;
13035 // 2. Let duration be ? ToTemporalDurationRecord(temporalDurationLike).
13036 DurationRecord duration;
13037 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13038 isolate, duration,
13039 temporal::ToTemporalDurationRecord(isolate, temporal_duration_like,
13040 method_name),
13041 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
13042
13043 TimeDurationRecord& time_duration = duration.time_duration;
13044
13045 // 3. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
13046 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
13047 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13048 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
13049 // 4. Let result be ? AddDateTime(dateTime.[[ISOYear]], dateTime.[[ISOMonth]],
13050 // dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]], dateTime.[[ISOMinute]],
13051 // dateTime.[[ISOSecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]],
13052 // dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]], dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]],
13053 // dateTime.[[Calendar]], duration.[[Years]], duration.[[Months]],
13054 // duration.[[Weeks]], duration.[[Days]], duration.[[Hours]],
13055 // duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]], duration.[[Milliseconds]],
13056 // duration.[[Microseconds]], duration.[[Nanoseconds]], options).
13057 DateTimeRecord result;
13058 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13059 isolate, result,
13060 AddDateTime(isolate,
13061 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(),
13062 date_time->iso_day()},
13063 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(),
13064 date_time->iso_second(), date_time->iso_millisecond(),
13065 date_time->iso_microsecond(), date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
13066 direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate),
13067 {sign * duration.years,
13068 sign * duration.months,
13069 sign * duration.weeks,
13070 {sign * time_duration.days, sign * time_duration.hours,
13071 sign * time_duration.minutes, sign * time_duration.seconds,
13072 sign * time_duration.milliseconds,
13073 sign * time_duration.microseconds,
13074 sign * time_duration.nanoseconds}},
13075 options),
13076 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>());
13077
13078 // 5. Assert: ! IsValidISODate(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
13079 // result.[[Day]]) is true.
13080 DCHECK(IsValidISODate(isolate, result.date));
13081 // 6. Assert: ! IsValidTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
13082 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
13083 // result.[[Nanosecond]]) is true.
13084 DCHECK(IsValidTime(isolate, result.time));
13085 // 7. Return ? CreateTemporalDateTime(result.[[Year]], result.[[Month]],
13086 // result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]], result.[[Second]],
13087 // result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]], result.[[Nanosecond]],
13088 // dateTime.[[Calendar]]).
13089 return temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
13090 isolate, result, direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate));
13091}

13115// #sec-temporal-differencetemporalplaindatetime
13116MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> DifferenceTemporalPlainDateTime(
13117 Isolate* isolate, TimePreposition operation,
13118 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time, Handle<Object> other_obj,
13119 DirectHandle<Object> options, const char* method_name) {
13120 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
13121 // 1. If operation is since, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
13122 double sign = operation == TimePreposition::kSince ? -1 : 1;
13123 // 2. Set other to ? ToTemporalDateTime(other).
13124 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> other;
13125 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13126 isolate, other, ToTemporalDateTime(isolate, other_obj, method_name));
13127 // 3. If ? CalendarEquals(dateTime.[[Calendar]], other.[[Calendar]]) is false,
13128 // throw a RangeError exception.
13129 bool calendar_equals;
13130 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13131 isolate, calendar_equals,
13132 CalendarEqualsBool(isolate, handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate),
13133 handle(other->calendar(), isolate)),
13134 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
13135 if (!calendar_equals) {
13136 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
13137 }
13138 // 4. Let settings be ? GetDifferenceSettings(operation, options, datetime, «
13139 // », "nanosecond", "day").
13140 DifferenceSettings settings;
13141 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13142 isolate, settings,
13143 GetDifferenceSettings(isolate, operation, options, UnitGroup::kDateTime,
13144 DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings::kNone,
13145 Unit::kNanosecond, Unit::kDay, method_name),
13146 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
13147 // 5. Let diff be ? DifferenceISODateTime(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
13148 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[ISOHour]],
13149 // dateTime.[[ISOMinute]], dateTime.[[ISOSecond]],
13150 // dateTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], dateTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
13151 // dateTime.[[ISONanosecond]], other.[[ISOYear]], other.[[ISOMonth]],
13152 // other.[[ISODay]], other.[[ISOHour]], other.[[ISOMinute]],
13153 // other.[[ISOSecond]], other.[[ISOMillisecond]], other.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
13154 // other.[[ISONanosecond]], dateTime.[[Calendar]], settings.[[LargestUnit]],
13155 // settings.[[Options]]).
13156 DurationRecord diff;
13157 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13158 isolate, diff,
13159 DifferenceISODateTime(
13160 isolate,
13161 {{date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(),
13162 date_time->iso_day()},
13163 {date_time->iso_hour(), date_time->iso_minute(),
13164 date_time->iso_second(), date_time->iso_millisecond(),
13165 date_time->iso_microsecond(), date_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
13166 {{other->iso_year(), other->iso_month(), other->iso_day()},
13167 {other->iso_hour(), other->iso_minute(), other->iso_second(),
13168 other->iso_millisecond(), other->iso_microsecond(),
13169 other->iso_nanosecond()}},
13170 direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate), settings.largest_unit,
13171 settings.options, method_name),
13172 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
13173 // 6. Let relativeTo be ! CreateTemporalDate(dateTime.[[ISOYear]],
13174 // dateTime.[[ISOMonth]], dateTime.[[ISODay]], dateTime.[[Calendar]]).
13175 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate> relative_to;
13176 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13177 isolate, relative_to,
13178 CreateTemporalDate(
13179 isolate,
13180 {date_time->iso_year(), date_time->iso_month(), date_time->iso_day()},
13181 direct_handle(date_time->calendar(), isolate)),
13182 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
13183 // 7. Let roundResult be (? RoundDuration(diff.[[Years]], diff.[[Months]],
13184 // diff.[[Weeks]], diff.[[Days]], diff.[[Hours]], diff.[[Minutes]],
13185 // diff.[[Seconds]], diff.[[Milliseconds]], diff.[[Microseconds]],
13186 // diff.[[Nanoseconds]], settings.[[RoundingIncrement]],
13187 // settings.[[SmallestUnit]], settings.[[RoundingMode]],
13188 // relativeTo)).[[DurationRecord]].
13189 DurationRecordWithRemainder round_result;
13190 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13191 isolate, round_result,
13192 RoundDuration(isolate, diff, settings.rounding_increment,
13193 settings.smallest_unit, settings.rounding_mode, relative_to,
13194 method_name),
13195 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
13196 // 8. Let result be ? BalanceDuration(roundResult.[[Days]],
13197 // roundResult.[[Hours]], roundResult.[[Minutes]], roundResult.[[Seconds]],
13198 // roundResult.[[Milliseconds]], roundResult.[[Microseconds]],
13199 // roundResult.[[Nanoseconds]], settings.[[LargestUnit]]).
13200 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13201 isolate, round_result.record.time_duration,
13202 BalanceDuration(isolate, settings.largest_unit,
13203 round_result.record.time_duration, method_name),
13204 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
13205 // 9. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign × roundResult.[[Years]], sign ×
13206 // roundResult.[[Months]], sign × roundResult.[[Weeks]], sign ×
13207 // result.[[Days]], sign × result.[[Hours]], sign × result.[[Minutes]], sign ×
13208 // result.[[Seconds]], sign × result.[[Milliseconds]], sign ×
13209 // result.[[Microseconds]], sign × result.[[Nanoseconds]]).
13210 return CreateTemporalDuration(
13211 isolate, {sign * round_result.record.years,
13212 sign * round_result.record.months,
13213 sign * round_result.record.weeks,
13214 {sign * round_result.record.time_duration.days,
13215 sign * round_result.record.time_duration.hours,
13216 sign * round_result.record.time_duration.minutes,
13217 sign * round_result.record.time_duration.seconds,
13218 sign * round_result.record.time_duration.milliseconds,
13219 sign * round_result.record.time_duration.microseconds,
13220 sign * round_result.record.time_duration.nanoseconds}})
13221 .ToHandleChecked();
13222}

13246// #sec-temporal.plaindatetime.prototype.getisofields
13247MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> JSTemporalPlainDateTime::GetISOFields(
13248 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time) {
13249 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
13250 // 1. Let dateTime be the this value.
13251 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalDateTime,
13252 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]]).
13253 // 3. Let fields be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
13254 Handle<JSObject> fields =
13255 isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function());
13256 // 4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "calendar",
13257 // temporalTime.[[Calendar]]).
13258 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
13259 isolate, fields, factory->calendar_string(),
13260 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(date_time->calendar(), isolate),
13261 Just(kThrowOnError))
13262 .FromJust());
13263 // 5. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoDay",
13264 // 𝔽(dateTime.[[ISODay]])).
13265 // 6. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoHour",
13266 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOHour]])).
13267 // 7. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMicrosecond",
13268 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]])).
13269 // 8. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMillisecond",
13270 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]])).
13271 // 9. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMinute",
13272 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]])).
13273 // 10. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMonth",
13274 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOMonth]])).
13275 // 11. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoNanosecond",
13276 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]])).
13277 // 12. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoSecond",
13278 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]])).
13279 // 13. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoYear",
13280 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOYear]])).
13281 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoDay, iso_day, date_time)
13282 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoHour, iso_hour, date_time)
13283 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMicrosecond, iso_microsecond, date_time)
13284 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMillisecond, iso_millisecond, date_time)
13285 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMinute, iso_minute, date_time)
13286 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMonth, iso_month, date_time)
13287 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoNanosecond, iso_nanosecond, date_time)
13288 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoSecond, iso_second, date_time)
13289 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoYear, iso_year, date_time)
13290 // 14. Return fields.
13291 return fields;
13292}

13324// #sec-temporal.plainmonthday
13325MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> JSTemporalPlainMonthDay::Constructor(
13326 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
13327 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<Object> iso_month_obj,
13328 Handle<Object> iso_day_obj, Handle<Object> calendar_like,
13329 Handle<Object> reference_iso_year_obj) {
13330 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainMonthDay";
13331 // 1. If NewTarget is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
13332 if (IsUndefined(*new_target)) {
13333 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
13334 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kMethodInvokedOnWrongType,
13335 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
13336 method_name)));
13337 }
13338
13339 // 3. Let m be ? ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isoMonth).
13340 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_month, JSTemporalPlainMonthDay);
13341 // 5. Let d be ? ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isoDay).
13342 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_day, JSTemporalPlainMonthDay);
13343 // 7. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendarLike).
13344 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
13345 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13346 isolate, calendar,
13347 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, calendar_like, method_name));
13348
13349 // 2. If referenceISOYear is undefined, then
13350 // a. Set referenceISOYear to 1972𝔽.
13351 // ...
13352 // 8. Let ref be ? ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(referenceISOYear).
13353 int32_t ref = 1972;
13354 if (!IsUndefined(*reference_iso_year_obj)) {
13355 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(reference_iso_year, JSTemporalPlainMonthDay);
13356 ref = reference_iso_year;
13357 }
13358
13359 // 10. Return ? CreateTemporalMonthDay(y, m, calendar, ref, NewTarget).
13360 return CreateTemporalMonthDay(isolate, target, new_target, iso_month, iso_day,
13361 calendar, ref);
13362}
13363
13364namespace {
13365
13366// #sec-temporal-parsetemporalmonthdaystring
13367Maybe<DateRecordWithCalendar> ParseTemporalMonthDayString(
13368 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string) {
13369 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
13370
13371 // 1. Assert: Type(isoString) is String.
13372 // 2. If isoString does not satisfy the syntax of a TemporalMonthDayString
13373 // (see 13.33), then
13374 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
13375 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalMonthDayString(isolate, iso_string);
13376 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
13377 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
13378 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
13379 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
13380 Nothing<DateRecordWithCalendar>());
13381 }
13382 // 3. If isoString contains a UTCDesignator, then
13383 if (parsed->utc_designator) {
13384 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
13385 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
13386 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
13387 Nothing<DateRecordWithCalendar>());
13388 }
13389
13390 // 3. Let result be ? ParseISODateTime(isoString).
13391 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar result;
13392 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13393 isolate, result, ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed),
13394 Nothing<DateRecordWithCalendar>());
13395 // 5. Let year be result.[[Year]].
13396 // 6. If no part of isoString is produced by the DateYear production, then
13397 // a. Set year to undefined.
13398
13399 // 7. Return the Record { [[Year]]: year, [[Month]]: result.[[Month]],
13400 // [[Day]]: result.[[Day]], [[Calendar]]: result.[[Calendar]] }.
13401 DateRecordWithCalendar ret({result.date, result.calendar});
13402 return Just(ret);
13403}
13404
13405// #sec-temporal-totemporalmonthday
13406MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> ToTemporalMonthDay(
13407 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, DirectHandle<Object> options,
13408 const char* method_name) {
13409 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
13410
13411 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
13412 // 2. Assert: Type(options) is Object or Undefined.
13413 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*options) || IsUndefined(*options));
13414
13415 // 3. Let referenceISOYear be 1972 (the first leap year after the Unix epoch).
13416 constexpr int32_t kReferenceIsoYear = 1972;
13417 // 4. If Type(item) is Object, then
13418 if (IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
13419 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
13420 // a. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]] internal slot, then
13421 // i. Return item.
13422 if (IsJSTemporalPlainMonthDay(*item_obj)) {
13423 return Cast<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>(item_obj);
13424 }
13425 bool calendar_absent = false;
13426 // b. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalDate]],
13427 // [[InitializedTemporalDateTime]], [[InitializedTemporalTime]],
13428 // [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]], or [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]]
13429 // internal slot, then
13430 // i. Let calendar be item.[[Calendar]].
13431 // ii. Let calendarAbsent be false.
13432 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
13433 if (IsJSTemporalPlainDate(*item_obj)) {
13434 calendar = direct_handle(Cast<JSTemporalPlainDate>(item_obj)->calendar(),
13435 isolate);
13436 } else if (IsJSTemporalPlainDateTime(*item_obj)) {
13437 calendar = direct_handle(
13438 Cast<JSTemporalPlainDateTime>(item_obj)->calendar(), isolate);
13439 } else if (IsJSTemporalPlainTime(*item_obj)) {
13440 calendar = direct_handle(Cast<JSTemporalPlainTime>(item_obj)->calendar(),
13441 isolate);
13442 } else if (IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*item_obj)) {
13443 calendar = direct_handle(
13444 Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(item_obj)->calendar(), isolate);
13445 } else if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item_obj)) {
13446 calendar = direct_handle(
13447 Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(item_obj)->calendar(), isolate);
13448 // c. Else,
13449 } else {
13450 // i. Let calendar be ? Get(item, "calendar").
13451 Handle<Object> calendar_obj;
13452 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13453 isolate, calendar_obj,
13454 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, item, factory->calendar_string()));
13455 // ii. If calendar is undefined, then
13456 if (IsUndefined(*calendar_obj)) {
13457 // 1. Let calendarAbsent be true.
13458 calendar_absent = true;
13459 }
13460 // iv. Set calendar to ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendar).
13461 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13462 isolate, calendar,
13463 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, calendar_obj, method_name));
13464 }
13465 // d. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "day", "month",
13466 // "monthCode", "year" »).
13467 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names =
13468 DayMonthMonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);
13469 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
13470 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
13471 // e. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(item, fieldNames, «»).
13472 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
13473 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, fields,
13474 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, item, field_names,
13475 RequiredFields::kNone));
13476 // f. Let month be ? Get(fields, "month").
13477 DirectHandle<Object> month;
13478 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13479 isolate, month,
13480 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->month_string()),
13481 Handle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>());
13482 // g. Let monthCode be ? Get(fields, "monthCode").
13483 DirectHandle<Object> month_code;
13484 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13485 isolate, month_code,
13486 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->monthCode_string()),
13487 Handle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>());
13488 // h. Let year be ? Get(fields, "year").
13489 DirectHandle<Object> year;
13490 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13491 isolate, year,
13492 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->year_string()),
13493 Handle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>());
13494 // i. If calendarAbsent is true, and month is not undefined, and monthCode
13495 // is undefined and year is undefined, then
13496 if (calendar_absent && !IsUndefined(*month) && IsUndefined(*month_code) &&
13497 IsUndefined(*year)) {
13498 // i. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "year",
13499 // 𝔽(referenceISOYear)).
13500 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
13501 isolate, fields, factory->year_string(),
13502 direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(kReferenceIsoYear), isolate),
13503 Just(kThrowOnError))
13504 .FromJust());
13505 }
13506 // j. Return ? MonthDayFromFields(calendar, fields, options).
13507 return MonthDayFromFields(isolate, calendar, fields, options);
13508 }
13509 // 5. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
13510 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13511 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
13512 Handle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>());
13513
13514 // 6. Let string be ? ToString(item).
13515 Handle<String> string;
13516 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, string,
13517 Object::ToString(isolate, item_obj));
13518
13519 // 7. Let result be ? ParseTemporalMonthDayString(string).
13520 DateRecordWithCalendar result;
13521 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13522 isolate, result, ParseTemporalMonthDayString(isolate, string),
13523 Handle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>());
13524
13525 // 8. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(result.[[Calendar]]).
13526 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
13527 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13528 isolate, calendar,
13529 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, result.calendar, method_name));
13530
13531 // 9. If result.[[Year]] is undefined, then
13532 // We use kMintInt31 to represent undefined
13533 if (result.date.year == kMinInt31) {
13534 // a. Return ? CreateTemporalMonthDay(result.[[Month]], result.[[Day]],
13535 // calendar, referenceISOYear).
13536 return CreateTemporalMonthDay(isolate, result.date.month, result.date.day,
13537 calendar, kReferenceIsoYear);
13538 }
13539
13540 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> created_result;
13541 // 10. Set result to ? CreateTemporalMonthDay(result.[[Month]],
13542 // result.[[Day]], calendar, referenceISOYear).
13543 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13544 isolate, created_result,
13545 CreateTemporalMonthDay(isolate, result.date.month, result.date.day,
13546 calendar, kReferenceIsoYear));
13547 // 11. NOTE: The following operation is called without options, in order for
13548 // the calendar to store a canonical value in the [[ISOYear]] internal slot of
13549 // the result.
13550 // 12. Return ? CalendarMonthDayFromFields(calendar, result).
13551 return MonthDayFromFields(isolate, calendar, created_result);
13552}
13553
13554MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> ToTemporalMonthDay(
13555 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, const char* method_name) {
13556 // 1. If options is not present, set options to undefined.
13557 return ToTemporalMonthDay(isolate, item_obj,
13558 isolate->factory()->undefined_value(), method_name);
13559}

13563// #sec-temporal.plainmonthday.from
13564MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> JSTemporalPlainMonthDay::From(
13565 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
13566 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainMonthDay.from";
13567 // 1. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
13568 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
13569 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13570 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
13571 // 2. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]]
13572 // internal slot, then
13573 if (IsJSTemporalPlainMonthDay(*item)) {
13574 // a. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
13575 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13576 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
13577 Handle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>());
13578 // b. Return ? CreateTemporalMonthDay(item.[[ISOMonth]], item.[[ISODay]],
13579 // item.[[Calendar]], item.[[ISOYear]]).
13580 auto month_day = Cast<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>(item);
13581 return CreateTemporalMonthDay(
13582 isolate, month_day->iso_month(), month_day->iso_day(),
13583 direct_handle(month_day->calendar(), isolate), month_day->iso_year());
13584 }
13585 // 3. Return ? ToTemporalMonthDay(item, options).
13586 return ToTemporalMonthDay(isolate, item, options, method_name);
13587}
13588
13589// #sec-temporal.plainyearmonth.prototype.equals
13590MaybeHandle<Oddball> JSTemporalPlainMonthDay::Equals(
13591 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> month_day,
13592 Handle<Object> other_obj) {
13593 // 1. Let monthDay be the this value.
13594 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(monthDay,
13595 // [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]]).
13596 // 3. Set other to ? ToTemporalMonthDay(other).
13597 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> other;
13598 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13599 isolate, other,
13600 ToTemporalMonthDay(isolate, other_obj,
13601 "Temporal.PlainMonthDay.prototype.equals"));
13602 // 4. If monthDay.[[ISOMonth]] ≠ other.[[ISOMonth]], return false.
13603 if (month_day->iso_month() != other->iso_month())
13604 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
13605 // 5. If monthDay.[[ISODay]] ≠ other.[[ISODay]], return false.
13606 if (month_day->iso_day() != other->iso_day())
13607 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
13608 // 6. If monthDay.[[ISOYear]] ≠ other.[[ISOYear]], return false.
13609 if (month_day->iso_year() != other->iso_year())
13610 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
13611 // 7. Return ? CalendarEquals(monthDay.[[Calendar]], other.[[Calendar]]).
13612 return CalendarEquals(isolate,
13613 Handle<JSReceiver>(month_day->calendar(), isolate),
13614 Handle<JSReceiver>(other->calendar(), isolate));
13615}

13625 DayMonthMonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);

13628 isolate, temporal_month_day, temporal_month_day_like_obj, options_obj,
13629 field_names, "Temporal.PlainMonthDay.prototype.with");
13630}

13632namespace {
13633
13634// Common code shared by PlainMonthDay and PlainYearMonth.prototype.toPlainDate
13635template <typename T>
13636MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> PlainMonthDayOrYearMonthToPlainDate(
13637 Isolate* isolate, Handle<T> temporal, DirectHandle<Object> item_obj,
13638 DirectHandle<String> receiver_field_name_1,
13639 DirectHandle<String> receiver_field_name_2,
13640 DirectHandle<String> input_field_name) {
13641 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
13642 // 1. Let monthDay be the this value.
13643 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(monthDay,
13644 // [[InitializedTemporalXXX]]).
13645 // 3. If Type(item) is not Object, then
13646 if (!IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
13647 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
13648 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
13649 }
13650 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
13651 // 4. Let calendar be Xxx.[[Calendar]].
13652 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(temporal->calendar(), isolate);
13653 // 5. Let receiverFieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, «
13654 // receiverFieldName1, receiverFieldName2 »).
13655 Handle<FixedArray> receiver_field_names = factory->NewFixedArray(2);
13656 receiver_field_names->set(0, *receiver_field_name_1);
13657 receiver_field_names->set(1, *receiver_field_name_2);
13658 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13659 isolate, receiver_field_names,
13660 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, receiver_field_names));
13661 // 6. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(temporal, receiverFieldNames, «»).
13662 Handle<JSReceiver> fields;
13663 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13664 isolate, fields,
13665 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, temporal, receiver_field_names,
13666 RequiredFields::kNone));
13667 // 7. Let inputFieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « inputFieldName »).
13668 DirectHandle<FixedArray> input_field_names = factory->NewFixedArray(1);
13669 input_field_names->set(0, *input_field_name);
13670 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13671 isolate, input_field_names,
13672 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, input_field_names));
13673 // 8. Let inputFields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(item, inputFieldNames, «»).
13674 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> input_fields;
13675 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13676 isolate, input_fields,
13677 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, item, input_field_names,
13678 RequiredFields::kNone));
13679 // 9. Let mergedFields be ? CalendarMergeFields(calendar, fields,
13680 // inputFields).
13681 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> merged_fields;
13682 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13683 isolate, merged_fields,
13684 CalendarMergeFields(isolate, calendar, fields, input_fields));
13685 // 10. Let mergedFieldNames be the List containing all the elements of
13686 // receiverFieldNames followed by all the elements of inputFieldNames, with
13687 // duplicate elements removed.
13688 Handle<FixedArray> merged_field_names = factory->NewFixedArray(
13689 receiver_field_names->length() + input_field_names->length());
13690 Handle<StringSet> added = StringSet::New(isolate);
13691 for (int i = 0; i < receiver_field_names->length(); i++) {
13692 Handle<Object> item(receiver_field_names->get(i), isolate);
13693 DCHECK(IsString(*item));
13694 auto string = Cast<String>(item);
13695 if (!added->Has(isolate, string)) {
13696 merged_field_names->set(added->NumberOfElements(), *item);
13697 added = StringSet::Add(isolate, added, string);
13698 }
13699 }
13700 for (int i = 0; i < input_field_names->length(); i++) {
13701 Handle<Object> item(input_field_names->get(i), isolate);
13702 DCHECK(IsString(*item));
13703 auto string = Cast<String>(item);
13704 if (!added->Has(isolate, string)) {
13705 merged_field_names->set(added->NumberOfElements(), *item);
13706 added = StringSet::Add(isolate, added, string);
13707 }
13708 }
13709 merged_field_names = FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, merged_field_names,
13710 added->NumberOfElements());
13711
13712 // 11. Set mergedFields to ? PrepareTemporalFields(mergedFields,
13713 // mergedFieldNames, «»).
13714 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13715 isolate, merged_fields,
13716 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, merged_fields, merged_field_names,
13717 RequiredFields::kNone));
13718 // 12. Let options be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
13719 DirectHandle<JSObject> options = factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
13720 // 13. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(options, "overflow", "reject").
13721 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
13722 isolate, options, factory->overflow_string(),
13723 factory->reject_string(), Just(kThrowOnError))
13724 .FromJust());
13725 // 14. Return ? DateFromFields(calendar, mergedFields, options).
13726 return DateFromFields(isolate, calendar, merged_fields, options);
13727}

13731// #sec-temporal.plainmonthday.prototype.toplaindate
13732MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> JSTemporalPlainMonthDay::ToPlainDate(
13733 Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> month_day,
13734 DirectHandle<Object> item_obj) {
13735 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
13736 // 5. Let receiverFieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "day",
13737 // "monthCode" »).
13738 // 7. Let inputFieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "year" »).
13739 return PlainMonthDayOrYearMonthToPlainDate<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay>(
13740 isolate, month_day, item_obj, factory->day_string(),

13744// #sec-temporal.plainmonthday.prototype.getisofields
13745MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> JSTemporalPlainMonthDay::GetISOFields(
13746 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainMonthDay> month_day) {
13747 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
13748 // 1. Let monthDay be the this value.
13749 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(monthDay,
13750 // [[InitializedTemporalMonthDay]]).
13751 // 3. Let fields be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
13752 Handle<JSObject> fields = factory->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function());
13753 // 4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "calendar",
13754 // montyDay.[[Calendar]]).
13755 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
13756 isolate, fields, factory->calendar_string(),
13757 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(month_day->calendar(), isolate),
13758 Just(kThrowOnError))
13759 .FromJust());
13760
13761 // 5. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoDay",
13762 // 𝔽(montyDay.[[ISODay]])).
13763 // 6. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMonth",
13764 // 𝔽(montyDay.[[ISOMonth]])).
13765 // 7. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoYear",
13766 // 𝔽(montyDay.[[ISOYear]])).
13767 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoDay, iso_day, month_day)
13768 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMonth, iso_month, month_day)
13769 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoYear, iso_year, month_day)
13770 // 8. Return fields.
13771 return fields;
13772}

13800
13801MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> JSTemporalPlainYearMonth::Constructor(
13802 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
13803 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<Object> iso_year_obj,
13804 Handle<Object> iso_month_obj, Handle<Object> calendar_like,
13805 Handle<Object> reference_iso_day_obj) {
13806 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainYearMonth";
13807 // 1. If NewTarget is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
13808 if (IsUndefined(*new_target)) {
13809 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
13810 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kMethodInvokedOnWrongType,
13811 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
13812 method_name)));
13813 }
13814 // 7. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendarLike).
13815 // 10. Return ? CreateTemporalYearMonth(y, m, calendar, ref, NewTarget).
13816
13817 // 3. Let y be ? ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isoYear).
13818 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_year, JSTemporalPlainYearMonth);
13819 // 5. Let m be ? ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(isoMonth).
13820 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(iso_month, JSTemporalPlainYearMonth);
13821 // 7. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendarLike).
13822 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
13823 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13824 isolate, calendar,
13825 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, calendar_like, method_name));
13826
13827 // 2. If referenceISODay is undefined, then
13828 // a. Set referenceISODay to 1𝔽.
13829 // ...
13830 // 8. Let ref be ? ToIntegerThrowOnInfinity(referenceISODay).
13831 int32_t ref = 1;
13832 if (!IsUndefined(*reference_iso_day_obj)) {
13833 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(reference_iso_day, JSTemporalPlainYearMonth);
13834 ref = reference_iso_day;
13835 }
13836
13837 // 10. Return ? CreateTemporalYearMonth(y, m, calendar, ref, NewTarget).
13838 return CreateTemporalYearMonth(isolate, target, new_target, iso_year,
13839 iso_month, calendar, ref);
13840}
13841
13842namespace {
13843
13844// #sec-temporal-parsetemporalyearmonthstring
13845Maybe<DateRecordWithCalendar> ParseTemporalYearMonthString(
13846 Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> iso_string) {
13847 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
13848
13849 // 1. Assert: Type(isoString) is String.
13850 // 2. If isoString does not satisfy the syntax of a TemporalYearMonthString
13851 // (see 13.33), then
13852 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
13853 TemporalParser::ParseTemporalYearMonthString(isolate, iso_string);
13854 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
13855 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
13856 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
13857 Nothing<DateRecordWithCalendar>());
13858 }
13859
13860 // 3. If _isoString_ contains a |UTCDesignator|, then
13861 if (parsed->utc_designator) {
13862 // a. Throw a *RangeError* exception.
13863 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
13864 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
13865 Nothing<DateRecordWithCalendar>());
13866 }
13867
13868 // 3. Let result be ? ParseISODateTime(isoString).
13869 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar result;
13870 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13871 isolate, result, ParseISODateTime(isolate, iso_string, *parsed),
13872 Nothing<DateRecordWithCalendar>());
13873
13874 // 4. Return the Record { [[Year]]: result.[[Year]], [[Month]]:
13875 // result.[[Month]], [[Day]]: result.[[Day]], [[Calendar]]:
13876 // result.[[Calendar]] }.
13877 DateRecordWithCalendar ret = {
13878 {result.date.year, result.date.month, result.date.day}, result.calendar};
13879 return Just(ret);
13880}
13881
13882// #sec-temporal-totemporalyearmonth
13883MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> ToTemporalYearMonth(
13884 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, DirectHandle<Object> options,
13885 const char* method_name) {
13886 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
13887
13888 // 2. Assert: Type(options) is Object or Undefined.
13889 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*options) || IsUndefined(*options));
13890 // 3. If Type(item) is Object, then
13891 if (IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
13892 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
13893 // a. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]] internal slot, then
13894 // i. Return item.
13895 if (IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*item_obj)) {
13896 return Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(item_obj);
13897 }
13898
13899 // b. Let calendar be ? GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(item).
13900 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
13901 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13902 isolate, calendar,
13903 GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, item, method_name));
13904 // c. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "month", "monthCode",
13905 // "year" »).
13906 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names =
13907 MonthMonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);
13908 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
13909 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
13910 // d. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(item, fieldNames, «»).
13911 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
13912 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, fields,
13913 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, item, field_names,
13914 RequiredFields::kNone));
13915 // e. Return ? YearMonthFromFields(calendar, fields, options).
13916 return YearMonthFromFields(isolate, calendar, fields, options);
13917 }
13918 // 4. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
13919 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13920 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
13921 Handle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>());
13922 // 5. Let string be ? ToString(item).
13923 Handle<String> string;
13924 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, string,
13925 Object::ToString(isolate, item_obj));
13926 // 6. Let result be ? ParseTemporalYearMonthString(string).
13927 DateRecordWithCalendar result;
13928 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13929 isolate, result, ParseTemporalYearMonthString(isolate, string),
13930 Handle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>());
13931 // 7. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(result.[[Calendar]]).
13932 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
13933 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13934 isolate, calendar,
13935 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, result.calendar, method_name));
13936 // 8. Set result to ? CreateTemporalYearMonth(result.[[Year]],
13937 // result.[[Month]], calendar, result.[[Day]]).
13938 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> created_result;
13939 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13940 isolate, created_result,
13941 CreateTemporalYearMonth(isolate, result.date.year, result.date.month,
13942 calendar, result.date.day));
13943 // 9. NOTE: The following operation is called without options, in order for
13944 // the calendar to store a canonical value in the [[ISODay]] internal slot of
13945 // the result.
13946 // 10. Return ? CalendarYearMonthFromFields(calendar, result).
13947 return YearMonthFromFields(isolate, calendar, created_result);
13948}
13949
13950MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> ToTemporalYearMonth(
13951 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, const char* method_name) {
13952 // 1. If options is not present, set options to undefined.
13953 return ToTemporalYearMonth(
13954 isolate, item_obj, isolate->factory()->undefined_value(), method_name);
13955}

13957} // namespace

13959// #sec-temporal.plainyearmonth.from
13960MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> JSTemporalPlainYearMonth::From(
13961 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
13962 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from";
13963 // 1. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
13964 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
13965 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13966 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
13967 // 2. If Type(item) is Object and item has an [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]]
13968 // internal slot, then
13969 if (IsJSTemporalPlainYearMonth(*item)) {
13970 // a. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
13971 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
13972 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
13973 Handle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>());
13974 // b. Return ? CreateTemporalYearMonth(item.[[ISOYear]], item.[[ISOMonth]],
13975 // item.[[Calendar]], item.[[ISODay]]).
13976 auto year_month = Cast<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(item);
13977 return CreateTemporalYearMonth(
13978 isolate, year_month->iso_year(), year_month->iso_month(),
13979 direct_handle(year_month->calendar(), isolate), year_month->iso_day());
13980 }
13981 // 3. Return ? ToTemporalYearMonth(item, options).
13982 return ToTemporalYearMonth(isolate, item, options, method_name);
13983}

13985// #sec-temporal.plainyearmonth.compare
13986MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalPlainYearMonth::Compare(Isolate* isolate,
13987 Handle<Object> one_obj,
13988 Handle<Object> two_obj) {
13989 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainYearMonth.compare";
13990 // 1. Set one to ? ToTemporalYearMonth(one).
13991 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> one;
13992 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13993 isolate, one, ToTemporalYearMonth(isolate, one_obj, method_name));
13994 // 2. Set two to ? ToTemporalYearMonth(two).
13995 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> two;
13996 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
13997 isolate, two, ToTemporalYearMonth(isolate, two_obj, method_name));
13998 // 3. Return 𝔽(! CompareISODate(one.[[ISOYear]], one.[[ISOMonth]],
13999 // one.[[ISODay]], two.[[ISOYear]], two.[[ISOMonth]], two.[[ISODay]])).
14000 return handle(Smi::FromInt(CompareISODate(
14001 {one->iso_year(), one->iso_month(), one->iso_day()},
14002 {two->iso_year(), two->iso_month(), two->iso_day()})),
14003 isolate);
14004}
14005
14006// #sec-temporal.plainyearmonth.prototype.equals
14007MaybeHandle<Oddball> JSTemporalPlainYearMonth::Equals(
14008 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> year_month,
14009 Handle<Object> other_obj) {
14010 // 1. Let yearMonth be the this value.
14011 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(yearMonth,
14012 // [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]]).
14013 // 3. Set other to ? ToTemporalYearMonth(other).
14014 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> other;
14015 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14016 isolate, other,
14017 ToTemporalYearMonth(isolate, other_obj,
14018 "Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.equals"));
14019 // 4. If yearMonth.[[ISOYear]] ≠ other.[[ISOYear]], return false.
14020 if (year_month->iso_year() != other->iso_year())
14021 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14022 // 5. If yearMonth.[[ISOMonth]] ≠ other.[[ISOMonth]], return false.
14023 if (year_month->iso_month() != other->iso_month())
14024 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14025 // 6. If yearMonth.[[ISODay]] ≠ other.[[ISODay]], return false.
14026 if (year_month->iso_day() != other->iso_day())
14027 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14028 // 7. Return ? CalendarEquals(yearMonth.[[Calendar]], other.[[Calendar]]).
14029 return CalendarEquals(isolate,
14030 Handle<JSReceiver>(year_month->calendar(), isolate),
14031 Handle<JSReceiver>(other->calendar(), isolate));
14032}

14034namespace {
14035
14036MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>
14037AddDurationToOrSubtractDurationFromPlainYearMonth(
14038 Isolate* isolate, Arithmetic operation,
14039 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> year_month,
14040 Handle<Object> temporal_duration_like, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj,
14041 const char* method_name) {
14042 // 1. Let duration be ? ToTemporalDurationRecord(temporalDurationLike).
14043 DurationRecord duration;
14044 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14045 isolate, duration,
14046 temporal::ToTemporalDurationRecord(isolate, temporal_duration_like,
14047 method_name),
14048 Handle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>());
14049
14050 // 2. If operation is subtract, then
14051 if (operation == Arithmetic::kSubtract) {
14052 // a. Set duration to ! CreateNegatedDurationRecord(duration).
14053 duration = CreateNegatedDurationRecord(isolate, duration).ToChecked();
14054 }
14055 // 3. Let balanceResult be ? BalanceDuration(duration.[[Days]],
14056 // duration.[[Hours]], duration.[[Minutes]], duration.[[Seconds]],
14057 // duration.[[Milliseconds]], duration.[[Microseconds]],
14058 // duration.[[Nanoseconds]], "day").
14059 TimeDurationRecord balance_result;
14060 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14061 isolate, balance_result,
14062 BalanceDuration(isolate, Unit::kDay, duration.time_duration, method_name),
14063 Handle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>());
14064 // 4. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
14065 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
14066 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14067 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
14068 // 5. Let calendar be yearMonth.[[Calendar]].
14069 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(year_month->calendar(), isolate);
14070
14071 // 6. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "monthCode", "year" »).
14072 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
14073 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names = MonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);
14074 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
14075 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
14076
14077 // 7. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(yearMonth, fieldNames, «»).
14078 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
14079 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14080 isolate, fields,
14081 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, year_month, field_names,
14082 RequiredFields::kNone));
14083
14084 // 8. Set sign to ! DurationSign(duration.[[Years]], duration.[[Months]],
14085 // duration.[[Weeks]], balanceResult.[[Days]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
14086 int32_t sign =
14087 DurationRecord::Sign({duration.years,
14088 duration.months,
14089 duration.weeks,
14090 {balance_result.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}});
14091
14092 // 9. If sign < 0, then
14093 DirectHandle<Object> day;
14094 if (sign < 0) {
14095 // a. Let dayFromCalendar be ? CalendarDaysInMonth(calendar, yearMonth).
14096 Handle<Object> day_from_calendar;
14097 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14098 isolate, day_from_calendar,
14099 temporal::CalendarDaysInMonth(isolate, calendar, year_month));
14100
14101 // b. Let day be ? ToPositiveInteger(dayFromCalendar).
14102 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, day,
14103 ToPositiveInteger(isolate, day_from_calendar));
14104 // 10. Else,
14105 } else {
14106 // a. Let day be 1.
14107 day = direct_handle(Smi::FromInt(1), isolate);
14108 }
14109 // 11. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "day", day).
14110 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, fields, factory->day_string(),
14111 day, Just(kThrowOnError))
14112 .FromJust());
14113
14114 // 12. Let date be ? CalendarDateFromFields(calendar, fields).
14115 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> date;
14116 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14117 isolate, date,
14118 FromFields<JSTemporalPlainDate>(
14119 isolate, calendar, fields, isolate->factory()->undefined_value(),
14120 isolate->factory()->dateFromFields_string(),
14121 JS_TEMPORAL_PLAIN_DATE_TYPE));
14122
14123 // 13. Let durationToAdd be ! CreateTemporalDuration(duration.[[Years]],
14124 // duration.[[Months]], duration.[[Weeks]], balanceResult.[[Days]], 0, 0, 0,
14125 // 0, 0, 0).
14126 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> duration_to_add =
14127 CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {duration.years,
14128 duration.months,
14129 duration.weeks,
14130 {balance_result.days, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
14131 .ToHandleChecked();
14132 // 14. Let optionsCopy be OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
14133 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options_copy =
14134 isolate->factory()->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
14135
14136 // 15. Let entries be ? EnumerableOwnPropertyNames(options, key+value).
14137 // 16. For each element nextEntry of entries, do
14138 // a. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(optionsCopy, nextEntry[0],
14139 // nextEntry[1]).
14140 bool set;
14141 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14142 isolate, set,
14143 JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
14144 isolate, options_copy, options,
14145 PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder, {}, false),
14146 Handle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>());
14147
14148 // 17. Let addedDate be ? CalendarDateAdd(calendar, date, durationToAdd,
14149 // options).
14150 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> added_date;
14151 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14152 isolate, added_date,
14153 CalendarDateAdd(isolate, calendar, date, duration_to_add, options));
14154 // 18. Let addedDateFields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(addedDate, fieldNames,
14155 // «»).
14156 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> added_date_fields;
14157 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14158 isolate, added_date_fields,
14159 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, added_date, field_names,
14160 RequiredFields::kNone));
14161 // 19. Return ? CalendarYearMonthFromFields(calendar, addedDateFields,
14162 // optionsCopy).
14163 return FromFields<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth>(
14164 isolate, calendar, added_date_fields, options_copy,
14165 isolate->factory()->yearMonthFromFields_string(),
14166 JS_TEMPORAL_PLAIN_YEAR_MONTH_TYPE);
14167}
