14189namespace {
14190// #sec-temporal-differencetemporalplandyearmonth
14191MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> DifferenceTemporalPlainYearMonth(
14192 Isolate* isolate, TimePreposition operation,
14193 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> year_month, Handle<Object> other_obj,
14194 DirectHandle<Object> options, const char* method_name) {
14195 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
14196 // 1. If operation is since, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
14197 double sign = operation == TimePreposition::kSince ? -1 : 1;
14198 // 2. Set other to ? ToTemporalDateTime(other).
14199 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> other;
14200 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14201 isolate, other, ToTemporalYearMonth(isolate, other_obj, method_name));
14202 // 3. Let calendar be yearMonth.[[Calendar]].
14203 Handle<JSReceiver> calendar(year_month->calendar(), isolate);
14204
14205 // 4. If ? CalendarEquals(calendar, other.[[Calendar]]) is false, throw a
14206 // RangeError exception.
14207 bool calendar_equals;
14208 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14209 isolate, calendar_equals,
14210 CalendarEqualsBool(isolate, calendar, handle(other->calendar(), isolate)),
14211 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
14212 if (!calendar_equals) {
14213 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
14214 }
14215
14216 // 5. Let settings be ? GetDifferenceSettings(operation, options, date, «
14217 // "week", "day" », "month", "year").
14218 DifferenceSettings settings;
14219 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14220 isolate, settings,
14221 GetDifferenceSettings(isolate, operation, options, UnitGroup::kDate,
14222 DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings::kWeekAndDay,
14223 Unit::kMonth, Unit::kYear, method_name),
14224 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
14225 // 6. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "monthCode", "year" »).
14226 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
14227 DirectHandle<FixedArray> field_names = MonthCodeYearInFixedArray(isolate);
14228 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
14229 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
14230
14231 // 7. Let otherFields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(other, fieldNames, «»).
14232 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> other_fields;
14233 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, other_fields,
14234 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, other, field_names,
14235 RequiredFields::kNone));
14236 // 8. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(otherFields, "day", 1𝔽).
14237 DirectHandle<Object> one(Smi::FromInt(1), isolate);
14238 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, other_fields,
14239 factory->day_string(), one,
14240 Just(kThrowOnError))
14241 .FromJust());
14242 // 9. Let otherDate be ? CalendarDateFromFields(calendar, otherFields).
14243 // DateFromFields(Isolate* isolate,
14244 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> other_date;
14245 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14246 isolate, other_date,
14247 DateFromFields(isolate, calendar, other_fields,
14248 isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
14249 // 10. Let thisFields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(yearMonth, fieldNames, «»).
14250 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> this_fields;
14251 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14252 isolate, this_fields,
14253 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, year_month, field_names,
14254 RequiredFields::kNone));
14255 // 11. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(thisFields, "day", 1𝔽).
14256 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, this_fields,
14257 factory->day_string(), one,
14258 Just(kThrowOnError))
14259 .FromJust());
14260 // 12. Let thisDate be ? CalendarDateFromFields(calendar, thisFields).
14261 Handle<JSTemporalPlainDate> this_date;
14262 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14263 isolate, this_date,
14264 DateFromFields(isolate, calendar, this_fields,
14265 isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
14266 // 13. Let untilOptions be ? MergeLargestUnitOption(settings.[[Options]],
14267 // settings.[[LargestUnit]]).
14268 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> until_options;
14269 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14270 isolate, until_options,
14271 MergeLargestUnitOption(isolate, settings.options, settings.largest_unit));
14272 // 14. Let result be ? CalendarDateUntil(calendar, thisDate, otherDate,
14273 // untilOptions).
14274 DirectHandle<JSTemporalDuration> result;
14275 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
14276 CalendarDateUntil(isolate, calendar, this_date,
14277 other_date, until_options));
14278
14279 // 15. If settings.[[SmallestUnit]] is not "month" or
14280 // settings.[[RoundingIncrement]] ≠ 1, then
14281 if (settings.smallest_unit != Unit::kMonth ||
14282 settings.rounding_increment != 1) {
14283 // a. Set result to (? RoundDuration(result.[[Years]], result.[[Months]], 0,
14284 // 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, settings.[[RoundingIncrement]],
14285 // settings.[[SmallestUnit]], settings.[[RoundingMode]],
14286 // thisDate)).[[DurationRecord]].
14287 DurationRecordWithRemainder round_result;
14288 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14289 isolate, round_result,
14290 RoundDuration(isolate,
14291 {Object::NumberValue(result->years()),
14292 Object::NumberValue(result->months()),
14293 0,
14294 {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
14295 settings.rounding_increment, settings.smallest_unit,
14296 settings.rounding_mode, this_date, method_name),
14297 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
14298 // 16. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign × result.[[Years]], sign ×
14299 // result.[[Months]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
14300 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, {round_result.record.years * sign,
14301 round_result.record.months * sign,
14302 0,
14303 {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
14304 .ToHandleChecked();
14305 }
14306 // 16. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(sign × result.[[Years]], sign ×
14307 // result.[[Months]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
14308 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate,
14309 {Object::NumberValue(result->years()) * sign,
14310 Object::NumberValue(result->months()) * sign,
14311 0,
14312 {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}})
14313 .ToHandleChecked();
14314}

14367// #sec-temporal.plainyearmonth.prototype.getisofields
14368MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> JSTemporalPlainYearMonth::GetISOFields(
14369 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainYearMonth> year_month) {
14370 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
14371 // 1. Let yearMonth be the this value.
14372 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(yearMonth,
14373 // [[InitializedTemporalYearMonth]]).
14374 // 3. Let fields be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
14375 Handle<JSObject> fields =
14376 isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function());
14377 // 4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "calendar",
14378 // yearMonth.[[Calendar]]).
14379 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
14380 isolate, fields, factory->calendar_string(),
14381 DirectHandle<JSReceiver>(year_month->calendar(), isolate),
14382 Just(kThrowOnError))
14383 .FromJust());
14384 // 5. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoDay",
14385 // 𝔽(yearMonth.[[ISODay]])).
14386 // 6. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMonth",
14387 // 𝔽(yearMonth.[[ISOMonth]])).
14388 // 7. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoYear",
14389 // 𝔽(yearMonth.[[ISOYear]])).
14390 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoDay, iso_day, year_month)
14391 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMonth, iso_month, year_month)
14392 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoYear, iso_year, year_month)
14393 // 8. Return fields.
14394 return fields;
14395}

14425// #sec-temporal-plaintime-constructor
14426MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> JSTemporalPlainTime::Constructor(
14427 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
14428 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<Object> hour_obj,
14429 Handle<Object> minute_obj, Handle<Object> second_obj,
14430 Handle<Object> millisecond_obj, Handle<Object> microsecond_obj,
14431 Handle<Object> nanosecond_obj) {
14432 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainTime";
14433 // 1. If NewTarget is undefined, then
14434 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
14435 if (IsUndefined(*new_target)) {
14436 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
14437 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
14438 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kMethodInvokedOnWrongType,
14439 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
14440 method_name)));
14441 }
14442
14443 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(hour, JSTemporalPlainTime);
14444 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(minute, JSTemporalPlainTime);
14445 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(second, JSTemporalPlainTime);
14446 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(millisecond, JSTemporalPlainTime);
14447 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(microsecond, JSTemporalPlainTime);
14448 TO_INT_THROW_ON_INFTY(nanosecond, JSTemporalPlainTime);
14449
14450 // 14. Return ? CreateTemporalTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond,
14451 // microsecond, nanosecond, NewTarget).
14452 return CreateTemporalTime(
14453 isolate, target, new_target,
14454 {hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond});
14455}

14457// #sec-temporal.plaintime.prototype.tozoneddatetime
14458MaybeHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> JSTemporalPlainTime::ToZonedDateTime(
14459 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time,
14460 DirectHandle<Object> item_obj) {
14461 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainTime.prototype.toZonedDateTime";
14462 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
14463 // 1. Let temporalTime be the this value.
14464 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalTime,
14465 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]]).
14466 // 3. If Type(item) is not Object, then
14467 if (!IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
14468 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
14469 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
14470 }
14471 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
14472 // 4. Let temporalDateLike be ? Get(item, "plainDate").
14473 Handle<Object> temporal_date_like;
14474 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14475 isolate, temporal_date_like,
14476 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, item, factory->plainDate_string()));
14477 // 5. If temporalDateLike is undefined, then
14478 if (IsUndefined(*temporal_date_like)) {
14479 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
14480 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
14481 }
14482 // 6. Let temporalDate be ? ToTemporalDate(temporalDateLike).
14483 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDate> temporal_date;
14484 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14485 isolate, temporal_date,
14486 ToTemporalDate(isolate, temporal_date_like, method_name));
14487 // 7. Let temporalTimeZoneLike be ? Get(item, "timeZone").
14488 Handle<Object> temporal_time_zone_like;
14489 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14490 isolate, temporal_time_zone_like,
14491 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, item, factory->timeZone_string()));
14492 // 8. If temporalTimeZoneLike is undefined, then
14493 if (IsUndefined(*temporal_time_zone_like)) {
14494 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
14495 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
14496 }
14497 // 9. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(temporalTimeZoneLike).
14498 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone;
14499 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14500 isolate, time_zone,
14501 temporal::ToTemporalTimeZone(isolate, temporal_time_zone_like,
14502 method_name));
14503 // 10. Let temporalDateTime be ?
14504 // CreateTemporalDateTime(temporalDate.[[ISOYear]], temporalDate.[[ISOMonth]],
14505 // temporalDate.[[ISODay]], temporalTime.[[ISOHour]],
14506 // temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]], temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]],
14507 // temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
14508 // temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]], temporalDate.[[Calendar]]).
14509 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar(temporal_date->calendar(), isolate);
14510 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> temporal_date_time;
14511 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14512 isolate, temporal_date_time,
14513 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
14514 isolate,
14515 {{temporal_date->iso_year(), temporal_date->iso_month(),
14516 temporal_date->iso_day()},
14517 {temporal_time->iso_hour(), temporal_time->iso_minute(),
14518 temporal_time->iso_second(), temporal_time->iso_millisecond(),
14519 temporal_time->iso_microsecond(), temporal_time->iso_nanosecond()}},
14520 calendar));
14521 // 11. Let instant be ? BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(timeZone,
14522 // temporalDateTime, "compatible").
14523 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant;
14524 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14525 isolate, instant,
14526 BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(isolate, time_zone, temporal_date_time,
14527 Disambiguation::kCompatible, method_name));
14528 // 12. Return ? CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(instant.[[Nanoseconds]], timeZone,
14529 // temporalDate.[[Calendar]]).
14530 return CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(
14531 isolate, direct_handle(instant->nanoseconds(), isolate), time_zone,
14532 calendar);
14533}

14535namespace {
14536// #sec-temporal-comparetemporaltime
14537int32_t CompareTemporalTime(const TimeRecord& time1, const TimeRecord& time2) {
14538 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
14539
14540 // 1. Assert: h1, min1, s1, ms1, mus1, ns1, h2, min2, s2, ms2, mus2, and ns2
14541 // are integers.
14542 // 2. If h1 > h2, return 1.
14543 if (time1.hour > time2.hour) return 1;
14544 // 3. If h1 < h2, return -1.
14545 if (time1.hour < time2.hour) return -1;
14546 // 4. If min1 > min2, return 1.
14547 if (time1.minute > time2.minute) return 1;
14548 // 5. If min1 < min2, return -1.
14549 if (time1.minute < time2.minute) return -1;
14550 // 6. If s1 > s2, return 1.
14551 if (time1.second > time2.second) return 1;
14552 // 7. If s1 < s2, return -1.
14553 if (time1.second < time2.second) return -1;
14554 // 8. If ms1 > ms2, return 1.
14555 if (time1.millisecond > time2.millisecond) return 1;
14556 // 9. If ms1 < ms2, return -1.
14557 if (time1.millisecond < time2.millisecond) return -1;
14558 // 10. If mus1 > mus2, return 1.
14559 if (time1.microsecond > time2.microsecond) return 1;
14560 // 11. If mus1 < mus2, return -1.
14561 if (time1.microsecond < time2.microsecond) return -1;
14562 // 12. If ns1 > ns2, return 1.
14563 if (time1.nanosecond > time2.nanosecond) return 1;
14564 // 13. If ns1 < ns2, return -1.
14565 if (time1.nanosecond < time2.nanosecond) return -1;
14566 // 14. Return 0.
14567 return 0;
14568}
14569} // namespace
14570
14571// #sec-temporal.plaintime.compare
14572MaybeHandle<Smi> JSTemporalPlainTime::Compare(Isolate* isolate,
14573 Handle<Object> one_obj,
14574 Handle<Object> two_obj) {
14575 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PainTime.compare";
14576 // 1. Set one to ? ToTemporalTime(one).
14577 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> one;
14578 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14579 isolate, one, temporal::ToTemporalTime(isolate, one_obj, method_name));
14580 // 2. Set two to ? ToTemporalTime(two).
14581 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> two;
14582 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14583 isolate, two, temporal::ToTemporalTime(isolate, two_obj, method_name));
14584 // 3. Return 𝔽(! CompareTemporalTime(one.[[ISOHour]], one.[[ISOMinute]],
14585 // one.[[ISOSecond]], one.[[ISOMillisecond]], one.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
14586 // one.[[ISONanosecond]], two.[[ISOHour]], two.[[ISOMinute]],
14587 // two.[[ISOSecond]], two.[[ISOMillisecond]], two.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
14588 // two.[[ISONanosecond]])).
14589 return handle(Smi::FromInt(CompareTemporalTime(
14590 {one->iso_hour(), one->iso_minute(), one->iso_second(),
14591 one->iso_millisecond(), one->iso_microsecond(),
14592 one->iso_nanosecond()},
14593 {two->iso_hour(), two->iso_minute(), two->iso_second(),
14594 two->iso_millisecond(), two->iso_microsecond(),
14595 two->iso_nanosecond()})),
14596 isolate);
14597}

14599// #sec-temporal.plaintime.prototype.equals
14600MaybeHandle<Oddball> JSTemporalPlainTime::Equals(
14601 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time,
14602 Handle<Object> other_obj) {
14603 // 1. Let temporalTime be the this value.
14604 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalTime,
14605 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]]).
14606 // 3. Set other to ? ToTemporalTime(other).
14607 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> other;
14608 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14609 isolate, other,
14610 temporal::ToTemporalTime(isolate, other_obj,
14611 "Temporal.PlainTime.prototype.equals"));
14612 // 4. If temporalTime.[[ISOHour]] ≠ other.[[ISOHour]], return false.
14613 if (temporal_time->iso_hour() != other->iso_hour())
14614 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14615 // 5. If temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]] ≠ other.[[ISOMinute]], return false.
14616 if (temporal_time->iso_minute() != other->iso_minute())
14617 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14618 // 6. If temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]] ≠ other.[[ISOSecond]], return false.
14619 if (temporal_time->iso_second() != other->iso_second())
14620 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14621 // 7. If temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]] ≠ other.[[ISOMillisecond]], return
14622 // false.
14623 if (temporal_time->iso_millisecond() != other->iso_millisecond())
14624 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14625 // 8. If temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]] ≠ other.[[ISOMicrosecond]], return
14626 // false.
14627 if (temporal_time->iso_microsecond() != other->iso_microsecond())
14628 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14629 // 9. If temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]] ≠ other.[[ISONanosecond]], return
14630 // false.
14631 if (temporal_time->iso_nanosecond() != other->iso_nanosecond())
14632 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
14633 // 10. Return true.
14634 return isolate->factory()->true_value();
14635}

14637namespace {
14638
14639// #sec-temporal-maximumtemporaldurationroundingincrement
14640Maximum MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(Unit unit) {
14641 switch (unit) {
14642 // 1. If unit is "year", "month", "week", or "day", then
14643 case Unit::kYear:
14644 case Unit::kMonth:
14645 case Unit::kWeek:
14646 case Unit::kDay:
14647 // a. Return undefined.
14648 return {false, 0};
14649 // 2. If unit is "hour", then
14650 case Unit::kHour:
14651 // a. Return 24.
14652 return {true, 24};
14653 // 3. If unit is "minute" or "second", then
14654 case Unit::kMinute:
14655 case Unit::kSecond:
14656 // a. Return 60.
14657 return {true, 60};
14658 // 4. Assert: unit is one of "millisecond", "microsecond", or "nanosecond".
14659 case Unit::kMillisecond:
14660 case Unit::kMicrosecond:
14661 case Unit::kNanosecond:
14662 // 5. Return 1000.
14663 return {true, 1000};
14664 default:
14665 UNREACHABLE();
14666 }
14667}
14668
14669} // namespace

14671// #sec-temporal.plaintime.prototype.round
14672MaybeHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> JSTemporalPlainTime::Round(
14673 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time,
14674 DirectHandle<Object> round_to_obj) {
14675 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainTime.prototype.round";
14676 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
14677 // 1. Let temporalTime be the this value.
14678 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalTime,
14679 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]]).
14680 // 3. If roundTo is undefined, then
14681 if (IsUndefined(*round_to_obj)) {
14682 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
14683 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_TYPE_ERROR());
14684 }
14685
14686 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> round_to;
14687 // 4. If Type(roundTo) is String, then
14688 if (IsString(*round_to_obj)) {
14689 // a. Let paramString be roundTo.
14690 DirectHandle<String> param_string = Cast<String>(round_to_obj);
14691 // b. Set roundTo to ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(null).
14692 round_to = factory->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
14693 // c. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(roundTo, "smallestUnit",
14694 // paramString).
14695 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, round_to,
14696 factory->smallestUnit_string(),
14697 param_string, Just(kThrowOnError))
14698 .FromJust());
14699 } else {
14700 // 5. Set roundTo to ? GetOptionsObject(roundTo).
14701 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14702 isolate, round_to,
14703 GetOptionsObject(isolate, round_to_obj, method_name));
14704 }
14705
14706 // 6. Let smallestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(roundTo, "smallestUnit", time,
14707 // required).
14708 Unit smallest_unit;
14709 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14710 isolate, smallest_unit,
14711 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, round_to, "smallestUnit", UnitGroup::kTime,
14712 Unit::kNotPresent, true, method_name),
14713 Handle<JSTemporalPlainTime>());
14714
14715 // 7. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(roundTo, "halfExpand").
14716 RoundingMode rounding_mode;
14717 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14718 isolate, rounding_mode,
14719 ToTemporalRoundingMode(isolate, round_to, RoundingMode::kHalfExpand,
14720 method_name),
14721 Handle<JSTemporalPlainTime>());
14722
14723 // 8. Let maximum be ! MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallestUnit).
14724 Maximum maximum = MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallest_unit);
14725
14726 // 9. Let roundingIncrement be ? ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(roundTo,
14727 // maximum, false).
14728 double rounding_increment;
14729 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14730 isolate, rounding_increment,
14731 ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(isolate, round_to, maximum.value,
14732 maximum.defined, false),
14733 Handle<JSTemporalPlainTime>());
14734
14735 // 12. Let result be ! RoundTime(temporalTime.[[ISOHour]],
14736 // temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]], temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]],
14737 // temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
14738 // temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]], roundingIncrement, smallestUnit,
14739 // roundingMode).
14740 DateTimeRecord result = RoundTime(
14741 isolate,
14742 {temporal_time->iso_hour(), temporal_time->iso_minute(),
14743 temporal_time->iso_second(), temporal_time->iso_millisecond(),
14744 temporal_time->iso_microsecond(), temporal_time->iso_nanosecond()},
14745 rounding_increment, smallest_unit, rounding_mode);
14746 // 13. Return ? CreateTemporalTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
14747 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
14748 // result.[[Nanosecond]]).
14749 return CreateTemporalTime(isolate, result.time);
14750}

14799 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
14800 // result.[[Nanosecond]]).
14801 return CreateTemporalTime(isolate, result);

14890 Isolate* isolate, Arithmetic operation,
14891 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time,
14892 Handle<Object> temporal_duration_like, const char* method_name) {
14893 // 1. If operation is subtract, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
14894 double sign = operation == Arithmetic::kSubtract ? -1.0 : 1.0;
14895 // 2. Let duration be ? ToTemporalDurationRecord(temporalDurationLike).
14896 DurationRecord duration;
14897 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14898 isolate, duration,
14899 temporal::ToTemporalDurationRecord(isolate, temporal_duration_like,
14900 method_name),
14901 Handle<JSTemporalPlainTime>());
14902 TimeDurationRecord& time_duration = duration.time_duration;
14903
14904 // 3. Let result be ! AddTime(temporalTime.[[ISOHour]],
14905 // temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]], temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]],
14906 // temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
14907 // temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]], sign x duration.[[Hours]], sign x
14908 // duration.[[Minutes]], sign x duration.[[Seconds]], sign x
14909 // duration.[[Milliseconds]], sign x duration.[[Microseconds]], sign x
14910 // duration.[[Nanoseconds]]).
14911 DateTimeRecord result = AddTime(
14912 isolate,
14913 {temporal_time->iso_hour(), temporal_time->iso_minute(),
14914 temporal_time->iso_second(), temporal_time->iso_millisecond(),
14915 temporal_time->iso_microsecond(), temporal_time->iso_nanosecond()},
14916 {0, sign * time_duration.hours, sign * time_duration.minutes,
14917 sign * time_duration.seconds, sign * time_duration.milliseconds,
14918 sign * time_duration.microseconds, sign * time_duration.nanoseconds});
14919 // 4. Assert: ! IsValidTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
14920 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
14921 // result.[[Nanosecond]]) is true.
14922 DCHECK(IsValidTime(isolate, result.time));
14923 // 5. Return ? CreateTemporalTime(result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
14924 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
14925 // result.[[Nanosecond]]).
14926 return CreateTemporalTime(isolate, result.time);
14927}
14928
14929} // namespace

14949namespace {
14950// #sec-temporal-differencetemporalplantime
14951MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> DifferenceTemporalPlainTime(
14952 Isolate* isolate, TimePreposition operation,
14953 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time, Handle<Object> other_obj,
14954 DirectHandle<Object> options, const char* method_name) {
14955 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
14956 // 1. If operation is since, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
14957 double sign = operation == TimePreposition::kSince ? -1 : 1;
14958 // 2. Set other to ? ToTemporalDate(other).
14959 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> other;
14960 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
14961 isolate, other,
14962 temporal::ToTemporalTime(isolate, other_obj, method_name));
14963
14964 // 3. Let settings be ? GetDifferenceSettings(operation, options, time, « »,
14965 // "nanosecond", "hour").
14966 DifferenceSettings settings;
14967 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
14968 isolate, settings,
14969 GetDifferenceSettings(isolate, operation, options, UnitGroup::kTime,
14970 DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings::kNone,
14971 Unit::kNanosecond, Unit::kHour, method_name),
14972 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
14973 // 4. Let result be ! DifferenceTime(temporalTime.[[ISOHour]],
14974 // temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]], temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]],
14975 // temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
14976 // temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]], other.[[ISOHour]], other.[[ISOMinute]],
14977 // other.[[ISOSecond]], other.[[ISOMillisecond]], other.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
14978 // other.[[ISONanosecond]]).
14979 DurationRecordWithRemainder result;
14980 result.record.time_duration =
14981 DifferenceTime(
14982 isolate,
14983 {temporal_time->iso_hour(), temporal_time->iso_minute(),
14984 temporal_time->iso_second(), temporal_time->iso_millisecond(),
14985 temporal_time->iso_microsecond(), temporal_time->iso_nanosecond()},
14986 {other->iso_hour(), other->iso_minute(), other->iso_second(),
14987 other->iso_millisecond(), other->iso_microsecond(),
14988 other->iso_nanosecond()})
14989 .ToChecked();
14990 // 5. Set result to (! RoundDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, result.[[Hours]],
14991 // result.[[Minutes]], result.[[Seconds]], result.[[Milliseconds]],
14992 // result.[[Microseconds]], result.[[Nanoseconds]],
14993 // settings.[[RoundingIncrement]], settings.[[SmallestUnit]],
14994 // settings.[[RoundingMode]])).[[DurationRecord]].
14995 result.record.years = result.record.months = result.record.weeks =
14996 result.record.time_duration.days = 0;
14997 result =
14998 RoundDuration(isolate, result.record, settings.rounding_increment,
14999 settings.smallest_unit, settings.rounding_mode, method_name)
15000 .ToChecked();
15001 // 6. Set result to ! BalanceDuration(0, result.[[Hours]], result.[[Minutes]],
15002 // result.[[Seconds]], result.[[Milliseconds]], result.[[Microseconds]],
15003 // result.[[Nanoseconds]], settings.[[LargestUnit]]).
15004 result.record.time_duration.days = 0;
15005 result.record.time_duration =
15006 BalanceDuration(isolate, settings.largest_unit,
15007 result.record.time_duration, method_name)
15008 .ToChecked();
15009
15010 // 7. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, sign × result.[[Hours]],
15011 // sign × result.[[Minutes]], sign × result.[[Seconds]], sign ×
15012 // result.[[Milliseconds]], sign × result.[[Microseconds]], sign ×
15013 // result.[[Nanoseconds]]).
15014 result.record.years = result.record.months = result.record.weeks =
15015 result.record.time_duration.days = 0;
15016 result.record.time_duration.hours *= sign;
15017 result.record.time_duration.minutes *= sign;
15018 result.record.time_duration.seconds *= sign;
15019 result.record.time_duration.milliseconds *= sign;
15020 result.record.time_duration.microseconds *= sign;
15021 result.record.time_duration.nanoseconds *= sign;
15022 return CreateTemporalDuration(isolate, result.record).ToHandleChecked();
15023}

15047// #sec-temporal.plaintime.prototype.getisofields
15048MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> JSTemporalPlainTime::GetISOFields(
15049 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time) {
15050 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
15051 // 1. Let temporalTime be the this value.
15052 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalTime,
15053 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]]).
15054 // 3. Let fields be ! OrdinaryObjectCreate(%Object.prototype%).
15055 Handle<JSObject> fields =
15056 isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function());
15057 // 4. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "calendar",
15058 // temporalTime.[[Calendar]]).
15059 DirectHandle<JSTemporalCalendar> iso8601_calendar =
15060 temporal::GetISO8601Calendar(isolate);
15061 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, fields,
15062 factory->calendar_string(),
15063 iso8601_calendar, Just(kThrowOnError))
15064 .FromJust());
15065
15066 // 5. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoHour",
15067 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOHour]])).
15068 // 6. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMicrosecond",
15069 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]])).
15070 // 7. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMillisecond",
15071 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]])).
15072 // 8. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoMinute",
15073 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]])).
15074 // 9. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoNanosecond",
15075 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]])).
15076 // 10. Perform ! CreateDataPropertyOrThrow(fields, "isoSecond",
15077 // 𝔽(temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]])).
15078 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoHour, iso_hour, temporal_time)
15079 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMicrosecond, iso_microsecond, temporal_time)
15080 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMillisecond, iso_millisecond, temporal_time)
15081 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoMinute, iso_minute, temporal_time)
15082 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoNanosecond, iso_nanosecond, temporal_time)
15083 DEFINE_INT_FIELD(fields, isoSecond, iso_second, temporal_time)
15084 // 11. Return fields.
15085 return fields;
15086}

15108
15109// #sec-temporal-getunsignedroundingmode
15110UnsignedRoundingMode GetUnsignedRoundingMode(RoundingMode rounding_mode,
15111 bool is_negative) {
15112 // 1. If isNegative is true, return the specification type in the third column
15113 // of Table 14 where the first column is roundingMode and the second column is
15114 // "negative".
15115 if (is_negative) {
15116 switch (rounding_mode) {
15117 case RoundingMode::kCeil:
15118 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kZero;
15119 case RoundingMode::kFloor:
15120 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kInfinity;
15121 case RoundingMode::kExpand:
15122 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kInfinity;
15123 case RoundingMode::kTrunc:
15124 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kZero;
15125 case RoundingMode::kHalfCeil:
15126 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfZero;
15127 case RoundingMode::kHalfFloor:
15128 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfInfinity;
15129 case RoundingMode::kHalfExpand:
15130 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfInfinity;
15131 case RoundingMode::kHalfTrunc:
15132 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfZero;
15133 case RoundingMode::kHalfEven:
15134 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfEven;
15135 }
15136 }
15137 // 2. Else, return the specification type in the third column of Table 14
15138 // where the first column is roundingMode and the second column is "positive".
15139 switch (rounding_mode) {
15140 case RoundingMode::kCeil:
15141 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kInfinity;
15142 case RoundingMode::kFloor:
15143 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kZero;
15144 case RoundingMode::kExpand:
15145 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kInfinity;
15146 case RoundingMode::kTrunc:
15147 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kZero;
15148 case RoundingMode::kHalfCeil:
15149 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfInfinity;
15150 case RoundingMode::kHalfFloor:
15151 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfZero;
15152 case RoundingMode::kHalfExpand:
15153 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfInfinity;
15154 case RoundingMode::kHalfTrunc:
15155 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfZero;
15156 case RoundingMode::kHalfEven:
15157 return UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfEven;
15158 }
15159}
15160
15161// #sec-temporal-applyunsignedroundingmode
15162double ApplyUnsignedRoundingMode(double x, double r1, double r2,
15163 UnsignedRoundingMode unsigned_rounding_mode) {
15164 // 1. If x is equal to r1, return r1.
15165 if (x == r1) return r1;
15166 // 2. Assert: r1 < x < r2.
15167 DCHECK_LT(r1, x);
15168 DCHECK_LT(x, r2);
15169 // 3. Assert: unsignedRoundingMode is not undefined.
15170 // 4. If unsignedRoundingMode is zero, return r1.
15171 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kZero) return r1;
15172 // 5. If unsignedRoundingMode is infinity, return r2.
15173 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kInfinity) return r2;
15174 // 6. Let d1 be x – r1.
15175 double d1 = x - r1;
15176 // 7. Let d2 be r2 – x.
15177 double d2 = r2 - x;
15178 // 8. If d1 < d2, return r1.
15179 if (d1 < d2) return r1;
15180 // 9. If d2 < d1, return r2.
15181 if (d2 < d1) return r2;
15182 // 10. Assert: d1 is equal to d2.
15183 DCHECK_EQ(d1, d2);
15184 // 11. If unsignedRoundingMode is half-zero, return r1.
15185 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfZero) return r1;
15186 // 12. If unsignedRoundingMode is half-infinity, return r2.
15187 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfInfinity) return r2;
15188 // 13. Assert: unsignedRoundingMode is half-even.
15189 DCHECK_EQ(unsigned_rounding_mode, UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfEven);
15190 // 14. Let cardinality be (r1 / (r2 – r1)) modulo 2.
15191 int64_t cardinality = static_cast<int64_t>(r1) % 2;
15192 // 15. If cardinality is 0, return r1.
15193 if (cardinality == 0) return r1;
15194 // 16. Return r2.
15195 return r2;
15196}
15197
15198// #sec-temporal-applyunsignedroundingmode
15199Handle<BigInt> ApplyUnsignedRoundingMode(
15200 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<BigInt> num, DirectHandle<BigInt> increment,
15201 Handle<BigInt> r1, Handle<BigInt> r2,
15202 UnsignedRoundingMode unsigned_rounding_mode) {
15203 // 1. If x is equal to r1, return r1.
15204 DirectHandle<BigInt> rr1 =
15205 BigInt::Multiply(isolate, increment, r1).ToHandleChecked();
15206 DirectHandle<BigInt> rr2 =
15207 BigInt::Multiply(isolate, increment, r2).ToHandleChecked();
15208 if (BigInt::EqualToBigInt(*num, *rr1)) return r1;
15209 // 2. Assert: r1 < x < r2.
15210 DCHECK_EQ(BigInt::CompareToBigInt(rr1, num), ComparisonResult::kLessThan);
15211 DCHECK_EQ(BigInt::CompareToBigInt(num, rr2), ComparisonResult::kLessThan);
15212 // 3. Assert: unsignedRoundingMode is not undefined.
15213 // 4. If unsignedRoundingMode is zero, return r1.
15214 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kZero) return r1;
15215 // 5. If unsignedRoundingMode is infinity, return r2.
15216 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kInfinity) return r2;
15217 // 6. Let d1 be x – r1.
15218 DirectHandle<BigInt> dd1 =
15219 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, num, rr1).ToHandleChecked();
15220 // 7. Let d2 be r2 – x.
15221 DirectHandle<BigInt> dd2 =
15222 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, rr2, num).ToHandleChecked();
15223 // 8. If d1 < d2, return r1.
15224 if (BigInt::CompareToBigInt(dd1, dd2) == ComparisonResult::kLessThan) {
15225 return r1;
15226 }
15227 // 9. If d2 < d1, return r2.
15228 if (BigInt::CompareToBigInt(dd2, dd1) == ComparisonResult::kLessThan) {
15229 return r2;
15230 }
15231 // 10. Assert: d1 is equal to d2.
15232 DCHECK_EQ(BigInt::CompareToBigInt(dd1, dd2), ComparisonResult::kEqual);
15233 // 11. If unsignedRoundingMode is half-zero, return r1.
15234 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfZero) return r1;
15235 // 12. If unsignedRoundingMode is half-infinity, return r2.
15236 if (unsigned_rounding_mode == UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfInfinity) return r2;
15237 // 13. Assert: unsignedRoundingMode is half-even.
15238 DCHECK_EQ(unsigned_rounding_mode, UnsignedRoundingMode::kHalfEven);
15239 // 14. Let cardinality be (r1 / (r2 – r1)) modulo 2.
15240 DirectHandle<BigInt> cardinality =
15241 BigInt::Remainder(isolate, r1, BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, 2))
15242 .ToHandleChecked();
15243 // 15. If cardinality is 0, return r1.
15244 if (!cardinality->ToBoolean()) return r1;
15245 // 16. Return r2.
15246 return r2;
15247}
15248
15249// #sec-temporal-roundnumbertoincrement
15250// For the case that x is double.
15251double RoundNumberToIncrement(Isolate* isolate, double x, double increment,
15252 RoundingMode rounding_mode) {
15253 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
15254
15255 // 1. Let quotient be x / increment.
15256 double quotient = x / increment;
15257 bool is_negative;
15258 // 2. If quotient < 0, then
15259 if (quotient < 0) {
15260 // a. Let isNegative be true.
15261 is_negative = true;
15262 // b. Set quotient to -quotient.
15263 quotient = -quotient;
15264 // 3. Else,
15265 } else {
15266 // a. Let isNegative be false.
15267 is_negative = false;
15268 }
15269 // 4. Let unsignedRoundingMode be GetUnsignedRoundingMode(roundingMode,
15270 // isNegative).
15271 UnsignedRoundingMode unsigned_rounding_mode =
15272 GetUnsignedRoundingMode(rounding_mode, is_negative);
15273
15274 // 5. Let r1 be the largest integer such that r1 ≤ quotient.
15275 double r1 = std::floor(quotient);
15276 // 6. Let r2 be the smallest integer such that r2 > quotient.
15277 double r2 = std::floor(quotient + 1);
15278 // 7. Let rounded be ApplyUnsignedRoundingMode(quotient, r1, r2,
15279 // unsignedRoundingMode).
15280 double rounded =
15281 ApplyUnsignedRoundingMode(quotient, r1, r2, unsigned_rounding_mode);
15282 // 8. If isNegative is true, set rounded to -rounded.
15283 if (is_negative) {
15284 rounded = -rounded;
15285 }
15286 // 9. Return rounded × increment.
15287 return rounded * increment;
15288}
15289
15290// #sec-temporal-roundnumbertoincrementasifpositive
15291Handle<BigInt> RoundNumberToIncrementAsIfPositive(Isolate* isolate,
15292 DirectHandle<BigInt> x,
15293 double increment,
15294 RoundingMode rounding_mode) {
15295 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
15296
15297 // 1. Let quotient be x / increment.
15298 // 2. Let unsignedRoundingMode be GetUnsignedRoundingMode(roundingMode,
15299 // false).
15300 UnsignedRoundingMode unsigned_rounding_mode =
15301 GetUnsignedRoundingMode(rounding_mode, false);
15302
15303 DirectHandle<BigInt> increment_bigint =
15304 BigInt::FromNumber(isolate, isolate->factory()->NewNumber(increment))
15305 .ToHandleChecked();
15306 // 3. Let r1 be the largest integer such that r1 ≤ quotient.
15307 Handle<BigInt> r1 =
15308 BigInt::Divide(isolate, x, increment_bigint).ToHandleChecked();
15309
15310 // Adjust for negative quotient.
15311 if (r1->IsNegative() && BigInt::Remainder(isolate, x, increment_bigint)
15312 .ToHandleChecked()
15313 ->ToBoolean()) {
15314 r1 = BigInt::Decrement(isolate, r1).ToHandleChecked();
15315 }
15316
15317 // 4. Let r2 be the smallest integer such that r2 > quotient.
15318 Handle<BigInt> r2 = BigInt::Increment(isolate, r1).ToHandleChecked();
15319 // 5. Let rounded be ApplyUnsignedRoundingMode(quotient, r1, r2,
15320 // unsignedRoundingMode).
15321 DirectHandle<BigInt> rounded = ApplyUnsignedRoundingMode(
15322 isolate, x, increment_bigint, r1, r2, unsigned_rounding_mode);
15323 // 6. Return rounded × increment.
15324 Handle<BigInt> result =
15325 BigInt::Multiply(isolate, rounded, increment_bigint).ToHandleChecked();
15326 return result;
15327}
15328
15329DateTimeRecord RoundTime(Isolate* isolate, const TimeRecord& time,
15330 double increment, Unit unit,
15331 RoundingMode rounding_mode, double day_length_ns) {
15332 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
15333
15334 // 1. Assert: hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond, and
15335 // increment are integers.
15336 // 2. Let fractionalSecond be nanosecond × 10^−9 + microsecond × 10^−6 +
15337 // millisecond × 10−3 + second.
15338 double fractional_second =
15339 static_cast<double>(time.nanosecond) / 100000000.0 +
15340 static_cast<double>(time.microsecond) / 1000000.0 +
15341 static_cast<double>(time.millisecond) / 1000.0 +
15342 static_cast<double>(time.second);
15343 double quantity;
15344 switch (unit) {
15345 // 3. If unit is "day", then
15346 case Unit::kDay:
15347 // a. If dayLengthNs is not present, set it to 8.64 × 10^13.
15348 // b. Let quantity be (((((hour × 60 + minute) × 60 + second) × 1000 +
15349 // millisecond) × 1000 + microsecond) × 1000 + nanosecond) / dayLengthNs.
15350 quantity =
15351 (((((time.hour * 60.0 + time.minute) * 60.0 + time.second) * 1000.0 +
15352 time.millisecond) *
15353 1000.0 +
15354 time.microsecond) *
15355 1000.0 +
15356 time.nanosecond) /
15357 day_length_ns;
15358 break;
15359 // 4. Else if unit is "hour", then
15360 case Unit::kHour:
15361 // a. Let quantity be (fractionalSecond / 60 + minute) / 60 + hour.
15362 quantity = (fractional_second / 60.0 + time.minute) / 60.0 + time.hour;
15363 break;
15364 // 5. Else if unit is "minute", then
15365 case Unit::kMinute:
15366 // a. Let quantity be fractionalSecond / 60 + minute.
15367 quantity = fractional_second / 60.0 + time.minute;
15368 break;
15369 // 6. Else if unit is "second", then
15370 case Unit::kSecond:
15371 // a. Let quantity be fractionalSecond.
15372 quantity = fractional_second;
15373 break;
15374 // 7. Else if unit is "millisecond", then
15375 case Unit::kMillisecond:
15376 // a. Let quantity be nanosecond × 10^−6 + microsecond × 10^−3 +
15377 // millisecond.
15378 quantity = time.nanosecond / 1000000.0 + time.microsecond / 1000.0 +
15379 time.millisecond;
15380 break;
15381 // 8. Else if unit is "microsecond", then
15382 case Unit::kMicrosecond:
15383 // a. Let quantity be nanosecond × 10^−3 + microsecond.
15384 quantity = time.nanosecond / 1000.0 + time.microsecond;
15385 break;
15386 // 9. Else,
15387 default:
15388 // a. Assert: unit is "nanosecond".
15389 DCHECK_EQ(unit, Unit::kNanosecond);
15390 // b. Let quantity be nanosecond.
15391 quantity = time.nanosecond;
15392 break;
15393 }
15394 // 10. Let result be ! RoundNumberToIncrement(quantity, increment,
15395 // roundingMode).
15396 int32_t result =
15397 RoundNumberToIncrement(isolate, quantity, increment, rounding_mode);
15398
15399 switch (unit) {
15400 // 11. If unit is "day", then
15401 case Unit::kDay:
15402 // a. Return the Record { [[Days]]: result, [[Hour]]: 0, [[Minute]]: 0,
15403 // [[Second]]: 0, [[Millisecond]]: 0, [[Microsecond]]: 0, [[Nanosecond]]:
15404 // 0 }.
15405 return {{0, 0, result}, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}};
15406 // 12. If unit is "hour", then
15407 case Unit::kHour:
15408 // a. Return ! BalanceTime(result, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
15409 return BalanceTime({static_cast<double>(result), 0, 0, 0, 0, 0});
15410 // 13. If unit is "minute", then
15411 case Unit::kMinute:
15412 // a. Return ! BalanceTime(hour, result, 0, 0, 0, 0).
15413 return BalanceTime({static_cast<double>(time.hour),
15414 static_cast<double>(result), 0, 0, 0, 0});
15415 // 14. If unit is "second", then
15416 case Unit::kSecond:
15417 // a. Return ! BalanceTime(hour, minute, result, 0, 0, 0).
15418 return BalanceTime({static_cast<double>(time.hour),
15419 static_cast<double>(time.minute),
15420 static_cast<double>(result), 0, 0, 0});
15421 // 15. If unit is "millisecond", then
15422 case Unit::kMillisecond:
15423 // a. Return ! BalanceTime(hour, minute, second, result, 0, 0).
15424 return BalanceTime({static_cast<double>(time.hour),
15425 static_cast<double>(time.minute),
15426 static_cast<double>(time.second),
15427 static_cast<double>(result), 0, 0});
15428 // 16. If unit is "microsecond", then
15429 case Unit::kMicrosecond:
15430 // a. Return ! BalanceTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond, result, 0).
15431 return BalanceTime({static_cast<double>(time.hour),
15432 static_cast<double>(time.minute),
15433 static_cast<double>(time.second),
15434 static_cast<double>(time.millisecond),
15435 static_cast<double>(result), 0});
15436 default:
15437 // 17. Assert: unit is "nanosecond".
15438 DCHECK_EQ(unit, Unit::kNanosecond);
15439 // 18. Return ! BalanceTime(hour, minute, second, millisecond,
15440 // microsecond, result).
15441 return BalanceTime(
15442 {static_cast<double>(time.hour), static_cast<double>(time.minute),
15443 static_cast<double>(time.second),
15444 static_cast<double>(time.millisecond),
15445 static_cast<double>(time.microsecond), static_cast<double>(result)});
15446 }
15447}
15448
15449// #sec-temporal-tosecondsstringprecision
15450Maybe<StringPrecision> ToSecondsStringPrecision(
15451 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> normalized_options,
15452 const char* method_name) {
15453 // 1. Let smallestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(normalizedOptions, "smallestUnit",
15454 // time, undefined).
15455 Unit smallest_unit;
15456 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15457 isolate, smallest_unit,
15458 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, normalized_options, "smallestUnit",
15459 UnitGroup::kTime, Unit::kNotPresent, false, method_name),
15460 Nothing<StringPrecision>());
15461
15462 switch (smallest_unit) {
15463 // 2. If smallestUnit is "hour", throw a RangeError exception.
15464 case Unit::kHour:
15465 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
15466 isolate,
15467 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyValueOutOfRange,
15468 isolate->factory()->smallestUnit_string()),
15469 Nothing<StringPrecision>());
15470 // 2. If smallestUnit is "minute", then
15471 case Unit::kMinute:
15472 // a. Return the new Record { [[Precision]]: "minute", [[Unit]]: "minute",
15473 // [[Increment]]: 1 }.
15474 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::kMinute, Unit::kMinute, 1}));
15475 // 3. If smallestUnit is "second", then
15476 case Unit::kSecond:
15477 // a. Return the new Record { [[Precision]]: 0, [[Unit]]: "second",
15478 // [[Increment]]: 1 }.
15479 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k0, Unit::kSecond, 1}));
15480 // 4. If smallestUnit is "millisecond", then
15481 case Unit::kMillisecond:
15482 // a. Return the new Record { [[Precision]]: 3, [[Unit]]: "millisecond",
15483 // [[Increment]]: 1 }.
15484 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k3, Unit::kMillisecond, 1}));
15485 // 5. If smallestUnit is "microsecond", then
15486 case Unit::kMicrosecond:
15487 // a. Return the new Record { [[Precision]]: 6, [[Unit]]: "microsecond",
15488 // [[Increment]]: 1 }.
15489 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k6, Unit::kMicrosecond, 1}));
15490 // 6. If smallestUnit is "nanosecond", then
15491 case Unit::kNanosecond:
15492 // a. Return the new Record { [[Precision]]: 9, [[Unit]]: "nanosecond",
15493 // [[Increment]]: 1 }.
15494 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k9, Unit::kNanosecond, 1}));
15495 default:
15496 break;
15497 }
15498 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
15499 // 8. Assert: smallestUnit is undefined.
15500 DCHECK(smallest_unit == Unit::kNotPresent);
15501 // 9. Let fractionalDigitsVal be ? Get(normalizedOptions,
15502 // "fractionalSecondDigits").
15503 Handle<Object> fractional_digits_val;
15504 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15505 isolate, fractional_digits_val,
15506 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, normalized_options,
15507 factory->fractionalSecondDigits_string()),
15508 Nothing<StringPrecision>());
15509
15510 // 10. If Type(fractionalDigitsVal) is not Number, then
15511 if (!IsNumber(*fractional_digits_val)) {
15512 // a. If fractionalDigitsVal is not undefined, then
15513 if (!IsUndefined(*fractional_digits_val)) {
15514 // i. If ? ToString(fractionalDigitsVal) is not "auto", throw a RangeError
15515 // exception.
15516 DirectHandle<String> string;
15517 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15518 isolate, string, Object::ToString(isolate, fractional_digits_val),
15519 Nothing<StringPrecision>());
15520 if (!String::Equals(isolate, string, factory->auto_string())) {
15521 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
15522 isolate,
15523 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyValueOutOfRange,
15524 factory->fractionalSecondDigits_string()),
15525 Nothing<StringPrecision>());
15526 }
15527 }
15528 // b. Return the Record { [[Precision]]: "auto", [[Unit]]: "nanosecond",
15529 // [[Increment]]: 1 }.
15530 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::kAuto, Unit::kNanosecond, 1}));
15531 }
15532 // 11. If fractionalDigitsVal is NaN, +∞𝔽, or -∞𝔽, throw a RangeError
15533 // exception.
15534 if (IsNaN(*fractional_digits_val) ||
15535 std::isinf(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*fractional_digits_val)))) {
15536 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
15537 isolate,
15538 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyValueOutOfRange,
15539 factory->fractionalSecondDigits_string()),
15540 Nothing<StringPrecision>());
15541 }
15542 // 12. Let fractionalDigitCount be RoundTowardsZero(ℝ(fractionalDigitsVal)).
15543 int64_t fractional_digit_count = RoundTowardsZero(
15544 Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*fractional_digits_val)));
15545 // 13. If fractionalDigitCount < 0 or fractionalDigitCount > 9, throw a
15546 // RangeError exception.
15547 if (fractional_digit_count < 0 || fractional_digit_count > 9) {
15548 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
15549 isolate,
15550 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyValueOutOfRange,
15551 factory->fractionalSecondDigits_string()),
15552 Nothing<StringPrecision>());
15553 }
15554 // 14. If fractionalDigitCount is 0, then
15555 switch (fractional_digit_count) {
15556 case 0:
15557 // a. Return the Record { [[Precision]]: 0, [[Unit]]: "second",
15558 // [[Increment]]: 1 }.
15559 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k0, Unit::kSecond, 1}));
15560 // 15. If fractionalDigitCount is 1, 2, or 3, then
15561 // a. Return the Record { [[Precision]]: fractionalDigitCount, [[Unit]]:
15562 // "millisecond", [[Increment]]: 10^(3 - fractionalDigitCount) }.
15563 case 1:
15564 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k1, Unit::kMillisecond, 100}));
15565 case 2:
15566 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k2, Unit::kMillisecond, 10}));
15567 case 3:
15568 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k3, Unit::kMillisecond, 1}));
15569 // 16. If fractionalDigitCount is 4, 5, or 6, then
15570 // a. Return the Record { [[Precision]]: fractionalDigitCount, [[Unit]]:
15571 // "microsecond", [[Increment]]: 10^(6 - fractionalDigitCount) }.
15572 case 4:
15573 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k4, Unit::kMicrosecond, 100}));
15574 case 5:
15575 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k5, Unit::kMicrosecond, 10}));
15576 case 6:
15577 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k6, Unit::kMicrosecond, 1}));
15578 // 17. Assert: fractionalDigitCount is 7, 8, or 9.
15579 // 18. Return the Record { [[Precision]]: fractionalDigitCount, [[Unit]]:
15580 // "nanosecond", [[Increment]]: 109 - fractionalDigitCount }.
15581 case 7:
15582 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k7, Unit::kNanosecond, 100}));
15583 case 8:
15584 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k8, Unit::kNanosecond, 10}));
15585 case 9:
15586 return Just(StringPrecision({Precision::k9, Unit::kNanosecond, 1}));
15587 default:
15588 UNREACHABLE();
15589 }
15590}
15591
15592// #sec-temporal-compareepochnanoseconds
15593MaybeHandle<Smi> CompareEpochNanoseconds(Isolate* isolate,
15594 DirectHandle<BigInt> one,
15595 DirectHandle<BigInt> two) {
15596 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
15597
15598 // 1. If epochNanosecondsOne > epochNanosecondsTwo, return 1.
15599 // 2. If epochNanosecondsOne < epochNanosecondsTwo, return -1.
15600 // 3. Return 0.
15601 return handle(
15602 Smi::FromInt(CompareResultToSign(BigInt::CompareToBigInt(one, two))),
15603 isolate);
15604}

15608// #sec-temporal.plaintime.prototype.tostring
15609MaybeHandle<String> JSTemporalPlainTime::ToString(
15610 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainTime> temporal_time,
15611 DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
15612 const char* method_name = "Temporal.PlainTime.prototype.toString";
15613 // 1. Let temporalTime be the this value.
15614 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(temporalTime,
15615 // [[InitializedTemporalTime]]).
15616 // 3. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
15617 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
15618 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15619 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
15620
15621 // 4. Let precision be ? ToSecondsStringPrecision(options).
15622 StringPrecision precision;
15623 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15624 isolate, precision,
15625 ToSecondsStringPrecision(isolate, options, method_name),
15626 Handle<String>());
15627
15628 // 5. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(options, "trunc").
15629 RoundingMode rounding_mode;
15630 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15631 isolate, rounding_mode,
15632 ToTemporalRoundingMode(isolate, options, RoundingMode::kTrunc,
15633 method_name),
15634 Handle<String>());
15635
15636 // 6. Let roundResult be ! RoundTime(temporalTime.[[ISOHour]],
15637 // temporalTime.[[ISOMinute]], temporalTime.[[ISOSecond]],
15638 // temporalTime.[[ISOMillisecond]], temporalTime.[[ISOMicrosecond]],
15639 // temporalTime.[[ISONanosecond]], precision.[[Increment]],
15640 // precision.[[Unit]], roundingMode).
15641
15642 DateTimeRecord round_result = RoundTime(
15643 isolate,
15644 {temporal_time->iso_hour(), temporal_time->iso_minute(),
15645 temporal_time->iso_second(), temporal_time->iso_millisecond(),
15646 temporal_time->iso_microsecond(), temporal_time->iso_nanosecond()},
15647 precision.increment, precision.unit, rounding_mode);
15648 // 7. Return ! TemporalTimeToString(roundResult.[[Hour]],
15649 // roundResult.[[Minute]], roundResult.[[Second]],
15650 // roundResult.[[Millisecond]], roundResult.[[Microsecond]],
15651 // roundResult.[[Nanosecond]], precision.[[Precision]]).
15652 return TemporalTimeToString(isolate, round_result.time, precision.precision);
15653}

15655// #sec-temporal.zoneddatetime
15656MaybeHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> JSTemporalZonedDateTime::Constructor(
15657 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> target,
15658 DirectHandle<HeapObject> new_target, Handle<Object> epoch_nanoseconds_obj,
15659 Handle<Object> time_zone_like, Handle<Object> calendar_like) {
15660 const char* method_name = "Temporal.ZonedDateTime";
15661 // 1. If NewTarget is undefined, then
15662 if (IsUndefined(*new_target)) {
15663 // a. Throw a TypeError exception.
15664 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
15665 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kMethodInvokedOnWrongType,
15666 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
15667 method_name)));
15668 }
15669 // 2. Set epochNanoseconds to ? ToBigInt(epochNanoseconds).
15670 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds;
15671 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15672 isolate, epoch_nanoseconds,
15673 BigInt::FromObject(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds_obj));
15674 // 3. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(epochNanoseconds) is false, throw a
15675 // RangeError exception.
15676 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)) {
15677 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
15678 }
15679
15680 // 4. Let timeZone be ? ToTemporalTimeZone(timeZoneLike).
15681 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone;
15682 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15683 isolate, time_zone,
15684 temporal::ToTemporalTimeZone(isolate, time_zone_like, method_name));
15685
15686 // 5. Let calendar be ? ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(calendarLike).
15687 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
15688 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15689 isolate, calendar,
15690 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, calendar_like, method_name));
15691
15692 // 6. Return ? CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(epochNanoseconds, timeZone,
15693 // calendar, NewTarget).
15694 return CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(isolate, target, new_target,
15695 epoch_nanoseconds, time_zone, calendar);
15696}
15697
15698// #sec-get-temporal.zoneddatetime.prototype.hoursinday
15699MaybeHandle<Object> JSTemporalZonedDateTime::HoursInDay(
15700 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> zoned_date_time) {
15701 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
15702 const char* method_name = "Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.hoursInDay";
15703 // 1. Let zonedDateTime be the this value.
15704 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(zonedDateTime,
15705 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]]).
15706 // 3. Let timeZone be zonedDateTime.[[TimeZone]].
15707 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone(zoned_date_time->time_zone(), isolate);
15708
15709 // 4. Let instant be ! CreateTemporalInstant(zonedDateTime.[[Nanoseconds]]).
15710 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant =
15711 temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(
15712 isolate, direct_handle(zoned_date_time->nanoseconds(), isolate))
15713 .ToHandleChecked();
15714
15715 // 5. Let isoCalendar be ! GetISO8601Calendar().
15716 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> iso_calendar = temporal::GetISO8601Calendar(isolate);
15717
15718 // 6. Let temporalDateTime be ? BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(timeZone,
15719 // instant, isoCalendar).
15720 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> temporal_date_time;
15721 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15722 isolate, temporal_date_time,
15723 temporal::BuiltinTimeZoneGetPlainDateTimeFor(isolate, time_zone, instant,
15724 iso_calendar, method_name));
15725 // 7. Let year be temporalDateTime.[[ISOYear]].
15726 // 8. Let month be temporalDateTime.[[ISOMonth]].
15727 // 9. Let day be temporalDateTime.[[ISODay]].
15728 // 10. Let today be ? CreateTemporalDateTime(year, month, day, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
15729 // 0, isoCalendar).
15730 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> today;
15731 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15732 isolate, today,
15733 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
15734 isolate,
15735 {{temporal_date_time->iso_year(), temporal_date_time->iso_month(),
15736 temporal_date_time->iso_day()},
15737 {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}},
15738 iso_calendar));
15739 // 11. Let tomorrowFields be BalanceISODate(year, month, day + 1).
15740 DateRecord tomorrow_fields = BalanceISODate(
15741 isolate, {temporal_date_time->iso_year(), temporal_date_time->iso_month(),
15742 temporal_date_time->iso_day() + 1});
15743
15744 // 12. Let tomorrow be ? CreateTemporalDateTime(tomorrowFields.[[Year]],
15745 // tomorrowFields.[[Month]], tomorrowFields.[[Day]], 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0,
15746 // isoCalendar).
15747 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> tomorrow;
15748 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15749 isolate, tomorrow,
15750 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
15751 isolate, {tomorrow_fields, {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}}, iso_calendar));
15752 // 13. Let todayInstant be ? BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(timeZone, today,
15753 // "compatible").
15754 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> today_instant;
15755 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15756 isolate, today_instant,
15757 BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(isolate, time_zone, today,
15758 Disambiguation::kCompatible, method_name));
15759 // 14. Let tomorrowInstant be ? BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(timeZone,
15760 // tomorrow, "compatible").
15761 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> tomorrow_instant;
15762 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15763 isolate, tomorrow_instant,
15764 BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(isolate, time_zone, tomorrow,
15765 Disambiguation::kCompatible, method_name));
15766 // 15. Let diffNs be tomorrowInstant.[[Nanoseconds]] −
15767 // todayInstant.[[Nanoseconds]].
15768 DirectHandle<BigInt> diff_ns =
15769 BigInt::Subtract(isolate,
15770 direct_handle(tomorrow_instant->nanoseconds(), isolate),
15771 direct_handle(today_instant->nanoseconds(), isolate))
15772 .ToHandleChecked();
15773 // 16. Return 𝔽(diffNs / (3.6 × 10^12)).
15774 //
15775 // Note: The result of the division may be non integer for TimeZone which
15776 // change fractional hours. Perform this division in two steps:
15777 // First convert it to seconds in BigInt, then perform floating point
15778 // division (seconds / 3600) to convert to hours.
15779 int64_t diff_seconds =
15780 BigInt::Divide(isolate, diff_ns, BigInt::FromUint64(isolate, 1000000000))
15781 .ToHandleChecked()
15782 ->AsInt64();
15783 double hours_in_that_day = static_cast<double>(diff_seconds) / 3600.0;
15784 return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(hours_in_that_day);
15785}

15787namespace {
15788
15789// #sec-temporal-totemporalzoneddatetime
15790MaybeHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> ToTemporalZonedDateTime(
15791 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, DirectHandle<Object> options,
15792 const char* method_name) {
15793 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
15794
15795 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
15796 // 2. Assert: Type(options) is Object or Undefined.
15797 DCHECK(IsUndefined(*options) || IsJSReceiver(*options));
15798 // 3. Let offsetBehaviour be option.
15799 OffsetBehaviour offset_behaviour = OffsetBehaviour::kOption;
15800 // 4. Let matchBehaviour be match exactly.
15801 MatchBehaviour match_behaviour = MatchBehaviour::kMatchExactly;
15802
15803 Handle<Object> offset_string;
15804 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone;
15805 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar;
15806
15807 temporal::DateTimeRecord result;
15808
15809 // 5. If Type(item) is Object, then
15810 if (IsJSReceiver(*item_obj)) {
15811 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> item = Cast<JSReceiver>(item_obj);
15812 // a. If item has an [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot,
15813 // then
15814 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item_obj)) {
15815 // i. Return item.
15816 return Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(item_obj);
15817 }
15818 // b. Let calendar be ? GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(item).
15819 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15820 isolate, calendar,
15821 GetTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, item, method_name));
15822 // c. Let fieldNames be ? CalendarFields(calendar, « "day", "hour",
15823 // "microsecond", "millisecond", "minute", "month", "monthCode",
15824 // "nanosecond", "second", "year" »).
15825 Handle<FixedArray> field_names = All10UnitsInFixedArray(isolate);
15826 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, field_names,
15827 CalendarFields(isolate, calendar, field_names));
15828
15829 // d. Append "timeZone" to fieldNames.
15830 int32_t field_length = field_names->length();
15831 field_names = FixedArray::SetAndGrow(isolate, field_names, field_length++,
15832 factory->timeZone_string());
15833
15834 // e. Append "offset" to fieldNames.
15835 field_names = FixedArray::SetAndGrow(isolate, field_names, field_length++,
15836 factory->offset_string());
15837 field_names->RightTrim(isolate, field_length);
15838
15839 // f. Let fields be ? PrepareTemporalFields(item, fieldNames, « "timeZone"
15840 // »).
15841 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> fields;
15842 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15843 isolate, fields,
15844 PrepareTemporalFields(isolate, item, field_names,
15845 RequiredFields::kTimeZone));
15846
15847 // g. Let timeZone be ? Get(fields, "timeZone").
15848 Handle<Object> time_zone_obj;
15849 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15850 isolate, time_zone_obj,
15851 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->timeZone_string()));
15852
15853 // h. Set timeZone to ? ToTemporalTimeZone(timeZone).
15854 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15855 isolate, time_zone,
15856 temporal::ToTemporalTimeZone(isolate, time_zone_obj, method_name));
15857 // i. Let offsetString be ? Get(fields, "offset").
15858 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15859 isolate, offset_string,
15860 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, fields, factory->offset_string()));
15861
15862 // j. If offsetString is undefined, then
15863 if (IsUndefined(*offset_string)) {
15864 // i. Set offsetBehaviour to wall.
15865 offset_behaviour = OffsetBehaviour::kWall;
15866 // k. Else,
15867 } else {
15868 // i. Set offsetString to ? ToString(offsetString).
15869 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, offset_string,
15870 Object::ToString(isolate, offset_string));
15871 }
15872
15873 // l. Let result be ? InterpretTemporalDateTimeFields(calendar, fields,
15874 // options).
15875 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15876 isolate, result,
15877 InterpretTemporalDateTimeFields(isolate, calendar, fields, options,
15878 method_name),
15879 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
15880 // 5. Else,
15881 } else {
15882 // a. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
15883 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15884 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
15885 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
15886 // b. Let string be ? ToString(item).
15887 Handle<String> string;
15888 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, string,
15889 Object::ToString(isolate, item_obj));
15890 // c. Let result be ? ParseTemporalZonedDateTimeString(string).
15891 DateTimeRecordWithCalendar parsed_result;
15892 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15893 isolate, parsed_result,
15894 ParseTemporalZonedDateTimeString(isolate, string),
15895 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
15896 result = {parsed_result.date, parsed_result.time};
15897
15898 // d. Let timeZoneName be result.[[TimeZone]].[[Name]].
15899 // e. Assert: timeZoneName is not undefined.
15900 DCHECK(!IsUndefined(*parsed_result.time_zone.name));
15901 Handle<String> time_zone_name = Cast<String>(parsed_result.time_zone.name);
15902
15903 // f. If ParseText(StringToCodePoints(timeZoneName),
15904 // TimeZoneNumericUTCOffset) is a List of errors, then
15905 std::optional<ParsedISO8601Result> parsed =
15906 TemporalParser::ParseTimeZoneNumericUTCOffset(isolate, time_zone_name);
15907 if (!parsed.has_value()) {
15908 // i. If ! IsValidTimeZoneName(timeZoneName) is false, throw a RangeError
15909 // exception.
15910 if (!IsValidTimeZoneName(isolate, time_zone_name)) {
15911 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
15912 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
15913 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
15914 }
15915 // ii. Set timeZoneName to ! CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(timeZoneName).
15916 time_zone_name = CanonicalizeTimeZoneName(isolate, time_zone_name);
15917 }
15918 // g. Let offsetString be result.[[TimeZone]].[[OffsetString]].
15919 offset_string = parsed_result.time_zone.offset_string;
15920
15921 // h. If result.[[TimeZone]].[[Z]] is true, then
15922 if (parsed_result.time_zone.z) {
15923 // i. Set offsetBehaviour to exact.
15924 offset_behaviour = OffsetBehaviour::kExact;
15925 // i. Else if offsetString is undefined, then
15926 } else if (IsUndefined(*offset_string)) {
15927 // i. Set offsetBehaviour to wall.
15928 offset_behaviour = OffsetBehaviour::kWall;
15929 }
15930 // j. Let timeZone be ! CreateTemporalTimeZone(timeZoneName).
15931 time_zone = temporal::CreateTemporalTimeZone(isolate, time_zone_name)
15932 .ToHandleChecked();
15933 // k. Let calendar be ?
15934 // ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(result.[[Calendar]]).
15935 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15936 isolate, calendar,
15937 ToTemporalCalendarWithISODefault(isolate, parsed_result.calendar,
15938 method_name));
15939 // j. Set matchBehaviour to match minutes.
15940 match_behaviour = MatchBehaviour::kMatchMinutes;
15941 }
15942 // 7. Let offsetNanoseconds be 0.
15943 int64_t offset_nanoseconds = 0;
15944
15945 // 6. If offsetBehaviour is option, then
15946 if (offset_behaviour == OffsetBehaviour::kOption) {
15947 // a. Set offsetNanoseconds to ? ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(offsetString).
15948 DCHECK(IsString(*offset_string));
15949 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15950 isolate, offset_nanoseconds,
15951 ParseTimeZoneOffsetString(isolate, Cast<String>(offset_string)),
15952 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
15953 }
15954
15955 // 7. Let disambiguation be ? ToTemporalDisambiguation(options).
15956 Disambiguation disambiguation;
15957 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15958 isolate, disambiguation,
15959 ToTemporalDisambiguation(isolate, options, method_name),
15960 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
15961
15962 // 8. Let offset be ? ToTemporalOffset(options, "reject").
15963 enum Offset offset;
15964 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
15965 isolate, offset,
15966 ToTemporalOffset(isolate, options, Offset::kReject, method_name),
15967 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
15968
15969 // 9. Let epochNanoseconds be ? InterpretISODateTimeOffset(result.[[Year]],
15970 // result.[[Month]], result.[[Day]], result.[[Hour]], result.[[Minute]],
15971 // result.[[Second]], result.[[Millisecond]], result.[[Microsecond]],
15972 // result.[[Nanosecond]], offsetBehaviour, offsetNanoseconds, timeZone,
15973 // disambiguation, offset, matchBehaviour).
15974 //
15975 DirectHandle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds;
15976 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
15977 isolate, epoch_nanoseconds,
15978 InterpretISODateTimeOffset(isolate, result, offset_behaviour,
15979 offset_nanoseconds, time_zone, disambiguation,
15980 offset, match_behaviour, method_name));
15981
15982 // 8. Return ? CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(epochNanoseconds, timeZone,
15983 // calendar).
15984 return CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds, time_zone,
15985 calendar);
15986}
15987
15988MaybeHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> ToTemporalZonedDateTime(
15989 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item_obj, const char* method_name) {
15990 // 1. If options is not present, set options to undefined.
15991 return ToTemporalZonedDateTime(
15992 isolate, item_obj, isolate->factory()->undefined_value(), method_name);
15993}

15997// #sec-temporal.zoneddatetime.from
15998MaybeHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> JSTemporalZonedDateTime::From(
15999 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> item, DirectHandle<Object> options_obj) {
16000 const char* method_name = "Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from";
16001 // 1. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
16002 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> options;
16003 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
16004 isolate, options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options_obj, method_name));
16005
16006 // 2. If Type(item) is Object and item has an
16007 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]] internal slot, then
16008 if (IsJSTemporalZonedDateTime(*item)) {
16009 // a. Perform ? ToTemporalOverflow(options).
16010 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
16011 isolate, ToTemporalOverflow(isolate, options, method_name),
16012 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
16013
16014 // b. Perform ? ToTemporalDisambiguation(options).
16015 {
16016 Disambiguation disambiguation;
16017 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
16018 isolate, disambiguation,
16019 ToTemporalDisambiguation(isolate, options, method_name),
16020 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
16021 USE(disambiguation);
16022 }
16023
16024 // c. Perform ? ToTemporalOffset(options, "reject").
16025 {
16026 enum Offset offset;
16027 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
16028 isolate, offset,
16029 ToTemporalOffset(isolate, options, Offset::kReject, method_name),
16030 Handle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>());
16031 USE(offset);
16032 }
16033
16034 // d. Return ? CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(item.[[Nanoseconds]],
16035 // item.[[TimeZone]], item.[[Calendar]]).
16036 auto zoned_date_time = Cast<JSTemporalZonedDateTime>(item);
16037 return CreateTemporalZonedDateTime(
16038 isolate, direct_handle(zoned_date_time->nanoseconds(), isolate),
16039 direct_handle(zoned_date_time->time_zone(), isolate),
16040 direct_handle(zoned_date_time->calendar(), isolate));
16041 }
16042 // 3. Return ? ToTemporalZonedDateTime(item, options).
16043 return ToTemporalZonedDateTime(isolate, item, options, method_name);
16044}

16050 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();

16064 direct_handle(two->nanoseconds(), isolate));

16069// #sec-temporal-timezoneequals
16070Maybe<bool> TimeZoneEquals(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSReceiver> one,
16071 Handle<JSReceiver> two) {
16072 // 1. If one and two are the same Object value, return true.
16073 if (one.is_identical_to(two)) {
16074 return Just(true);
16075 }
16076
16077 // 2. Let timeZoneOne be ? ToString(one).
16078 DirectHandle<String> time_zone_one;
16079 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
16080 isolate, time_zone_one, Object::ToString(isolate, one), Nothing<bool>());
16081 // 3. Let timeZoneTwo be ? ToString(two).
16082 DirectHandle<String> time_zone_two;
16083 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
16084 isolate, time_zone_two, Object::ToString(isolate, two), Nothing<bool>());
16085 // 4. If timeZoneOne is timeZoneTwo, return true.
16086 if (String::Equals(isolate, time_zone_one, time_zone_two)) {
16087 return Just(true);
16088 }
16089 // 5. Return false.
16090 return Just(false);
16091}

16095// #sec-temporal.zoneddatetime.prototype.equals
16096MaybeHandle<Oddball> JSTemporalZonedDateTime::Equals(
16097 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> zoned_date_time,
16098 Handle<Object> other_obj) {
16099 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
16100 const char* method_name = "Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.equals";
16101 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
16102 // 1. Let zonedDateTime be the this value.
16103 // 2. Perform ? RequireInternalSlot(zonedDateTime,
16104 // [[InitializedTemporalZonedDateTime]]).
16105 // 3. Set other to ? ToTemporalZonedDateTime(other).
16106 DirectHandle<JSTemporalZonedDateTime> other;
16107 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
16108 isolate, other, ToTemporalZonedDateTime(isolate, other_obj, method_name));
16109 // 4. If zonedDateTime.[[Nanoseconds]] ≠ other.[[Nanoseconds]], return false.
16110 if (!BigInt::EqualToBigInt(zoned_date_time->nanoseconds(),
16111 other->nanoseconds())) {
16112 return factory->false_value();
16113 }
16114 // 5. If ? TimeZoneEquals(zonedDateTime.[[TimeZone]], other.[[TimeZone]]) is
16115 // false, return false.
16116 bool equals;
16117 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
16118 isolate, equals,
16119 TimeZoneEquals(isolate, handle(zoned_date_time->time_zone(), isolate),
16120 handle(other->time_zone(), isolate)),
16121 Handle<Oddball>());
16122 if (!equals) {
16123 return factory->false_value();
16124 }
16125 // 6. Return ? CalendarEquals(zonedDateTime.[[Calendar]], other.[[Calendar]]).
16126 return CalendarEquals(isolate, handle(zoned_date_time->calendar(), isolate),
16127 handle(other->calendar(), isolate));
16128}

16130namespace {
16131
16132// #sec-temporal-interpretisodatetimeoffset
16133MaybeHandle<BigInt> InterpretISODateTimeOffset(
16134 Isolate* isolate, const DateTimeRecord& data,
16135 OffsetBehaviour offset_behaviour, int64_t offset_nanoseconds,
16136 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> time_zone, Disambiguation disambiguation,
16137 Offset offset_option, MatchBehaviour match_behaviour,
16138 const char* method_name) {
16139 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
16140
16141 // 1. Assert: offsetNanoseconds is an integer or undefined.
16142 // 2. Let calendar be ! GetISO8601Calendar().
16143 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> calendar = temporal::GetISO8601Calendar(isolate);
16144
16145 // 3. Let dateTime be ? CreateTemporalDateTime(year, month, day, hour, minute,
16146 // second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond, calendar).
16147 DirectHandle<JSTemporalPlainDateTime> date_time;
16148 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, date_time,
16149 temporal::CreateTemporalDateTime(
16150 isolate, {data.date, data.time}, calendar));
16151
16152 // 4. If offsetBehaviour is wall, or offsetOption is "ignore", then
16153 if (offset_behaviour == OffsetBehaviour::kWall ||
16154 offset_option == Offset::kIgnore) {
16155 // a. Let instant be ? BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(timeZone, dateTime,
16156 // disambiguation).
16157 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant;
16158 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
16159 isolate, instant,
16160 BuiltinTimeZoneGetInstantFor(isolate, time_zone, date_time,
16161 disambiguation, method_name));
16162 // b. Return instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
16163 return handle(instant->nanoseconds(), isolate);
16164 }
16165 // 5. If offsetBehaviour is exact, or offsetOption is "use", then
16166 if (offset_behaviour == OffsetBehaviour::kExact ||
16167 offset_option == Offset::kUse) {
16168 // a. Let epochNanoseconds be ? GetEpochFromISOParts(year, month, day, hour,
16169 // minute, second, millisecond, microsecond, nanosecond).
16170 Handle<BigInt> epoch_nanoseconds =
16171 GetEpochFromISOParts(isolate, {data.date, data.time});
16172
16173 // b. Set epochNanoseconds to epochNanoseconds - ℤ(offsetNanoseconds).
16174 epoch_nanoseconds =
16175 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds,
16176 BigInt::FromInt64(isolate, offset_nanoseconds))
16177 .ToHandleChecked();
16178 // c. If ! IsValidEpochNanoseconds(epochNanoseconds) is false, throw a
16179 // RangeError exception.
16180 if (!IsValidEpochNanoseconds(isolate, epoch_nanoseconds)) {
16181 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
16182 }
16183 // d. Return epochNanoseconds.
16184 return epoch_nanoseconds;
16185 }
16186 // 6. Assert: offsetBehaviour is option.
16187 DCHECK_EQ(offset_behaviour, OffsetBehaviour::kOption);
16188 // 7. Assert: offsetOption is "prefer" or "reject".
16189 DCHECK(offset_option == Offset::kPrefer || offset_option == Offset::kReject);
16190 // 8. Let possibleInstants be ? GetPossibleInstantsFor(timeZone, dateTime).
16191 DirectHandle<FixedArray> possible_instants;
16192 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
16193 isolate, possible_instants,
16194 GetPossibleInstantsFor(isolate, time_zone, date_time));
16195
16196 // 9. For each element candidate of possibleInstants, do
16197 for (int i = 0; i < possible_instants->length(); i++) {
16198 DCHECK(IsJSTemporalInstant(possible_instants->get(i)));
16199 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> candidate(
16200 Cast<JSTemporalInstant>(possible_instants->get(i)), isolate);
16201 // a. Let candidateNanoseconds be ? GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(timeZone,
16202 // candidate).
16203 int64_t candidate_nanoseconds;
16204 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
16205 isolate, candidate_nanoseconds,
16206 GetOffsetNanosecondsFor(isolate, time_zone, candidate, method_name),
16207 Handle<BigInt>());
16208 // b. If candidateNanoseconds = offsetNanoseconds, then
16209 if (candidate_nanoseconds == offset_nanoseconds) {
16210 // i. Return candidate.[[Nanoseconds]].
16211 return Handle<BigInt>(candidate->nanoseconds(), isolate);
16212 }
16213 // c. If matchBehaviour is match minutes, then
16214 if (match_behaviour == MatchBehaviour::kMatchMinutes) {
16215 // i. Let roundedCandidateNanoseconds be !
16216 // RoundNumberToIncrement(candidateNanoseconds, 60 × 10^9, "halfExpand").
16217 double rounded_candidate_nanoseconds = RoundNumberToIncrement(
16218 isolate, candidate_nanoseconds, 6e10, RoundingMode::kHalfExpand);
16219 // ii. If roundedCandidateNanoseconds = offsetNanoseconds, then
16220 if (rounded_candidate_nanoseconds == offset_nanoseconds) {
16221 // 1. Return candidate.[[Nanoseconds]].
16222 return Handle<BigInt>(candidate->nanoseconds(), isolate);
16223 }
16224 }
16225 }
16226 // 10. If offsetOption is "reject", throw a RangeError exception.
16227 if (offset_option == Offset::kReject) {
16228 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR());
16229 }
16230 // 11. Let instant be ? DisambiguatePossibleInstants(possibleInstants,
16231 // timeZone, dateTime, disambiguation).
16232 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant;
16233 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
16234 isolate, instant,
16235 DisambiguatePossibleInstants(isolate, possible_instants, time_zone,
16236 date_time, disambiguation, method_name));
16237 // 12. Return instant.[[Nanoseconds]].
16238 return Handle<BigInt>(instant->nanoseconds(), isolate);
16239}

16241} // namespace
