18169// #sec-temporal-adddurationtoorsubtractdurationfrominstant
18170MaybeHandle<JSTemporalInstant> AddDurationToOrSubtractDurationFromInstant(
18171 Isolate* isolate, Arithmetic operation,
18172 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> handle,
18173 Handle<Object> temporal_duration_like, const char* method_name) {
18174 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
18175 // 1. If operation is subtract, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
18176 double sign = operation == Arithmetic::kSubtract ? -1.0 : 1.0;
18177
18178 // See https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/pull/2253
18179 // 2. Let duration be ? ToTemporalDurationRecord(temporalDurationLike).
18180 DurationRecord duration;
18181 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
18182 isolate, duration,
18183 temporal::ToTemporalDurationRecord(isolate, temporal_duration_like,
18184 method_name),
18185 Handle<JSTemporalInstant>());
18186
18187 TimeDurationRecord& time_duration = duration.time_duration;
18188 if (time_duration.days != 0 || duration.months != 0 || duration.weeks != 0 ||
18189 duration.years != 0) {
18190 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(isolate,
18191 NEW_TEMPORAL_INVALID_ARG_RANGE_ERROR(),
18192 Handle<JSTemporalInstant>());
18193 }
18194
18195 // 3. Let ns be ? AddInstant(instant.[[EpochNanoseconds]], sign x
18196 // duration.[[Hours]], sign x duration.[[Minutes]], sign x
18197 // duration.[[Seconds]], sign x duration.[[Milliseconds]], sign x
18198 // duration.[[Microseconds]], sign x duration.[[Nanoseconds]]).
18199 DirectHandle<BigInt> ns;
18200 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
18201 isolate, ns,
18202 AddInstant(
18203 isolate, DirectHandle<BigInt>(handle->nanoseconds(), isolate),
18204 {0, sign * time_duration.hours, sign * time_duration.minutes,
18205 sign * time_duration.seconds, sign * time_duration.milliseconds,
18206 sign * time_duration.microseconds,
18207 sign * time_duration.nanoseconds}));
18208 // 4. Return ! CreateTemporalInstant(ns).
18209 return temporal::CreateTemporalInstant(isolate, ns);
18210}
18211
18212// #sec-temporal-negatetemporalroundingmode
18213RoundingMode NegateTemporalRoundingMode(RoundingMode rounding_mode) {
18214 switch (rounding_mode) {
18215 // 1. If roundingMode is "ceil", return "floor".
18216 case RoundingMode::kCeil:
18217 return RoundingMode::kFloor;
18218 // 2. If roundingMode is "floor", return "ceil".
18219 case RoundingMode::kFloor:
18220 return RoundingMode::kCeil;
18221 // 3. If roundingMode is "halfCeil", return "halfFloor".
18222 case RoundingMode::kHalfCeil:
18223 return RoundingMode::kHalfFloor;
18224 // 4. If roundingMode is "halfFloor", return "halfCeil".
18225 case RoundingMode::kHalfFloor:
18226 return RoundingMode::kHalfCeil;
18227 // 5. Return roundingMode.
18228 default:
18229 return rounding_mode;
18230 }
18231}
18232
18233// #sec-temporal-getdifferencesettings
18234Maybe<DifferenceSettings> GetDifferenceSettings(
18235 Isolate* isolate, TimePreposition operation, DirectHandle<Object> options,
18236 UnitGroup unit_group, DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings disallowed_units,
18237 Unit fallback_smallest_unit, Unit smallest_largest_default_unit,
18238 const char* method_name) {
18239 DifferenceSettings record;
18240 // 1. Set options to ? GetOptionsObject(options).
18241 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
18242 isolate, record.options, GetOptionsObject(isolate, options, method_name),
18243 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18244 // 2. Let smallestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(options, "smallestUnit",
18245 // unitGroup, fallbackSmallestUnit).
18246 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
18247 isolate, record.smallest_unit,
18248 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, record.options, "smallestUnit", unit_group,
18249 fallback_smallest_unit,
18250 fallback_smallest_unit == Unit::kNotPresent, method_name),
18251 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18252 // 3. If disallowedUnits contains smallestUnit, throw a RangeError exception.
18253 if (disallowed_units == DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings::kWeekAndDay) {
18254 if (record.smallest_unit == Unit::kWeek) {
18255 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
18256 isolate,
18257 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidUnit,
18258 isolate->factory()->smallestUnit_string(),
18259 isolate->factory()->week_string()),
18260 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18261 }
18262 if (record.smallest_unit == Unit::kDay) {
18263 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
18264 isolate,
18265 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidUnit,
18266 isolate->factory()->smallestUnit_string(),
18267 isolate->factory()->day_string()),
18268 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18269 }
18270 }
18271 // 4. Let defaultLargestUnit be !
18272 // LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(smallestLargestDefaultUnit, smallestUnit).
18273 Unit default_largest_unit = LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(
18274 smallest_largest_default_unit, record.smallest_unit);
18275 // 5. Let largestUnit be ? GetTemporalUnit(options, "largestUnit", unitGroup,
18276 // "auto").
18277 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
18278 isolate, record.largest_unit,
18279 GetTemporalUnit(isolate, record.options, "largestUnit", unit_group,
18280 Unit::kAuto, false, method_name),
18281 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18282 // 6. If disallowedUnits contains largestUnit, throw a RangeError exception.
18283 if (disallowed_units == DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings::kWeekAndDay) {
18284 if (record.largest_unit == Unit::kWeek) {
18285 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
18286 isolate,
18287 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidUnit,
18288 isolate->factory()->largestUnit_string(),
18289 isolate->factory()->week_string()),
18290 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18291 }
18292 if (record.largest_unit == Unit::kDay) {
18293 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
18294 isolate,
18295 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidUnit,
18296 isolate->factory()->largestUnit_string(),
18297 isolate->factory()->day_string()),
18298 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18299 }
18300 }
18301 // 7. If largestUnit is "auto", set largestUnit to defaultLargestUnit.
18302 if (record.largest_unit == Unit::kAuto) {
18303 record.largest_unit = default_largest_unit;
18304 }
18305 // 8. If LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(largestUnit, smallestUnit) is not
18306 // largestUnit, throw a RangeError exception.
18307 if (LargerOfTwoTemporalUnits(record.largest_unit, record.smallest_unit) !=
18308 record.largest_unit) {
18309 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
18310 isolate,
18311 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgumentForTemporal,
18312 isolate->factory()->largestUnit_string()),
18313 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18314 }
18315 // 9. Let roundingMode be ? ToTemporalRoundingMode(options, "trunc").
18316 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
18317 isolate, record.rounding_mode,
18318 ToTemporalRoundingMode(isolate, record.options, RoundingMode::kTrunc,
18319 method_name),
18320 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18321 // 10. If operation is since, then
18322 if (operation == TimePreposition::kSince) {
18323 // a. Set roundingMode to ! NegateTemporalRoundingMode(roundingMode).
18324 record.rounding_mode = NegateTemporalRoundingMode(record.rounding_mode);
18325 }
18326 // 11. Let maximum be !
18327 // MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(smallestUnit).
18328 Maximum maximum =
18329 MaximumTemporalDurationRoundingIncrement(record.smallest_unit);
18330 // 12. Let roundingIncrement be ? ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(options,
18331 // maximum, false).
18332 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
18333 isolate, record.rounding_increment,
18334 ToTemporalRoundingIncrement(isolate, record.options, maximum.value,
18335 maximum.defined, false),
18336 Nothing<DifferenceSettings>());
18337 // 13. Return the Record { [[SmallestUnit]]: smallestUnit, [[LargestUnit]]:
18338 // largestUnit, [[RoundingMode]]: roundingMode, [[RoundingIncrement]]:
18339 // roundingIncrement, [[Options]]: options }.
18340 return Just(record);
18341}
18342
18343// #sec-temporal-differenceinstant
18344TimeDurationRecord DifferenceInstant(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<BigInt> ns1,
18345 DirectHandle<BigInt> ns2,
18346 double rounding_increment,
18347 Unit smallest_unit, Unit largest_unit,
18348 RoundingMode rounding_mode,
18349 const char* method_name) {
18350 // 1. Assert: Type(ns1) is BigInt.
18351 // 2. Assert: Type(ns2) is BigInt.
18352 // 3. Assert: The following step cannot fail due to overflow in the Number
18353 // domain because abs(ns2 - ns1) <= 2 x nsMaxInstant.
18354
18355 // 4. Let roundResult be ! RoundDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, ns2 - ns1,
18356 // roundingIncrement, smallestUnit, roundingMode).[[DurationRecord]].
18357 DirectHandle<BigInt> diff =
18358 BigInt::Subtract(isolate, ns2, ns1).ToHandleChecked();
18359 // Note: Since diff could be very big and over the precision of double can
18360 // hold, break diff into diff_hours and diff_nanoseconds before pass into
18361 // RoundDuration.
18362 DirectHandle<BigInt> nanoseconds_in_a_hour =
18363 BigInt::FromUint64(isolate, 3600000000000);
18364 double diff_hours = Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(
18365 isolate,
18366 BigInt::Divide(isolate, diff, nanoseconds_in_a_hour).ToHandleChecked()));
18367 double diff_nanoseconds = Object::NumberValue(*BigInt::ToNumber(
18368 isolate, BigInt::Remainder(isolate, diff, nanoseconds_in_a_hour)
18369 .ToHandleChecked()));
18370 DurationRecordWithRemainder round_record =
18371 RoundDuration(
18372 isolate, {0, 0, 0, {0, diff_hours, 0, 0, 0, 0, diff_nanoseconds}},
18373 rounding_increment, smallest_unit, rounding_mode, method_name)
18374 .ToChecked();
18375 // 5. Assert: roundResult.[[Days]] is 0.
18376 DCHECK_EQ(0, round_record.record.time_duration.days);
18377 // 6. Return ! BalanceDuration(0, roundResult.[[Hours]],
18378 // roundResult.[[Minutes]], roundResult.[[Seconds]],
18379 // roundResult.[[Milliseconds]], roundResult.[[Microseconds]],
18380 // roundResult.[[Nanoseconds]], largestUnit).
18381 return BalanceDuration(isolate, largest_unit,
18382 isolate->factory()->undefined_value(),
18383 round_record.record.time_duration, method_name)
18384 .ToChecked();
18385}
18386
18387// #sec-temporal-differencetemporalinstant
18388MaybeHandle<JSTemporalDuration> DifferenceTemporalInstant(
18389 Isolate* isolate, TimePreposition operation,
18390 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> instant, Handle<Object> other_obj,
18391 DirectHandle<Object> options, const char* method_name) {
18392 TEMPORAL_ENTER_FUNC();
18393 // 1. If operation is since, let sign be -1. Otherwise, let sign be 1.
18394 double sign = operation == TimePreposition::kSince ? -1 : 1;
18395 // 2. Set other to ? ToTemporalInstant(other).
18396 DirectHandle<JSTemporalInstant> other;
18397 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
18398 isolate, other, ToTemporalInstant(isolate, other_obj, method_name));
18399 // 3. Let settings be ? GetDifferenceSettings(operation, options, time, « »,
18400 // "nanosecond", "second").
18401 DifferenceSettings settings;
18402 MAYBE_ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
18403 isolate, settings,
18404 GetDifferenceSettings(isolate, operation, options, UnitGroup::kTime,
18405 DisallowedUnitsInDifferenceSettings::kNone,
18406 Unit::kNanosecond, Unit::kSecond, method_name),
18407 Handle<JSTemporalDuration>());
18408 // 4. Let result be ! DifferenceInstant(instant.[[Nanoseconds]],
18409 // other.[[Nanoseconds]], settings.[[RoundingIncrement]],
18410 // settings.[[SmallestUnit]], settings.[[LargestUnit]],
18411 // settings.[[RoundingMode]]).
18412 TimeDurationRecord result = DifferenceInstant(
18413 isolate, direct_handle(instant->nanoseconds(), isolate),
18414 direct_handle(other->nanoseconds(), isolate), settings.rounding_increment,
18415 settings.smallest_unit, settings.largest_unit, settings.rounding_mode,
18416 method_name);
18417 // 5. Return ! CreateTemporalDuration(0, 0, 0, 0, sign × result.[[Hours]],
18418 // sign × result.[[Minutes]], sign × result.[[Seconds]], sign ×
18419 // result.[[Milliseconds]], sign × result.[[Microseconds]], sign ×
18420 // result.[[Nanoseconds]]).
18421 return CreateTemporalDuration(
18422 isolate, {0,
18423 0,
18424 0,
18425 {0, sign * result.hours, sign * result.minutes,
18426 sign * result.seconds, sign * result.milliseconds,
18427 sign * result.microseconds, sign * result.nanoseconds}})
18428 .ToHandleChecked();
18429}

18473// Step iii and iv of #sec-temporal.calendar.prototype.fields
18474MaybeHandle<Oddball> IsInvalidTemporalCalendarField(
18475 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> next_value,
18476 DirectHandle<FixedArray> fields_name) {
18477 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
18478 // iii. iii. If fieldNames contains nextValue, then
18479 for (int i = 0; i < fields_name->length(); i++) {
18480 Tagged<Object> item = fields_name->get(i);
18481 DCHECK(IsString(item));
18482 if (String::Equals(isolate, next_value,
18483 direct_handle(Cast<String>(item), isolate))) {
18484 return isolate->factory()->true_value();
18485 }
18486 }
18487 // iv. If nextValue is not one of "year", "month", "monthCode", "day", "hour",
18488 // "minute", "second", "millisecond", "microsecond", "nanosecond", then
18489 if (!(String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->year_string()) ||
18490 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->month_string()) ||
18491 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->monthCode_string()) ||
18492 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->day_string()) ||
18493 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->hour_string()) ||
18494 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->minute_string()) ||
18495 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->second_string()) ||
18496 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->millisecond_string()) ||
18497 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->microsecond_string()) ||
18498 String::Equals(isolate, next_value, factory->nanosecond_string()))) {
18499 return isolate->factory()->true_value();
18500 }
18501 return isolate->factory()->false_value();
18502}
